68 /* flag for INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE statement */
69 typedef enum
70 {
71  FOR_INSERT_OR_DELETE, /* It is an delete or insert statement, not update statement */
72  FOR_MOVE /* It is an update statement on partitioned table, move a record from one partition to
73  * another */
74 } LOCATOR_INDEX_ACTION_FLAG;

82 typedef struct locator_classname_action LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ACTION;
83 struct locator_classname_action
84 {
85  LC_FIND_CLASSNAME action; /* The transient operation, delete or reserve name */
86  OID oid; /* The class identifier of classname */
87  LOG_LSA savep_lsa; /* A top action LSA address (likely a savepoint) for return NULL is for current */
88  LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ACTION *prev; /* To previous top action */
89 };
90 
91 typedef struct locator_classname_entry LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY;
92 struct locator_classname_entry
93 {
94  char *e_name; /* Name of the class */
95  int e_tran_index; /* Transaction of entry */
96  LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ACTION e_current; /* The most current action */
97 };

99 typedef struct locator_return_nxobj LOCATOR_RETURN_NXOBJ;
100 struct locator_return_nxobj
101 { /* Location of next object to return in communication (fetch) area */
102  LC_COPYAREA *comm_area; /* Communication area where objects are returned and described */
103  LC_COPYAREA_MANYOBJS *mobjs; /* Location in the communication area where all objects to be returned are described. */
104  LC_COPYAREA_ONEOBJ *obj; /* Location in the communication area where the next object to return is described. */
105  HEAP_SCANCACHE *ptr_scancache; /* Scan cache used for fetching purposes */
106  HEAP_SCANCACHE area_scancache; /* Scan cache used for fetching purposes */
107  RECDES recdes; /* Location in the communication area where the content of the next object to return is
108  * placed. */
109  int area_offset; /* Relative offset to recdes->data in the communication area */
110 };

234 /*
235  * locator_initialize () - Initialize the locator on the server
236  *
237  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
238  *
239  * Note: Initialize the server transaction object locator.
240  * Currently, only the classname memory hash table is initialized.
241  */
242 int
243 locator_initialize (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p)
244 {
245  RECDES peek = RECDES_INITIALIZER; /* Record descriptor for peeking object */
246  HFID root_hfid;
247  OID class_oid;
248  char *classname = NULL;
249  HEAP_SCANCACHE scan_cache;
250  LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *entry;
251 
252  if (csect_enter (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE, INF_WAIT) != NO_ERROR)
253  {
254  /* Some kind of failure. We must notify the error to the caller. */
255  assert (false);
256  return DISK_ERROR;
257  }
258 
259  if (csect_enter (thread_p, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE, INF_WAIT) != NO_ERROR)
260  {
261  assert (false);
262  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
263  return DISK_ERROR;
264  }
265 
266  if (locator_Mht_classnames != NULL)
267  {
268  (void) mht_map (locator_Mht_classnames, locator_force_drop_class_name_entry, NULL);
269  }
270  else
271  {
272  locator_Mht_classnames =
273  mht_create ("Memory hash Classname to OID", CLASSNAME_CACHE_SIZE, mht_1strhash, mht_compare_strings_are_equal);
274  }
275 
276  if (locator_Mht_classnames == NULL)
277  {
278  assert (false);
279  goto error;
280  }
281 
282  /* Find every single class */
283 
284  if (boot_find_root_heap (&root_hfid) != NO_ERROR || HFID_IS_NULL (&root_hfid))
285  {
286  goto error;
287  }
288 
289  if (heap_scancache_start (thread_p, &scan_cache, &root_hfid, NULL, true, false, NULL) != NO_ERROR)
290  {
291  goto error;
292  }
293 
294  OID_SET_NULL (&class_oid);
295 
296  while (heap_next (thread_p, &root_hfid, NULL, &class_oid, &peek, &scan_cache, PEEK) == S_SUCCESS)
297  {
298  assert (!OID_ISNULL (&class_oid));
299 
300  classname = or_class_name (&peek);
301  assert (classname != NULL);
302  assert (strlen (classname) < 255);
303 
304  entry = ((LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *) malloc (sizeof (*entry)));
305  if (entry == NULL)
306  {
307  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (*entry));
308  goto error;
309  }
310 
311  entry->e_name = strdup ((char *) classname);
312  if (entry->e_name == NULL)
313  {
314  free_and_init (entry);
315  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) (strlen (classname) + 1));
316  goto error;
317  }
318 
319  entry->e_tran_index = NULL_TRAN_INDEX;
320 
321  entry->e_current.action = LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST;
322  COPY_OID (&entry->e_current.oid, &class_oid);
323  LSA_SET_NULL (&entry->e_current.savep_lsa);
324  entry->e_current.prev = NULL;
325 
326  assert (locator_is_exist_class_name_entry (thread_p, entry));
327 
328  (void) mht_put (locator_Mht_classnames, entry->e_name, entry);
329  }
330 
331  /* End the scan cursor */
332  if (heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache) != NO_ERROR)
333  {
334  goto error;
335  }
336 
337  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE);
338 
339  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
340 
341  return NO_ERROR;
342 
343 error:
344 
345  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE);
346 
347  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
348 
349  return DISK_ERROR;
350 }
351 
352 /*
353  * locator_finalize () - Terminates the locator on the server
354  *
355  * return: nothing
356  *
357  * Note:Terminate the object locator on the server. Currently, only
358  * the classname memory hash table is removed.
359  */
360 void
361 locator_finalize (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p)
362 {
363  if (csect_enter (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE, INF_WAIT) != NO_ERROR)
364  {
365  /* Some kind of failure. We will leak resources. */
366  assert (false);
367  return;
368  }
369 
370  if (locator_Mht_classnames == NULL)
371  {
372  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
373  return;
374  }
375 
376  if (csect_enter (thread_p, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE, INF_WAIT) != NO_ERROR)
377  {
378  assert (false);
379  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
380  return;
381  }
382 
383  (void) mht_map (locator_Mht_classnames, locator_force_drop_class_name_entry, NULL);
384 
385  mht_destroy (locator_Mht_classnames);
386  locator_Mht_classnames = NULL;
387 
388  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE);
389 
390  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
391 }
392 
393 /*
394  * xlocator_reserve_class_names () - Reserve several classnames
395  *
396  * return: LC_FIND_CLASSNAME
397  * (either of LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED,
398  * LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST,
399  * LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR)
400  *
401  * num_classes(in): Number of classes
402  * classnames(in): Names of the classes
403  * class_oids(in/out): Object identifiers of the classes
404  */
405 LC_FIND_CLASSNAME
406 xlocator_reserve_class_names (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const int num_classes, const char **classnames, OID * class_oids)
407 {
408  int i = 0;
409  LC_FIND_CLASSNAME result = LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED;
410 
411  for (i = 0; i < num_classes; ++i)
412  {
413  assert (classnames[i] != NULL);
414  assert (strlen (classnames[i]) < 255);
415 
416  result = xlocator_reserve_class_name (thread_p, classnames[i], &class_oids[i]);
417  if (result != LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED)
418  {
419  /* We could potentially revert the reservation but the transient entries should be properly cleaned up by the
420  * rollback so we don't really need to do this here. */
421  break;
422  }
423  }
424 
425  return result;
426 }
427 
428 /*
429  * xlocator_reserve_class_name () - Reserve a classname
430  *
431  * return: LC_FIND_CLASSNAME
432  * (either of LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED,
433  * LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST,
434  * LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR)
435  *
436  * classname(in): Name of class
437  * class_oid(in/out): Object identifier of the class
438  *
439  * Note: Reserve the name of a class.
440  * If there is an entry on the memory classname table,
441  * we can proceed if the entry belongs to the current
442  * transaction, otherwise, we must wait until the transaction
443  * holding the entry terminates since the fate of the classname
444  * entry cannot be predicted. If the entry belongs to
445  * the current transaction, we can reserve the name only if the
446  * entry indicates that a class with such a name has been
447  * deleted or reserved. If there is not a entry with such a name,
448  * the classname is reserved or an error is returned.
449  */
450 static LC_FIND_CLASSNAME
451 xlocator_reserve_class_name (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const char *classname, OID * class_oid)
452 {
453  LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *entry;
454  LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ACTION *old_action;
455  LC_FIND_CLASSNAME reserve = LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED;
456  OID tmp_classoid;
457  int tran_index;
458 
459  if (classname == NULL)
460  {
461  return LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
462  }
463 
464  assert (classname != NULL);
465  assert (strlen (classname) < 255);
466 
467  tran_index = LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p);
468 
469 start:
470  reserve = LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED;
471 
472  if (csect_enter (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE, INF_WAIT) != NO_ERROR)
473  {
474  /* Some kind of failure. We must notify the error to the caller. */
475  assert (false);
476  return LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
477  }
478 
479  /* Is there any entries on the classname hash table ? */
480  entry = (LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *) mht_get (locator_Mht_classnames, classname);
481 
482  if (locator_is_exist_class_name_entry (thread_p, entry))
483  {
484  /* There is a class with such a name on the classname cache. */
485  reserve = LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST;
486  }
487  else if (entry != NULL)
488  {
489  assert (entry->e_current.action != LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST);
490 
491  /*
492  * We can only proceed if the entry belongs to the current transaction,
493  * otherwise, we must lock the class associated with the classname and
494  * retry the operation once the lock is granted.
495  */
496  if (entry->e_tran_index == tran_index)
497  {
498  /*
499  * The name can be reserved only if it has been deleted or
500  * previously reserved. We allow double reservations in order for
501  * multiple table renaming to properly reserve all the names
502  * involved.
503  */
504  if (entry->e_current.action == LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED || entry->e_current.action == LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED_RENAME
505  || (entry->e_current.action == LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED && LSA_ISNULL (&entry->e_current.savep_lsa)))
506  {
507  /*
508  * The entry can be changed.
509  * Do we need to save the old action...just in case we do a
510  * partial rollback ?
511  */
512  if (!LSA_ISNULL (&entry->e_current.savep_lsa))
513  {
514  /*
515  * There is a possibility of returning to this top LSA
516  * (savepoint). Save the action.. just in case
517  */
518  old_action = (LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ACTION *) malloc (sizeof (*old_action));
519 
520  if (old_action == NULL)
521  {
522  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (*old_action));
523  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
524  return LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
525  }
526 
527  *old_action = entry->e_current;
528  LSA_SET_NULL (&entry->e_current.savep_lsa);
529  entry->e_current.prev = old_action;
530  }
531 
532  entry->e_current.action = LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED;
533  if (OID_ISNULL (class_oid))
534  {
535  locator_generate_class_pseudo_oid (thread_p, class_oid);
536  }
537  COPY_OID (&entry->e_current.oid, class_oid);
538 
539  /* Add dummy log to make sure we can revert transient state change. See comment in
540  * xlocator_rename_class_name. Since reserve has been moved before any change (or flush) is done, same
541  * scenario can happen here. */
542  log_append_redo_data2 (thread_p, RVLOC_CLASSNAME_DUMMY, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, NULL);
543  }
544  else
545  {
546  assert ((entry->e_current.action == LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED && !LSA_ISNULL (&entry->e_current.savep_lsa))
547  || entry->e_current.action == LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED_RENAME);
548 
549  reserve = LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST;
550  }
551  }
552  else
553  {
554  COPY_OID (&tmp_classoid, &entry->e_current.oid);
555 
556  /*
557  * The fate of this entry is known when the transaction holding
558  * this entry either commits or aborts. Get the lock and try again.
559  */
560 
561  /*
562  * Exit from critical section since we are going to be suspended and
563  * then retry again.
564  */
565  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
566 
567  if (lock_object (thread_p, &tmp_classoid, oid_Root_class_oid, SCH_M_LOCK, LK_UNCOND_LOCK) != LK_GRANTED)
568  {
569  /*
570  * Unable to acquired lock
571  */
572  return LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
573  }
574  else
575  {
576  /*
577  * Try again
578  * Remove the lock.. since the above was a dirty read
579  */
580  lock_unlock_object (thread_p, &tmp_classoid, oid_Root_class_oid, SCH_M_LOCK, true);
581  goto start;
582  }
583  }
584  }
585  else
586  {
587  entry = (LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *) malloc (sizeof (*entry));
588  if (entry == NULL)
589  {
590  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (*entry));
591  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
592  return LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
593  }
594 
595  entry->e_name = strdup ((char *) classname);
596  if (entry->e_name == NULL)
597  {
598  free_and_init (entry);
599  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) (strlen (classname) + 1));
600  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
601  return LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
602  }
603 
604  entry->e_tran_index = tran_index;
605 
606  entry->e_current.action = LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED;
607  if (OID_ISNULL (class_oid))
608  {
609  locator_generate_class_pseudo_oid (thread_p, class_oid);
610  }
611  COPY_OID (&entry->e_current.oid, class_oid);
612  LSA_SET_NULL (&entry->e_current.savep_lsa);
613  entry->e_current.prev = NULL;
614 
615  /* Add dummy log to make sure we can revert transient state change. See comment in xlocator_rename_class_name.
616  * Since reserve has been moved before any change (or flush) is done, same scenario can happen here. */
617  log_append_redo_data2 (thread_p, RVLOC_CLASSNAME_DUMMY, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, NULL);
618 
619  assert (locator_is_exist_class_name_entry (thread_p, entry) == false);
620 
621  (void) mht_put (locator_Mht_classnames, entry->e_name, entry);
622 
623  locator_incr_num_transient_classnames (entry->e_tran_index);
624  }
625 
626  /*
627  * Note that the index has not been made permanently into the database.
628  * That is, it has not been inserted onto extendible hash.
629  */
630 
631  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
632 
633  /*
634  * Get the lock on the class if we were able to reserve the name
635  */
636  if (reserve == LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED && entry != NULL)
637  {
638  assert (entry->e_tran_index == tran_index);
639 
640  if (lock_object (thread_p, class_oid, oid_Root_class_oid, SCH_M_LOCK, LK_UNCOND_LOCK) != LK_GRANTED)
641  {
642  /*
643  * Something wrong. Remove the entry from hash table.
644  */
645  if (csect_enter (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE, INF_WAIT) != NO_ERROR)
646  {
647  assert (false);
648  return LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
649  }
650 
651  if (entry->e_current.prev == NULL)
652  {
653  locator_decr_num_transient_classnames (entry->e_tran_index);
654 
655  (void) mht_rem (locator_Mht_classnames, entry->e_name, NULL, NULL);
656 
657  free_and_init (entry->e_name);
658  free_and_init (entry);
659  }
660  else
661  {
662  old_action = entry->e_current.prev;
663  entry->e_current = *old_action;
664  free_and_init (old_action);
665  }
666 
667  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
668 
669  reserve = LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
670  }
671  }
672 
673  return reserve;
674 }
675 
676 /*
677  * xlocator_get_reserved_class_name_oid () - Is class name reserved by this
678  * transaction?
679  *
680  * return : Error code.
681  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry.
682  * classname (in) : Class name.
683  * class_oid (out) : Class OID.
684  */
685 int
686 xlocator_get_reserved_class_name_oid (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const char *classname, OID * class_oid)
687 {
688  int tran_index;
689  LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *entry;
690 
691  tran_index = LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p);
692 
693  if (csect_enter_as_reader (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE, INF_WAIT) != NO_ERROR)
694  {
695  assert (false);
696  return ER_FAILED;
697  }
698  entry = (LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *) mht_get (locator_Mht_classnames, classname);
699  if (entry == NULL)
700  {
701  assert (false);
702  goto error;
703  }
704 
705  if (entry->e_current.action != LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED)
706  {
707  assert (false);
708  goto error;
709  }
710 
711  if (entry->e_tran_index != tran_index)
712  {
713  assert (false);
714  goto error;
715  }
716 
717  COPY_OID (class_oid, &entry->e_current.oid);
718 
719  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
720 
721  return NO_ERROR;
722 
723 error:
724  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
725  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_GENERIC_ERROR, 0);
726  return ER_FAILED;
727 }
728 
729 /*
730  * xlocator_delete_class_name () - Remove a classname
731  *
732  * return: LC_FIND_CLASSNAME (either of LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED,
733  * LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR)
734  *
735  * classname(in): Name of the class to delete
736  *
737  * Note: Indicate that a classname has been deleted.
738  * A classname to OID entry is created in memory to indicate the
739  * deletion.
740  * If there is an entry on the memory classname table,
741  * we can proceed if the entry belongs to the current
742  * transaction, otherwise, we must wait until the transaction
743  * holding the entry terminates since the fate of the classname
744  * entry cannot be predicted. If the entry belongs to
745  * the current transaction, we can delete the name only if the
746  * entry indicates that a class with such a name has been
747  * reserved. If there is not a entry with such a namek,
748  * the deleted class is locked and a entry is created informing
749  * of the deletion.
750  */
751 LC_FIND_CLASSNAME
752 xlocator_delete_class_name (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const char *classname)
753 {
754  LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *entry;
755  LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ACTION *old_action;
756  LC_FIND_CLASSNAME classname_delete = LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED;
757  OID tmp_classoid;
758  int tran_index;
759 
760  if (classname == NULL)
761  {
762  return LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
763  }
764 
765  assert (classname != NULL);
766  assert (strlen (classname) < 255);
767 
768  tran_index = LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p);
769 
770 start:
771  classname_delete = LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED;
772 
773  if (csect_enter (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE, INF_WAIT) != NO_ERROR)
774  {
775  /* Some kind of failure. We must notify the error to the caller. */
776  assert (false);
777  return LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
778  }
779 
780  entry = (LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *) mht_get (locator_Mht_classnames, classname);
781  if (entry != NULL)
782  {
783  assert (entry->e_tran_index == NULL_TRAN_INDEX || entry->e_tran_index == tran_index);
784 
785  COPY_OID (&tmp_classoid, &entry->e_current.oid);
786  }
787 
788  if (locator_is_exist_class_name_entry (thread_p, entry))
789  {
790  /* There is a class with such a name on the classname cache. We should convert it to transient one. */
791  entry->e_tran_index = tran_index;
792  entry->e_current.action = LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED;
793 
794  locator_incr_num_transient_classnames (entry->e_tran_index);
795  }
796  else if (entry != NULL)
797  {
798  assert (entry->e_current.action != LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST);
799  assert (entry->e_tran_index == tran_index);
800 
801  /*
802  * We can only proceed if the entry belongs to the current transaction,
803  * otherwise, we must lock the class associated with the classname and
804  * retry the operation once the lock is granted.
805  */
806  if (entry->e_tran_index == tran_index)
807  {
808  /*
809  * The name can be deleted only if it has been reserved by current
810  * transaction
811  */
812  if (entry->e_current.action == LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED || entry->e_current.action == LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED_RENAME)
813  {
814  classname_delete = LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
815  goto error;
816  }
817 
818  assert (entry->e_current.action == LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED
819  || entry->e_current.action == LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED_RENAME);
820 
821  /*
822  * The entry can be changed.
823  * Do we need to save the old action...just in case we do a partial
824  * rollback ?
825  */
826  if (!LSA_ISNULL (&entry->e_current.savep_lsa))
827  {
828  /*
829  * There is a possibility of returning to this top LSA (savepoint).
830  * Save the action.. just in case
831  */
832  old_action = (LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ACTION *) malloc (sizeof (*old_action));
833  if (old_action == NULL)
834  {
835  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (*old_action));
836  classname_delete = LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
837  goto error;
838  }
839 
840  *old_action = entry->e_current;
841  LSA_SET_NULL (&entry->e_current.savep_lsa);
842  entry->e_current.prev = old_action;
843  }
844 
845  entry->e_current.action = LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED;
846  }
847  else
848  {
849  /*
850  * Do not know the fate of this entry until the transaction holding
851  * this entry either commits or aborts. Get the lock and try again.
852  */
853 
854  /*
855  * Exit from critical section since we are going to be suspended and
856  * then retry again.
857  */
858 
859  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
860 
861  if (lock_object (thread_p, &tmp_classoid, oid_Root_class_oid, SCH_M_LOCK, LK_UNCOND_LOCK) != LK_GRANTED)
862  {
863  /*
864  * Unable to acquired lock
865  */
866  return LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
867  }
868  else
869  {
870  /*
871  * Try again
872  * Remove the lock.. since the above was a dirty read
873  */
874  lock_unlock_object (thread_p, &tmp_classoid, oid_Root_class_oid, SCH_M_LOCK, true);
875  goto start;
876  }
877  }
878  }
879  else
880  {
881  /* Some kind of failure. We must notify the error to the caller. */
882  classname_delete = LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
883  }
884 
885 error:
886  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
887 
888  /*
889  * We do not need to lock the entry->oid since it has already been locked
890  * in exclusive mode when the class was deleted or renamed. Avoid duplicate
891  * calls.
892  */
893 
894  /* Note that the index has not been dropped permanently from the database */
895  return classname_delete;
896 }
897 
898 /*
899  * xlocator_rename_class_name () - Rename a classname
900  *
901  * return: LC_FIND_CLASSNAME
902  * (either of LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED_RENAME,
903  * LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST,
904  * LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR)
905  *
906  * oldname(in): Old name of class
907  * newname(in): New name of class
908  * class_oid(in/out): Object identifier of the class
909  *
910  * Note: Rename a class in transient form.
911  */
912 LC_FIND_CLASSNAME
913 xlocator_rename_class_name (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const char *oldname, const char *newname, OID * class_oid)
914 {
915  LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *entry;
916  LC_FIND_CLASSNAME renamed;
917  int tran_index;
918 
919  if (oldname == NULL || newname == NULL)
920  {
921  return LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
922  }
923 
924  assert (oldname != NULL);
925  assert (strlen (oldname) < 255);
926  assert (newname != NULL);
927  assert (strlen (newname) < 255);
928  assert (!OID_ISNULL (class_oid));
929 
930  tran_index = LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p);
931 
932  renamed = xlocator_reserve_class_name (thread_p, newname, class_oid);
933  if (renamed != LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED)
934  {
935  return renamed;
936  }
937 
938  if (csect_enter (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE, INF_WAIT) != NO_ERROR)
939  {
940  /* Some kind of failure. We must notify the error to the caller. */
941  assert (false);
942  return LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
943  }
944 
945  entry = (LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *) mht_get (locator_Mht_classnames, newname);
946  if (entry != NULL)
947  {
948  assert (entry->e_current.action == LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED);
949 
950  entry->e_current.action = LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED_RENAME;
951  renamed = xlocator_delete_class_name (thread_p, oldname);
952  entry = (LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *) mht_get (locator_Mht_classnames, oldname);
953  if (renamed == LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED && entry != NULL)
954  {
955  entry->e_current.action = LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED_RENAME;
956  renamed = LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED_RENAME;
957 
958  /* We need to add a dummy log here. If rename is the first clause of alter statement, there will be no log
959  * entries between parent system savepoint and next flush. Next flush will start a system operation which
960  * will mark the delete action of old class name with same LSA as parent system savepoint. Therefore, the
961  * delete action is not removed when alter statement is aborted and a new table with the same name may be
962  * created. */
963  log_append_redo_data2 (thread_p, RVLOC_CLASSNAME_DUMMY, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, NULL);
964  }
965  else
966  {
967  entry = ((LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *) mht_get (locator_Mht_classnames, newname));
968  if (entry == NULL)
969  {
970  renamed = LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
971  goto error;
972  }
973 
974  assert (locator_is_exist_class_name_entry (thread_p, entry) == false);
975  assert (entry->e_tran_index == tran_index);
976 
977  if (csect_enter (thread_p, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE, INF_WAIT) != NO_ERROR)
978  {
979  assert (false);
980  renamed = LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
981  goto error;
982  }
983 
984  if (locator_drop_class_name_entry (thread_p, newname, NULL) != NO_ERROR)
985  {
986  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE);
987  renamed = LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
988  goto error;
989  }
990 
991  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE);
992  }
993  }
994 
995 error:
996 
997  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
998 
999  return renamed;
1000 }
1001 
1002 /*
1003  * xlocator_find_class_oid () - Find oid of a classname
1004  *
1005  * return: LC_FIND_CLASSNAME
1006  * (either of LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST,
1007  * LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED,
1008  * LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR)
1009  *
1010  * classname(in): Name of class to find
1011  * class_oid(out): Set as a side effect
1012  * lock(in): Lock to acquire for the class
1013  *
1014  * Note: Find the class identifier of the given class name and lock the
1015  * class with the given mode.
1016  * If there is an entry on the memory classname table,
1017  * we can proceed if the entry belongs to the current
1018  * transaction, otherwise, we must wait until the transaction
1019  * holding the entry terminates since the fate of the classname
1020  * entry cannot be predicted.
1021  */
1022 LC_FIND_CLASSNAME
1023 xlocator_find_class_oid (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const char *classname, OID * class_oid, LOCK lock)
1024 {
1025  int tran_index;
1026  LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *entry;
1027  LOCK tmp_lock;
1028  LC_FIND_CLASSNAME find = LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST;
1029 
1030  tran_index = LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p);
1031 
1032 start:
1033  find = LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST;
1034 
1035  if (csect_enter_as_reader (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE, INF_WAIT) != NO_ERROR)
1036  {
1037  assert (false);
1038  return LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
1039  }
1040 
1041  entry = (LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *) mht_get (locator_Mht_classnames, classname);
1042 
1043  if (entry != NULL)
1044  {
1045  COPY_OID (class_oid, &entry->e_current.oid);
1046  assert (find == LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST);
1047  }
1048 
1049  if (locator_is_exist_class_name_entry (thread_p, entry))
1050  {
1051  assert (find == LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST); /* OK, go ahead */
1052  }
1053  else if (entry != NULL)
1054  {
1055  assert (entry->e_current.action != LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST);
1056 
1057  /*
1058  * We can only proceed if the entry belongs to the current transaction,
1059  * otherwise, we must lock the class associated with the classname and
1060  * retry the operation once the lock is granted.
1061  */
1062  assert (find == LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST);
1063 
1064  if (entry->e_tran_index == tran_index)
1065  {
1066  if (entry->e_current.action == LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED || entry->e_current.action == LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED_RENAME)
1067  {
1068  OID_SET_NULL (class_oid); /* clear */
1069  find = LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED;
1070  }
1071  else
1072  {
1073  assert (find == LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST); /* OK, go ahead */
1074  }
1075  }
1076  else
1077  {
1078  /*
1079  * Do not know the fate of this entry until the transaction is
1080  * committed or aborted. Get the lock and try again.
1081  */
1082  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
1083 
1084  if (lock != NULL_LOCK)
1085  {
1086  tmp_lock = lock;
1087  }
1088  else
1089  {
1090  tmp_lock = IS_LOCK;
1091  }
1092 
1093  if (lock_object (thread_p, class_oid, oid_Root_class_oid, tmp_lock, LK_UNCOND_LOCK) != LK_GRANTED)
1094  {
1095  /*
1096  * Unable to acquired lock
1097  */
1098  OID_SET_NULL (class_oid); /* clear */
1099  return LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
1100  }
1101  else
1102  {
1103  /*
1104  * Try again
1105  * Remove the lock.. since the above was a dirty read
1106  */
1107  lock_unlock_object (thread_p, class_oid, oid_Root_class_oid, tmp_lock, true);
1108  goto start;
1109  }
1110  }
1111  }
1112  else
1113  {
1114  find = LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED;
1115  }
1116 
1117  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
1118 
1119  if (lock != NULL_LOCK && find == LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST)
1120  {
1121  /* Now acquired the desired lock */
1122  if (lock_object (thread_p, class_oid, oid_Root_class_oid, lock, LK_UNCOND_LOCK) != LK_GRANTED)
1123  {
1124  /*
1125  * Unable to acquired lock
1126  */
1127  OID_SET_NULL (class_oid); /* clear */
1128  find = LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
1129  }
1130  else
1131  {
1132  lock_unlock_object (thread_p, class_oid, oid_Root_class_oid, lock, false);
1133  }
1134  }
1135 
1136 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
1137  if (find == LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST)
1138  {
1139  assert (!OID_ISNULL (class_oid));
1140  }
1141  else if (find == LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR)
1142  {
1143  assert (OID_ISNULL (class_oid));
1144  }
1145 #endif
1146 
1147  return find;
1148 }
1149 
1150 /*
1151  * locator_permoid_class_name () - Change reserve name with permanent oid
1152  *
1153  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
1154  *
1155  * classname(in): Name of class
1156  * class_oid(in): New OID
1157  *
1158  * Note: Update the entry for the given classname with the
1159  * given class identifier. The entry must belong to the
1160  * current transaction.
1161  */
1162 static int
1163 locator_permoid_class_name (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const char *classname, const OID * class_oid)
1164 {
1165  LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *entry;
1166  LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ACTION *old_action;
1167  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
1168 
1169  /* Is there any entries on the classname hash table ? */
1170  if (csect_enter (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE, INF_WAIT) != NO_ERROR)
1171  {
1172  assert (false);
1173  return ER_FAILED;
1174  }
1175 
1176  entry = (LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *) mht_get (locator_Mht_classnames, classname);
1177  if (entry == NULL || entry->e_tran_index != LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p))
1178  {
1179  assert (false);
1180  error_code = ER_FAILED;
1181  goto error; /* should be impossible */
1182  }
1183 
1184  assert (locator_is_exist_class_name_entry (thread_p, entry) == false);
1185  assert (entry->e_tran_index == LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p));
1186 
1187  if (entry->e_current.action != LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST)
1188  {
1189  /*
1190  * Remove the old lock entry. The new entry has already been acquired by
1191  * the caller
1192  */
1193  lock_unlock_object (thread_p, &entry->e_current.oid, oid_Root_class_oid, X_LOCK, true);
1194 
1195  /*
1196  * Do we need to save the old action...just in case we do a partial
1197  * rollback ?
1198  */
1199  if (!LSA_ISNULL (&entry->e_current.savep_lsa))
1200  {
1201  /*
1202  * There is a possibility of returning to this top LSA (savepoint).
1203  * Save the action.. just in case
1204  */
1205  old_action = (LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ACTION *) malloc (sizeof (*old_action));
1206  if (old_action == NULL)
1207  {
1208  error_code = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
1209  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error_code, 1, sizeof (*old_action));
1210  goto error;
1211  }
1212 
1213  *old_action = entry->e_current;
1214  LSA_SET_NULL (&entry->e_current.savep_lsa);
1215  entry->e_current.prev = old_action;
1216  }
1217 
1218  COPY_OID (&entry->e_current.oid, class_oid);
1219  }
1220 
1221  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
1222 
1223  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
1224 
1225  return NO_ERROR;
1226 
1227 error:
1228 
1229  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
1230 
1231  assert (error_code != NO_ERROR);
1232 
1233  return error_code;
1234 }
1235 
1236 /*
1237  * locator_drop_transient_class_name_entries () - Drop transient classname entries
1238  *
1239  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
1240  *
1241  * savep_lsa(in): up to given LSA
1242  *
1243  * Note: Remove all the classname transient entries of the given
1244  * transaction up to the given savepoint.
1245  * This is done when the transaction terminates.
1246  */
1247 int
1248 locator_drop_transient_class_name_entries (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_LSA * savep_lsa)
1249 {
1250  MODIFIED_CLASS_ENTRY *t;
1251  int tran_index;
1252  LOG_TDES *tdes; /* Transaction descriptor */
1253  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
1254 
1255  tran_index = LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p);
1256 
1257  if (tran_index != NULL_TRAN_INDEX)
1258  {
1259  if (locator_get_num_transient_classnames (tran_index) <= 0)
1260  {
1261  return NO_ERROR;
1262  }
1263  }
1264 
1265  tdes = LOG_FIND_TDES (tran_index);
1266 
1267  if (csect_enter (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE, INF_WAIT) != NO_ERROR)
1268  {
1269  /* Some kind of failure. We must notify the error to the caller. */
1270  assert (false);
1271  return ER_FAILED;
1272  }
1273 
1274  if (csect_enter (thread_p, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE, INF_WAIT) != NO_ERROR)
1275  {
1276  assert (false);
1277  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
1278  return ER_FAILED;
1279  }
1280 
1281  for (t = tdes->modified_class_list; t != NULL; t = t->m_next)
1282  {
1283  assert (t->m_classname != NULL);
1284  error_code = locator_drop_class_name_entry (thread_p, t->m_classname, savep_lsa);
1285  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
1286  {
1287  assert (false); /* is impossible */
1288  break;
1289  }
1290  }
1291  assert (locator_get_num_transient_classnames (tran_index) >= 0);
1292 
1293  /* defence for commit or rollback; include partial rollback */
1294  if (tran_index != NULL_TRAN_INDEX)
1295  {
1296  if (locator_get_num_transient_classnames (tran_index) > 0)
1297  {
1298  (void) mht_map (locator_Mht_classnames, locator_defence_drop_class_name_entry, savep_lsa);
1299  }
1300  }
1301 
1302  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
1303  {
1304  /* defence for commit or rollback; exclude partial rollback */
1305  if (savep_lsa == NULL)
1306  {
1307  if (locator_get_num_transient_classnames (tran_index) != 0)
1308  {
1309  assert (false); /* something wrong */
1310  error_code = ER_FAILED;
1311  }
1312  }
1313  }
1314 
1315  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE);
1316 
1317  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
1318 
1319  return error_code;
1320 }
1321 
1322 /*
1323  * locator_drop_class_name_entry () - Remove one transient entry
1324  *
1325  * return: NO_ERROR or error code
1326  *
1327  * thread_p(in):
1328  * classname(in): The classname (key)
1329  * savep_lsa(in): up to given LSA
1330  *
1331  * Note: Remove transient entry if it belongs to current transaction.
1332  */
1333 static int
1334 locator_drop_class_name_entry (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const char *classname, LOG_LSA * savep_lsa)
1335 {
1336  int tran_index;
1337  LOG_TDES *tdes; /* Transaction descriptor */
1338  LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *entry;
1339  LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ACTION *old_action;
1340 
1341  tran_index = LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p);
1342 
1343  tdes = LOG_FIND_TDES (tran_index);
1344 
1345  assert (csect_check_own (thread_p, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE) == 1);
1346  assert (csect_check_own (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE) == 1);
1347 
1348  entry = (LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *) mht_get (locator_Mht_classnames, classname);
1349  if (entry == NULL)
1350  {
1351  /* table is dropped by myself; not exist */
1352  return NO_ERROR; /* do nothing */
1353  }
1354 
1355  if (!(entry->e_tran_index == NULL_TRAN_INDEX || entry->e_tran_index == tran_index))
1356  {
1357  /* table is dropped by myself and reserved by other tranx */
1358  return NO_ERROR;
1359  }
1360 
1361  assert (entry->e_name != NULL);
1362  assert (!OID_ISNULL (&entry->e_current.oid));
1363 
1364 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
1365  if (entry->e_current.action == LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST)
1366  {
1367  assert (locator_is_exist_class_name_entry (thread_p, entry));
1368  }
1369 #endif
1370 
1371  assert (savep_lsa == NULL || !LSA_ISNULL (savep_lsa));
1372 
1373  if (locator_is_exist_class_name_entry (thread_p, entry) == false)
1374  {
1375  assert (entry->e_tran_index == tran_index);
1376 
1377  if (savep_lsa == NULL && tdes->state != TRAN_UNACTIVE_ABORTED)
1378  {
1379  /* is commit; get current */
1380  while (entry->e_current.prev != NULL)
1381  {
1382  old_action = entry->e_current.prev;
1383  entry->e_current.prev = old_action->prev;
1384  free_and_init (old_action);
1385  }
1386  assert (entry->e_current.prev == NULL);
1387 
1388  locator_decr_num_transient_classnames (entry->e_tran_index);
1389 
1390  if (entry->e_current.action == LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED
1391  || entry->e_current.action == LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED_RENAME)
1392  {
1393  entry->e_tran_index = NULL_TRAN_INDEX;
1394 
1395  entry->e_current.action = LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST;
1396  LSA_SET_NULL (&entry->e_current.savep_lsa);
1397 
1398  assert (locator_is_exist_class_name_entry (thread_p, entry));
1399  }
1400  else
1401  {
1402  assert (entry->e_current.action == LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED
1403  || entry->e_current.action == LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED_RENAME);
1404 
1405  (void) locator_force_drop_class_name_entry (entry->e_name, entry, NULL);
1406  entry = NULL; /* clear */
1407  }
1408  }
1409  else
1410  {
1411  /* is rollback or partial rollback; get prev */
1412  while (savep_lsa == NULL /* is rollback */
1413  || LSA_ISNULL (&entry->e_current.savep_lsa) || LSA_LT (savep_lsa, &entry->e_current.savep_lsa))
1414  {
1415  if (entry->e_current.prev == NULL)
1416  {
1417  break;
1418  }
1419 
1420  old_action = entry->e_current.prev;
1421  entry->e_current = *old_action;
1422  free_and_init (old_action);
1423  }
1424 
1425  if (savep_lsa == NULL /* is rollback */
1426  || LSA_ISNULL (&entry->e_current.savep_lsa) || LSA_LT (savep_lsa, &entry->e_current.savep_lsa))
1427  {
1428  assert (entry->e_current.prev == NULL);
1429 
1430  locator_decr_num_transient_classnames (entry->e_tran_index);
1431 
1432  if (entry->e_current.action == LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED
1433  || entry->e_current.action == LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED_RENAME)
1434  {
1435  entry->e_tran_index = NULL_TRAN_INDEX;
1436 
1437  entry->e_current.action = LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST;
1438  LSA_SET_NULL (&entry->e_current.savep_lsa);
1439 
1440  assert (locator_is_exist_class_name_entry (thread_p, entry));
1441  }
1442  else
1443  {
1444  assert (entry->e_current.action == LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED
1445  || entry->e_current.action == LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED_RENAME);
1446 
1447  (void) locator_force_drop_class_name_entry (entry->e_name, entry, NULL);
1448  entry = NULL; /* clear */
1449  }
1450  }
1451  } /* else */
1452  }
1453 
1454 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
1455  /* check iff permanent entry */
1456  if (locator_is_exist_class_name_entry (thread_p, entry))
1457  {
1458  OID class_oid;
1459 
1460  COPY_OID (&class_oid, &entry->e_current.oid);
1461 
1462  if (class_oid.slotid <= 0 || class_oid.volid < 0 || class_oid.pageid < 0)
1463  {
1464  assert (false);
1465  }
1466 
1467  if (disk_is_page_sector_reserved_with_debug_crash (thread_p, class_oid.volid, class_oid.pageid, true)
1468  != DISK_VALID)
1469  {
1470  assert (false);
1471  }
1472  }
1473 #endif
1474 
1475  return NO_ERROR;
1476 }
1477 
1478 /*
1479  * locator_defence_drop_class_name_entry () - Remove one transient entry
1480  *
1481  * return: NO_ERROR or error code
1482  *
1483  * name(in):
1484  * ent(in):
1485  * args(in):
1486  *
1487  * Note: Remove transient entry if it belongs to current transaction.
1488  */
1489 static int
1490 locator_defence_drop_class_name_entry (const void *name, void *ent, void *args)
1491 {
1492  LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *entry = (LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *) ent;
1493  LOG_LSA *savep_lsa = (LOG_LSA *) args;
1494  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p;
1495  int tran_index;
1496 
1497  thread_p = thread_get_thread_entry_info ();
1498 
1499  assert (csect_check_own (thread_p, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE) == 1);
1500  assert (csect_check_own (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE) == 1);
1501 
1502  tran_index = LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p);
1503  assert (tran_index != NULL_TRAN_INDEX);
1504 
1505 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
1506  if (locator_is_exist_class_name_entry (thread_p, entry))
1507  {
1508  OID class_oid;
1509 
1510  COPY_OID (&class_oid, &entry->e_current.oid);
1511 
1512  assert (heap_does_exist (thread_p, oid_Root_class_oid, &class_oid));
1513 
1514  /* check class_oid */
1515  if (class_oid.slotid <= 0 || class_oid.volid < 0 || class_oid.pageid < 0)
1516  {
1517  assert (false);
1518  }
1519 
1520  if (disk_is_page_sector_reserved_with_debug_crash (thread_p, class_oid.volid, class_oid.pageid, true)
1521  != DISK_VALID)
1522  {
1523  assert (false);
1524  }
1525  }
1526 #endif
1527 
1528  /* check iff uncleared entry */
1529  if (entry->e_tran_index == tran_index)
1530  {
1531  assert (entry->e_tran_index != NULL_TRAN_INDEX);
1532 
1533  (void) locator_drop_class_name_entry (thread_p, entry->e_name, savep_lsa);
1534  }
1535 
1536  return NO_ERROR;
1537 }
1538 
1539 /*
1540  * locator_force_drop_class_name_entry () -
1541  *
1542  * return:
1543  *
1544  * name(in):
1545  * ent(in):
1546  * args(in): Not used
1547  */
1548 static int
1549 locator_force_drop_class_name_entry (const void *name, void *ent, void *args)
1550 {
1551  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p;
1552  LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *entry = (LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *) ent;
1553  LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ACTION *old_action;
1554  OID class_oid;
1555 
1556  thread_p = thread_get_thread_entry_info ();
1557 
1558  assert (csect_check_own (thread_p, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE) == 1);
1559  assert (csect_check_own (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE) == 1);
1560 
1561  COPY_OID (&class_oid, &entry->e_current.oid);
1562 
1563  while (entry->e_current.prev != NULL)
1564  {
1565  old_action = entry->e_current.prev;
1566  entry->e_current = *old_action;
1567  free_and_init (old_action);
1568  }
1569 
1570  (void) mht_rem (locator_Mht_classnames, name, NULL, NULL);
1571 
1572  free_and_init (entry->e_name);
1573  free_and_init (entry);
1574 
1575  (void) catcls_remove_entry (thread_p, &class_oid);
1576 
1577  return NO_ERROR;
1578 }
1579 
1580 /*
1581  * locator_savepoint_transient_class_name_entries () - Reset savepoint of
1582  * classname entries
1583  *
1584  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
1585  *
1586  * savep_lsa(in): LSA of a possible rollback point
1587  *
1588  * Note: Reset the classname entries of the current
1589  * transaction with the given LSA address. This is done when a
1590  * new savepoint is taken or top system operations is started
1591  */
1592 int
1593 locator_savepoint_transient_class_name_entries (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_LSA * savep_lsa)
1594 {
1595  MODIFIED_CLASS_ENTRY *t;
1596  int tran_index;
1597  LOG_TDES *tdes; /* Transaction descriptor */
1598  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
1599 
1600  tran_index = LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p);
1601 
1602  if (tran_index != NULL_TRAN_INDEX)
1603  {
1604  if (locator_get_num_transient_classnames (tran_index) <= 0)
1605  {
1606  return NO_ERROR;
1607  }
1608  }
1609 
1610  tdes = LOG_FIND_TDES (tran_index);
1611 
1612  if (tdes->modified_class_list == NULL)
1613  {
1614  /* We may have new transient classnames or dropping classnames whose heap files have not yet been updated; Then,
1615  * Those classnames have not been added to the modifed list Refer locator_defence_drop_class_name_entry () */
1616  return NO_ERROR; /* do nothing */
1617  }
1618 
1619  if (csect_enter (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE, INF_WAIT) != NO_ERROR)
1620  {
1621  /* Some kind of failure. We must notify the error to the caller. */
1622  assert (false);
1623  return ER_FAILED;
1624  }
1625 
1626  for (t = tdes->modified_class_list; t != NULL; t = t->m_next)
1627  {
1628  assert (t->m_classname != NULL);
1629  error_code = locator_savepoint_class_name_entry (t->m_classname, savep_lsa);
1630  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
1631  {
1632  assert (false); /* is impossible */
1633  break;
1634  }
1635  }
1636 
1637  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
1638 
1639  return error_code;
1640 }
1641 
1642 /*
1643  * locator_savepoint_class_name_entry () - Savepoint one transient entry
1644  *
1645  * return: NO_ERROR
1646  *
1647  * classname(in): The classname
1648  * savep_lsa(in): LSA of a possible rollback point
1649  *
1650  * Note: Savepoint a transient entry if it belongs to current
1651  * transaction and it does not have a savepoint as the last
1652  * modified point.
1653  */
1654 static int
1655 locator_savepoint_class_name_entry (const char *classname, LOG_LSA * savep_lsa)
1656 {
1657  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p;
1658  int tran_index;
1659  LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *entry;
1660 
1661  thread_p = thread_get_thread_entry_info ();
1662 
1663  tran_index = LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p);
1664 
1665  assert (csect_check_own (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE) == 1);
1666 
1667  entry = (LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *) mht_get (locator_Mht_classnames, classname);
1668  if (entry == NULL)
1669  {
1670  /* table is dropped by myself; not exist */
1671  return NO_ERROR; /* do nothing */
1672  }
1673 
1674  if (!(entry->e_tran_index == NULL_TRAN_INDEX || entry->e_tran_index == tran_index))
1675  {
1676  /* table is dropped by myself and reserved by other tranx */
1677  return NO_ERROR; /* do nothing */
1678  }
1679 
1680  assert (entry->e_name != NULL);
1681  assert (!OID_ISNULL (&entry->e_current.oid));
1682 
1683  /* check iff need to savepoint */
1684  if (locator_is_exist_class_name_entry (thread_p, entry) == false)
1685  {
1686  assert (entry->e_tran_index == tran_index);
1687 
1688  if (LSA_ISNULL (&entry->e_current.savep_lsa))
1689  {
1690  LSA_COPY (&entry->e_current.savep_lsa, savep_lsa);
1691  }
1692  }
1693 
1694  return NO_ERROR;
1695 }
1696 
1697 /*
1698  * locator_print_class_name () - Print an entry of classname memory hash table
1699  *
1700  * return: always return true
1701  *
1702  * outfp(in): FILE stream where to dump the entry
1703  * key(in): Classname
1704  * ent(in): The entry associated with classname
1705  * args(in): class No
1706  *
1707  * Note:Print an entry of the classname memory hash table.
1708  */
1709 static int
1710 locator_print_class_name (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, FILE * outfp, const void *key, void *ent, void *args)
1711 {
1712  LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *entry = (LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *) ent;
1713  int *class_no_p = (int *) args;
1714  LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ACTION *action;
1715  const char *str_action;
1716  size_t i;
1717  size_t key_size;
1718 
1719  assert (class_no_p != NULL);
1720 
1721  fprintf (outfp, " %2d %s ", *class_no_p, (char *) key);
1722  (*class_no_p)++;
1723  key_size = strlen ((char *) key);
1724  for (i = 0; i < (29 - key_size); i++)
1725  {
1726  fprintf (outfp, " ");
1727  }
1728  fprintf (outfp, "TRAN_INDEX = %d\n", entry->e_tran_index);
1729 
1730  action = &entry->e_current;
1731  while (action != NULL)
1732  {
1733  switch (action->action)
1734  {
1735  case LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED:
1736  str_action = "LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVE";
1737  break;
1738  case LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED:
1739  str_action = "LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED";
1740  break;
1741  case LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST:
1742  str_action = "LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST";
1743  break;
1744  case LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED_RENAME:
1745  str_action = "LC_CLASSNAME_RESERVED_RENAME";
1746  break;
1747  case LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED_RENAME:
1748  str_action = "LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED_RENAME";
1749  break;
1750  default:
1751  assert (action->action == LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR);
1752  str_action = "UNKNOWN";
1753  break;
1754  }
1755  fprintf (outfp, " action = %s, OID = %d|%d|%d, Save_Lsa = %lld|%d\n", str_action, action->oid.volid,
1756  action->oid.pageid, action->oid.slotid, LSA_AS_ARGS (&action->savep_lsa));
1757  action = action->prev;
1758  }
1759 
1760  return (true);
1761 }
1762 
1763 /*
1764  * locator_dump_class_names () - Dump all classname entries
1765  *
1766  * return:
1767  *
1768  * out_fp(in): output file
1769  *
1770  * Note:Dump all names of classes and their corresponding OIDs.
1771  * This function is used for debugging purposes.
1772  */
1773 void
1774 locator_dump_class_names (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, FILE * out_fp)
1775 {
1776  int class_no;
1777 
1778 #if defined(NDEBUG) /* skip at debug build */
1779  if (csect_enter_as_reader (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE, INF_WAIT) != NO_ERROR)
1780  {
1781  assert (false);
1782  return;
1783  }
1784 #endif
1785 
1786  class_no = 1; /* init */
1787  (void) mht_dump (thread_p, out_fp, locator_Mht_classnames, false, locator_print_class_name, &class_no);
1788 
1789 #if defined(NDEBUG) /* skip at debug build */
1790  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
1791 #endif
1792 }

1794 /*
1795  * locator_generate_class_pseudo_oid () - Generate a pseudo-OID to be used
1796  * by reserved class name until a
1797  * permanent one is provided.
1798  *
1799  * return :
1800  * thread_p (in) :
1801  * class_oid (in) :
1802  */
1803 static void
1804 locator_generate_class_pseudo_oid (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OID * class_oid)
1805 {
1806  assert (csect_check_own (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE) == 1);
1807 
1808  class_oid->volid = -2;
1809  class_oid->slotid = -2;
1810  class_oid->pageid = locator_Pseudo_pageid_crt;
1811 
1812  if (locator_Pseudo_pageid_crt == locator_Pseudo_pageid_last)
1813  {
1814  locator_Pseudo_pageid_crt = locator_Pseudo_pageid_first;
1815  }
1816  else
1817  {
1818  locator_Pseudo_pageid_crt--;
1819  }
1820 }

1822 /*
1823  * locator_check_class_on_heap () - Check the classname on the heap object
1824  *
1825  * return: NO_ERROR continue checking, error code stop checking, bad error
1826  *
1827  * name(in): The expected class name
1828  * ent(in):
1829  * args(out): Could be set as a side effect to either: DISK_INVALID,
1830  * DISK_ERROR when an inconsistency is found. Otherwise, it is
1831  * left in touch. The caller should initialize it to DISK_VALID
1832  *
1833  * Note: Check if the classname of the class associated with ent
1834  * is the same as the given class name.
1835  * If class does not exist, or its name is different from the
1836  * given one, isvalid is set to DISK_INVALID. In the case of other
1837  * kind of error, isvalid is set to DISK_ERROR.
1838  * If isvalid is set to DISK_ERROR, we return false to stop
1839  * the map hash, otherwise, we return true to continue.
1840  */
1841 static int
1842 locator_check_class_on_heap (const void *name, void *ent, void *args)
1843 {
1844  THREAD_ENTRY *thread_p;
1845  LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *entry = (LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *) ent;
1846  DISK_ISVALID *isvalid = (DISK_ISVALID *) args;
1847  const char *classname;
1848  char *heap_classname;
1849  OID *class_oid;
1850 
1851  thread_p = thread_get_thread_entry_info ();
1852 
1853  assert (csect_check_own (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE) == 1);
1854 
1855  if (entry->e_current.action != LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST)
1856  {
1857  /* is not permanent classname */
1858  return NO_ERROR;
1859  }
1860 
1861  classname = (char *) name;
1862  class_oid = &entry->e_current.oid;
1863 
1864  if (heap_get_class_name_alloc_if_diff (thread_p, class_oid, (char *) classname, &heap_classname) != NO_ERROR
1865  || heap_classname == NULL)
1866  {
1867  if (er_errid () == ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT)
1868  {
1869  er_set (ER_FATAL_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_LC_INCONSISTENT_CLASSNAME_TYPE4, 4, classname,
1870  class_oid->volid, class_oid->pageid, class_oid->slotid);
1871  *isvalid = DISK_INVALID;
1872  }
1873  else
1874  {
1875  *isvalid = DISK_ERROR;
1876  }
1877 
1878  goto error;
1879  }
1880 
1881  /* Compare the classname pointers. If the same pointers classes are the same since the class was no malloc */
1882  if (heap_classname != classname)
1883  {
1884  /* Different names */
1885  er_set (ER_FATAL_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_LC_INCONSISTENT_CLASSNAME_TYPE1, 5, class_oid->volid,
1886  class_oid->pageid, class_oid->slotid, classname, heap_classname);
1887  *isvalid = DISK_INVALID;
1888  free_and_init (heap_classname);
1889  }
1890 
1891 error:
1892  if (*isvalid == DISK_ERROR)
1893  {
1894  return ER_FAILED;
1895  }
1896  else
1897  {
1898  return NO_ERROR;
1899  }
1900 }
1901 
1902 /*
1903  * locator_check_class_names () - Check classname consistency
1904  *
1905  * return: DISK_ISVALID
1906  *
1907  * Note: Check the consistency of the classname_to_oid and the heap of
1908  * classes and vice versa.
1909  */
1910 DISK_ISVALID
1911 locator_check_class_names (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p)
1912 {
1913  DISK_ISVALID isvalid;
1914  RECDES peek = RECDES_INITIALIZER; /* Record descriptor for peeking object */
1915  HFID root_hfid;
1916  OID class_oid;
1917  char *classname = NULL;
1918  HEAP_SCANCACHE scan_cache;
1919  MVCC_SNAPSHOT *mvcc_snapshot = NULL;
1920  LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *entry;
1921 
1922  mvcc_snapshot = logtb_get_mvcc_snapshot (thread_p);
1923  if (mvcc_snapshot == NULL)
1924  {
1925  return DISK_ERROR;
1926  }
1927 
1928  if (csect_enter (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE, INF_WAIT) != NO_ERROR)
1929  {
1930  /* Some kind of failure. We must notify the error to the caller. */
1931  assert (false);
1932  return DISK_ERROR;
1933  }
1934 
1935  /*
1936  * CHECK 1: Each class that is found by scanning the heap of classes, must
1937  * be part of the permanent classname_to_oid table.
1938  */
1939 
1940  /* Find the heap for the classes */
1941 
1942  /* Find every single class */
1943 
1944  if (boot_find_root_heap (&root_hfid) != NO_ERROR || HFID_IS_NULL (&root_hfid))
1945  {
1946  goto error;
1947  }
1948 
1949  if (heap_scancache_start (thread_p, &scan_cache, &root_hfid, oid_Root_class_oid, true, false, mvcc_snapshot) !=
1950  NO_ERROR)
1951  {
1952  goto error;
1953  }
1954 
1955  class_oid.volid = root_hfid.vfid.volid;
1956  class_oid.pageid = NULL_PAGEID;
1957  class_oid.slotid = NULL_SLOTID;
1958 
1959  isvalid = DISK_VALID;
1960  while (heap_next (thread_p, &root_hfid, oid_Root_class_oid, &class_oid, &peek, &scan_cache, PEEK) == S_SUCCESS)
1961  {
1962  classname = or_class_name (&peek);
1963  assert (classname != NULL);
1964  assert (strlen (classname) < 255);
1965 
1966  /*
1967  * Make sure that this class exists in classname_to_OID table and that
1968  * the OIDS matches
1969  */
1970  entry = (LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *) mht_get (locator_Mht_classnames, classname);
1971  if (entry == NULL)
1972  {
1973  isvalid = DISK_INVALID;
1974  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_LC_INCONSISTENT_CLASSNAME_TYPE3, 4, classname, class_oid.volid,
1975  class_oid.pageid, class_oid.slotid);
1976  }
1977  else
1978  {
1979  /* Are OIDs the same ? */
1980  if (!OID_EQ (&class_oid, &entry->e_current.oid))
1981  {
1982  er_set (ER_FATAL_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_LC_INCONSISTENT_CLASSNAME_TYPE2, 7, classname,
1983  entry->e_current.oid.volid, entry->e_current.oid.pageid, entry->e_current.oid.slotid,
1984  class_oid.volid, class_oid.pageid, class_oid.slotid);
1985  isvalid = DISK_INVALID;
1986  }
1987  }
1988  } /* while (...) */
1989 
1990  /* End the scan cursor */
1991  if (heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache) != NO_ERROR)
1992  {
1993  isvalid = DISK_ERROR;
1994  }
1995 
1996  /*
1997  * CHECK 2: Same that check1 but from classname_to_OID to existance of class
1998  */
1999  (void) mht_map (locator_Mht_classnames, locator_check_class_on_heap, &isvalid);
2000 
2001  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
2002 
2003  return isvalid;
2004 
2005 error:
2006  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
2007 
2008  return DISK_ERROR;
2009 }
2010 
2011 /*
2012  * Functions related to fetching and flushing
2013  */
2014 
2015 /*
2016  * xlocator_assign_oid () - Assign a permanent oid
2017  *
2018  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
2019  *
2020  * hfid(in): Heap where the object will be stored
2021  * perm_oid(in/out): Object identifier.. (set as a side effect)
2022  * expected_length(in): Expected length of the object
2023  * class_oid(in): The class of the instance
2024  * classname(in): Optional... classname for classes
2025  *
2026  * Note: A permanent oid is assigned, the object associated with that
2027  * OID is locked through the new OID. If the object is a class
2028  * the classname to OID entry is updated to reflect the
2029  * newly assigned OID.
2030  */
2031 int
2032 xlocator_assign_oid (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const HFID * hfid, OID * perm_oid, int expected_length, OID * class_oid,
2033  const char *classname)
2034 {
2035  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
2036 
2037  if (heap_assign_address (thread_p, hfid, class_oid, perm_oid, expected_length) != NO_ERROR)
2038  {
2039  return ER_FAILED;
2040  }
2041 
2042  if (classname != NULL)
2043  {
2044  error_code = locator_permoid_class_name (thread_p, classname, perm_oid);
2045  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
2046  }
2047 
2048  return error_code;
2049 }
