2051 /*
2052  * locator_find_lockset_missing_class_oids () - Find missing class oids
2053  *
2054  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
2055  *
2056  * lockset(in): Request for finding missing classes
2057  *
2058  * Note: Find missing class oids in requested area.
2059  * The function does not quit when an error is found if the value
2060  * of lockset->quit_on_errors is false. In this case the
2061  * object with the error is set to a NULL_OID. For example, when
2062  * a class of an object does not exist.
2063  * Note: There must be enough space in the lockset area to define all
2064  * missing classes.
2065  */
2066 static int
2067 locator_find_lockset_missing_class_oids (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LC_LOCKSET * lockset)
2068 {
2069  LC_LOCKSET_REQOBJ *reqobjs; /* Description of one instance to fetch */
2070  LC_LOCKSET_CLASSOF *reqclasses; /* Description of one class of a requested object */
2071  OID class_oid; /* Uses to hold the class_oid when it is unknown */
2072  int i, j;
2073  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
2074 
2075  /* Locate array of objects and array of classes */
2076 
2077  reqobjs = lockset->objects;
2078  reqclasses = lockset->classes;
2079 
2080 #if defined(CUBRID_DEBUG)
2081  i = (sizeof (*lockset) + (lockset->num_reqobjs * (sizeof (*reqclasses) + sizeof (*reqobjs))));
2082 
2083  if (lockset->length < i || lockset->classes != ((LC_LOCKSET_CLASSOF *) (lockset->mem + sizeof (*lockset)))
2084  || lockset->objects < ((LC_LOCKSET_REQOBJ *) (lockset->classes + lockset->num_reqobjs)))
2085  {
2086  er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE,
2087  "locator_find_lockset_missing_class_oids: *** SYSTEM ERROR. Requesting area is incorrect,\n"
2088  " either area is too small %d (expect at least %d),\n pointer to classes %p (expected %p), or\n"
2089  " pointer to objects %p (expected >= %p) are incorrect\n", lockset->length, i, lockset->classes,
2090  ((LC_LOCKSET_CLASSOF *) (lockset->mem + sizeof (*lockset))), lockset->objects,
2091  ((LC_LOCKSET_REQOBJ *) (lockset->classes + lockset->num_reqobjs)));
2092  er_set (ER_FATAL_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_GENERIC_ERROR, 0);
2093 
2094  error_code = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
2095  goto error;
2096  }
2097 #endif /* CUBRID_DEBUG */
2098 
2099 
2100  /*
2101  * All class identifiers of requested objects must be known. Find the ones
2102  * that the caller is unaware
2103  */
2104 
2105  for (i = 0; i < lockset->num_reqobjs; i++)
2106  {
2107  if (reqobjs[i].class_index != -1 || OID_ISNULL (&reqobjs[i].oid))
2108  {
2109  continue;
2110  }
2111  /*
2112  * Caller does not know the class identifier of the requested object.
2113  * Get the class identifier from disk
2114  */
2115  if (heap_get_class_oid (thread_p, &reqobjs[i].oid, &class_oid) != S_SUCCESS)
2116  {
2117  /*
2118  * Unable to find the class of the object. Remove the object from
2119  * the list of requested objects.
2120  */
2121  OID_SET_NULL (&reqobjs[i].oid);
2122  if (lockset->quit_on_errors != false)
2123  {
2124  error_code = ER_FAILED;
2125  goto error;
2126  }
2127  continue;
2128  }
2129 
2130  /*
2131  * Insert this class in the list of classes of requested objects.
2132  * Make sure that the class is not already present in the list.
2133  */
2134 
2135  for (j = 0; j < lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs; j++)
2136  {
2137  if (OID_EQ (&class_oid, &reqclasses[j].oid))
2138  {
2139  /* OID is already in the list */
2140  reqobjs[i].class_index = j;
2141  break;
2142  }
2143  }
2144  if (j >= lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs)
2145  {
2146  /* OID is not in the list */
2147  COPY_OID (&reqclasses[lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs].oid, &class_oid);
2148  reqclasses[lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs].chn = CHN_UNKNOWN_ATCLIENT;
2149  reqobjs[i].class_index = lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs;
2150  lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs++;
2151  }
2152  }
2153 
2154 error:
2155  return error_code;
2156 }
2157 
2158 static SCAN_CODE
2159 locator_return_object_assign (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOCATOR_RETURN_NXOBJ * assign, OID * class_oid, OID * oid,
2160  int chn, int guess_chn, SCAN_CODE scan, int tran_index)
2161 {
2162  int round_length; /* Length of object rounded to integer alignment */
2163 
2164  switch (scan)
2165  {
2166  case S_SUCCESS:
2167  /*
2168  * The cached object was obsolete.
2169  */
2170  round_length = DB_ALIGN (assign->recdes.length, MAX_ALIGNMENT);
2171  if (assign->recdes.area_size < (round_length + (int) sizeof (*assign->obj)))
2172  {
2173  assign->recdes.area_size -= (round_length + sizeof (*assign->obj));
2174  scan = S_DOESNT_FIT;
2175  }
2176  else
2177  {
2178  if (OID_IS_ROOTOID (class_oid))
2179  {
2180  if (tran_index == NULL_TRAN_INDEX)
2181  {
2182  tran_index = LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p);
2183  }
2184  (void) heap_chnguess_put (thread_p, oid, tran_index, or_chn (&assign->recdes));
2185  }
2186  assign->mobjs->num_objs++;
2187 
2188  COPY_OID (&assign->obj->class_oid, class_oid);
2189  COPY_OID (&assign->obj->oid, oid);
2190 
2191  /* Set object flag */
2192  assign->obj->flag = 0;
2193 
2194  assign->obj->hfid = NULL_HFID;
2195  assign->obj->length = assign->recdes.length;
2196  assign->obj->offset = assign->area_offset;
2197  assign->obj->operation = LC_FETCH;
2198  assign->obj = LC_NEXT_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (assign->obj);
2199 
2200 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
2201  /* suppress valgrind UMW error */
2202  memset (assign->recdes.data + assign->recdes.length, 0,
2203  MIN (round_length - assign->recdes.length, assign->recdes.area_size - assign->recdes.length));
2204 #endif
2205  assign->recdes.length = round_length;
2206  assign->area_offset += round_length;
2207  assign->recdes.data += round_length;
2208  assign->recdes.area_size -= round_length + sizeof (*assign->obj);
2209  }
2210 
2211  break;
2212 
2213  case S_SUCCESS_CHN_UPTODATE:
2214  /*
2215  * the cached object was on the right state
2216  */
2217  scan = S_SUCCESS;
2218 
2219  if (guess_chn == CHN_UNKNOWN_ATCLIENT)
2220  {
2221  if (assign->recdes.area_size < (int) sizeof (*assign->obj))
2222  {
2223  assign->recdes.area_size -= sizeof (*assign->obj);
2224  scan = S_DOESNT_FIT;
2225  }
2226  else
2227  {
2228  assign->mobjs->num_objs++;
2229 
2230  /* Indicate to the caller that the object does not exist any longer */
2231  COPY_OID (&assign->obj->class_oid, class_oid);
2232  COPY_OID (&assign->obj->oid, oid);
2233  assign->obj->flag = 0;
2234  assign->obj->hfid = NULL_HFID;
2235  assign->obj->length = -chn;
2236  assign->obj->offset = -1;
2237  assign->obj->operation = LC_FETCH_VERIFY_CHN;
2238  assign->obj = LC_NEXT_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (assign->obj);
2239  assign->recdes.area_size -= sizeof (*assign->obj);
2240  }
2241  }
2242  break;
2243 
2244  case S_DOESNT_EXIST:
2245  /*
2246  * The object does not exist
2247  */
2248  if (assign->recdes.area_size < (int) sizeof (*assign->obj))
2249  {
2250  assign->recdes.area_size -= sizeof (*assign->obj);
2251  scan = S_DOESNT_FIT;
2252  }
2253  else
2254  {
2255  assign->mobjs->num_objs++;
2256 
2257  /* Indicate to the caller that the object does not exist any longer */
2258  COPY_OID (&assign->obj->class_oid, class_oid);
2259  COPY_OID (&assign->obj->oid, oid);
2260  assign->obj->flag = 0;
2261  assign->obj->hfid = NULL_HFID;
2262  assign->obj->length = -1;
2263  assign->obj->offset = -1;
2264  assign->obj->operation = LC_FETCH_DELETED;
2265  assign->obj = LC_NEXT_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (assign->obj);
2266  assign->recdes.area_size -= sizeof (*assign->obj);
2267  }
2268 
2269  break;
2270 
2271  default:
2272  break;
2273 
2274  }
2275 
2276  return scan;
2277 }
2278 
2279 /*
2280  * locator_lock_and_return_object () - Lock object, get its data and place it
2281  * in communication area.
2282  *
2283  * return : SCAN_CODE
2284  * (Either of S_SUCCESS,
2285  * S_DOESNT_FIT,
2286  * S_DOESNT_EXIST,
2287  * S_ERROR)
2288  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry.
2289  * assign (in/out) : Locator structure to store object data.
2290  * class_oid (in) : Class OID.
2291  * oid (in) : Object OID.
2292  * chn (in) : Known object CHN (or NULL_CHN if not known).
2293  * lock_mode (in) : Require lock on object.
2294  *
2295  * Note: The desired object is placed in the assigned return area when the
2296  * state of the object(chn) in the client workspace is different from
2297  * the one on disk. If the object does not fit in assigned return area,
2298  * the length of the object is returned as a negative value in the area
2299  * recdes length.
2300  */
2301 static SCAN_CODE
2302 locator_lock_and_return_object (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOCATOR_RETURN_NXOBJ * assign, OID * class_oid, OID * oid,
2303  int chn, LOCK lock_mode, SCAN_OPERATION_TYPE op_type)
2304 {
2305  SCAN_CODE scan; /* Scan return value for next operation */
2306  int guess_chn = chn;
2307  int tran_index = NULL_TRAN_INDEX;
2308 
2309  /*
2310  * The next object is placed in the assigned recdes area if the cached
2311  * object is obsolete and the object fits in the recdes
2312  */
2313  assert (oid != NULL);
2314  if (chn == CHN_UNKNOWN_ATCLIENT)
2315  {
2316  tran_index = LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p);
2317  chn = heap_chnguess_get (thread_p, oid, tran_index);
2318  }
2319 
2320  scan = locator_get_object (thread_p, oid, class_oid, &assign->recdes, assign->ptr_scancache, op_type, lock_mode, COPY,
2321  chn);
2322  if (scan == S_ERROR || scan == S_SNAPSHOT_NOT_SATISFIED || scan == S_END || scan == S_DOESNT_EXIST)
2323  {
2324  return scan;
2325  }
2326 
2327  scan = locator_return_object_assign (thread_p, assign, class_oid, oid, chn, guess_chn, scan, tran_index);
2328 
2329  return scan;
2330 }
2331 
2332 /*
2333  * xlocator_fetch () - Lock and fetch an object, and prefetch some other objects
2334  *
2335  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
2336  *
2337  * thread_p(in):
2338  * oid(in): Object identifier of requested object
2339  * chn(in): Cache coherence number of object
2340  * lock(in): Lock to acquire before the object is fetched
2341  * fetch_version_type(in): fetch version type
2342  * initial_fetch_version_type(in): initial fetch version type
2343  * class_oid(in): Class identifier of the object
2344  * class_chn(in): Cache coherence number of the class of the object
2345  * prefetching(in): true when prefetching of neighbors is desired
2346  * fetch_area(in/out): Pointer to area where the objects are placed
2347  (set to point to fetching area)
2348  *
2349  * Note: This function locks and fetches the object associated with the
2350  * given oid. The object is only placed in the fetch area when
2351  * the state of the object (chn) in the workspace (client) is
2352  * different from the one on disk. The class along with several
2353  * other neighbors of the object may also be included in the
2354  * fetch area. It is up to the caller if the additional objects
2355  * are cached. Fetch_area is set to NULL when there is an error
2356  * or when there is not a need to send any object back since the
2357  * cache coherent numbers were the same as those on disk. The
2358  * caller must check the return value of the function to find out
2359  * if there was any error.
2360  * The returned fetch area should be freed by the caller.
2361  */
2362 int
2363 xlocator_fetch (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OID * oid, int chn, LOCK lock,
2364  LC_FETCH_VERSION_TYPE fetch_version_type, LC_FETCH_VERSION_TYPE initial_fetch_version_type,
2365  OID * class_oid, int class_chn, int prefetching, LC_COPYAREA ** fetch_area)
2366 {
2367  OID tmp_oid; /* Uses to hold the class_oid when it is not know by the caller */
2368  LC_COPYAREA_DESC prefetch_des;
2369  LOCATOR_RETURN_NXOBJ nxobj; /* Description to return next obj */
2370  int copyarea_length;
2371  SCAN_CODE scan = S_ERROR;
2372  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
2373  MVCC_SNAPSHOT *mvcc_snapshot;
2374  MVCC_SNAPSHOT mvcc_snapshot_dirty;
2375  SCAN_OPERATION_TYPE operation_type;
2376  OID *p_oid = oid;
2377  bool object_locked = false;
2378  int is_mvcc_disabled_class = -1;
2379  LOCK class_lock;
2380  /* We assume that the object have to be locked; after it is locked or we determine that this is not necessary,
2381  * object_need_locking will be set to false; */
2382  bool object_need_locking = true;
2383  bool skip_fetch_version_type_check = false;
2384 
2385  if (fetch_version_type == LC_FETCH_CURRENT_VERSION_NO_CHECK)
2386  {
2387  /* The purpose was to fetch the current version. Avoid checks. */
2388  fetch_version_type = LC_FETCH_CURRENT_VERSION;
2389  skip_fetch_version_type_check = true;
2390  }
2391 
2392  if (LC_FETCH_IS_MVCC_VERSION_NEEDED (initial_fetch_version_type))
2393  {
2394  skip_fetch_version_type_check = true;
2395  }
2396 
2397  switch (fetch_version_type)
2398  {
2399  case LC_FETCH_MVCC_VERSION:
2400  mvcc_snapshot = logtb_get_mvcc_snapshot (thread_p);
2401  if (mvcc_snapshot == NULL)
2402  {
2403  error_code = er_errid ();
2404  return (error_code == NO_ERROR ? ER_FAILED : error_code);
2405  }
2406  break;
2407 
2408  case LC_FETCH_DIRTY_VERSION:
2409  mvcc_snapshot_dirty.snapshot_fnc = mvcc_satisfies_dirty;
2410  mvcc_snapshot = &mvcc_snapshot_dirty;
2411  break;
2412 
2413  case LC_FETCH_CURRENT_VERSION:
2414  mvcc_snapshot = NULL;
2415  break;
2416 
2417  default:
2418  /* no usage at this point */
2419  assert (0);
2420  break;
2421  }
2422 
2423  /* Compute operation type */
2424  operation_type = locator_decide_operation_type (lock, fetch_version_type);
2425 
2426  if (class_oid == NULL)
2427  {
2428  /* The class_oid is not known by the caller. */
2429  class_oid = &tmp_oid;
2430  OID_SET_NULL (class_oid);
2431  }
2432 
2433 #if !defined (NDEBUG)
2434  if (OID_ISNULL (class_oid))
2435  {
2436  /*
2437  * Caller does not know the class of the object. Get the class
2438  * identifier from disk
2439  */
2440  scan = heap_get_class_oid (thread_p, oid, class_oid);
2441  if (scan != S_SUCCESS)
2442  {
2443  /* Unable to find the class of the object.. return */
2444  *fetch_area = NULL;
2445 
2446  error_code = ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT;
2447  if (er_errid () != error_code)
2448  {
2449  /* error was not previously set; set error in order to have it returned to client */
2450  er_set (ER_WARNING_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error_code, 3, oid->volid, oid->pageid, oid->slotid);
2451  }
2452  return error_code;
2453  }
2454  }
2455 
2456  assert (!OID_ISNULL (class_oid));
2457 
2458  /* Current version or dirty version for instance with NULL_LOCK is allowed only if the transaction already has a
2459  * lock. This means that is not necessary to request the lock again. */
2460  assert (skip_fetch_version_type_check || (OID_EQ (class_oid, oid_Root_class_oid))
2461  || ((lock != NULL_LOCK)
2462  || (lock_get_object_lock (oid, class_oid, LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p)) != NULL_LOCK)
2463  || ((class_lock = lock_get_object_lock (class_oid, oid_Root_class_oid,
2464  LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p))) == S_LOCK
2465  || class_lock >= SIX_LOCK)
2466  || ((class_lock = lock_get_object_lock (oid_Root_class_oid, NULL,
2467  LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p))) == S_LOCK
2468  || class_lock >= SIX_LOCK)));
2469 
2470  /* LC_FETCH_CURRENT_VERSION should be used for classes only */
2471  assert (fetch_version_type != LC_FETCH_CURRENT_VERSION || OID_IS_ROOTOID (class_oid));
2472 #endif /* DEBUG */
2473 
2474  /*
2475  * Lock and fetch the object.
2476  */
2477 
2478  /* Assume that the needed object can fit in one page */
2479  copyarea_length = DB_PAGESIZE;
2480 
2481  error_code = heap_scancache_start (thread_p, &nxobj.area_scancache, NULL, NULL, false, false, mvcc_snapshot);
2482  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
2483  {
2484  nxobj.mobjs = NULL;
2485  error_code = ER_FAILED;
2486  goto error;
2487  }
2488  nxobj.ptr_scancache = &nxobj.area_scancache;
2489 
2490  while (true)
2491  {
2492  nxobj.comm_area = *fetch_area = locator_allocate_copy_area_by_length (copyarea_length);
2493  if (nxobj.comm_area == NULL)
2494  {
2495  heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &nxobj.area_scancache);
2496  nxobj.mobjs = NULL;
2497  error_code = ER_FAILED;
2498  goto error;
2499  }
2500 
2501  nxobj.mobjs = LC_MANYOBJS_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (nxobj.comm_area);
2502  nxobj.obj = LC_START_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (nxobj.mobjs);
2503  LC_RECDES_IN_COPYAREA (nxobj.comm_area, &nxobj.recdes);
2504  nxobj.area_offset = 0;
2505  nxobj.mobjs->num_objs = 0;
2506 
2507  /* Get the interested object first */
2508  scan = locator_lock_and_return_object (thread_p, &nxobj, class_oid, p_oid, chn,
2509  object_need_locking ? lock : NULL_LOCK, operation_type);
2510  if (scan == S_SUCCESS)
2511  {
2512  if (object_need_locking)
2513  {
2514  object_need_locking = false;
2515  is_mvcc_disabled_class = mvcc_is_mvcc_disabled_class (class_oid) ? 1 : 0;
2516  if (is_mvcc_disabled_class == 1)
2517  {
2518  if (lock > NULL_LOCK)
2519  {
2520  /* Non-MVCC: Always lock object */
2521  object_locked = true;
2522  }
2523  }
2524  else if (lock == X_LOCK)
2525  {
2526  /* MVCC X_LOCK: Need exclusive lock on object. Get MVCC object version for delete/update. */
2527  object_locked = true;
2528  }
2529  else if (operation_type == S_SELECT_WITH_LOCK)
2530  {
2531  /* MVCC S_SELECT_WITH_LOCK: We need to read and lock last object version found with satisfy dirty
2532  * rules. This object must be also locked. */
2533  object_locked = true;
2534  }
2535  }
2536  break;
2537  }
2538 
2539  /* Get the real length of current fetch/copy area */
2540  copyarea_length = nxobj.comm_area->length;
2541  locator_free_copy_area (nxobj.comm_area);
2542 
2543  /*
2544  * If the object does not fit even when the copy area seems to be
2545  * large enough, increase the copy area by at least one page size.
2546  */
2547  if (scan == S_DOESNT_EXIST || scan == S_SNAPSHOT_NOT_SATISFIED)
2548  {
2549  heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &nxobj.area_scancache);
2550  nxobj.comm_area = *fetch_area = NULL;
2551  error_code = ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT;
2552  if (er_errid () != error_code)
2553  {
2554  /* error was not previously set; set error in order to have it returned to client */
2555  er_set (ER_WARNING_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error_code, 3, oid->volid, oid->pageid, oid->slotid);
2556  }
2557  goto error;
2558  }
2559  else if (scan != S_DOESNT_FIT)
2560  {
2561  heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &nxobj.area_scancache);
2562  nxobj.comm_area = *fetch_area = NULL;
2563  error_code = ER_FAILED;
2564  goto error;
2565  }
2566 
2567  if ((-nxobj.recdes.length) > copyarea_length)
2568  {
2569  copyarea_length = (DB_ALIGN (-nxobj.recdes.length, MAX_ALIGNMENT) + sizeof (*nxobj.mobjs));
2570  }
2571  else
2572  {
2573  copyarea_length += DB_PAGESIZE;
2574  }
2575  }
2576 
2577  /*
2578  * Then, get the interested class, if given class coherency number is not
2579  * current.
2580  */
2581  scan = locator_lock_and_return_object (thread_p, &nxobj, oid_Root_class_oid, class_oid, class_chn, NULL_LOCK,
2582  S_SELECT);
2583  if (scan == S_SUCCESS && nxobj.mobjs->num_objs == 2)
2584  {
2585  LC_COPYAREA_ONEOBJ *first, *second;
2586  LC_COPYAREA_ONEOBJ save;
2587  /*
2588  * It is better if the class is cached first, so swap the
2589  * description. The object was stored first because it has
2590  * priority of retrieval, however, if both the object and its
2591  * class fits, the class should go first for performance reasons
2592  */
2593 
2594  /* Save the object information, then move the class information */
2595  first = LC_START_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (nxobj.mobjs);
2596  second = LC_NEXT_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (first);
2597 
2598  /* Swap the values */
2599  save = *first;
2600  *first = *second;
2601  *second = save;
2602  }
2603 
2604  error_code = heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &nxobj.area_scancache);
2605  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
2606  {
2607  locator_free_copy_area (nxobj.comm_area);
2608  *fetch_area = NULL;
2609  error_code = ER_FAILED;
2610  goto error;
2611  }
2612  nxobj.ptr_scancache = NULL;
2613 
2614 
2615  prefetch_des.mobjs = nxobj.mobjs;
2616  prefetch_des.obj = &nxobj.obj;
2617 
2618  prefetch_des.offset = &nxobj.area_offset;
2619  prefetch_des.recdes = &nxobj.recdes;
2620 
2621  /*
2622  * Find any decache notifications and prefetch any neighbors of the
2623  * instance
2624  */
2625 
2626  lock_notify_isolation_incons (thread_p, locator_notify_decache, &prefetch_des);
2627  if (prefetching && nxobj.mobjs->num_objs > 0)
2628  {
2629  error_code = heap_prefetch (thread_p, class_oid, oid, &prefetch_des);
2630  }
2631 
2632  if (nxobj.mobjs->num_objs == 0)
2633  {
2634  /*
2635  * Don't need to send anything. The cache coherency numbers were
2636  * identical. Deallocate the area and return without failure
2637  */
2638  locator_free_copy_area (nxobj.comm_area);
2639  *fetch_area = NULL;
2640  }
2641 
2642 error:
2643  if (lock != NULL_LOCK)
2644  {
2645  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
2646  {
2647  if (object_locked)
2648  {
2649  lock_unlock_object_donot_move_to_non2pl (thread_p, p_oid, class_oid, lock);
2650  }
2651  }
2652  else if (is_mvcc_disabled_class == 1 || (is_mvcc_disabled_class == -1 && mvcc_is_mvcc_disabled_class (class_oid)))
2653  {
2654  if (lock <= S_LOCK)
2655  {
2656  assert (object_locked);
2657  lock_unlock_object (thread_p, p_oid, class_oid, lock, false);
2658  }
2659  }
2660  }
2661 
2662  return error_code;
2663 }
2664 
2665 /*
2666  * xlocator_get_class () - Lock and fetch the class of an instance, and prefetch
2667  * given instance and some other instances of class
2668  *
2669  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
2670  *
2671  * class_oid(in/out): Class identifier of the object. (It is set as a side
2672  * effect when its initial value is a null OID)
2673  * class_chn(in): Cache coherence number of the class of the object
2674  * oid(in): Object identifier of the instance of the desired class
2675  * lock(in): Lock to acquire before the class is acquired/fetched
2676  * Note that the lock is for the class.
2677  * prefetching(in): true when pretching of neighbors is desired
2678  * fetch_area(in/out): Pointer to area where the objects are placed (set to
2679  * point to fetching area)
2680  *
2681  * Note: This function locks and fetches the class of the given
2682  * instance. The class is only placed in a communication copy
2683  * area when the state of the class (class_chn) in the workspace
2684  * (client) is different from the one on disk. Other neighbors of
2685  * the class are included in the copy_area. It is up to the
2686  * caller if the additional classes are cached. Fetch_area is
2687  * set to NULL when there is an error or when there is not a need
2688  * to send any object back since the cache coherent numbers were
2689  * the same as those on disk. The caller must check the return
2690  * value of the function to find out if there was any error.
2691  *
2692  * Note: The returned fetch area should be freed by the caller.
2693  */
2694 int
2695 xlocator_get_class (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OID * class_oid, int class_chn, const OID * oid, LOCK lock,
2696  int prefetching, LC_COPYAREA ** fetch_area)
2697 {
2698  int error_code;
2699 
2700  if (OID_ISNULL (class_oid))
2701  {
2702  /*
2703  * Caller does not know the class of the object. Get the class identifier
2704  * from disk
2705  */
2706  if (heap_get_class_oid (thread_p, oid, class_oid) != S_SUCCESS)
2707  {
2708  /*
2709  * Unable to find out the class identifier.
2710  */
2711  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
2712  *fetch_area = NULL;
2713  return error_code;
2714  }
2715  }
2716 
2717  /* Now acquired the desired lock */
2718  if (lock != NULL_LOCK)
2719  {
2720  /* Now acquired the desired lock */
2721  if (lock_object (thread_p, class_oid, oid_Root_class_oid, lock, LK_UNCOND_LOCK) != LK_GRANTED)
2722  {
2723  /*
2724  * Unable to acquired lock
2725  */
2726  *fetch_area = NULL;
2727  return ER_FAILED;
2728  }
2729  }
2730 
2731  /*
2732  * Now fetch the class, the instance and optionally prefetch some
2733  * neighbors of the instance. No need to get the last version for class.
2734  */
2735 
2736  error_code =
2737  xlocator_fetch (thread_p, class_oid, class_chn, NULL_LOCK, LC_FETCH_CURRENT_VERSION, LC_FETCH_CURRENT_VERSION,
2738  oid_Root_class_oid, -1, prefetching, fetch_area);
2739 
2740  if (error_code != NO_ERROR && lock != NULL_LOCK)
2741  {
2742  lock_unlock_object (thread_p, class_oid, oid_Root_class_oid, lock, false);
2743  }
2744 
2745  return error_code;
2746 }
2747 
2748 /*
2749  * xlocator_fetch_all () - Fetch all instances of a class
2750  *
2751  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
2752  *
2753  * hfid(in): Heap file where the instances of the class are placed
2754  * lock(in): Lock to acquired (Set as a side effect to NULL_LOCKID)
2755  * fetch_version_type(in): fetch version type
2756  * class_oid(in): Class identifier of the instances to fetch
2757  * nobjects(out): Total number of objects to fetch.
2758  * nfetched(out): Current number of object fetched.
2759  * last_oid(out): Object identifier of last fetched object
2760  * fetch_area(in/out): Pointer to area where the objects are placed
2761  *
2762  */
2763 int
2764 xlocator_fetch_all (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const HFID * hfid, LOCK * lock, LC_FETCH_VERSION_TYPE fetch_version_type,
2765  OID * class_oid, int *nobjects, int *nfetched, OID * last_oid, LC_COPYAREA ** fetch_area)
2766 {
2767  LC_COPYAREA_DESC prefetch_des; /* Descriptor for decache of objects related to transaction isolation level */
2768  LC_COPYAREA_MANYOBJS *mobjs; /* Describe multiple objects in area */
2769  LC_COPYAREA_ONEOBJ *obj; /* Describe on object in area */
2770  RECDES recdes; /* Record descriptor for insertion */
2771  int offset; /* Place to store next object in area */
2772  int round_length; /* Length of object rounded to integer alignment */
2773  int copyarea_length;
2774  OID oid;
2775  HEAP_SCANCACHE scan_cache;
2776  SCAN_CODE scan;
2777  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
2778  MVCC_SNAPSHOT *mvcc_snapshot = NULL;
2779  MVCC_SNAPSHOT mvcc_snapshot_dirty;
2780 
2781  assert (lock != NULL);
2782  if (OID_ISNULL (last_oid))
2783  {
2784  /* FIRST TIME. */
2785 
2786  /* Obtain the desired lock for the class scan */
2787  if (*lock != NULL_LOCK
2788  && lock_object (thread_p, class_oid, oid_Root_class_oid, *lock, LK_UNCOND_LOCK) != LK_GRANTED)
2789  {
2790  /*
2791  * Unable to acquired lock
2792  */
2793  *fetch_area = NULL;
2794  *lock = NULL_LOCK;
2795  *nobjects = -1;
2796  *nfetched = -1;
2797 
2798  error_code = ER_FAILED;
2799  goto error;
2800  }
2801 
2802  /* Get statistics */
2803  last_oid->volid = hfid->vfid.volid;
2804  last_oid->pageid = NULL_PAGEID;
2805  last_oid->slotid = NULL_SLOTID;
2806  /* Estimate the number of objects to be fetched */
2807  *nobjects = heap_estimate_num_objects (thread_p, hfid);
2808  *nfetched = 0;
2809  if (*nobjects == -1)
2810  {
2811  if (*lock != NULL_LOCK)
2812  {
2813  lock_unlock_object (thread_p, class_oid, oid_Root_class_oid, *lock, false);
2814  }
2815  *fetch_area = NULL;
2816  error_code = ER_FAILED;
2817  goto error;
2818  }
2819  }
2820 
2821  switch (fetch_version_type)
2822  {
2823  case LC_FETCH_MVCC_VERSION:
2824  mvcc_snapshot = logtb_get_mvcc_snapshot (thread_p);
2825  if (mvcc_snapshot == NULL)
2826  {
2827  error_code = er_errid ();
2828  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
2829  {
2830  error_code = ER_FAILED;
2831  }
2832  goto error;
2833  }
2834  break;
2835 
2836  case LC_FETCH_DIRTY_VERSION:
2837  mvcc_snapshot_dirty.snapshot_fnc = mvcc_satisfies_dirty;
2838  mvcc_snapshot = &mvcc_snapshot_dirty;
2839  break;
2840 
2841  case LC_FETCH_CURRENT_VERSION:
2842  mvcc_snapshot = NULL;
2843  break;
2844 
2845  default:
2846  assert (0);
2847  }
2848 
2849  /* Set OID to last fetched object */
2850  COPY_OID (&oid, last_oid);
2851 
2852  /* Start a scan cursor for getting several classes */
2853  error_code = heap_scancache_start (thread_p, &scan_cache, hfid, class_oid, true, false, mvcc_snapshot);
2854  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
2855  {
2856  if (*lock != NULL_LOCK)
2857  {
2858  lock_unlock_object (thread_p, class_oid, oid_Root_class_oid, *lock, false);
2859  }
2860  *fetch_area = NULL;
2861 
2862  goto error;
2863  }
2864 
2865  /* Assume that the next object can fit in one page */
2866  copyarea_length = DB_PAGESIZE;
2867 
2868  while (true)
2869  {
2870  *fetch_area = locator_allocate_copy_area_by_length (copyarea_length);
2871  if (*fetch_area == NULL)
2872  {
2873  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache);
2874  if (*lock != NULL_LOCK)
2875  {
2876  lock_unlock_object (thread_p, class_oid, oid_Root_class_oid, *lock, false);
2877  }
2878 
2879  error_code = ER_FAILED;
2880  goto error;
2881  }
2882 
2883  mobjs = LC_MANYOBJS_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (*fetch_area);
2884  LC_RECDES_IN_COPYAREA (*fetch_area, &recdes);
2885  obj = LC_START_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (mobjs);
2886  mobjs->num_objs = 0;
2887  offset = 0;
2888 
2889  while ((scan = heap_next (thread_p, hfid, class_oid, &oid, &recdes, &scan_cache, COPY)) == S_SUCCESS)
2890  {
2891  mobjs->num_objs++;
2892  COPY_OID (&obj->class_oid, class_oid);
2893  COPY_OID (&obj->oid, &oid);
2894  obj->flag = 0;
2895  obj->hfid = NULL_HFID;
2896  obj->length = recdes.length;
2897  obj->offset = offset;
2898  obj->operation = LC_FETCH;
2899  obj = LC_NEXT_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (obj);
2900  round_length = DB_ALIGN (recdes.length, MAX_ALIGNMENT);
2901 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
2902  /* suppress valgrind UMW error */
2903  memset (recdes.data + recdes.length, 0, MIN (round_length - recdes.length, recdes.area_size - recdes.length));
2904 #endif
2905  offset += round_length;
2906  recdes.data += round_length;
2907  recdes.area_size -= round_length + sizeof (*obj);
2908 
2909  if (mobjs->num_objs == DB_INT32_MAX)
2910  {
2911  /* Prevent overflow */
2912  break;
2913  }
2914  }
2915 
2916  if (scan != S_DOESNT_FIT || mobjs->num_objs > 0)
2917  {
2918  break;
2919  }
2920  /*
2921  * The first object does not fit into given copy area
2922  * Get a larger area
2923  */
2924 
2925  /* Get the real length of current fetch/copy area */
2926  copyarea_length = (*fetch_area)->length;
2927  locator_free_copy_area (*fetch_area);
2928 
2929  /*
2930  * If the object does not fit even when the copy area seems to be
2931  * large enough, increase the copy area by at least one page size.
2932  */
2933 
2934  if ((-recdes.length) > copyarea_length)
2935  {
2936  copyarea_length = DB_ALIGN (-recdes.length, MAX_ALIGNMENT) + sizeof (*mobjs);
2937  }
2938  else
2939  {
2940  copyarea_length += DB_PAGESIZE;
2941  }
2942  }
2943 
2944  if (scan == S_END)
2945  {
2946  /*
2947  * This is the end of the loop. Indicate the caller that no more calls
2948  * are needed by setting nobjects and nfetched to the same value.
2949  */
2950  error_code = heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache);
2951  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
2952  {
2953  locator_free_copy_area (*fetch_area);
2954  *fetch_area = NULL;
2955  if (*lock != NULL_LOCK)
2956  {
2957  lock_unlock_object (thread_p, class_oid, oid_Root_class_oid, *lock, false);
2958  }
2959  *nobjects = *nfetched = -1;
2960 
2961  goto error;
2962  }
2963 
2964  *nfetched += mobjs->num_objs;
2965  *nobjects = *nfetched;
2966  OID_SET_NULL (last_oid);
2967  if (*lock != NULL_LOCK)
2968  {
2969  lock_unlock_object (thread_p, class_oid, oid_Root_class_oid, *lock, false);
2970  }
2971  }
2972  else if (scan == S_ERROR)
2973  {
2974  /* There was an error.. */
2975  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache);
2976 
2977  locator_free_copy_area (*fetch_area);
2978  *fetch_area = NULL;
2979  if (*lock != NULL_LOCK)
2980  {
2981  lock_unlock_object (thread_p, class_oid, oid_Root_class_oid, *lock, false);
2982  }
2983  *nobjects = *nfetched = -1;
2984 
2985  error_code = ER_FAILED;
2986  goto error;
2987  }
2988  else if (mobjs->num_objs != 0)
2989  {
2990  heap_scancache_end_when_scan_will_resume (thread_p, &scan_cache);
2991  /* Set the last_oid.. and the number of fetched objects */
2992  obj = LC_PRIOR_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (obj);
2993  COPY_OID (last_oid, &obj->oid);
2994  *nfetched += mobjs->num_objs;
2995  /*
2996  * If the guess on the number of objects to fetch was low, reset the
2997  * value, so that the caller continue to call us until the end of the
2998  * scan
2999  */
3000  if (*nobjects <= *nfetched)
3001  {
3002  *nobjects = *nfetched + 10;
3003  }
3004  }
3005  else
3006  {
3007  error_code = heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache);
3008  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
3009  {
3010  goto error;
3011  }
3012  }
3013 
3014  if (*fetch_area != NULL)
3015  {
3016  prefetch_des.mobjs = mobjs;
3017  prefetch_des.obj = &obj;
3018  prefetch_des.offset = &offset;
3019  prefetch_des.recdes = &recdes;
3020  lock_notify_isolation_incons (thread_p, locator_notify_decache, &prefetch_des);
3021  }
3022 
3023 error:
3024  return error_code;
3025 }
3026 
3027 /*
3028  * xlocator_fetch_lockset () - Lock and fetch many objects
3029  *
3030  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
3031  *
3032  * lockset(in/out): Request for finding missing classes and the lock
3033  * requested objects (Set as a side effect).
3034  * fetch_area(in/out): Pointer to area where the objects are placed
3035  *
3036  */
3037 int
3038 xlocator_fetch_lockset (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LC_LOCKSET * lockset, LC_COPYAREA ** fetch_area)
3039 {
3040  LC_COPYAREA_DESC prefetch_des; /* Descriptor for decache of objects related to transaction isolation level */
3041  LOCATOR_RETURN_NXOBJ nxobj; /* Description to return next obj */
3042  struct lc_lockset_reqobj *reqobjs; /* Description of requested objects */
3043  struct lc_lockset_classof *reqclasses; /* Description of classes of requested objects. */
3044  int copyarea_length;

3046  int i, j;

3048  MVCC_SNAPSHOT *mvcc_snapshot = NULL;
3049 
3050  mvcc_snapshot = logtb_get_mvcc_snapshot (thread_p);
3051  if (mvcc_snapshot == NULL)
3052  {
3053  error_code = er_errid ();
3054  return (error_code == NO_ERROR ? ER_FAILED : error_code);
3055  }
3056 
3057  *fetch_area = NULL;
3058 
3059  reqobjs = lockset->objects;
3060  reqclasses = lockset->classes;
3061 
3062  if (lockset->num_reqobjs_processed == -1)
3063  {
3064  /*
3065  * FIRST CALL.
3066  * Initialize num of object processed.
3067  * Make sure that all classes are known and lock the classes and objects
3068  */
3069  lockset->num_reqobjs_processed = 0;
3070  lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs_processed = 0;
3071 
3072  error_code = locator_find_lockset_missing_class_oids (thread_p, lockset);
3073  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
3074  {
3075  goto error;
3076  }
3077  }
3078 
3079  /* Start a scan cursor for getting several classes */
3080  error_code = heap_scancache_start (thread_p, &nxobj.area_scancache, NULL, NULL, true, false, NULL);
3081  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
3082  {
3083  lock_unlock_objects_lock_set (thread_p, lockset);
3084  goto error;
3085  }
3086  nxobj.ptr_scancache = &nxobj.area_scancache;
3087 
3088  /*
3089  * Assume that there are not any objects larger than one page. If there are
3090  * the number of pages is fixed later.
3091  */
3092 
3093  copyarea_length = DB_PAGESIZE;
3094 
3095  nxobj.mobjs = NULL;
3096  nxobj.comm_area = NULL;
3097 
3098  while (scan == S_SUCCESS
3099  && ((lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs_processed < lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs)
3100  || (lockset->num_reqobjs_processed < lockset->num_reqobjs)))
3101  {
3102  nxobj.comm_area = locator_allocate_copy_area_by_length (copyarea_length);
3103  if (nxobj.comm_area == NULL)
3104  {
3105  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &nxobj.area_scancache);
3106  lock_unlock_objects_lock_set (thread_p, lockset);
3107  error_code = ER_FAILED;
3108  goto error;
3109  }
3110 
3111  nxobj.mobjs = LC_MANYOBJS_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (nxobj.comm_area);
3112  nxobj.obj = LC_START_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (nxobj.mobjs);
3113  LC_RECDES_IN_COPYAREA (nxobj.comm_area, &nxobj.recdes);
3114  nxobj.area_offset = 0;
3115  nxobj.mobjs->num_objs = 0;
3116 
3117  /*
3118  * CLASSES
3119  * Place the classes on the communication area, don't place those classes
3120  * with correct chns.
3121  */
3122 
3123  for (i = lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs_processed; scan == S_SUCCESS && i < lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs; i++)
3124  {
3125  if (OID_ISNULL (&reqclasses[i].oid))
3126  {
3127  lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs_processed++;
3128  continue;
3129  }
3130  if (OID_ISTEMP (&reqclasses[i].oid))
3131  {
3132  lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs_processed++;
3133  continue;
3134  }
3135  scan =
3136  locator_lock_and_return_object (thread_p, &nxobj, oid_Root_class_oid, &reqclasses[i].oid, reqclasses[i].chn,
3137  lockset->reqobj_class_lock, S_SELECT);
3138  if (scan == S_SUCCESS)
3139  {
3140  lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs_processed++;
3141  }
3142  else if (scan == S_DOESNT_FIT && nxobj.mobjs->num_objs == 0)
3143  {
3144  /*
3145  * The first object does not fit into given copy area
3146  * Get a larger area
3147  */
3148 
3149  /* Get the real length of current fetch/copy area */
3150 
3151  copyarea_length = nxobj.comm_area->length;
3152 
3153  /*
3154  * If the object does not fit even when the copy area seems
3155  * to be large enough, increase the copy area by at least one
3156  * page size.
3157  */
3158 
3159  if ((-nxobj.recdes.length) > copyarea_length)
3160  {
3161  copyarea_length = (DB_ALIGN (-nxobj.recdes.length, MAX_ALIGNMENT) + sizeof (*nxobj.mobjs));
3162  }
3163  else
3164  {
3165  copyarea_length += DB_PAGESIZE;
3166  }
3167 
3168  locator_free_copy_area (nxobj.comm_area);
3169  scan = S_SUCCESS;
3170  break; /* finish the for */
3171  }
3172  else if (scan != S_DOESNT_FIT && (scan == S_DOESNT_EXIST || lockset->quit_on_errors == false))
3173  {
3174  OID_SET_NULL (&reqclasses[i].oid);
3175  lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs_processed += 1;
3176  scan = S_SUCCESS;
3177  }
3178  else
3179  {
3180  break; /* Quit on errors */
3181  }
3182  }
3183 
3184  if (i >= lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs)
3185  {
3186  /*
3187  * DONE WITH CLASSES... NOW START WITH INSTANCES
3188  * Place the instances in the fetching area, don't place those
3189  * instances with correct chns or when they have been placed through
3190  * the class array
3191  */
3192 
3193  for (i = lockset->num_reqobjs_processed; scan == S_SUCCESS && i < lockset->num_reqobjs; i++)
3194  {
3195  if (OID_ISNULL (&reqobjs[i].oid) || OID_ISTEMP (&reqobjs[i].oid) || reqobjs[i].class_index == -1
3196  || OID_ISNULL (&reqclasses[reqobjs[i].class_index].oid))
3197  {
3198  lockset->num_reqobjs_processed += 1;
3199  continue;
3200  }
3201 
3202  if (OID_IS_ROOTOID (&reqclasses[reqobjs[i].class_index].oid))
3203  {
3204  /*
3205  * The requested object is a class. If this object is a class
3206  * of other requested objects, the object has already been
3207  * processed in the previous class iteration
3208  */
3209  for (j = 0; j < lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs; j++)
3210  {
3211  if (OID_EQ (&reqobjs[i].oid, &reqclasses[j].oid))
3212  {
3213  /* It has already been processed */
3214  lockset->num_reqobjs_processed += 1;
3215  break;
3216  }
3217  }
3218  if (j < lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs)
3219  {
3220  continue;
3221  }
3222  nxobj.ptr_scancache->mvcc_snapshot = NULL;
3223  }
3224  else
3225  {
3226  nxobj.ptr_scancache->mvcc_snapshot = mvcc_snapshot;
3227  }
3228 
3229  /* Now return the object */
3230  scan = locator_lock_and_return_object (thread_p, &nxobj, &reqclasses[reqobjs[i].class_index].oid,
3231  &reqobjs[i].oid, reqobjs[i].chn, lockset->reqobj_inst_lock,
3232  S_SELECT);
3233  if (scan == S_SUCCESS)
3234  {
3235  lockset->num_reqobjs_processed++;
3236  continue;
3237  }
3238 
3239  if (scan == S_DOESNT_FIT && nxobj.mobjs->num_objs == 0)
3240  {
3241  /*
3242  * The first object does not fit into given copy area
3243  * Get a larger area
3244  */
3245 
3246  /* Get the real length of current fetch/copy area */
3247 
3248  copyarea_length = nxobj.comm_area->length;
3249 
3250  /*
3251  * If the object does not fit even when the copy area
3252  * seems to be large enough, increase the copy area by at
3253  * least one page size.
3254  */
3255 
3256  if ((-nxobj.recdes.length) > copyarea_length)
3257  {
3258  copyarea_length = ((-nxobj.recdes.length) + sizeof (*nxobj.mobjs));
3259  }
3260  else
3261  {
3262  copyarea_length += DB_PAGESIZE;
3263  }
3264 
3265  locator_free_copy_area (nxobj.comm_area);
3266  scan = S_SUCCESS;
3267  break; /* finish the for */
3268  }
3269  else if (scan != S_DOESNT_FIT && (scan == S_DOESNT_EXIST || lockset->quit_on_errors == false))
3270  {
3271  OID_SET_NULL (&reqobjs[i].oid);
3272  lockset->num_reqobjs_processed += 1;
3273  scan = S_SUCCESS;
3274  }
3275  }
3276  }
3277  }
3278 
3279  /* End the scan cursor */
3280  error_code = heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &nxobj.area_scancache);
3281  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
3282  {
3283  /* There was an error.. */
3284  if (nxobj.mobjs != NULL)
3285  {
3286  locator_free_copy_area (nxobj.comm_area);
3287  }
3288  lock_unlock_objects_lock_set (thread_p, lockset);
3289  goto error;
3290  }
3291 
3292  if (scan == S_ERROR)
3293  {
3294  /* There was an error.. */
3295  if (nxobj.mobjs != NULL)
3296  {
3297  locator_free_copy_area (nxobj.comm_area);
3298  }
3299  lock_unlock_objects_lock_set (thread_p, lockset);
3300  error_code = ER_FAILED;
3301  goto error;
3302  }
3303  else if (nxobj.mobjs != NULL && nxobj.mobjs->num_objs == 0)
3304  {
3305  locator_free_copy_area (nxobj.comm_area);
3306  }
3307  else
3308  {
3309  *fetch_area = nxobj.comm_area;
3310  }
3311 
3312  if (*fetch_area != NULL)
3313  {
3314  prefetch_des.mobjs = nxobj.mobjs;
3315  prefetch_des.obj = &nxobj.obj;
3316  prefetch_des.offset = &nxobj.area_offset;
3317  prefetch_des.recdes = &nxobj.recdes;
3318  lock_notify_isolation_incons (thread_p, locator_notify_decache, &prefetch_des);
3319  }
3320 
3321  if ((lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs_processed >= lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs)
3322  && lockset->num_reqobjs_processed >= lockset->num_reqobjs)
3323  {
3324  lock_unlock_objects_lock_set (thread_p, lockset);
3325  }
3326 
3327 error:
3328  return error_code;
3329 }
3330 
3331 /*
3332  * locator_all_reference_lockset () - Find all objects referenced by given object
3333  *
3334  * return: LC_LOCKSET * or NULL (in case of error)
3335  *
3336  * oid(in): The desired object.
3337  * prune_level(in): Get references up to this level. If the value is <= 0
3338  * means up to an infinite level (i.e., all references).
3339  * inst_lock(in): Indicate this lock in the request area for objects that
3340  * are instances.
3341  * class_lock(in): Indicate this lock in the request area for objects that
3342  * are classes.
3343  * quit_on_errors(in): Quit when an error is found such as cannot lock all
3344  * nested objects.
3345  *
3346  * Note: This function find all direct and indirect references from the
3347  * given object upto the given prune level in the nested graph.
3348  * The given object is also included as a reference. Thus, the
3349  * function can be seen as listing a graph of referenced/nested
3350  * objects.
3351  *
3352  * For performance reasons, the search for duplicate oids now uses an
3353  * mht (hash table). This means that we have to copy the oids into a
3354  * non-relocatable place (see lc_ht_permoids below) until the entire
3355  * graph is known.
3356  */
3357 static LC_LOCKSET *
3358 locator_all_reference_lockset (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OID * oid, int prune_level, LOCK inst_lock, LOCK class_lock,
3359  bool quit_on_errors)
3360 {
3361  OID class_oid; /* The class_oid of an inst */
3362  int max_refs, ref_num; /* Max and reference number in request area */
3363  int max_stack; /* Total size of stack */
3364  int stack_actual_size; /* Actual size of stack */
3365  int level; /* The current listing level */
3366  int oid_list_size = 0; /* Oid list size */
3367  OID *oid_list = NULL; /* List of ref for one object */
3368  LC_LOCKSET *lockset = NULL; /* Building request for obj. */
3369  struct lc_lockset_reqobj *reqobjs; /* Description of one inst */
3370  struct lc_lockset_reqobj *to_reqobjs; /* Description of one inst */
3371  struct lc_lockset_classof *reqclasses; /* Description of one class */
3372  int *stack = NULL; /* The stack for the search */
3373  HEAP_SCANCACHE scan_cache; /* Scan cache used for fetching purposes */
3374  SCAN_CODE scan; /* Scan return value for an object */
3375  RECDES peek_recdes;
3376  void *new_ptr;
3377  int i, tmp_ref_num, number;
3378  MHT_TABLE *lc_ht_permoids = NULL; /* Hash table of already found oids */
3379  HL_HEAPID heap_id = HL_NULL_HEAPID; /* Id of Heap allocator */
3380  MVCC_SNAPSHOT *mvcc_snapshot = NULL;
3381 
3382  struct ht_obj_info
3383  {
3384  OID oid;
3385  int ref_num;
3386  }; /* info stored into hash table */
3387  struct ht_obj_info *ht_obj;
3388 
3389  /* Make sure that the object exists ? */
3390  if (!heap_does_exist (thread_p, NULL, oid))
3391  {
3392  if (er_errid () != ER_INTERRUPTED)
3393  {
3394  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT, 3, oid->volid, oid->pageid, oid->slotid);
3395  }
3396 
3397  goto error;
3398  }
3399 
3400  /* Let's assume a number of references for allocation start purposes */
3401  max_refs = max_stack = LOCATOR_GUESS_NUM_NESTED_REFERENCES;
3402 
3403  lockset = locator_allocate_lockset (max_refs, inst_lock, class_lock, quit_on_errors);
3404  if (lockset == NULL)
3405  {
3406  goto error;
3407  }
3408 
3409  stack = (int *) malloc (sizeof (*stack) * max_stack);
3410  if (stack == NULL)
3411  {
3412  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (*stack) * max_stack);
3413  goto error;
3414  }
3415 
3416  /* Use a hash table to speed up lockset verification when looking for cycles in the graph */
3417  lc_ht_permoids = mht_create ("Memory hash lc_allrefs", LOCATOR_GUESS_HT_SIZE, oid_hash, oid_compare_equals);
3418  if (lc_ht_permoids == NULL)
3419  {
3420  goto error;
3421  }
3422 
3423  /* Use a chunky memory manager, for fewer mallocs of small stuff */
3424  heap_id = db_create_fixed_heap (sizeof (struct ht_obj_info), LOCATOR_GUESS_HT_SIZE);
3425  if (heap_id == HL_NULL_HEAPID)
3426  {
3427  goto error;
3428  }
3429 
3430  /* Initialize the stack */
3431  stack_actual_size = 0;
3432  level = 0;
3433 
3434  reqobjs = lockset->objects;
3435  reqclasses = lockset->classes;
3436 
3437  /*
3438  * Add first object to the stack and request structure.
3439  * Indicate that the object is only on the stack. That is, the object has
3440  * not been visited.
3441  * The cache coherence number is used to hold the level of the object in
3442  * the nested graph/tree
3443  */
3444 
3445  COPY_OID (&reqobjs->oid, oid);
3446  reqobjs->class_index = -1;
3447  reqobjs->chn = level;
3448  stack[stack_actual_size++] = lockset->num_reqobjs++; /* Push */
3449  reqobjs++;
3450 
3451  mvcc_snapshot = logtb_get_mvcc_snapshot (thread_p);
3452  if (mvcc_snapshot == NULL)
3453  {
3454  goto error;
3455  }
3456 
3457  /*
3458  * Start a kind of depth-first search algorithm to find out all references
3459  * until the prune level is reached
3460  */
3461 
3462  /* Start a scan cursor for getting several classes */
3463  if (heap_scancache_start (thread_p, &scan_cache, NULL, NULL, true, false, mvcc_snapshot) != NO_ERROR)
3464  {
3465  goto error;
3466  }
3467 
3468  while (stack_actual_size > 0)
3469  {
3470  ref_num = stack[--stack_actual_size]; /* Pop */
3471 
3472  /* Get the object to find out its direct references */
3473  OID_SET_NULL (&class_oid);
3474  scan = heap_get_visible_version (thread_p, &lockset->objects[ref_num].oid, &class_oid, &peek_recdes, &scan_cache,
3475  PEEK, NULL_CHN);
3476  if (scan != S_SUCCESS)
3477  {
3478  if (scan != S_DOESNT_EXIST && (quit_on_errors == true || er_errid () == ER_INTERRUPTED))
3479  {
3480  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache);
3481  goto error;
3482  }
3483 
3484  /* Remove the object from the list of requested objects */
3485  if (ref_num == lockset->num_reqobjs - 1)
3486  {
3487  /* Last element remove it */
3488  lockset->num_reqobjs--;
3489  reqobjs--;
3490  }
3491  else
3492  {
3493  /* Marked it as invalid */
3494  OID_SET_NULL (&lockset->objects[ref_num].oid);
3495  }
3496  er_clear ();
3497  continue;
3498  }
3499 
3500  /*
3501  * has the object been visited ?
3502  */
3503  if (lockset->objects[ref_num].class_index == -1)
3504  {
3505  /*
3506  * Object has never been visited. First time in the stack.
3507  * Find its class and marked as listed in the lockset structure
3508  */
3509 
3510  /* Is this class already stored ? */
3511 
3512  for (i = 0; i < lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs; i++)
3513  {
3514  if (OID_EQ (&class_oid, &lockset->classes[i].oid))
3515  {
3516  break;
3517  }
3518  }
3519  if (i < lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs)
3520  {
3521  /* Class is already in the lockset class list array */
3522  lockset->objects[ref_num].class_index = i;
3523  }
3524  else
3525  {
3526  /*
3527  * Class is not in the lockset class list array.
3528  * Make sure that this is a valid class
3529  */
3530  if (!heap_does_exist (thread_p, oid_Root_class_oid, &class_oid))
3531  {
3532  /* Remove the object from the list of requested objects */
3533  if (ref_num == lockset->num_reqobjs - 1)
3534  {
3535  /* Last element remove it */
3536  lockset->num_reqobjs--;
3537  reqobjs--;
3538  }
3539  else
3540  {
3541  /* Marked it as invalid */
3542  OID_SET_NULL (&lockset->objects[ref_num].oid);
3543  }
3544  continue;
3545  }
3546  COPY_OID (&reqclasses->oid, &class_oid);
3547  reqclasses->chn = NULL_CHN; /* Note that this is a level */
3548  lockset->objects[ref_num].class_index = lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs;
3549  lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs++;
3550  reqclasses++;
3551  }
3552  }
3553 
3554  /* Level for the directly referenced objects */
3555 
3556  level = lockset->objects[ref_num].chn + 1;
3557  if (prune_level >= 0 && level > prune_level)
3558  {
3559  continue;
3560  }
3561 
3562  /*
3563  * Find all direct references from the given object
3564  */
3565  if (OID_IS_ROOTOID (&class_oid))
3566  {
3567  continue;
3568  }
3569  number =
3570  heap_get_referenced_by (thread_p, &class_oid, &lockset->objects[ref_num].oid, &peek_recdes, &oid_list_size,
3571  &oid_list);
3572  if (number <= 0)
3573  {
3574  continue;
3575  }
3576 
3577  /*
3578  * Add the above references to the stack if these objects have not
3579  * been alredy visited or if their current level is smaller than their
3580  * visited level
3581  */
3582 
3583  if (oid_list == NULL || number <= 0)
3584  {
3585  continue;
3586  }
3587  for (i = 0; i < number; i++)
3588  {
3589  if (OID_ISNULL (&oid_list[i]))
3590  {
3591  continue;
3592  }
3593 
3594  ht_obj = (struct ht_obj_info *) mht_get (lc_ht_permoids, &oid_list[i]);
3595  if (ht_obj != NULL)
3596  {
3597  tmp_ref_num = ht_obj->ref_num;
3598  if (lockset->objects[tmp_ref_num].chn > level)
3599  {
3600  /*
3601  * Re-visit the object again since some of its
3602  * references may have been pruned
3603  */
3604  lockset->objects[tmp_ref_num].chn = level;
3605  /* push */
3606  stack[stack_actual_size++] = tmp_ref_num;
3607  }
3608  }
3609  else
3610  {
3611  tmp_ref_num = lockset->num_reqobjs;
3612  /*
3613  * Push the object onto the stack.
3614  * Make sure that we have area in the stack and the
3615  * request area
3616  */
3617  if (stack_actual_size >= max_stack)
3618  {
3619  /* Expand the stack */
3620  if (number > LOCATOR_GUESS_NUM_NESTED_REFERENCES)
3621  {
3622  max_stack += number;
3623  }
3624  else
3625  {
3626  max_stack += LOCATOR_GUESS_NUM_NESTED_REFERENCES;
3627  }
3628  new_ptr = realloc (stack, sizeof (*stack) * max_stack);
3629  if (new_ptr == NULL)
3630  {
3631  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
3632  sizeof (*stack) * max_stack);
3633  if (quit_on_errors == false)
3634  {
3635  break;
3636  }
3637  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache);
3638  goto error;
3639  }
3640  stack = (int *) new_ptr;
3641  }
3642 
3643  if ((lockset->num_reqobjs + 1) > max_refs)
3644  {
3645  if (number > LOCATOR_GUESS_NUM_NESTED_REFERENCES)
3646  {
3647  max_refs += number;
3648  }
3649  else
3650  {
3651  max_refs += LOCATOR_GUESS_NUM_NESTED_REFERENCES;
3652  }
3653  new_ptr = locator_reallocate_lockset (lockset, max_refs);
3654  if (new_ptr == NULL)
3655  {
3656  if (quit_on_errors == false)
3657  {
3658  break;
3659  }
3660  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache);
3661  goto error;
3662  }
3663  lockset = (LC_LOCKSET *) new_ptr;
3664  /* Find the new locations since the structure was reallocated */
3665  reqobjs = lockset->objects + lockset->num_reqobjs;
3666  reqclasses = lockset->classes + lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs;
3667  }
3668 
3669  /* Put object in the hash table */
3670  ht_obj = (struct ht_obj_info *) db_fixed_alloc (heap_id, sizeof (*ht_obj));
3671  if (ht_obj == NULL)
3672  {
3673  if (quit_on_errors == false)
3674  {
3675  break;
3676  }
3677  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache);
3678  goto error;
3679  }
3680  COPY_OID (&ht_obj->oid, &oid_list[i]);
3681  ht_obj->ref_num = tmp_ref_num;
3682 
3683  if (mht_put (lc_ht_permoids, &ht_obj->oid, ht_obj) != ht_obj)
3684  {
3685  if (quit_on_errors == false)
3686  {
3687  break;
3688  }
3689  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache);
3690  goto error;
3691  }
3692 
3693  /*
3694  * Push the object
3695  * Indicate that the object is only on the stack. That is,
3696  * the object has not been visited.
3697  * The cache coherence number is used to hold the level of
3698  * the object in the nested graph/tree
3699  */
3700  COPY_OID (&reqobjs->oid, &oid_list[i]);
3701  reqobjs->class_index = -1;
3702  reqobjs->chn = level;
3703  /* Push */
3704  stack[stack_actual_size++] = lockset->num_reqobjs++;
3705  reqobjs++;
3706  }
3707  }
3708  }
3709 
3710  /* Cleanup */
3711  if (oid_list != NULL)
3712  {
3713  free_and_init (oid_list);
3714  }
3715  free_and_init (stack);
3716  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache);
3717  db_destroy_fixed_heap (heap_id);
3718  mht_destroy (lc_ht_permoids);
3719 
3720  /*
3721  * Set the cache coherence numbers as unknown (these are the ones of the
3722  * client workspace) and compact the array of requested objects. Note that
3723  * before we have used the chn as the level, so it needs to be reset.
3724  */
3725 
3726  number = 0;
3727  to_reqobjs = reqobjs = lockset->objects;
3728  for (i = 0; i < lockset->num_reqobjs; i++)
3729  {
3730  if (!OID_ISNULL (&reqobjs->oid))
3731  {
3732  /* Move it to */
3733  if (to_reqobjs != reqobjs)
3734  {
3735  memcpy (to_reqobjs, reqobjs, sizeof (*reqobjs));
3736  }
3737  to_reqobjs->chn = NULL_CHN;
3738  to_reqobjs++;
3739  }
3740  else
3741  {
3742  number++;
3743  }
3744  reqobjs++;
3745  }
3746  lockset->num_reqobjs -= number;
3747 
3748  for (i = 0; i < lockset->num_classes_of_reqobjs; i++)
3749  {
3750  lockset->classes[i].chn = CHN_UNKNOWN_ATCLIENT;
3751  }
3752 
3753  return lockset;
3754 
3755 error:
3756  if (oid_list != NULL)
3757  {
3758  free_and_init (oid_list);
3759  }
3760  if (lc_ht_permoids != NULL)
3761  {
3762  mht_destroy (lc_ht_permoids);
3763  lc_ht_permoids = NULL;
3764  }
3765  if (stack != NULL)
3766  {
3767  free_and_init (stack);
3768  }
3769  if (lockset != NULL)
3770  {
3771  locator_free_lockset (lockset);
3772  lockset = NULL;
3773  }
3774  if (heap_id != HL_NULL_HEAPID)
3775  {
3776  db_destroy_fixed_heap (heap_id);
3777  }
3778 
3779  return NULL;
3780 }
3781 
3782 /*
3783  * xlocator_fetch_all_reference_lockset () - Lock and fetch the requested objects and its
3784  * direct and indirect references
3785  *
3786  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
3787  *
3788  * oid(in): The desired object in the root of nested references
3789  * chn(in): Cache coherence number of desired object
3790  * class_oid(in): Class identifier of the desired object
3791  * class_chn(in): Cache coherence number of the class of the desired object
3792  * lock(in): Lock to acquire on the desired object and its references
3793  * quit_on_errors(in): Wheater to continue in case an error, such as an
3794  * object can be locked
3795  * prune_level(in): Get references upto this level. If the value is <= 0
3796  * means upto an infonite level (i.e., all references).
3797  * lockset(in/out): Request for finding the all references. This is set to
3798  * NULL when the references are unknown.
3799  * fetch_area(in/out): Pointer to area where the objects are placed (Set as a
3800  * side effect)
3801  *
3802  */
3803 int
3804 xlocator_fetch_all_reference_lockset (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OID * oid, int chn, OID * class_oid, int class_chn,
3805  LOCK lock, int quit_on_errors, int prune_level, LC_LOCKSET ** lockset,
3806  LC_COPYAREA ** fetch_area)
3807 {
3808  int i;
3809  LOCK instance_lock;
3810 
3811  /* Find all the references */
3812  if (lock <= S_LOCK)
3813  {
3814  instance_lock = IS_LOCK;
3815  }
3816  else
3817  {
3818  instance_lock = IX_LOCK;
3819  }
3820  *lockset = locator_all_reference_lockset (thread_p, oid, prune_level, lock, instance_lock, quit_on_errors != 0);
3821  if (*lockset == NULL)
3822  {
3823  return ER_FAILED;
3824  }
3825 
3826  /*
3827  * Set the known cache coherence numbers of the desired object and its
3828  * class
3829  */
3830 
3831  if (chn != NULL_CHN)
3832  {
3833  for (i = 0; i < (*lockset)->num_reqobjs; i++)
3834  {
3835  if (OID_EQ (oid, &(*lockset)->objects[i].oid))
3836  {
3837  (*lockset)->objects[i].chn = chn;
3838  break;
3839  }
3840  }
3841  }
3842 
3843  if (class_oid != NULL && class_chn != NULL_CHN)
3844  {
3845  for (i = 0; i < (*lockset)->num_classes_of_reqobjs; i++)
3846  {
3847  if (OID_EQ (class_oid, &(*lockset)->classes[i].oid))
3848  {
3849  (*lockset)->classes[i].chn = class_chn;
3850  break;
3851  }
3852  }
3853  }
3854 
3855  /* Get the first batch of classes and objects */
3856  return xlocator_fetch_lockset (thread_p, *lockset, fetch_area);
3857 }
3858 
3859 /*
3860  * xlocator_does_exist () - Does object exist? if it does prefetch it
3861  *
3862  * return: Either of (LC_EXIST, LC_DOESNOT_EXIST, LC_ERROR)
3863  *
3864  * oid(in): Object identifier of desired object
3865  * chn(in): Cache coherence number of object
3866  * lock(in): Lock to acquire for the object
3867  * fetch_type(in): fetch type
3868  * class_oid(in): Class identifier of the object
3869  * class_chn(in): Cache coherence number of the class of the object
3870  * need_fetching(in):
3871  * prefetching(in): true if prefetching of some of the object neighbors is
3872  * desired.
3873  * fetch_area(in/out): Pointer to area where the objects are placed
3874  (set to point to fetching area)
3875  *
3876  * Note:This function checks if the desired object exist. An error is
3877  * not set if the object does not exist. If the object exists and
3878  * prefetching is desired, prefetching is done for the object and
3879  * some of its neighbors.
3880  */
3881 int
3882 xlocator_does_exist (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OID * oid, int chn, LOCK lock, LC_FETCH_VERSION_TYPE fetch_version_type,
3883  OID * class_oid, int class_chn, int need_fetching, int prefetching, LC_COPYAREA ** fetch_area)
3884 {
3885  OID tmp_oid;
3886  SCAN_CODE scan_code = S_SUCCESS;
3887 
3888  if (need_fetching && fetch_area != NULL)
3889  {
3890  *fetch_area = NULL;
3891  }
3892 
3893  if (class_oid == NULL)
3894  {
3895  class_oid = &tmp_oid;
3896  OID_SET_NULL (class_oid);
3897  }
3898 
3899  /* Quick fix: we need to check if OID is valid - meaning that page is still valid. This code is going to be
3900  * removed with one of the refactoring issues anyway.
3901  */
3902  if (HEAP_ISVALID_OID (thread_p, oid) != DISK_VALID)
3903  {
3904  return LC_DOESNOT_EXIST;
3905  }
3906 
3907  /* Prefetch the object if that operation is desirable */
3908  if (need_fetching && fetch_area != NULL)
3909  {
3910  int ret = xlocator_fetch (thread_p, oid, NULL_CHN, lock, fetch_version_type, fetch_version_type,
3911  class_oid, class_chn, prefetching, fetch_area);
3912  if (ret == ER_FAILED)
3913  {
3914  ASSERT_ERROR ();
3915  if (lock != NULL_LOCK)
3916  {
3917  lock_unlock_object (thread_p, oid, class_oid, lock, false);
3918  }
3919  return LC_ERROR;
3920  }
3921  else if (ret != NO_ERROR)
3922  {
3923  return LC_DOESNOT_EXIST;
3924  }
3925 
3926  /* success -> fall through */
3927  }
3928  else
3929  {
3930  if (lock != NULL_LOCK)
3931  {
3932  /* try to aquire requested lock or the appropriate one; it will be decided according to class type */
3933  SCAN_OPERATION_TYPE op_type;
3934  HEAP_SCANCACHE scan_cache;
3935 
3936  op_type = locator_decide_operation_type (lock, fetch_version_type);
3937 
3938  (void) heap_scancache_quick_start (&scan_cache);
3939 
3940  scan_code = locator_get_object (thread_p, oid, class_oid, NULL, &scan_cache, op_type, lock, PEEK, NULL_CHN);
3941  heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache);
3942  if (scan_code == S_ERROR)
3943  {
3944  ASSERT_ERROR ();
3945  return LC_ERROR;
3946  }
3947  else if (scan_code != S_SUCCESS)
3948  {
3949  return LC_DOESNOT_EXIST;
3950  }
3951  }
3952  else if (!heap_does_exist (thread_p, class_oid, oid))
3953  {
3954  /* object doesn't exist */
3955  return LC_DOESNOT_EXIST;
3956  }
3957 
3958  /* success -> fall through */
3959  }
3960 
3961  /* Success */
3962  return LC_EXIST;
3963 }
3964 
3965 /*
3966  * locator_start_force_scan_cache () -
3967  *
3968  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
3969  *
3970  * scan_cache(in/out):
3971  * hfid(in):
3972  * class_oid(in):
3973  * op_type(in):
3974  */
3975 int
3976 locator_start_force_scan_cache (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, HEAP_SCANCACHE * scan_cache, const HFID * hfid,
3977  const OID * class_oid, int op_type)
3978 {
3979  return heap_scancache_start_modify (thread_p, scan_cache, hfid, class_oid, op_type, NULL);
3980 }
3981 
3982 /*
3983  * locator_end_force_scan_cache () -
3984  *
3985  * return:
3986  *
3987  * scan_cache(in):
3988  */
3989 void
3990 locator_end_force_scan_cache (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, HEAP_SCANCACHE * scan_cache)
3991 {
3992  heap_scancache_end_modify (thread_p, scan_cache);
