3995 /*
3996  * locator_check_foreign_key () -
3997  *
3998  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
3999  *
4000  * hfid(in):
4001  * class_oid(in):
4002  * inst_oid(in):
4003  * recdes(in):
4004  * new_recdes(in):
4005  * is_cached(in):
4006  * copyarea(in):
4007  */
4008 static int
4009 locator_check_foreign_key (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, HFID * hfid, OID * class_oid, OID * inst_oid, RECDES * recdes,
4010  RECDES * new_recdes, bool * is_cached, LC_COPYAREA ** copyarea)
4011 {
4012  int num_found, i;
4013  HEAP_CACHE_ATTRINFO index_attrinfo;
4014  HEAP_IDX_ELEMENTS_INFO idx_info;
4015  BTID btid, local_btid;
4016  DB_VALUE *key_dbvalue;
4017  DB_VALUE dbvalue;
4018  char buf[DBVAL_BUFSIZE + MAX_ALIGNMENT], *aligned_buf;
4019  OR_INDEX *index;
4020  OID unique_oid;
4021  OID part_oid;
4022  HFID class_hfid;
4023  bool has_null;
4024  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
4025  PRUNING_CONTEXT pcontext;
4026  bool clear_pcontext = false;
4027  OR_CLASSREP *classrepr = NULL;
4028  int classrepr_cacheindex = -1;
4029  BTREE_SEARCH ret;
4030 
4031  db_make_null (&dbvalue);
4032 
4033  aligned_buf = PTR_ALIGN (buf, MAX_ALIGNMENT);
4034 
4035  num_found = heap_attrinfo_start_with_index (thread_p, class_oid, NULL, &index_attrinfo, &idx_info);
4036  if (num_found <= 0)
4037  {
4038  return error_code;
4039  }
4040 
4041  if (idx_info.has_single_col)
4042  {
4043  error_code = heap_attrinfo_read_dbvalues (thread_p, inst_oid, recdes, NULL, &index_attrinfo);
4044  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4045  {
4046  goto error;
4047  }
4048  }
4049 
4050  for (i = 0; i < idx_info.num_btids; i++)
4051  {
4052  index = &(index_attrinfo.last_classrepr->indexes[i]);
4053  if (index->type != BTREE_FOREIGN_KEY)
4054  {
4055  continue;
4056  }
4057 
4058  /* must be updated when key_prefix_length will be added for FK and PK */
4059  key_dbvalue =
4060  heap_attrvalue_get_key (thread_p, i, &index_attrinfo, recdes, &btid, &dbvalue, aligned_buf, NULL, NULL);
4061  if (key_dbvalue == NULL)
4062  {
4063  error_code = ER_FAILED;
4064  goto error;
4065  }
4066 
4067  /* SQL standard defines as follows:
4068  * If no <match type> was specified then, for each row R1 of the referencing table,
4069  * either at least one of the values of the referencing columns in R1 shall be a null value,
4070  * or the value of each referencing column in R1 shall be equal to the value of
4071  * the corresponding referenced column in some row of the referenced table.
4072  * Please notice that we don't currently support <match type>.
4073  */
4074  if (index->n_atts > 1)
4075  {
4076 
4077  has_null = btree_multicol_key_has_null (key_dbvalue);
4078  }
4079  else
4080  {
4081  has_null = DB_IS_NULL (key_dbvalue);
4082  }
4083 
4084  if (!has_null)
4085  {
4086  /* get class representation to find partition information */
4087  classrepr =
4088  heap_classrepr_get (thread_p, &index->fk->ref_class_oid, NULL, NULL_REPRID, &classrepr_cacheindex);
4089  if (classrepr == NULL)
4090  {
4091  error_code = ER_FAILED;
4092  goto error;
4093  }
4094  if (classrepr->has_partition_info > 0)
4095  {
4096  (void) partition_init_pruning_context (&pcontext);
4097  clear_pcontext = true;
4098  error_code =
4099  partition_load_pruning_context (thread_p, &index->fk->ref_class_oid, DB_PARTITIONED_CLASS, &pcontext);
4100  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4101  {
4102  goto error;
4103  }
4104  }
4105 
4106  BTID_COPY (&local_btid, &index->fk->ref_class_pk_btid);
4107  COPY_OID (&part_oid, &index->fk->ref_class_oid);
4108 
4109  if (classrepr->has_partition_info > 0 && pcontext.partitions != NULL)
4110  {
4111  error_code = partition_prune_unique_btid (&pcontext, key_dbvalue, &part_oid, &class_hfid, &local_btid);
4112  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4113  {
4114  goto error;
4115  }
4116  }
4117  ret =
4118  xbtree_find_unique (thread_p, &local_btid, S_SELECT_WITH_LOCK, key_dbvalue, &part_oid, &unique_oid, true);
4119  if (ret == BTREE_KEY_NOTFOUND)
4120  {
4121  char *val_print = NULL;
4122 
4123  val_print = pr_valstring (thread_p, key_dbvalue);
4124  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_FK_INVALID, 2, index->fk->fkname,
4125  (val_print ? val_print : "unknown value"));
4126  error_code = ER_FK_INVALID;
4127  if (val_print)
4128  {
4129  db_private_free (thread_p, val_print);
4130  }
4131 
4132  if (key_dbvalue == &dbvalue)
4133  {
4134  pr_clear_value (&dbvalue);
4135  }
4136 
4137  if (LOG_CHECK_LOG_APPLIER (thread_p))
4138  {
4139  continue;
4140  }
4141 
4142  goto error;
4143  }
4144  else if (ret == BTREE_ERROR_OCCURRED)
4145  {
4146  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
4147  goto error;
4148  }
4149  assert (ret == BTREE_KEY_FOUND);
4150  /* TODO: For read committed... Do we need to keep the lock? */
4151  }
4152 
4153  if (key_dbvalue == &dbvalue)
4154  {
4155  pr_clear_value (&dbvalue);
4156  }
4157  }
4158 
4159 error:
4160  if (clear_pcontext == true)
4161  {
4162  partition_clear_pruning_context (&pcontext);
4163  }
4164  if (classrepr != NULL)
4165  {
4166  heap_classrepr_free_and_init (classrepr, &classrepr_cacheindex);
4167  }
4168  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, &index_attrinfo);
4169  return error_code;
4170 }
4171 
4172 /*
4173  * locator_check_primary_key_delete () -
4174  *
4175  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
4176  *
4177  * fkref(in):
4178  * key(in):
4179  */
4180 static int
4181 locator_check_primary_key_delete (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OR_INDEX * index, DB_VALUE * key)
4182 {
4183  OR_FOREIGN_KEY *fkref;
4184  int oid_cnt, force_count, i;
4185  RECDES recdes;
4186  HEAP_SCANCACHE scan_cache;
4187  HFID hfid;
4188  BTREE_SCAN bt_scan;
4189  INDX_SCAN_ID isid;
4190  KEY_VAL_RANGE key_val_range;
4191  bool is_upd_scan_init;
4192  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
4193  HEAP_CACHE_ATTRINFO attr_info;
4194  DB_VALUE null_value;
4195  ATTR_ID *attr_ids = NULL;
4196  int num_attrs = 0;
4197  int k;
4198  int *keys_prefix_length = NULL;
4199  MVCC_SNAPSHOT *mvcc_snapshot = NULL;
4200  OID found_oid;
4201  BTREE_ISCAN_OID_LIST oid_list;
4202 
4203  oid_list.oidp = NULL;
4204 
4205  mvcc_snapshot = logtb_get_mvcc_snapshot (thread_p);
4206  if (mvcc_snapshot == NULL)
4207  {
4208  error_code = er_errid ();
4209  return (error_code == NO_ERROR ? ER_FAILED : error_code);
4210  }
4211 
4212  db_make_null (&null_value);
4213  db_make_null (&key_val_range.key1);
4214  db_make_null (&key_val_range.key2);
4215 
4216  heap_attrinfo_start (thread_p, NULL, 0, NULL, &attr_info);
4217 
4218  for (fkref = index->fk; fkref != NULL; fkref = fkref->next)
4219  {
4220  if (fkref->del_action == SM_FOREIGN_KEY_RESTRICT || fkref->del_action == SM_FOREIGN_KEY_NO_ACTION)
4221  {
4222  if (!LOG_CHECK_LOG_APPLIER (thread_p))
4223  {
4224  error_code = btree_find_foreign_key (thread_p, &fkref->self_btid, key, &fkref->self_oid, &found_oid);
4225  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4226  {
4227  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
4228  goto error3;
4229  }
4230  if (!OID_ISNULL (&found_oid))
4231  {
4232  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_FK_RESTRICT, 1, fkref->fkname);
4233  error_code = ER_FK_RESTRICT;
4234  /* Unlock child object. */
4235  lock_unlock_object_donot_move_to_non2pl (thread_p, &found_oid, &fkref->self_oid, S_LOCK);
4236  goto error3;
4237  }
4238  }
4239  }
4240  else if (fkref->del_action == SM_FOREIGN_KEY_CASCADE || fkref->del_action == SM_FOREIGN_KEY_SET_NULL)
4241  {
4242  if (attr_ids)
4243  {
4244  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, attr_ids);
4245  }
4246  error_code =
4247  heap_get_indexinfo_of_btid (thread_p, &fkref->self_oid, &fkref->self_btid, NULL, &num_attrs, &attr_ids,
4248  &keys_prefix_length, NULL, NULL);
4249  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4250  {
4251  goto error3;
4252  }
4253  assert (num_attrs == index->n_atts);
4254  /* We might check for foreign key and schema consistency problems here but we rely on the schema manager to
4255  * prevent inconsistency; see do_check_fk_constraints() for details */
4256 
4257  error_code = heap_get_hfid_from_class_oid (thread_p, &fkref->self_oid, &hfid);
4258  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4259  {
4260  goto error3;
4261  }
4262 
4263  if (oid_list.oidp == NULL)
4264  {
4265  oid_list.oidp = (OID *) db_private_alloc (thread_p, ISCAN_OID_BUFFER_CAPACITY);
4266  if (oid_list.oidp == NULL)
4267  {
4268  error_code = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
4269  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error_code, 1, ISCAN_OID_BUFFER_CAPACITY);
4270  goto error3;
4271  }
4272  oid_list.oid_cnt = 0;
4273  oid_list.capacity = ISCAN_OID_BUFFER_CAPACITY / OR_OID_SIZE;
4274  oid_list.max_oid_cnt = oid_list.capacity;
4275  oid_list.next_list = NULL;
4276  }
4277 
4278  error_code = heap_scancache_start (thread_p, &isid.scan_cache, &hfid, &fkref->self_oid, true, true, NULL);
4279  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4280  {
4281  ASSERT_ERROR ();
4282  goto error3;
4283  }
4284  scan_init_index_scan (&isid, &oid_list, mvcc_snapshot);
4285  is_upd_scan_init = false;
4286  pr_clone_value (key, &key_val_range.key1);
4287  pr_clone_value (key, &key_val_range.key2);
4288  key_val_range.range = GE_LE;
4289  key_val_range.num_index_term = 0;
4290  BTREE_INIT_SCAN (&bt_scan);
4291 
4292  do
4293  {
4294  bool lob_exist = false;
4295 
4296  error_code =
4297  btree_prepare_bts (thread_p, &bt_scan, &fkref->self_btid, &isid, &key_val_range, NULL, &fkref->self_oid,
4298  NULL, NULL, false, NULL);
4299  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4300  {
4301  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
4302  goto error2;
4303  }
4304  error_code = btree_range_scan (thread_p, &bt_scan, btree_range_scan_select_visible_oids);
4305  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4306  {
4307  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
4308  goto error2;
4309  }
4310  oid_cnt = bt_scan.n_oids_read_last_iteration;
4311 
4312  if (oid_cnt < 0)
4313  {
4314  assert (false);
4315  error_code = ER_FAILED;
4316  goto error2;
4317  }
4318  else if (oid_cnt == 0)
4319  {
4320  break;
4321  }
4322 
4323  if (is_upd_scan_init == false)
4324  {
4325  int op_type = -1;
4326  if (fkref->del_action == SM_FOREIGN_KEY_CASCADE)
4327  {
4328  op_type = SINGLE_ROW_DELETE;
4329  }
4330  else if (fkref->del_action == SM_FOREIGN_KEY_SET_NULL)
4331  {
4332  op_type = SINGLE_ROW_UPDATE;
4333  }
4334  else
4335  {
4336  assert (false);
4337  }
4338  error_code =
4339  heap_scancache_start_modify (thread_p, &scan_cache, &hfid, &fkref->self_oid, op_type, NULL);
4340  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4341  {
4342  goto error2;
4343  }
4344  is_upd_scan_init = true;
4345  if (fkref->del_action == SM_FOREIGN_KEY_CASCADE || fkref->del_action == SM_FOREIGN_KEY_SET_NULL)
4346  {
4347  HEAP_ATTRVALUE *value;
4348  error_code = heap_attrinfo_start (thread_p, &fkref->self_oid, -1, NULL, &attr_info);
4349  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4350  {
4351  goto error1;
4352  }
4353 
4354  for (i = 0; i < attr_info.num_values; i++)
4355  {
4356  value = &attr_info.values[i];
4357  if (value->last_attrepr->type == DB_TYPE_BLOB || value->last_attrepr->type == DB_TYPE_CLOB)
4358  {
4359  lob_exist = true;
4360  break;
4361  }
4362  }
4363  }
4364  }
4365 
4366  for (i = 0; i < oid_cnt; i++)
4367  {
4368  OID *oid_ptr = &(oid_list.oidp[i]);
4369  SCAN_CODE scan_code = S_SUCCESS;
4370  recdes.data = NULL;
4371  /* TO DO - handle reevaluation */
4372 
4373  scan_code = locator_lock_and_get_object (thread_p, oid_ptr, &fkref->self_oid, &recdes, &scan_cache,
4374  X_LOCK, COPY, NULL_CHN, LOG_ERROR_IF_DELETED);
4375  if (scan_code != S_SUCCESS)
4376  {
4377  if (scan_code == S_DOESNT_EXIST && er_errid () != ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT)
4378  {
4379  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT, oid_ptr->volid,
4380  oid_ptr->pageid, oid_ptr->slotid);
4381  }
4382 
4383  if (er_errid () == ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT)
4384  {
4385  er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE, "locator_update_force: unknown oid ( %d|%d|%d )\n",
4386  oid_ptr->pageid, oid_ptr->slotid, oid_ptr->volid);
4387  continue;
4388  }
4389 
4390  error_code = er_errid ();
4391  error_code = (error_code == NO_ERROR ? ER_FAILED : error_code);
4392  goto error1;
4393  }
4394 
4395  if (fkref->del_action == SM_FOREIGN_KEY_CASCADE)
4396  {
4397  if (lob_exist)
4398  {
4399  error_code = locator_delete_lob_force (thread_p, &fkref->self_oid, oid_ptr, NULL);
4400  }
4401  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4402  {
4403  goto error1;
4404  }
4405 
4406  /* oid already locked at locator_lock_and_get_object */
4407  error_code =
4408  locator_delete_force (thread_p, &hfid, oid_ptr, true, SINGLE_ROW_DELETE, &scan_cache,
4409  &force_count, NULL, false);
4410  if (error_code == ER_MVCC_NOT_SATISFIED_REEVALUATION)
4411  {
4412  /* skip foreign keys that were already deleted. For example the "cross type" reference */
4413  error_code = NO_ERROR;
4414  }
4415  else if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4416  {
4417  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_FK_CANT_DELETE_INSTANCE, 1, fkref->fkname);
4418  goto error1;
4419  }
4420  }
4421  else if (fkref->del_action == SM_FOREIGN_KEY_SET_NULL)
4422  {
4423  error_code = heap_attrinfo_clear_dbvalues (&attr_info);
4424  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4425  {
4426  goto error1;
4427  }
4428  for (k = 0; k < num_attrs; ++k)
4429  {
4430  error_code = heap_attrinfo_set (oid_ptr, attr_ids[k], &null_value, &attr_info);
4431  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4432  {
4433  goto error1;
4434  }
4435  }
4436  /* oid already locked at locator_lock_and_get_object */
4437  error_code =
4438  locator_attribute_info_force (thread_p, &hfid, oid_ptr, &attr_info, attr_ids, index->n_atts,
4439  LC_FLUSH_UPDATE, SINGLE_ROW_UPDATE, &scan_cache, &force_count,
4440  false, REPL_INFO_TYPE_RBR_NORMAL, DB_NOT_PARTITIONED_CLASS, NULL,
4441  NULL, NULL, UPDATE_INPLACE_NONE, &recdes, false);
4442  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4443  {
4444  if (error_code == ER_MVCC_NOT_SATISFIED_REEVALUATION)
4445  {
4446  error_code = NO_ERROR;
4447  }
4448  else
4449  {
4450  goto error1;
4451  }
4452  }
4453  }
4454  else
4455  {
4456  assert (false);
4457  }
4458  }
4459  }
4460  while (!BTREE_END_OF_SCAN (&bt_scan));
4461 
4462  if (is_upd_scan_init)
4463  {
4464  heap_scancache_end_modify (thread_p, &scan_cache);
4465  if (fkref->del_action == SM_FOREIGN_KEY_CASCADE || fkref->del_action == SM_FOREIGN_KEY_SET_NULL)
4466  {
4467  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, &attr_info);
4468  }
4469  }
4470 
4471  btree_scan_clear_key (&bt_scan);
4472  pr_clear_value (&key_val_range.key1);
4473  pr_clear_value (&key_val_range.key2);
4474  error_code = heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &isid.scan_cache);
4475  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4476  {
4477  error_code = NO_ERROR;
4478  goto end;
4479  }
4480  }
4481  else
4482  {
4483  assert (false);
4484  }
4485  }
4486 
4487 end:
4488  if (oid_list.oidp)
4489  {
4490  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, oid_list.oidp);
4491  }
4492  if (attr_ids)
4493  {
4494  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, attr_ids);
4495  }
4496  if (keys_prefix_length)
4497  {
4498  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, keys_prefix_length);
4499  }
4500 
4501  return error_code;
4502 
4503 error1:
4504  heap_scancache_end_modify (thread_p, &scan_cache);
4505 
4506 error2:
4507  btree_scan_clear_key (&bt_scan);
4508  pr_clear_value (&key_val_range.key1);
4509  pr_clear_value (&key_val_range.key2);
4510  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &isid.scan_cache);
4511 
4512 error3:
4513  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, &attr_info);
4514 
4515  goto end;
4516 }
4517 
4518 /*
4519  * locator_check_primary_key_update () -
4520  *
4521  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
4522  *
4523  * index(in):
4524  * key(in):
4525  */
4526 static int
4527 locator_check_primary_key_update (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OR_INDEX * index, DB_VALUE * key)
4528 {
4529  OR_FOREIGN_KEY *fkref;
4530  int oid_cnt, force_count, i;
4531  RECDES recdes;
4532  HEAP_SCANCACHE scan_cache;
4533  HFID hfid;
4534  BTREE_SCAN bt_scan;
4535  INDX_SCAN_ID isid;
4536  KEY_VAL_RANGE key_val_range;
4537  bool is_upd_scan_init;
4538  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
4539  HEAP_CACHE_ATTRINFO attr_info;
4540  DB_VALUE null_value;
4541  ATTR_ID *attr_ids = NULL;
4542  int num_attrs = 0;
4543  int k;
4544  int *keys_prefix_length = NULL;
4545  MVCC_SNAPSHOT *mvcc_snapshot = NULL;
4546  OID found_oid;
4547  BTREE_ISCAN_OID_LIST oid_list;
4548 
4549  oid_list.oidp = NULL;
4550 
4551  mvcc_snapshot = logtb_get_mvcc_snapshot (thread_p);
4552  if (mvcc_snapshot == NULL)
4553  {
4554  error_code = er_errid ();
4555  return (error_code == NO_ERROR ? ER_FAILED : error_code);
4556  }
4557 
4558  db_make_null (&key_val_range.key1);
4559  db_make_null (&key_val_range.key2);
4560  db_make_null (&null_value);
4561  heap_attrinfo_start (thread_p, NULL, 0, NULL, &attr_info);
4562 
4563  for (fkref = index->fk; fkref != NULL; fkref = fkref->next)
4564  {
4565  if (fkref->upd_action == SM_FOREIGN_KEY_RESTRICT || fkref->upd_action == SM_FOREIGN_KEY_NO_ACTION)
4566  {
4567  if (!LOG_CHECK_LOG_APPLIER (thread_p))
4568  {
4569  error_code = btree_find_foreign_key (thread_p, &fkref->self_btid, key, &fkref->self_oid, &found_oid);
4570  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4571  {
4572  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
4573  goto error3;
4574  }
4575  if (!OID_ISNULL (&found_oid))
4576  {
4577  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_FK_RESTRICT, 1, fkref->fkname);
4578  error_code = ER_FK_RESTRICT;
4579  /* Unlock child object. */
4580  lock_unlock_object_donot_move_to_non2pl (thread_p, &found_oid, &fkref->self_oid, S_LOCK);
4581  goto error3;
4582  }
4583  }
4584  }
4585  else if (fkref->upd_action == SM_FOREIGN_KEY_CASCADE || fkref->upd_action == SM_FOREIGN_KEY_SET_NULL)
4586  {
4587  if (attr_ids)
4588  {
4589  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, attr_ids);
4590  }
4591  error_code =
4592  heap_get_indexinfo_of_btid (thread_p, &fkref->self_oid, &fkref->self_btid, NULL, &num_attrs, &attr_ids,
4593  &keys_prefix_length, NULL, NULL);
4594  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4595  {
4596  goto error3;
4597  }
4598  assert (num_attrs == index->n_atts);
4599  /* We might check for foreign key and schema consistency problems here but we rely on the schema manager to
4600  * prevent inconsistency; see do_check_fk_constraints() for details */
4601 
4602  error_code = heap_get_hfid_from_class_oid (thread_p, &fkref->self_oid, &hfid);
4603  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4604  {
4605  goto error3;
4606  }
4607 
4608  if (oid_list.oidp == NULL)
4609  {
4610  oid_list.oidp = (OID *) db_private_alloc (thread_p, ISCAN_OID_BUFFER_CAPACITY);
4611  if (oid_list.oidp == NULL)
4612  {
4613  error_code = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
4614  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error_code, 1, ISCAN_OID_BUFFER_CAPACITY);
4615  goto error3;
4616  }
4617  oid_list.capacity = ISCAN_OID_BUFFER_CAPACITY / OR_OID_SIZE;
4618  oid_list.max_oid_cnt = oid_list.capacity;
4619  oid_list.oid_cnt = 0;
4620  oid_list.next_list = NULL;
4621  }
4622 
4623  error_code = heap_scancache_start (thread_p, &isid.scan_cache, &hfid, &fkref->self_oid, true, true, NULL);
4624  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4625  {
4626  ASSERT_ERROR ();
4627  goto error3;
4628  }
4629 
4630  scan_init_index_scan (&isid, &oid_list, mvcc_snapshot);
4631 
4632  is_upd_scan_init = false;
4633  pr_clone_value (key, &key_val_range.key1);
4634  pr_clone_value (key, &key_val_range.key2);
4635  key_val_range.range = GE_LE;
4636  key_val_range.num_index_term = 0;
4637  BTREE_INIT_SCAN (&bt_scan);
4638 
4639  do
4640  {
4641  error_code =
4642  btree_prepare_bts (thread_p, &bt_scan, &fkref->self_btid, &isid, &key_val_range, NULL, &fkref->self_oid,
4643  NULL, NULL, false, NULL);
4644  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4645  {
4646  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
4647  goto error2;
4648  }
4649  error_code = btree_range_scan (thread_p, &bt_scan, btree_range_scan_select_visible_oids);
4650  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4651  {
4652  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
4653  goto error2;
4654  }
4655  oid_cnt = bt_scan.n_oids_read_last_iteration;
4656  if (oid_cnt < 0)
4657  {
4658  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
4659  error_code = er_errid ();
4660  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
4661  {
4662  error_code = ER_FAILED;
4663  }
4664 
4665  goto error2;
4666  }
4667  else if (oid_cnt == 0)
4668  {
4669  break;
4670  }
4671 
4672  if (is_upd_scan_init == false)
4673  {
4674  error_code =
4675  heap_scancache_start_modify (thread_p, &scan_cache, &hfid, &fkref->self_oid, SINGLE_ROW_UPDATE,
4676  NULL);
4677  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4678  {
4679  goto error2;
4680  }
4681  is_upd_scan_init = true;
4682  error_code = heap_attrinfo_start (thread_p, &fkref->self_oid, -1, NULL, &attr_info);
4683  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4684  {
4685  goto error1;
4686  }
4687  }
4688 
4689  for (i = 0; i < oid_cnt; i++)
4690  {
4691  OID *oid_ptr = &(oid_list.oidp[i]);
4692  SCAN_CODE scan_code = S_SUCCESS;
4693  recdes.data = NULL;
4694  /* TO DO - handle reevaluation */
4695 
4696  scan_code = locator_lock_and_get_object (thread_p, oid_ptr, &fkref->self_oid, &recdes, &scan_cache,
4697  X_LOCK, COPY, NULL_CHN, LOG_ERROR_IF_DELETED);
4698  if (scan_code != S_SUCCESS)
4699  {
4700  if (scan_code == S_DOESNT_EXIST && er_errid () != ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT)
4701  {
4702  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT, oid_ptr->volid,
4703  oid_ptr->pageid, oid_ptr->slotid);
4704  }
4705  if (er_errid () == ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT)
4706  {
4707  er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE, "locator_update_force: unknown oid ( %d|%d|%d )\n",
4708  oid_ptr->pageid, oid_ptr->slotid, oid_ptr->volid);
4709  continue;
4710  }
4711 
4712  error_code = er_errid ();
4713  error_code = (error_code == NO_ERROR ? ER_FAILED : error_code);
4714  goto error1;
4715  }
4716 
4717  if ((error_code = heap_attrinfo_clear_dbvalues (&attr_info)) != NO_ERROR)
4718  {
4719  goto error1;
4720  }
4721 
4722  if (fkref->upd_action == SM_FOREIGN_KEY_CASCADE)
4723  {
4724  /* This is not yet implemented and this code should not be reached. */
4725  assert (false);
4726  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_FK_RESTRICT, 1, fkref->fkname);
4727  error_code = ER_FK_RESTRICT;
4728  goto error1;
4729  }
4730  else if (fkref->upd_action == SM_FOREIGN_KEY_SET_NULL)
4731  {
4732  for (k = 0; k < num_attrs; ++k)
4733  {
4734  error_code = heap_attrinfo_set (oid_ptr, attr_ids[k], &null_value, &attr_info);
4735  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4736  {
4737  goto error1;
4738  }
4739  }
4740  }
4741  else
4742  {
4743  assert (false);
4744  }
4745  /* oid already locked at locator_lock_and_get_object */
4746  error_code =
4747  locator_attribute_info_force (thread_p, &hfid, oid_ptr, &attr_info, attr_ids, index->n_atts,
4748  LC_FLUSH_UPDATE, SINGLE_ROW_UPDATE, &scan_cache, &force_count, false,
4749  REPL_INFO_TYPE_RBR_NORMAL, DB_NOT_PARTITIONED_CLASS, NULL, NULL, NULL,
4750  UPDATE_INPLACE_NONE, &recdes, false);
4751  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4752  {
4753  if (error_code == ER_MVCC_NOT_SATISFIED_REEVALUATION)
4754  {
4755  error_code = NO_ERROR;
4756  }
4757  else
4758  {
4759  goto error1;
4760  }
4761  }
4762  }
4763  }
4764  while (!BTREE_END_OF_SCAN (&bt_scan));
4765 
4766  if (is_upd_scan_init)
4767  {
4768  heap_scancache_end_modify (thread_p, &scan_cache);
4769  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, &attr_info);
4770  }
4771 
4772  btree_scan_clear_key (&bt_scan);
4773  pr_clear_value (&key_val_range.key1);
4774  pr_clear_value (&key_val_range.key2);
4775  error_code = heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &isid.scan_cache);
4776  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4777  {
4778  error_code = NO_ERROR;
4779  goto end;
4780  }
4781  }
4782  else
4783  {
4784  assert (false);
4785  }
4786  }
4787 
4788 end:
4789  if (oid_list.oidp)
4790  {
4791  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, oid_list.oidp);
4792  }
4793  if (attr_ids)
4794  {
4795  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, attr_ids);
4796  }
4797  if (keys_prefix_length)
4798  {
4799  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, keys_prefix_length);
4800  }
4801 
4802  return error_code;
4803 
4804 error1:
4805  heap_scancache_end_modify (thread_p, &scan_cache);
4806 
4807 error2:
4808  btree_scan_clear_key (&bt_scan);
4809  pr_clear_value (&key_val_range.key1);
4810  pr_clear_value (&key_val_range.key2);
4811  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &isid.scan_cache);
4812 
4813 error3:
4814  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, &attr_info);
4815 
4816  goto end;
4817 }
4818 
4819 /*
4820  * locator_insert_force () - Insert the given object on this heap
4821  *
4822  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
4823  *
4824  * hfid(in): Heap where the object is going to be inserted
4825  * class_oid(in/out): the class OID in which it was inserted
4826  * (in case of a partitioned class: it will hold the class OID of
4827  * the actual partition in which the record was inserted)
4828  * oid(in/out): The new object identifier
4829  * recdes(in): The object in disk format
4830  * has_index(in): false if we now for sure that there is not any index on the
4831  * instances of the class.
4832  * op_type(in):
4833  * scan_cache(in/out): Scan cache used to estimate the best space pages
4834  * between heap changes.
4835  * force_count(in):
4836  * pruning_type(in): type of pruning that should be performed
4837  * pcontext(in): partition pruning context
4838  * func_preds(in): cached function index expressions
4839  * force_in_place:
4840  *
4841  * Note: The given object is inserted on this heap and all appropriate
4842  * index entries are inserted.
4843  */
4844 static int
4845 locator_insert_force (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, HFID * hfid, OID * class_oid, OID * oid, RECDES * recdes, int has_index,
4846  int op_type, HEAP_SCANCACHE * scan_cache, int *force_count, int pruning_type,
4847  PRUNING_CONTEXT * pcontext, FUNC_PRED_UNPACK_INFO * func_preds,
4848  UPDATE_INPLACE_STYLE force_in_place)
4849 {
4850 #if 0 /* TODO - dead code; do not delete me */
4851  OID rep_dir = { NULL_PAGEID, NULL_SLOTID, NULL_VOLID };
4852 #endif
4853  bool isold_object; /* Make sure that this is an old object */
4854  RECDES new_recdes;
4855  bool is_cached = false;
4856  LC_COPYAREA *cache_attr_copyarea = NULL;
4857  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
4858  OID real_class_oid;
4859  HFID real_hfid;
4860  HEAP_SCANCACHE *local_scan_cache = NULL;
4861  FUNC_PRED_UNPACK_INFO *local_func_preds = NULL;
4862  HEAP_OPERATION_CONTEXT context;
4863 
4864  assert (class_oid != NULL);
4865  assert (!OID_ISNULL (class_oid));
4866  assert (!OID_IS_ROOTOID (class_oid));
4867 
4868  HFID_COPY (&real_hfid, hfid);
4869  COPY_OID (&real_class_oid, class_oid);
4870 
4871  local_scan_cache = scan_cache;
4872  local_func_preds = func_preds;
4873 
4874  if (pruning_type != DB_NOT_PARTITIONED_CLASS)
4875  {
4876  OID superclass_oid;
4877  int granted;
4878  /* Perform partition pruning on the given class */
4879  error_code =
4880  partition_prune_insert (thread_p, class_oid, recdes, scan_cache, pcontext, pruning_type, &real_class_oid,
4881  &real_hfid, &superclass_oid);
4882  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4883  {
4884  goto error2;
4885  }
4886  if (!OID_ISNULL (&superclass_oid))
4887  {
4888  granted = lock_subclass (thread_p, &real_class_oid, &superclass_oid, IX_LOCK, LK_UNCOND_LOCK);
4889  if (granted != LK_GRANTED)
4890  {
4891  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
4892  error_code = er_errid ();
4893  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
4894  {
4895  error_code = ER_FAILED;
4896  }
4897  goto error2;
4898  }
4899  if (pcontext != NULL)
4900  {
4901  /* The scan_cache above is started for the partitioned class, not for the actual partition in which we
4902  * will be performing the insert. See if we already have a scan_cache structure created for the target
4903  * partition and use that one instead of the one supplied to this function */
4904  PRUNING_SCAN_CACHE *ins_cache = NULL;
4905  bool has_func_idx = (func_preds != NULL);
4906 
4907  ins_cache =
4908  locator_get_partition_scancache (pcontext, &real_class_oid, &real_hfid, op_type, has_func_idx);
4909  if (ins_cache == NULL)
4910  {
4911  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
4912  error_code = er_errid ();
4913  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
4914  {
4915  error_code = ER_FAILED;
4916  }
4917  goto error2;
4918  }
4919  local_func_preds = ins_cache->func_index_pred;
4920  local_scan_cache = &ins_cache->scan_cache;
4921  }
4922  else
4923  {
4924  /* disable function indexes optimization if we don't have access to a pruning context */
4925  local_func_preds = NULL;
4926  }
4927  }
4928  else
4929  {
4930  /* class_oid was not a partitioned class. This can happen if, for example, this is a request from HA. In this
4931  * which case class_oid already points to the designated partition */
4932  assert_release (OID_EQ (class_oid, &real_class_oid));
4933  }
4934  }
4935 
4936  *force_count = 0;
4937 
4938  /*
4939  * This is a new object. The object must be locked in exclusive mode,
4940  * once its OID is assigned. We just do it for the classes, the new
4941  * instances are not locked since another client cannot get to them,
4942  * in any way. How can a client know their OIDs
4943  */
4944 
4945  /* insert object and lock it */
4946 
4947  assert (!OID_IS_ROOTOID (&real_class_oid));
4948 
4949  /* adjust recdes type (if we got here it should be REC_HOME or REC_BIGONE; REC_BIGONE is detected and handled in
4950  * heap_insert_logical */
4951  recdes->type = REC_HOME;
4952 
4953  /* prepare context */
4954  heap_create_insert_context (&context, &real_hfid, &real_class_oid, recdes, local_scan_cache);
4955  context.update_in_place = force_in_place;
4956 
4957  if (force_in_place == UPDATE_INPLACE_OLD_MVCCID)
4958  {
4959  REPR_ID rep;
4960 
4961  /* insert due to redistribute partition data - set the correct representation id of the new class */
4962 
4963  rep = heap_get_class_repr_id (thread_p, &real_class_oid);
4964  (void) or_replace_rep_id (context.recdes_p, rep);
4965  }
4966 
4967  /* execute insert */
4968  if (heap_insert_logical (thread_p, &context) != NO_ERROR)
4969  {
4970  /*
4971  * Problems inserting the object...Maybe, the transaction should be
4972  * aborted by the caller...Quit..
4973  */
4974  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
4975  error_code = er_errid ();
4976  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
4977  {
4978  error_code = ER_FAILED;
4979  }
4980  goto error2;
4981  }
4982  COPY_OID (oid, &context.res_oid);
4983 
4984 #if 0 /* TODO - dead code; do not delete me */
4985  if (OID_IS_ROOTOID (&real_class_oid))
4986  {
4987  assert (false); /* is impossible */
4988 
4989  /*
4990  * A CLASS: Add the classname to class_OID entry and add the class
4991  * to the catalog.
4992  * Update the classname table.
4993  * Remove XASL cache entries which is relevant with that class.
4994  */
4995 
4996  classname = or_class_name (recdes);
4997  assert (classname != NULL);
4998  assert (strlen (classname) < 255);
4999 
5000  /* Indicate new oid to classname table */
5001  if (locator_permoid_class_name (thread_p, classname, oid) != NO_ERROR)
5002  {
5003  assert (false); /* should be impossible */
5004  goto error1;
5005  }
5006 
5007  if (!OID_IS_ROOTOID (oid))
5008  {
5009  HEAP_OPERATION_CONTEXT update_context;
5010  char *rep_dir_offset;
5011 
5012  or_class_rep_dir (recdes, &rep_dir);
5013  assert (OID_ISNULL (&rep_dir));
5014 
5015  if (catalog_insert (thread_p, recdes, oid, &rep_dir) < 0)
5016  {
5017  /*
5018  * There is an error inserting the hash entry or catalog
5019  * information. Maybe, the transaction should be aborted by
5020  * the caller...Quit
5021  */
5022  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
5023  error_code = er_errid ();
5024  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
5025  {
5026  error_code = ER_FAILED;
5027  }
5028  goto error1;
5029  }
5030 
5031  assert (!OID_ISNULL (&rep_dir));
5032 
5033  /* save oid of the representation directory */
5034  rep_dir_offset =
5035  (char *) recdes->data + OR_FIXED_ATTRIBUTES_OFFSET (recdes->data,
5036  ORC_CLASS_VAR_ATT_COUNT) + ORC_REP_DIR_OFFSET;
5037 
5038  OR_PUT_OID (rep_dir_offset, &rep_dir);
5039 
5040  heap_create_update_context (&update_context, &real_hfid, oid, &real_class_oid, recdes, local_scan_cache);
5041  update_context.force_non_mvcc = true;
5042 
5043  if (heap_update_logical (thread_p, &update_context) != NO_ERROR)
5044  {
5045  /*
5046  * Problems updating the object...Maybe, the transaction should be
5047  * aborted by the caller...Quit..
5048  */
5049  error_code = er_errid ();
5050  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
5051  {
5052  error_code = ER_FAILED;
5053  }
5054  goto error1;
5055  }
5056 
5057  assert (isold_object == true);
5058 
5059 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
5060  or_class_rep_dir (recdes, &rep_dir);
5061  assert (!OID_ISNULL (&rep_dir));
5062 #endif
5063  }
5064 
5065  if (catcls_Enable == true && catcls_insert_catalog_classes (thread_p, recdes) != NO_ERROR)
5066  {
5067  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
5068  error_code = er_errid ();
5069  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
5070  {
5071  error_code = ER_FAILED;
5072  }
5073  goto error1;
5074  }
5075 
5076  /* system class do not include foreign keys, we need not check here. */
5077  }
5078  else
5079  {
5080 #endif
5081  /*
5082  * AN INSTANCE: Apply the necessary index insertions
5083  */
5084  if (has_index
5085  && locator_add_or_remove_index (thread_p, recdes, oid, &real_class_oid, true, op_type, local_scan_cache, true,
5086  true, &real_hfid, local_func_preds) != NO_ERROR)
5087  {
5088  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
5089  error_code = er_errid ();
5090  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
5091  {
5092  error_code = ER_FAILED;
5093  }
5094  goto error1;
5095  }
5096 
5097  /* check the foreign key constraints */
5098  if (has_index && !locator_Dont_check_foreign_key)
5099  {
5100  error_code =
5101  locator_check_foreign_key (thread_p, &real_hfid, &real_class_oid, oid, recdes, &new_recdes, &is_cached,
5102  &cache_attr_copyarea);
5103  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5104  {
5105  goto error1;
5106  }
5107 
5108  if (is_cached)
5109  {
5110  HEAP_OPERATION_CONTEXT update_context;
5111 
5112  recdes = &new_recdes;
5113  /* Cache object has been updated, we need update the value again */
5114  heap_create_update_context (&update_context, &real_hfid, oid, &real_class_oid, recdes, local_scan_cache,
5115  UPDATE_INPLACE_CURRENT_MVCCID);
5116  if (heap_update_logical (thread_p, &update_context) != NO_ERROR)
5117  {
5118  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
5119  error_code = er_errid ();
5120  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
5121  {
5122  error_code = ER_FAILED;
5123  }
5124  goto error1;
5125  }
5126 
5127  assert (update_context.is_logical_old);
5128  isold_object = update_context.is_logical_old;
5129  }
5130  }
5131 
5132 #if defined(ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
5133  /* increase the counter of the catalog */
5134  locator_increase_catalog_count (thread_p, &real_class_oid);
5135 #endif
5136 
5137  /* remove query result cache entries which are relevant with this class */
5138  if (!QFILE_IS_LIST_CACHE_DISABLED)
5139  {
5140  if (qexec_clear_list_cache_by_class (thread_p, &real_class_oid) != NO_ERROR)
5141  {
5142  er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE,
5143  "locator_insert_force: qexec_clear_list_cache_by_class failed for class { %d %d %d }\n",
5144  real_class_oid.pageid, real_class_oid.slotid, real_class_oid.volid);
5145  }
5146  qmgr_add_modified_class (thread_p, &real_class_oid);
5147  }
5148 #if 0 /* TODO - dead code; do not delete me */
5149  }
5150 #endif
5151 
5152  *force_count = 1;
5153 
5154 error1:
5155  /* update the OID of the class with the actual partition in which the object was inserted */
5156  COPY_OID (class_oid, &real_class_oid);
5157  HFID_COPY (hfid, &real_hfid);
5158 
5159 error2:
5160  if (cache_attr_copyarea != NULL)
5161  {
5162  locator_free_copy_area (cache_attr_copyarea);
5163  }
5164 
5165  return error_code;
5166 }

5168 /*
5169  * locator_move_record () - relocate a record from a partitioned class
5170  * return : error code or NO_ERROR
5171  * thread_p (in) : caller thread
5172  * old_hfid (in) : source location of the record
5173  * old_class_oid (in) : class owning the record
5174  * obj_oid (in) : record OID
5175  * new_class_oid (in) : destination class
5176  * new_class_hfid (in) : destination hfid
5177  * recdes (in) : record
5178  * scan_cache (in) : scan cache
5179  * op_type (in) : operation type
5180  * has_index (in) : true if the class has indexes
5181  * force_count (in/out) :
5182  * context(in) : pruning context
5183  * mvcc_reev_data(in) : MVCC reevaluation data
5184  * need_locking(in) : true, if need locking
5185  *
5186  * Note: this function calls locator_delete_force on the current object oid
5187  * and locator_insert_force for the RECDES it receives. The record has already
5188  * been set to be used by the receiving class when it went through the pruning
5189  * algorithm (see function partition_find_partition_for_record)
5190  */
5191 static int
5192 locator_move_record (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, HFID * old_hfid, OID * old_class_oid, OID * obj_oid, OID * new_class_oid,
5193  HFID * new_class_hfid, RECDES * recdes, HEAP_SCANCACHE * scan_cache, int op_type, int has_index,
5194  int *force_count, PRUNING_CONTEXT * context, MVCC_REEV_DATA * mvcc_reev_data, bool need_locking)
5195 {
5196  int error = NO_ERROR;
5197  OID new_obj_oid;
5198 
5199  assert (!OID_IS_ROOTOID (old_class_oid));
5200  assert (!OID_IS_ROOTOID (new_class_oid));
5201 
5202  if (context != NULL)
5203  {
5204  /* setup a PRUNING_SCAN_CACHE object for this class */
5205  HEAP_SCANCACHE *insert_cache = NULL;
5206  PRUNING_SCAN_CACHE *ins_cache = NULL;
5207  ins_cache = locator_get_partition_scancache (context, new_class_oid, new_class_hfid, op_type, false);
5208  if (ins_cache == NULL)
5209  {
5210  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
5211  error = er_errid ();
5212  return (error != NO_ERROR) ? error : ER_FAILED;
5213  }
5214 
5215  insert_cache = &ins_cache->scan_cache;
5216 
5217  error =
5218  locator_insert_force (thread_p, new_class_hfid, new_class_oid, &new_obj_oid, recdes, has_index, op_type,
5219  insert_cache, force_count, context->pruning_type, NULL, NULL, UPDATE_INPLACE_NONE);
5220  }
5221  else
5222  {
5223  HEAP_SCANCACHE insert_cache;
5224 
5225  error =
5226  locator_start_force_scan_cache (thread_p, &insert_cache, new_class_hfid, new_class_oid, SINGLE_ROW_INSERT);
5227  if (error != NO_ERROR)
5228  {
5229  return error;
5230  }
5231 
5232  /* insert the new record */
5233  error =
5234  locator_insert_force (thread_p, new_class_hfid, new_class_oid, &new_obj_oid, recdes, has_index, op_type,
5235  &insert_cache, force_count, DB_NOT_PARTITIONED_CLASS, NULL, NULL, UPDATE_INPLACE_NONE);
5236  heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &insert_cache);
5237  }
5238 
5239  if (error != NO_ERROR)
5240  {
5241  return error;
5242  }
5243 
5244  /* delete this record from the class it currently resides in */
5245  error =
5246  locator_delete_force_for_moving (thread_p, old_hfid, obj_oid, true, op_type, scan_cache, force_count,
5247  mvcc_reev_data, &new_obj_oid, new_class_oid, need_locking);
5248  if (error != NO_ERROR)
5249  {
5250  return error;
5251  }
5252 
5253  COPY_OID (obj_oid, &new_obj_oid);
5254 
5255  return NO_ERROR;
5256 }
5257 
5258 /*
5259  * locator_update_force () - Update the given object
5260  *
5261  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
5262  *
5263  * hfid(in): Heap where the object is going to be inserted
5264  * class_oid(in):
5265  * oid(in): The object identifier
5266  * oldrecdes(in):
5267  * recdes(in): The object in disk format
5268  * has_index(in): false if we now for sure that there is not any index
5269  * on the instances of the class.
5270  * att_id(in): Updated attr id array
5271  * n_att_id(in): Updated attr id array length
5272  * op_type(in):
5273  * scan_cache(in/out): Scan cache used to estimate the best space pages
5274  * between heap changes.
5275  * force_count(in):
5276  * not_check_fk(in):
5277  * repl_inf(in): replication info
5278  * pruning_type(in): pruning type
5279  * pcontext(in): pruning context
5280  * mvcc_reev_data(in): MVCC reevaluation data
5281  * force_in_place(in): if UPDATE_INPLACE_NONE then the 'in place' will not be forced
5282  * and the update style will be decided in this function.
5283  * Otherwise the update of the instance will be made in
5284  * place and according to provided style.
5285  *
5286  * Note: The given object is updated on this heap and all appropriate
5287  * index entries are updated.
5288  */
5289 static int
5290 locator_update_force (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, HFID * hfid, OID * class_oid, OID * oid, RECDES * oldrecdes,
5291  RECDES * recdes, int has_index, ATTR_ID * att_id, int n_att_id, int op_type,
5292  HEAP_SCANCACHE * scan_cache, int *force_count, bool not_check_fk, REPL_INFO_TYPE repl_info_type,
5293  int pruning_type, PRUNING_CONTEXT * pcontext, MVCC_REEV_DATA * mvcc_reev_data,
5294  UPDATE_INPLACE_STYLE force_in_place, bool need_locking)
5295 {
5296  OID rep_dir = { NULL_PAGEID, NULL_SLOTID, NULL_VOLID };
5297  char *rep_dir_offset;
5298  char *classname = NULL; /* Classname to update */
5299  char *old_classname = NULL; /* Classname that may have been renamed */
5300 
5301  bool isold_object; /* Make sure that this is an old object */
5302  RECDES copy_recdes;
5303  SCAN_CODE scan = S_SUCCESS;
5304 
5305  RECDES new_record;
5306  bool is_cached = false;
5307  LC_COPYAREA *cache_attr_copyarea = NULL;
5308  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
5309  HEAP_SCANCACHE *local_scan_cache;
5310  bool no_data_new_address = false;
5311  REPL_INFO repl_info;
5312 
5313  assert (class_oid != NULL && !OID_ISNULL (class_oid));
5314 
5315  /*
5316  * While scanning objects, the given scancache does not fix the last
5317  * accessed page. So, the object must be copied to the record descriptor.
5318  */
5319  copy_recdes.data = NULL;
5320 
5321  *force_count = 0;
5322 
5323  repl_info.repl_info_type = repl_info_type;
5324  repl_info.need_replication = true;
5325  repl_info.info = NULL;
5326 
5327  if (OID_IS_ROOTOID (class_oid))
5328  {
5329  HEAP_OPERATION_CONTEXT update_context;
5330 
5331  /*
5332  * A CLASS: classes do not have any indices...however, the classname
5333  * to oid table may need to be updated
5334  */
5335  classname = or_class_name (recdes);
5336  assert (classname != NULL);
5337  assert (strlen (classname) < 255);
5338 
5339  if (heap_get_class_name_alloc_if_diff (thread_p, oid, classname, &old_classname) != NO_ERROR)
5340  {
5341  /* it is unexpected to fail to get the classname of an existing class */
5342  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
5343  goto error;
5344  }
5345 
5346  /*
5347  * Compare the classname pointers. If the same pointers classes are the
5348  * same since the class was no malloc
5349  */
5350  if (old_classname != NULL && old_classname != classname)
5351  {
5352  assert (old_classname != NULL);
5353  assert (strlen (old_classname) < 255);
5354 
5355  /* Different names, the class was renamed. */
5356  error_code = log_add_to_modified_class_list (thread_p, old_classname, oid);
5357  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5358  {
5359  goto error;
5360  }
5361  }
5362 
5363  if ((catcls_Enable == true) && (old_classname != NULL))
5364  {
5365  error_code = catcls_update_catalog_classes (thread_p, old_classname, recdes, oid, force_in_place);
5366  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5367  {
5368  goto error;
5369  }
5370  }
5371 
5372  /* TODO - defence code to save oid of the representation directory */
5373  if (!OID_IS_ROOTOID (oid))
5374  {
5375  or_class_rep_dir (recdes, &rep_dir);
5376 
5377  if (OID_ISNULL (&rep_dir))
5378  {
5379  OID old_rep_dir = { NULL_PAGEID, NULL_SLOTID, NULL_VOLID };
5380  RECDES old_record, *old_recdes;
5381 
5382  old_record.data = NULL;
5383  old_recdes = &old_record;
5384 
5385  if (heap_get_class_record (thread_p, oid, old_recdes, scan_cache, PEEK) == S_SUCCESS)
5386  {
5387  or_class_rep_dir (old_recdes, &old_rep_dir);
5388 
5389  /* save current oid of the representation directory */
5390  if (!OID_ISNULL (&old_rep_dir))
5391  {
5392  assert (false); /* should avoid */
5393 
5394  rep_dir_offset =
5395  (char *) recdes->data + OR_FIXED_ATTRIBUTES_OFFSET (recdes->data, ORC_CLASS_VAR_ATT_COUNT)
5396  + ORC_REP_DIR_OFFSET;
5397 
5398  OR_PUT_OID (rep_dir_offset, &old_rep_dir);
5399  }
5400  }
5401  else
5402  {
5403  /* ignore if the class hasn't been flushed yet */
5404  if (er_errid () == ER_HEAP_NODATA_NEWADDRESS)
5405  {
5406  er_clear (); /* clear ER_HEAP_NODATA_NEWADDRESS */
5407  }
5408  }
5409  }
5410  }
5411 
5412  heap_create_update_context (&update_context, hfid, oid, class_oid, recdes, scan_cache,
5413  UPDATE_INPLACE_CURRENT_MVCCID);
5414  error_code = heap_update_logical (thread_p, &update_context);
5415  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5416  {
5417  /*
5418  * Problems updating the object...Maybe, the transaction should be
5419  * aborted by the caller...Quit..
5420  */
5421  if (error_code == ER_FAILED)
5422  {
5423  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
5424  /* FIXME: better to make functions to return ER_INTERRUPTED rather than ER_FAILED for the case */
5425  assert (error_code == ER_INTERRUPTED);
5426  }
5427  else
5428  {
5429  ASSERT_ERROR ();
5430  }
5431 
5432  goto error;
5433  }
5434  isold_object = update_context.is_logical_old;
5435 
5436  if (update_context.is_logical_old)
5437  {
5438  /* Update the catalog as long as it is not the root class */
5439  if (!OID_IS_ROOTOID (oid))
5440  {
5441 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
5442  or_class_rep_dir (recdes, &rep_dir);
5443  assert (!OID_ISNULL (&rep_dir));
5444 #endif
5445  error_code = catalog_update (thread_p, recdes, oid);
5446  if (error_code < 0)
5447  {
5448  /*
5449  * An error occurred during the update of the catalog
5450  */
5451  goto error;
5452  }
5453  }
5454  }
5455  else
5456  {
5457  /*
5458  * NEW CLASS
5459  */
5460  if (!OID_IS_ROOTOID (oid))
5461  {
5462  HEAP_OPERATION_CONTEXT update_context;
5463  or_class_rep_dir (recdes, &rep_dir);
5464  assert (OID_ISNULL (&rep_dir));
5465 
5466  if (catalog_insert (thread_p, recdes, oid, &rep_dir) < 0)
5467  {
5468  /*
5469  * There is an error inserting the hash entry or catalog
5470  * information. The transaction must be aborted by the caller
5471  */
5472  error_code = ER_FAILED;
5473  goto error;
5474  }
5475 
5476  assert (!OID_ISNULL (&rep_dir));
5477 
5478  /* save oid of the representation directory */
5479  rep_dir_offset =
5480  (char *) recdes->data + OR_FIXED_ATTRIBUTES_OFFSET (recdes->data, ORC_CLASS_VAR_ATT_COUNT)
5481  + ORC_REP_DIR_OFFSET;
5482 
5483  OR_PUT_OID (rep_dir_offset, &rep_dir);
5484 
5485  heap_create_update_context (&update_context, hfid, oid, class_oid, recdes, scan_cache,
5486  UPDATE_INPLACE_CURRENT_MVCCID);
5487  error_code = heap_update_logical (thread_p, &update_context);
5488  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5489  {
5490  /*
5491  * Problems updating the object...Maybe, the transaction should be
5492  * aborted by the caller...Quit..
5493  */
5494  if (error_code == ER_FAILED)
5495  {
5496  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
5497  }
5498  else
5499  {
5500  ASSERT_ERROR ();
5501  }
5502  goto error;
5503  }
5504  isold_object = update_context.is_logical_old;
5505 
5506 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
5507  or_class_rep_dir (recdes, &rep_dir);
5508  assert (!OID_ISNULL (&rep_dir));
5509 #endif
5510  }
5511 
5512  if (catcls_Enable == true)
5513  {
5514  error_code = catcls_insert_catalog_classes (thread_p, recdes);
5515  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5516  {
5517  goto error;
5518  }
5519  }
5520  }
5521 
5522  /* system class do not include foreign keys. we need not check here. */
5523 
5524  /* remove XASL cache entries which is relevant with that class */
5525  if (!OID_IS_ROOTOID (oid))
5526  {
5527  xcache_remove_by_oid (thread_p, oid);
5528  }
5529 
5530  if (!OID_IS_ROOTOID (oid))
5531  {
5532  fpcache_remove_by_class (thread_p, oid);
5533  }
5534  }
5535  else
5536  {
5537  HEAP_OPERATION_CONTEXT update_context;
5538 
5539  local_scan_cache = scan_cache;
5540  if (pruning_type != DB_NOT_PARTITIONED_CLASS && pcontext != NULL)
5541  {
5542  /* Get a scan_cache object for the actual class which is updated. This object is kept in a list in the
5543  * pruning context */
5544  OID real_class_oid;
5545  HFID real_hfid;
5546  PRUNING_SCAN_CACHE *pcache;
5547 
5548  HFID_COPY (&real_hfid, hfid);
5549  COPY_OID (&real_class_oid, class_oid);
5550  pcache = locator_get_partition_scancache (pcontext, &real_class_oid, &real_hfid, op_type, false);
5551  if (pcache == NULL)
5552  {
5553  return ER_FAILED;
5554  }
5555  local_scan_cache = &pcache->scan_cache;
5556  }
5557 
5558  /* There will be no pruning after this point so we should reset op_type to a non pruning operation */
5559 
5560  if (!mvcc_is_mvcc_disabled_class (class_oid))
5561  {
5562  if (oldrecdes == NULL)
5563  {
5564  copy_recdes.data = NULL;
5565  if (mvcc_reev_data != NULL && mvcc_reev_data->type == REEV_DATA_UPDDEL)
5566  {
5567  /* The new recdes can be changed during reevaluation. That's because new recdes fields may refer
5568  * fields of old recdes */
5569  mvcc_reev_data->upddel_reev_data->new_recdes = recdes;
5570  }
5571 
5572  if (need_locking)
5573  {
5574  scan = locator_lock_and_get_object_with_evaluation (thread_p, oid, class_oid, &copy_recdes,
5575  local_scan_cache, COPY, NULL_CHN, mvcc_reev_data,
5576  LOG_ERROR_IF_DELETED);
5577  }
5578  else
5579  {
5580  scan = heap_get_visible_version (thread_p, oid, class_oid, &copy_recdes, local_scan_cache, COPY,
5581  NULL_CHN);
5582  }
5583 
5584 
5585  if (scan == S_SUCCESS && mvcc_reev_data != NULL && mvcc_reev_data->filter_result == V_FALSE)
5586  {
5587  return ER_MVCC_NOT_SATISFIED_REEVALUATION;
5588  }
5589  else if (scan != S_SUCCESS)
5590  {
5591  if (er_errid () == ER_HEAP_NODATA_NEWADDRESS)
5592  {
5593  force_in_place = UPDATE_INPLACE_CURRENT_MVCCID;
5594 
5595  /* The object is a new instance, that is only the address (no content) is known by the heap
5596  * manager. This is a normal behavior and, if we have an index, we need to add the object to the
5597  * index later. Because the following processing can remove this error, we save it here in
5598  * no_data_new_address */
5599  no_data_new_address = true;
5600  er_clear (); /* clear ER_HEAP_NODATA_NEWADDRESS */
5601  }
5602  else
5603  {
5604  if ((scan == S_DOESNT_EXIST || scan == S_SNAPSHOT_NOT_SATISFIED)
5605  && er_errid () != ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT)
5606  {
5607  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT, oid->volid, oid->pageid,
5608  oid->slotid);
5609  }
5610  error_code = er_errid ();
5611  if (error_code == ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT)
5612  {
5613  er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE, "locator_update_force: unknown oid ( %d|%d|%d )\n",
5614  oid->pageid, oid->slotid, oid->volid);
5615  }
5616  else if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
5617  {
5618  error_code = ER_FAILED;
5619  }
5620 
5621  goto error;
5622  }
5623  }
5624  else
5625  {
5626  oldrecdes = &copy_recdes;
5627  }
5628  }
5629 
5630  if (!HEAP_IS_UPDATE_INPLACE (force_in_place))
5631  {
5632  LOG_TDES *tdes;
5633 
5634  tdes = LOG_FIND_CURRENT_TDES (thread_p);
5635  if (!(has_index & LC_FLAG_HAS_UNIQUE_INDEX))
5636  {
5637  MVCC_REC_HEADER old_rec_header;
5638 
5639  or_mvcc_get_header (oldrecdes, &old_rec_header);
5640  if (logtb_find_current_mvccid (thread_p) != old_rec_header.mvcc_ins_id)
5641  {
5642 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
5643  /* If not inserted by me, I must have lock. */
5644  assert (lock_has_lock_on_object (oid, class_oid, logtb_get_current_tran_index (), X_LOCK) > 0);
5645 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
5646  }
5647  }
5648  }
5649  else if (force_in_place == UPDATE_INPLACE_OLD_MVCCID)
5650  {
5651  MVCC_REC_HEADER old_rec_header, new_rec_header;
5652 
5653  if (or_mvcc_get_header (oldrecdes, &old_rec_header) != NO_ERROR
5654  || or_mvcc_get_header (recdes, &new_rec_header) != NO_ERROR)
5655  {
5656  goto error;
5657  }
5658 
5659  if (MVCC_IS_FLAG_SET (&old_rec_header, OR_MVCC_FLAG_VALID_INSID))
5660  {
5661  MVCC_SET_FLAG_BITS (&new_rec_header, OR_MVCC_FLAG_VALID_INSID);
5662  MVCC_SET_INSID (&new_rec_header, MVCC_GET_INSID (&old_rec_header));
5663  }
5664  else
5665  {
5666  MVCC_CLEAR_FLAG_BITS (&new_rec_header, OR_MVCC_FLAG_VALID_INSID);
5667  }
5668 
5669  if (MVCC_IS_HEADER_DELID_VALID (&old_rec_header))
5670  {
5671  MVCC_SET_FLAG_BITS (&new_rec_header, OR_MVCC_FLAG_VALID_DELID);
5672  MVCC_SET_DELID (&new_rec_header, MVCC_GET_DELID (&old_rec_header));
5673  }
5674  else
5675  {
5676  MVCC_CLEAR_FLAG_BITS (&new_rec_header, OR_MVCC_FLAG_VALID_DELID);
5677  }
5678 
5679  if (MVCC_IS_FLAG_SET (&old_rec_header, OR_MVCC_FLAG_VALID_PREV_VERSION))
5680  {
5681  MVCC_SET_FLAG_BITS (&new_rec_header, OR_MVCC_FLAG_VALID_PREV_VERSION);
5682  MVCC_SET_PREVIOUS_VERSION_LSA (&new_rec_header, &MVCC_GET_PREV_VERSION_LSA (&old_rec_header));
5683  }
5684  else
5685  {
5686  MVCC_CLEAR_FLAG_BITS (&new_rec_header, OR_MVCC_FLAG_VALID_PREV_VERSION);
5687  }
5688 
5689  if (or_mvcc_set_header (recdes, &new_rec_header) != NO_ERROR)
5690  {
5691  goto error;
5692  }
5693  }
5694  }
5695  else
5696  {
5697  if (!HEAP_IS_UPDATE_INPLACE (force_in_place))
5698  {
5699  force_in_place = UPDATE_INPLACE_CURRENT_MVCCID;
5700  }
5701 
5702  if (lock_object (thread_p, oid, class_oid, X_LOCK, LK_UNCOND_LOCK) != LK_GRANTED)
5703  {
5704  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
5705  goto error;
5706  }
5707 
5708  if (has_index && oldrecdes == NULL)
5709  {
5710  /* get the old record first */
5711  local_scan_cache->mvcc_snapshot = logtb_get_mvcc_snapshot (thread_p);
5712  if (local_scan_cache->mvcc_snapshot == NULL)
5713  {
5714  error_code = er_errid ();
5715  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
5716  {
5717  error_code = ER_FAILED;
5718  }
5719  goto error;
5720  }
5721 
5722  scan =
5723  heap_get_visible_version (thread_p, oid, class_oid, &copy_recdes, local_scan_cache, COPY, NULL_CHN);
5724  if (scan == S_SUCCESS)
5725  {
5726  oldrecdes = &copy_recdes;
5727  }
5728  else if (er_errid () == ER_HEAP_NODATA_NEWADDRESS)
5729  {
5730  er_clear (); /* clear ER_HEAP_NODATA_NEWADDRESS */
5731 
5732  /* The object is a new instance, that is only the address (no content) is known by the heap manager.
5733  * This is a normal behaviour and, if we have an index, we need to add the object to the index later.
5734  * Because the following processing can remove this error, we save it here in no_data_new_address */
5735  no_data_new_address = true;
5736  }
5737  else
5738  {
5739  if (er_errid () == ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT)
5740  {
5741  er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE, "locator_update_force: unknown oid ( %d|%d|%d )\n", oid->pageid,
5742  oid->slotid, oid->volid);
5743  }
5744 
5745  error_code = ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT;
5746  goto error;
5747  }
5748  }
5749  }
5750 
5751  if (pruning_type != DB_NOT_PARTITIONED_CLASS)
5752  {
5753  OID superclass_oid;
5754  OID real_class_oid;
5755  HFID real_hfid;
5756  int granted;
5757 
5758  HFID_COPY (&real_hfid, hfid);
5759  COPY_OID (&real_class_oid, class_oid);
5760  error_code =
5761  partition_prune_update (thread_p, class_oid, recdes, pcontext, pruning_type, &real_class_oid, &real_hfid,
5762  &superclass_oid);
5763  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5764  {
5765  goto error;
5766  }
5767 
5768  /* make sure we use the correct class oid - we could be dealing with a classoid resulted from a unique btid
5769  * pruning */
5770  if (heap_get_class_oid (thread_p, oid, class_oid) != S_SUCCESS)
5771  {
5772  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
5773  goto error;
5774  }
5775 
5776  if (heap_get_hfid_from_class_oid (thread_p, class_oid, hfid) != NO_ERROR)
5777  {
5778  goto error;
5779  }
5780 
5781  if (!OID_EQ (class_oid, &real_class_oid))
5782  {
5783  /* If we have to move the record to another partition, we have to lock the target partition for insert.
5784  * The class from which we delete was already locked (X_LOCK for heap scan or IX_LOCK for index scan)
5785  * during the SELECT phase of UPDATE */
5786  granted = lock_subclass (thread_p, &real_class_oid, &superclass_oid, IX_LOCK, LK_UNCOND_LOCK);
5787  if (granted != LK_GRANTED)
5788  {
5789  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
5790  error_code = er_errid ();
5791  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
5792  {
5793  error_code = ER_FAILED;
5794  }
5795  goto error;
5796  }
5797 
5798  error_code =
5799  locator_move_record (thread_p, hfid, class_oid, oid, &real_class_oid, &real_hfid, recdes, scan_cache,
5800  op_type, has_index, force_count, pcontext, mvcc_reev_data, need_locking);
5801  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
5802  {
5803  COPY_OID (class_oid, &real_class_oid);
5804  HFID_COPY (hfid, &real_hfid);
5805  }
5806  return error_code;
5807  }
5808  }
5809 
5810  /* AN INSTANCE: Update indices if any */
5811  if (has_index)
5812  {
5813  if (scan == S_SUCCESS)
5814  {
5815  error_code =
5816  locator_update_index (thread_p, recdes, oldrecdes, att_id, n_att_id, oid, class_oid, op_type,
5817  local_scan_cache, &repl_info);
5818  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5819  {
5820  /*
5821  * There is an error updating the index... Quit... The
5822  * transaction must be aborted by the caller
5823  */
5824  goto error;
5825  }
5826  }
5827  else
5828  {
5829  /*
5830  * We could not get the object.
5831  * The object may be a new instance, that is only the address
5832  * (no content) is known by the heap manager.
5833  */
5834 
5835  if (no_data_new_address)
5836  {
5837  er_clear (); /* clear the error code */
5838  if (op_type == SINGLE_ROW_MODIFY)
5839  { /* to enable uniqueness checking */
5840  op_type = SINGLE_ROW_INSERT;
5841  }
5842 
5843  error_code =
5844  locator_add_or_remove_index (thread_p, recdes, oid, class_oid, true, op_type, local_scan_cache,
5845  true, true, hfid, NULL);
5846  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5847  {
5848  goto error;
5849  }
5850  }
5851  }
5852 
5853  /* check the foreign key constraints */
5854  if (!not_check_fk && !locator_Dont_check_foreign_key)
5855  {
5856  error_code =
5857  locator_check_foreign_key (thread_p, hfid, class_oid, oid, recdes, &new_record, &is_cached,
5858  &cache_attr_copyarea);
5859  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5860  {
5861  goto error;
5862  }
5863 
5864  if (is_cached)
5865  {
5866  recdes = &new_record;
5867  }
5868  }
5869  }
5870 
5871  heap_create_update_context (&update_context, hfid, oid, class_oid, recdes, local_scan_cache, force_in_place);
5872  error_code = heap_update_logical (thread_p, &update_context);
5873  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5874  {
5875  /*
5876  * Problems updating the object...Maybe, the transaction should be aborted by the caller...Quit..
5877  */
5878  if (error_code == ER_FAILED)
5879  {
5880  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
5881  assert (error_code == ER_INTERRUPTED);
5882  }
5883  else
5884  {
5885  ASSERT_ERROR ();
5886  }
5887  goto error;
5888  }
5889  isold_object = update_context.is_logical_old;
5890 
5891  /*
5892  * for replication,
5893  * We have to set UPDATE LSA number to the log info.
5894  * The target log info was already created when the locator_update_index
5895  */
5896  if (!LOG_CHECK_LOG_APPLIER (thread_p) && log_does_allow_replication () == true
5897  && repl_info.need_replication == true)
5898  {
5899  repl_add_update_lsa (thread_p, oid);
5900  }
5901 
5902 #if defined(ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
5903  if (isold_object == false)
5904  {
5905  locator_increase_catalog_count (thread_p, class_oid);
5906  }
5907 #endif
5908 
5909  /* remove query result cache entries which are relevant with this class */
5910  if (!QFILE_IS_LIST_CACHE_DISABLED)
5911  {
5912  if (qexec_clear_list_cache_by_class (thread_p, class_oid) != NO_ERROR)
5913  {
5914  er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE,
5915  "locator_update_force: qexec_clear_list_cache_by_class failed for class { %d %d %d }\n",
5916  class_oid->pageid, class_oid->slotid, class_oid->volid);
5917  }
5918  qmgr_add_modified_class (thread_p, class_oid);
5919  }
5920  }
5921 
5922  *force_count = 1;
5923 
5924 error:
5925 
5926  if (old_classname != NULL && old_classname != classname)
5927  {
5928  free_and_init (old_classname);
5929  }
5930 
5931  if (cache_attr_copyarea != NULL)
5932  {
5933  locator_free_copy_area (cache_attr_copyarea);
5934  }
5935 
5936  return error_code;
5937 }
5938 
5939 /*
5940  * locator_delete_force () - Delete the given object
5941  *
5942  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
5943  *
5944  * hfid(in): Heap where the object is going to be inserted
5945  * oid(in): The object identifier
5946  * has_index(in): false if we now for sure that there is not any index on the instances of the class.
5947  * op_type(in):
5948  * scan_cache(in/out): Scan cache used to estimate the best space pages between heap changes.
5949  * force_count(in):
5950  * mvcc_reev_data(in): MVCC data
5951  * need_locking(in): true, if need locking
5952  *
5953  * Note: The given object is deleted on this heap and all appropiate index entries are deleted.
5954  */
5955 int
5956 locator_delete_force (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, HFID * hfid, OID * oid, int has_index, int op_type,
5957  HEAP_SCANCACHE * scan_cache, int *force_count, MVCC_REEV_DATA * mvcc_reev_data, bool need_locking)
5958 {
5959  return locator_delete_force_internal (thread_p, hfid, oid, has_index, op_type, scan_cache, force_count,
5960  mvcc_reev_data, FOR_INSERT_OR_DELETE, NULL, NULL, need_locking);
5961 }
5962 
5963 /*
5964  * locator_delete_force_for_moving () - Delete the given object
5965  * To move record between partitions.
5966  *
5967  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
5968  *
5969  * thread_p(in):
5970  * hfid(in): Heap where the object is going to be inserted
5971  * oid(in): The object identifier
5972  * has_index(in): false if we now for sure that there is not any index on the instances of the class.
5973  * op_type(in):
5974  * scan_cache(in/out): Scan cache used to estimate the best space pages between heap changes.
5975  * force_count(in):
5976  * mvcc_reev_data(in): MVCC data
5977  * new_obj_oid(in): next version - only to be used with records relocated in other partitions, in MVCC.
5978  * partition_oid(in): new partition class oid
5979  * need_locking(in): true, if need locking
5980  *
5981  * Note: The given object is deleted on this heap and all appropriate index entries are deleted.
5982  */
5983 static int
5984 locator_delete_force_for_moving (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, HFID * hfid, OID * oid, int has_index, int op_type,
5985  HEAP_SCANCACHE * scan_cache, int *force_count, MVCC_REEV_DATA * mvcc_reev_data,
5986  OID * new_obj_oid, OID * partition_oid, bool need_locking)
5987 {
5988  return locator_delete_force_internal (thread_p, hfid, oid, has_index, op_type, scan_cache, force_count,
5989  mvcc_reev_data, FOR_MOVE, new_obj_oid, partition_oid, need_locking);
5990 }
5991 
5992 /*
5993  * locator_delete_force_internal () - helper function of locator_delete_force
5994  *
5995  * hfid(in): Heap where the object is going to be inserted
5996  * oid(in): The object identifier
5997  * has_index(in): false if we now for sure that there is not any index on the instances of the class.
5998  * op_type(in):
5999  * scan_cache(in/out): Scan cache used to estimate the best space pages between heap changes.
6000  * force_count(in):
6001  * mvcc_reev_data(in): MVCC data
6002  * idx_action_flag(in): is moving record between partitioned table?
6003  * If FOR_MOVE, this delete&insert is caused by
6004  * 'UPDATE ... SET ...', NOT 'DELETE FROM ...'
6005  * new_obj_oid(in): next version - only to be used with records relocated in other partitions, in MVCC.
6006  * partition_oid(in): new partition class oid
6007  * need_locking(in): true, if need locking
6008  *
6009  * Note: The given object is deleted on this heap and all appropriate index entries are deleted.
6010  */
6011 static int
6012 locator_delete_force_internal (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, HFID * hfid, OID * oid, int has_index, int op_type,
6013  HEAP_SCANCACHE * scan_cache, int *force_count, MVCC_REEV_DATA * mvcc_reev_data,
6014  LOCATOR_INDEX_ACTION_FLAG idx_action_flag, OID * new_obj_oid, OID * partition_oid,
6015  bool need_locking)
6016 {
6017  bool isold_object; /* Make sure that this is an old object during the deletion */
6018  OID class_oid = { NULL_PAGEID, NULL_SLOTID, NULL_VOLID };
6019  /* Class identifier */
6020  char *classname; /* Classname to update */
6021  RECDES copy_recdes;
6022  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
6023  bool deleted = false;
6024  SCAN_CODE scan_code = S_SUCCESS;
6025 
6026  /* Update note : While scanning objects, the given scancache does not fix the last accessed page. So, the object must
6027  * be copied to the record descriptor. Changes : (1) variable name : peek_recdes => copy_recdes (2) function call :
6028  * heap_get_visible_version(..., PEEK, ...) => heap_get_visible_version(..., COPY, ...) (3) SCAN_CODE scan, char *new_area are added */
6029 
6030  copy_recdes.data = NULL;
6031 
6032  *force_count = 0;
6033 
6034  /*
6035  * Is the object a class ?
6036  */
6037  isold_object = true;
6038 
6039  copy_recdes.data = NULL;
6040 
6041  if (need_locking == false)
6042  {
6043  /* the reevaluation is not necessary if the object is already locked */
6044  mvcc_reev_data = NULL;
6045  }
6046 
6047  /* IMPORTANT TODO: use a different get function when need_locking==false, but make sure it gets the last version,
6048  not the visible one; we need only the last version to use it to retrieve the last version of the btree key */
6049  scan_code =
6050  locator_lock_and_get_object_with_evaluation (thread_p, oid, &class_oid, &copy_recdes, scan_cache, COPY, NULL_CHN,
6051  mvcc_reev_data, LOG_WARNING_IF_DELETED);
6052 
6053  if (scan_code == S_SUCCESS && mvcc_reev_data != NULL && mvcc_reev_data->filter_result == V_FALSE)
6054  {
6055  return ER_MVCC_NOT_SATISFIED_REEVALUATION;
6056  }
6057 
6058  if (scan_code != S_SUCCESS)
6059  {
6060  error_code = er_errid ();
6061 
6062  if (error_code == ER_HEAP_NODATA_NEWADDRESS)
6063  {
6064  isold_object = false;
6065  er_clear (); /* clear ER_HEAP_NODATA_NEWADDRESS */
6066 
6067  error_code = NO_ERROR;
6068  }
6069  else if (error_code == ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT || scan_code == S_DOESNT_EXIST)
6070  {
6071  isold_object = false;
6072  er_clear ();
6073 
6074  error_code = NO_ERROR;
6075  goto error;
6076  }
6077  else
6078  {
6079  /*
6080  * Problems reading the object...Maybe, the transaction should be
6081  * aborted by the caller...Quit..
6082  */
6083  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
6084  {
6085  error_code = ER_FAILED;
6086  }
6087  goto error;
6088  }
6089  }
6090 
6091  if (isold_object == false)
6092  {
6093  OID_SET_NULL (&class_oid);
6094  }
6095 
6096  if (isold_object == true && OID_IS_ROOTOID (&class_oid))
6097  {
6098  /*
6099  * A CLASS: Remove class from catalog and
6100  * remove any indices on that class
6101  * remove XASL cache entries which is relevant with that class
6102  */
6103 
6104  /* Delete the classname entry */
6105  classname = or_class_name (&copy_recdes);
6106  assert (classname != NULL);
6107  assert (strlen (classname) < 255);
6108 
6109  /* Note: by now, the client has probably already requested this class be deleted. We try again here just to be
6110  * sure it has been marked properly. Note that we would normally want to check the return code, but we must not
6111  * check the return code for this one function in its current form, because we cannot distinguish between a class
6112  * that has already been marked deleted and a real error. */
6113  (void) xlocator_delete_class_name (thread_p, classname);
6114  /* remove from the catalog... when is not the root */
6115  if (!OID_IS_ROOTOID (oid))
6116  {
6117  error_code = catalog_delete (thread_p, oid);
6118  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6119  {
6120  er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE, "locator_delete_force: ct_delete_catalog failed for tran %d\n",
6121  LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p));
6122  goto error;
6123  }
6124  }
6125  if (catcls_Enable)
6126  {
6127  error_code = catcls_delete_catalog_classes (thread_p, classname, oid);
6128  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6129  {
6130  goto error;
6131  }
6132  }
6133 
6134  /* remove XASL cache entries which is relevant with that class */
6135  if (!OID_IS_ROOTOID (oid))
6136  {
6137  xcache_remove_by_oid (thread_p, oid);
6138  }
6139 
6140  if (!OID_IS_ROOTOID (oid))
6141  {
6142  fpcache_remove_by_class (thread_p, oid);
6143  }
6144  }
6145  else
6146  {
6147  /*
6148  * Likely an INSTANCE: Apply the necessary index deletions
6149  *
6150  * If this is a server delete on an instance, the object must be locked
6151  * in exclusive mode since it is likely that we have just added an
6152  * SIX lock on the class at this moment.
6153  *
6154  * Note that we cannot have server deletes on classes.
6155  */
6156  if (isold_object == true && has_index)
6157  {
6158  /* if MVCC then delete before updating index */
6159  if (!mvcc_is_mvcc_disabled_class (&class_oid))
6160  {
6161  HEAP_OPERATION_CONTEXT delete_context;
6162 
6163  /* build operation context */
6164  heap_create_delete_context (&delete_context, hfid, oid, &class_oid, scan_cache);
6165 
6166  /* attempt delete */
6167  if (heap_delete_logical (thread_p, &delete_context) != NO_ERROR)
6168  {
6169  /*
6170  * Problems deleting the object...Maybe, the transaction should be
6171  * aborted by the caller...Quit..
6172  */
6173  error_code = er_errid ();
6174  er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE, "locator_delete_force: hf_delete failed for tran %d\n",
6175  LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p));
6176  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
6177  {
6178  error_code = ER_FAILED;
6179  }
6180  goto error;
6181  }
6182 
6183  deleted = true;
6184  }
6185 
6186  if (idx_action_flag == FOR_INSERT_OR_DELETE)
6187  {
6188  error_code =
6189  locator_add_or_remove_index (thread_p, &copy_recdes, oid, &class_oid, false, op_type, scan_cache, true,
6190  true, hfid, NULL);
6191  }
6192  else
6193  {
6194  error_code =
6195  locator_add_or_remove_index_for_moving (thread_p, &copy_recdes, oid, &class_oid, false, op_type,
6196  scan_cache, true, true, hfid, NULL);
6197  }
6198 
6199  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6200  {
6201  /*
6202  * There is an error deleting the index... Quit... The
6203  * transaction must be aborted by the caller
6204  */
6205  goto error;
6206  }
6207  }
6208 
6209  /* remove query result cache entries which are relevant with this class */
6210  if (!QFILE_IS_LIST_CACHE_DISABLED)
6211  {
6212  if (qexec_clear_list_cache_by_class (thread_p, &class_oid) != NO_ERROR)
6213  {
6214  er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE,
6215  "locator_delete_force: qexec_clear_list_cache_by_class failed for class { %d %d %d }\n",
6216  class_oid.pageid, class_oid.slotid, class_oid.volid);
6217  }
6218  qmgr_add_modified_class (thread_p, &class_oid);
6219  }
6220  }
6221 
6222  if (!deleted)
6223  {
6224  HEAP_OPERATION_CONTEXT delete_context;
6225 
6226  /* build operation context */
6227  heap_create_delete_context (&delete_context, hfid, oid, &class_oid, scan_cache);
6228 
6229  /* attempt delete */
6230  if (heap_delete_logical (thread_p, &delete_context) != NO_ERROR)
6231  {
6232  /*
6233  * Problems deleting the object...Maybe, the transaction should be
6234  * aborted by the caller...Quit..
6235  */
6236  er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE, "locator_delete_force: hf_delete failed for tran %d\n",
6237  LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p));
6238  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
6239  error_code = er_errid ();
6240  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
6241  {
6242  error_code = ER_FAILED;
6243  }
6244  goto error;
6245  }
6246  deleted = true;
6247  }
6248  *force_count = 1;
6249 
6250 #if defined(ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
6251  if (isold_object == true && !OID_IS_ROOTOID (&class_oid))
6252  {
6253  /* decrease the counter of the catalog */
6254  locator_decrease_catalog_count (thread_p, &class_oid);
6255  }
6256 #endif
6257 
6258 error:
6259 
6260  return error_code;
6261 }
6262 
6263 /*
6264  * locator_delete_lob_force () - Delete all blob which is in the given object
6265  *
6266  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
6267  *
6268  * thread_p(in):
6269  * class_oid(in):
6270  * oid(in):
6271  * recdes(in):
6272  */
6273 int
6274 locator_delete_lob_force (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OID * class_oid, OID * oid, RECDES * recdes)
6275 {
6276  HEAP_CACHE_ATTRINFO attr_info;
6277  HEAP_ATTRVALUE *value;
6278  bool attr_info_inited;
6279  HEAP_SCANCACHE scan_cache;
6280  RECDES copy_recdes;
6281  bool scan_cache_inited;
6282  bool found;
6283  int i;
6284  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
6285 
6286  assert ((class_oid != NULL) && (recdes != NULL || oid != NULL));
6287 
6288  attr_info_inited = false;
6289  scan_cache_inited = false;
6290  found = false;
6291 
6292  error_code = heap_attrinfo_start (thread_p, class_oid, -1, NULL, &attr_info);
6293  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6294  {
6295  goto error;
6296  }
6297  attr_info_inited = true;
6298 
6299  /* check if lob attribute exists */
6300  for (i = 0; i < attr_info.num_values; i++)
6301  {
6302  value = &attr_info.values[i];
6303  if (value->last_attrepr->type == DB_TYPE_BLOB || value->last_attrepr->type == DB_TYPE_CLOB)
6304  {
6305  found = true;
6306  break;
6307  }
6308  }
6309 
6310  if (found)
6311  {
6312  if (recdes == NULL)
6313  {
6314  SCAN_CODE scan;
6315  error_code = heap_scancache_quick_start (&scan_cache);
6316  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6317  {
6318  goto error;
6319  }
6320  scan_cache_inited = true;
6321  copy_recdes.data = NULL;
6322  scan = heap_get_visible_version (thread_p, oid, class_oid, &copy_recdes, &scan_cache, COPY, NULL_CHN);
6323  if (scan != S_SUCCESS)
6324  {
6325  goto error;
6326  }
6327  recdes = &copy_recdes;
6328  }
6329 
6330  error_code = heap_attrinfo_delete_lob (thread_p, recdes, &attr_info);
6331  }
6332 
6333 error:
6334 
6335  if (attr_info_inited)
6336  {
6337  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, &attr_info);
6338  }
6339  if (scan_cache_inited)
6340  {
6341  error_code = heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache);
6342  }
6343 
6344  return error_code;
6345 }
6346 
6347 /*
6348  * locator_force_for_multi_update () -
6349  *
6350  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
6351  *
6352  * force_area(in): Copy area where objects are placed
6353  *
6354  * Note: This function update given objects that are sent by clients.
6355  * The objects are updated by multiple row update performed
6356  * on client and sent to the server through flush request.
6357  */
6358 static int
6359 locator_force_for_multi_update (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LC_COPYAREA * force_area)
6360 {
6361  LC_COPYAREA_MANYOBJS *mobjs; /* Describe multiple objects in area */
6362  LC_COPYAREA_ONEOBJ *obj; /* Describe on object in area */
6363  RECDES recdes; /* Record descriptor for object */
6364  HEAP_SCANCACHE scan_cache;
6365  int scan_cache_inited = 0;
6366  LOG_TDES *tdes;
6367  int i, s, t;
6368  int malloc_size;
6369  BTREE_UNIQUE_STATS *temp_info;
6370  char *ptr;
6371  int force_count;
6372  int tran_index;
6373  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
6374  REPL_INFO_TYPE repl_info;
6375  int has_index;
6376 
6377  tran_index = LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p);
6378  tdes = LOG_FIND_TDES (tran_index);
6379  if (tdes == NULL)
6380  {
6381  er_set (ER_FATAL_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_LOG_UNKNOWN_TRANINDEX, 1, tran_index);
6382  error_code = ER_LOG_UNKNOWN_TRANINDEX;
6383  goto error;
6384  }
6385 
6386  mobjs = LC_MANYOBJS_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (force_area);
6387 
6388  if (mobjs->start_multi_update && tdes->tran_unique_stats == NULL)
6389  {
6390  tdes->num_unique_btrees = 0;
6391  tdes->max_unique_btrees = UNIQUE_STAT_INFO_INCREMENT;
6392 
6393  malloc_size = sizeof (BTREE_UNIQUE_STATS) * UNIQUE_STAT_INFO_INCREMENT;
6394 
6395  /* Do not use db_private_alloc */
6396  tdes->tran_unique_stats = (BTREE_UNIQUE_STATS *) malloc (malloc_size);
6397  if (tdes->tran_unique_stats == NULL)
6398  {
6399  error_code = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
6400  goto error;
6401  }
6402  }
6403 
6404  if (mobjs->num_objs > 0)
6405  {
6406  int first_update_obj = -1, last_update_obj = -1;
6407 
6408  /*
6409  * Find first and last UPDATE objects
6410  */
6411  obj = LC_START_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (mobjs);
6412  obj = LC_PRIOR_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (obj);
6413  for (i = 0; i < mobjs->num_objs; i++)
6414  {
6415  obj = LC_NEXT_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (obj);
6416  if (LC_IS_FLUSH_UPDATE (obj->operation))
6417  {
6418  last_update_obj = i;
6419  if (first_update_obj == -1)
6420  {
6421  first_update_obj = i;
6422  }
6423  }
6424  }
6425  if (last_update_obj == -1)
6426  {
6427  /* this is not exactly an error case, but we somehow managed to generate a multi-update flush with no updated
6428  * objects */
6429  error_code = NO_ERROR;
6430  goto error;
6431  }
6432 
6433  /*
6434  * Flush objects
6435  */
6436  obj = LC_START_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (mobjs);
6437  obj = LC_PRIOR_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (obj);
6438  LC_RECDES_IN_COPYAREA (force_area, &recdes);
6439 
6440  for (i = 0; i < mobjs->num_objs; i++)
6441  {
6442  obj = LC_NEXT_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (obj);
6443  LC_RECDES_TO_GET_ONEOBJ (force_area, obj, &recdes);
6444 
6445  /* skip all non-updates operations and updates of class objects (non-updates operations and class objects are
6446  * already flushed in xlocator_force) */
6447  if (!LC_IS_FLUSH_UPDATE (obj->operation) || OID_EQ (&obj->class_oid, oid_Root_class_oid))
6448  {
6449  continue;
6450  }
6451 
6452  if (!scan_cache_inited)
6453  {
6454  /* Initialize a modify scancache */
6455  error_code =
6456  locator_start_force_scan_cache (thread_p, &scan_cache, &obj->hfid, &obj->class_oid, MULTI_ROW_UPDATE);
6457  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6458  {
6459  goto error;
6460  }
6461  scan_cache_inited = 1;
6462  }
6463 
6464  if (mobjs->start_multi_update && i == first_update_obj)
6465  {
6466  repl_info = REPL_INFO_TYPE_RBR_START;
6467  }
6468  else if (mobjs->end_multi_update && i == last_update_obj)
6469  {
6470  repl_info = REPL_INFO_TYPE_RBR_END;
6471  }
6472  else
6473  {
6474  repl_info = REPL_INFO_TYPE_RBR_NORMAL;
6475  }
6476  has_index = LC_ONEOBJ_GET_INDEX_FLAG (obj);
6477 
6478  scan_cache.mvcc_snapshot = logtb_get_mvcc_snapshot (thread_p);
6479  if (scan_cache.mvcc_snapshot == NULL)
6480  {
6481  error_code = er_errid ();
6482  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
6483  {
6484  error_code = ER_FAILED;
6485  }
6486 
6487  goto error;
6488  }
6489 
6490  /* update */
6491  error_code =
6492  locator_update_force (thread_p, &obj->hfid, &obj->class_oid, &obj->oid, NULL, &recdes,
6493  has_index, NULL, 0, MULTI_ROW_UPDATE, &scan_cache, &force_count, false, repl_info,
6494  DB_NOT_PARTITIONED_CLASS, NULL, NULL, UPDATE_INPLACE_NONE, true);
6495  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6496  {
6497  /*
6498  * Problems updating the object...Maybe, the transaction should be
6499  * aborted by the caller...Quit..
6500  */
6501  goto error;
6502  }
6503  } /* end-for */
6504 
6505  for (s = 0; s < scan_cache.num_btids; s++)
6506  {
6507  temp_info = &(scan_cache.index_stat_info[s]);
6508  if (temp_info->num_nulls == 0 && temp_info->num_keys == 0 && temp_info->num_oids == 0)
6509  {
6510  continue;
6511  }
6512  /* non-unique index would be filtered out at above statement. */
6513 
6514  for (t = 0; t < tdes->num_unique_btrees; t++)
6515  {
6516  if (BTID_IS_EQUAL (&temp_info->btid, &tdes->tran_unique_stats[t].btid))
6517  {
6518  break;
6519  }
6520  }
6521  if (t < tdes->num_unique_btrees)
6522  {
6523  /* The same unique index has been found */
6524  tdes->tran_unique_stats[t].num_nulls += temp_info->num_nulls;
6525  tdes->tran_unique_stats[t].num_keys += temp_info->num_keys;
6526  tdes->tran_unique_stats[t].num_oids += temp_info->num_oids;
6527  }
6528  else
6529  {
6530  /* The same unique index has not been found */
6531  if (tdes->num_unique_btrees == tdes->max_unique_btrees)
6532  {
6533  /* we need more space for storing unique index stat. info. */
6534  tdes->max_unique_btrees += UNIQUE_STAT_INFO_INCREMENT;
6535  malloc_size = (sizeof (BTREE_UNIQUE_STATS) * tdes->max_unique_btrees);
6536 
6537  /* Do not use db_private_realloc */
6538  ptr = (char *) realloc (tdes->tran_unique_stats, malloc_size);
6539  if (ptr == NULL)
6540  {
6541  error_code = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
6542  goto error;
6543  }
6544  tdes->tran_unique_stats = (BTREE_UNIQUE_STATS *) ptr;
6545  }
6546  t = tdes->num_unique_btrees;
