6547  BTID_COPY (&tdes->tran_unique_stats[t].btid, &temp_info->btid);
6548  tdes->tran_unique_stats[t].num_nulls = temp_info->num_nulls;
6549  tdes->tran_unique_stats[t].num_keys = temp_info->num_keys;
6550  tdes->tran_unique_stats[t].num_oids = temp_info->num_oids;
6551  tdes->num_unique_btrees++; /* increment */
6552  }
6553  }
6554 
6555  locator_end_force_scan_cache (thread_p, &scan_cache);
6556  scan_cache_inited = 0;
6557  }
6558 
6559  if (mobjs->end_multi_update)
6560  {
6561  BTREE_UNIQUE_STATS *unique_stats = NULL;
6562 
6563  for (s = 0; s < tdes->num_unique_btrees; s++)
6564  {
6565  unique_stats = &tdes->tran_unique_stats[s];
6566  if (unique_stats->num_nulls == 0 && unique_stats->num_keys == 0 && unique_stats->num_oids == 0)
6567  {
6568  continue; /* no modification : non-unique index */
6569  }
6570  if ((unique_stats->num_nulls + unique_stats->num_keys) != unique_stats->num_oids)
6571  {
6572  BTREE_SET_UNIQUE_VIOLATION_ERROR (thread_p, NULL, NULL, &mobjs->objs.class_oid, &unique_stats->btid,
6573  NULL);
6574  error_code = ER_BTREE_UNIQUE_FAILED;
6575  goto error;
6576  }
6577 
6578  error_code =
6579  logtb_tran_update_unique_stats (thread_p, &unique_stats->btid, unique_stats->num_keys,
6580  unique_stats->num_oids, unique_stats->num_nulls, true);
6581  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6582  {
6583  goto error;
6584  }
6585  }
6586 
6587  if (tdes->tran_unique_stats != NULL)
6588  {
6589  free_and_init (tdes->tran_unique_stats);
6590  }
6591  }
6592 
6593  return error_code;
6594 
6595 error:
6596  if (scan_cache_inited)
6597  {
6598  locator_end_force_scan_cache (thread_p, &scan_cache);
6599  }
6600 
6601  if (tdes != NULL && tdes->tran_unique_stats != NULL)
6602  {
6603  free_and_init (tdes->tran_unique_stats);
6604  }
6605 
6606  return error_code;
6607 }
6608 
6609 /*
6610  * locator_repl_add_error_to_copyarea () - place error info into copy area that
6611  * will be sent to client
6612  *
6613  * return:
6614  *
6615  * copy_area(out): copy area where error info will be placed
6616  * recdes(in): struct that describes copy_area
6617  * obj(in): object that describes the operation which caused an error
6618  * key_value(in): primary key value
6619  * err_code(in):
6620  * err_msg(in):
6621  */
6622 static void
6623 locator_repl_add_error_to_copyarea (LC_COPYAREA ** copy_area, RECDES * recdes, LC_COPYAREA_ONEOBJ * obj,
6624  DB_VALUE * key_value, int err_code, const char *err_msg)
6625 {
6626  LC_COPYAREA *new_copy_area = NULL;
6627  LC_COPYAREA_MANYOBJS *reply_mobjs = NULL;
6628  LC_COPYAREA_ONEOBJ *reply_obj = NULL;
6629  char *ptr;
6630  int packed_length = 0, round_length;
6631  int prev_offset, prev_length;
6632 
6633  packed_length += OR_VALUE_ALIGNED_SIZE (key_value);
6634  packed_length += OR_INT_SIZE;
6635  packed_length += or_packed_string_length (err_msg, NULL);
6636 
6637  if (packed_length > recdes->area_size)
6638  {
6639  int new_length, nw_pagesize;
6640 
6641  prev_offset = CAST_BUFLEN (recdes->data - (*copy_area)->mem);
6642  prev_length = (*copy_area)->length;
6643 
6644  nw_pagesize = db_network_page_size ();
6645  new_length = prev_length + CEIL_PTVDIV (packed_length - recdes->area_size, nw_pagesize) * nw_pagesize;
6646 
6647  new_copy_area = locator_reallocate_copy_area_by_length (*copy_area, new_length);
6648  if (new_copy_area == NULL)
6649  {
6650  /* failed to reallocate copy area. skip the current error */
6651  return;
6652  }
6653  else
6654  {
6655  recdes->data = new_copy_area->mem + prev_offset;
6656  recdes->area_size += CAST_BUFLEN (new_copy_area->length - prev_length);
6657  *copy_area = new_copy_area;
6658  }
6659  }
6660 
6661  reply_mobjs = LC_MANYOBJS_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (*copy_area);
6662  reply_obj = LC_FIND_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (reply_mobjs, reply_mobjs->num_objs);
6663 
6664  ptr = recdes->data;
6665  ptr = or_pack_mem_value (ptr, key_value, NULL);
6666  ptr = or_pack_int (ptr, err_code);
6667  ptr = or_pack_string (ptr, err_msg);
6668 
6669  reply_obj->length = CAST_BUFLEN (ptr - recdes->data);
6670  reply_obj->offset = CAST_BUFLEN (recdes->data - (*copy_area)->mem);
6671  COPY_OID (&reply_obj->class_oid, &obj->class_oid);
6672  reply_obj->operation = obj->operation;
6673 
6674  reply_mobjs->num_objs++;
6675 
6676  recdes->length = reply_obj->length;
6677  round_length = DB_ALIGN (recdes->length, MAX_ALIGNMENT);
6678 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
6679  /* suppress valgrind UMW error */
6680  memset (recdes->data + recdes->length, 0, MIN (round_length - recdes->length, recdes->area_size - recdes->length));
6681 #endif
6682  recdes->data += round_length;
6683  recdes->area_size -= round_length + sizeof (*reply_obj);
6684 }
6685 
6686 /*
6687  * locator_repl_prepare_force () - prepare required info for each operation
6688  *
6689  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
6690  *
6691  * thread_p(in):
6692  * obj(in): object that describes the current operation
6693  * old_recdes(out): original record needed for update operation
6694  * recdes(in/out): record to be applied
6695  * key_value(in): primary key value
6696  * force_scancache(in):
6697  */
6698 static int
6699 locator_repl_prepare_force (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LC_COPYAREA_ONEOBJ * obj, RECDES * old_recdes, RECDES * recdes,
6700  DB_VALUE * key_value, HEAP_SCANCACHE * force_scancache)
6701 {
6702  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
6703  int last_repr_id = -1;
6704  int old_chn = -1;
6705  BTID btid;
6706  SCAN_CODE scan;
6707  SCAN_OPERATION_TYPE scan_op_type;
6708 
6709  if (obj->operation == LC_FLUSH_DELETE)
6710  {
6711  scan_op_type = S_DELETE;
6712  }
6713  else if (LC_IS_FLUSH_UPDATE (obj->operation) == true)
6714  {
6715  scan_op_type = S_UPDATE;
6716  }
6717 
6718  if (obj->operation != LC_FLUSH_DELETE)
6719  {
6720  last_repr_id = heap_get_class_repr_id (thread_p, &obj->class_oid);
6721  if (last_repr_id == 0)
6722  {
6723  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_CT_INVALID_REPRID, 1, last_repr_id);
6724  return ER_CT_INVALID_REPRID;
6725  }
6726 
6727  error_code = or_replace_rep_id (recdes, last_repr_id);
6728  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6729  {
6730  return error_code;
6731  }
6732  }
6733 
6734  if (LC_IS_FLUSH_INSERT (obj->operation) == false)
6735  {
6736  error_code = btree_get_pkey_btid (thread_p, &obj->class_oid, &btid);
6737  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6738  {
6739  return error_code;
6740  }
6741 
6742  if (xbtree_find_unique (thread_p, &btid, scan_op_type, key_value, &obj->class_oid, &obj->oid, true) !=
6743  BTREE_KEY_FOUND)
6744  {
6745  er_set (ER_WARNING_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OBJ_OBJECT_NOT_FOUND, 0);
6746  return ER_OBJ_OBJECT_NOT_FOUND;
6747  }
6748  }
6749 
6750 
6751  if (LC_IS_FLUSH_UPDATE (obj->operation) == true)
6752  {
6753  assert (OID_ISNULL (&obj->oid) != true);
6754 
6755  scan =
6756  heap_get_visible_version (thread_p, &obj->oid, &obj->class_oid, old_recdes, force_scancache, PEEK, NULL_CHN);
6757 
6758  if (scan != S_SUCCESS)
6759  {
6760  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
6761  error_code = er_errid ();
6762  if (error_code == ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT)
6763  {
6764  er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE, "locator_repl_prepare_force : unknown oid ( %d|%d|%d )\n",
6765  obj->oid.pageid, obj->oid.slotid, obj->oid.volid);
6766  }
6767 
6768  return error_code;
6769  }
6770 
6771  old_chn = or_chn (old_recdes);
6772 
6773  error_code = or_replace_chn (recdes, old_chn + 1);
6774  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6775  {
6776  return error_code;
6777  }
6778  }
6779 
6780  return NO_ERROR;
6781 }
6782 
6783 /*
6784  * locator_repl_get_key_value () - read pkey value from copy_area
6785  *
6786  * return: length of unpacked key value
6787  *
6788  * key_value(out): primary key value
6789  * force_area(in):
6790  * obj(in): object that describes memory location of key_value
6791  *
6792  */
6793 static int
6794 locator_repl_get_key_value (DB_VALUE * key_value, LC_COPYAREA * force_area, LC_COPYAREA_ONEOBJ * obj)
6795 {
6796  char *ptr, *start_ptr;
6797 
6798  start_ptr = ptr = force_area->mem + obj->offset;
6799  ptr = or_unpack_mem_value (ptr, key_value);
6800 
6801  return (int) (ptr - start_ptr);
6802 }
6803 
6804 /*
6805  * xlocator_force () - Updates objects sent by log applier
6806  *
6807  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
6808  *
6809  * force_area(in): Copy area where objects are placed
6810  *
6811  * Note: This function applies all the desired operations on each of
6812  * object placed in the force_area.
6813  */
6814 int
6815 xlocator_repl_force (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LC_COPYAREA * force_area, LC_COPYAREA ** reply_area)
6816 {
6817  LC_COPYAREA_MANYOBJS *mobjs; /* Describe multiple objects in area */
6818  LC_COPYAREA_ONEOBJ *obj; /* Describe on object in area */
6819  RECDES recdes; /* Record descriptor for object */
6820  RECDES old_recdes;
6821  RECDES reply_recdes; /* Describe copy area for reply */
6822  int i;
6823  HEAP_SCANCACHE *force_scancache = NULL;
6824  HEAP_SCANCACHE scan_cache;
6825  int force_count;
6826  LOG_LSA lsa, oneobj_lsa;
6827  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
6828  int pruning_type = 0;
6829  int num_continue_on_error = 0;
6830  DB_VALUE key_value;
6831  int packed_key_value_len;
6832  HFID prev_hfid;
6833  int has_index;
6834 
6835  /* need to start a topop to ensure the atomic operation. */
6836  error_code = xtran_server_start_topop (thread_p, &lsa);
6837  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6838  {
6839  return error_code;
6840  }
6841 
6842  mobjs = LC_MANYOBJS_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (force_area);
6843 
6844  obj = LC_START_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (mobjs);
6845  obj = LC_PRIOR_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (obj);
6846 
6847  HFID_SET_NULL (&prev_hfid);
6848  db_value_put_null (&key_value);
6849 
6850  LC_RECDES_IN_COPYAREA (*reply_area, &reply_recdes);
6851 
6852  for (i = 0; i < mobjs->num_objs; i++)
6853  {
6854  er_clear ();
6855 
6856  obj = LC_NEXT_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (obj);
6857 
6858  packed_key_value_len = locator_repl_get_key_value (&key_value, force_area, obj);
6859 
6860  LC_REPL_RECDES_FOR_ONEOBJ (force_area, obj, packed_key_value_len, &recdes);
6861 
6862  error_code = heap_get_hfid_from_class_oid (thread_p, &obj->class_oid, &obj->hfid);
6863  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6864  {
6865  goto exit_on_error;
6866  }
6867 
6868  if (HFID_EQ (&prev_hfid, &obj->hfid) != true && force_scancache != NULL)
6869  {
6870  locator_end_force_scan_cache (thread_p, force_scancache);
6871  force_scancache = NULL;
6872  }
6873 
6874  if (force_scancache == NULL)
6875  {
6876  /* Initialize a modify scancache */
6877  error_code =
6878  locator_start_force_scan_cache (thread_p, &scan_cache, &obj->hfid, &obj->class_oid, SINGLE_ROW_UPDATE);
6879  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6880  {
6881  goto exit_on_error;
6882  }
6883  force_scancache = &scan_cache;
6884  HFID_COPY (&prev_hfid, &obj->hfid);
6885  }
6886 
6887  error_code = xtran_server_start_topop (thread_p, &oneobj_lsa);
6888  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6889  {
6890  goto exit_on_error;
6891  }
6892 
6893  error_code = locator_repl_prepare_force (thread_p, obj, &old_recdes, &recdes, &key_value, force_scancache);
6894  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
6895  {
6896  has_index = LC_ONEOBJ_GET_INDEX_FLAG (obj);
6897 
6898  switch (obj->operation)
6899  {
6900  case LC_FLUSH_INSERT:
6901  case LC_FLUSH_INSERT_PRUNE:
6902  case LC_FLUSH_INSERT_PRUNE_VERIFY:
6903  pruning_type = locator_area_op_to_pruning_type (obj->operation);
6904  error_code =
6905  locator_insert_force (thread_p, &obj->hfid, &obj->class_oid, &obj->oid, &recdes, has_index,
6906  SINGLE_ROW_INSERT, force_scancache, &force_count, pruning_type, NULL, NULL,
6907  UPDATE_INPLACE_NONE);
6908 
6909  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
6910  {
6911  /* monitor */
6912  perfmon_inc_stat (thread_p, PSTAT_QM_NUM_INSERTS);
6913  }
6914  break;
6915 
6916  case LC_FLUSH_UPDATE:
6917  case LC_FLUSH_UPDATE_PRUNE:
6918  case LC_FLUSH_UPDATE_PRUNE_VERIFY:
6919  pruning_type = locator_area_op_to_pruning_type (obj->operation);
6920  error_code =
6921  locator_update_force (thread_p, &obj->hfid, &obj->class_oid, &obj->oid, NULL, &recdes, has_index,
6922  NULL, 0, SINGLE_ROW_UPDATE, force_scancache, &force_count, false,
6923  REPL_INFO_TYPE_RBR_NORMAL, pruning_type, NULL, NULL, UPDATE_INPLACE_NONE, true);
6924 
6925  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
6926  {
6927  /* monitor */
6928  perfmon_inc_stat (thread_p, PSTAT_QM_NUM_UPDATES);
6929  }
6930  break;
6931 
6932  case LC_FLUSH_DELETE:
6933  error_code =
6934  locator_delete_force (thread_p, &obj->hfid, &obj->oid, has_index, SINGLE_ROW_DELETE, force_scancache,
6935  &force_count, NULL, true);
6936 
6937  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
6938  {
6939  /* monitor */
6940  perfmon_inc_stat (thread_p, PSTAT_QM_NUM_DELETES);
6941  }
6942  break;
6943 
6944  default:
6945  /*
6946  * Problems forcing the object. Don't known what flush/force operation
6947  * to execute on the object... This is a system error...
6948  * Maybe, the transaction should be aborted by the caller...Quit..
6949  */
6950  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_LC_BADFORCE_OPERATION, 4, obj->operation, obj->oid.volid,
6951  obj->oid.pageid, obj->oid.slotid);
6952  error_code = ER_LC_BADFORCE_OPERATION;
6953  break;
6954  } /* end-switch */
6955  }
6956 
6957  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6958  {
6959  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
6960  locator_repl_add_error_to_copyarea (reply_area, &reply_recdes, obj, &key_value, er_errid (), er_msg ());
6961 
6962  error_code = NO_ERROR;
6963  num_continue_on_error++;
6964 
6965  (void) xtran_server_end_topop (thread_p, LOG_RESULT_TOPOP_ABORT, &oneobj_lsa);
6966  }
6967  else
6968  {
6969  (void) xtran_server_end_topop (thread_p, LOG_RESULT_TOPOP_ATTACH_TO_OUTER, &oneobj_lsa);
6970  }
6971  pr_clear_value (&key_value);
6972  }
6973 
6974  if (force_scancache != NULL)
6975  {
6976  locator_end_force_scan_cache (thread_p, force_scancache);
6977  }
6978 
6979  (void) xtran_server_end_topop (thread_p, LOG_RESULT_TOPOP_ATTACH_TO_OUTER, &lsa);
6980 
6981  if (num_continue_on_error > 0)
6982  {
6983  return ER_LC_PARTIALLY_FAILED_TO_FLUSH;
6984  }
6985 
6986  return error_code;
6987 
6988 exit_on_error:
6989  assert_release (error_code == ER_FAILED || error_code == er_errid ());
6990 
6991  if (DB_IS_NULL (&key_value) == false)
6992  {
6993  pr_clear_value (&key_value);
6994  }
6995 
6996  if (force_scancache != NULL)
6997  {
6998  locator_end_force_scan_cache (thread_p, force_scancache);
6999  }
7000 
7001  (void) xtran_server_end_topop (thread_p, LOG_RESULT_TOPOP_ABORT, &lsa);
7002 
7003  return error_code;
7004 }
7005 
7006 /*
7007  * xlocator_force () - Updates objects placed on page
7008  *
7009  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
7010  *
7011  * force_area(in): Copy area where objects are placed
7012  *
7013  * Note: This function applies all the desired operations on each of
7014  * object placed in the force_area.
7015  */
7016 int
7017 xlocator_force (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LC_COPYAREA * force_area, int num_ignore_error, int *ignore_error_list)
7018 {
7019  LC_COPYAREA_MANYOBJS *mobjs; /* Describe multiple objects in area */
7020  LC_COPYAREA_ONEOBJ *obj; /* Describe on object in area */
7021  RECDES recdes; /* Record descriptor for object */
7022  int i;
7023  HEAP_SCANCACHE *force_scancache = NULL;
7024  HEAP_SCANCACHE scan_cache;
7025  int force_count;
7026  LOG_LSA lsa, oneobj_lsa;
7027  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
7028  int pruning_type = 0;
7029  int has_index;
7030 
7031  /* need to start a topop to ensure the atomic operation. */
7032  error_code = xtran_server_start_topop (thread_p, &lsa);
7033  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
7034  {
7035  return error_code;
7036  }
7037 
7038  mobjs = LC_MANYOBJS_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (force_area);
7039  obj = LC_START_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (mobjs);
7040  obj = LC_PRIOR_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (obj);
7041  LC_RECDES_IN_COPYAREA (force_area, &recdes);
7042 
7043  for (i = 0; i < mobjs->num_objs; i++)
7044  {
7045  obj = LC_NEXT_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (obj);
7046  LC_RECDES_TO_GET_ONEOBJ (force_area, obj, &recdes);
7047 
7048  if (i == 0)
7049  {
7050  /*
7051  * Initialize a modify scancache
7052  */
7053  error_code =
7054  locator_start_force_scan_cache (thread_p, &scan_cache, &obj->hfid, &obj->class_oid, SINGLE_ROW_UPDATE);
7055  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
7056  {
7057  goto error;
7058  }
7059  force_scancache = &scan_cache;
7060  }
7061 
7062  if (LOG_CHECK_LOG_APPLIER (thread_p) || num_ignore_error > 0)
7063  {
7064  error_code = xtran_server_start_topop (thread_p, &oneobj_lsa);
7065  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
7066  {
7067  goto error;
7068  }
7069  }
7070 
7071  has_index = LC_ONEOBJ_GET_INDEX_FLAG (obj);
7072 
7073  /* For multi update, we're just interested in the INSERT and DELETE operations here, which were generated by
7074  * triggers operating on the same class that is being updated; treat these operations as single row and skip all
7075  * updates. Also, for multi UPDATE operations, the class objects should be flushed here as single row. Instance
7076  * updates will be handled by locator_force_for_multi_update() TODO: trigger generated updates will not be
7077  * treated correctly. */
7078  if (mobjs->start_multi_update && LC_IS_FLUSH_UPDATE (obj->operation)
7079  && !OID_EQ (&obj->class_oid, oid_Root_class_oid))
7080  {
7081  continue;
7082  }
7083 
7084  /* delete old row must be set to true for system classes and false for others, therefore it must be updated for
7085  * each object. */
7086 
7087  switch (obj->operation)
7088  {
7089  case LC_FLUSH_INSERT:
7090  case LC_FLUSH_INSERT_PRUNE:
7091  case LC_FLUSH_INSERT_PRUNE_VERIFY:
7092  pruning_type = locator_area_op_to_pruning_type (obj->operation);
7093  error_code =
7094  locator_insert_force (thread_p, &obj->hfid, &obj->class_oid, &obj->oid, &recdes, has_index,
7095  SINGLE_ROW_INSERT, force_scancache, &force_count, pruning_type, NULL, NULL,
7096  UPDATE_INPLACE_NONE);
7097 
7098  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
7099  {
7100  /* monitor */
7101  perfmon_inc_stat (thread_p, PSTAT_QM_NUM_INSERTS);
7102  }
7103  break;
7104 
7105  case LC_FLUSH_UPDATE:
7106  case LC_FLUSH_UPDATE_PRUNE:
7107  case LC_FLUSH_UPDATE_PRUNE_VERIFY:
7108  pruning_type = locator_area_op_to_pruning_type (obj->operation);
7109  error_code =
7110  locator_update_force (thread_p, &obj->hfid, &obj->class_oid, &obj->oid, NULL, &recdes,
7111  has_index, NULL, 0, SINGLE_ROW_UPDATE, force_scancache, &force_count, false,
7112  REPL_INFO_TYPE_RBR_NORMAL, pruning_type, NULL, NULL, UPDATE_INPLACE_NONE, true);
7113 
7114  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
7115  {
7116  /* monitor */
7117  perfmon_inc_stat (thread_p, PSTAT_QM_NUM_UPDATES);
7118  }
7119  break;
7120 
7121  case LC_FLUSH_DELETE:
7122  error_code =
7123  locator_delete_force (thread_p, &obj->hfid, &obj->oid, has_index, SINGLE_ROW_DELETE, force_scancache,
7124  &force_count, NULL, true);
7125 
7126  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
7127  {
7128  /* monitor */
7129  perfmon_inc_stat (thread_p, PSTAT_QM_NUM_DELETES);
7130  }
7131  break;
7132 
7133  default:
7134  /*
7135  * Problems forcing the object. Don't known what flush/force operation
7136  * to execute on the object... This is a system error...
7137  * Maybe, the transaction should be aborted by the caller...Quit..
7138  */
7139  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_LC_BADFORCE_OPERATION, 4, obj->operation, obj->oid.volid,
7140  obj->oid.pageid, obj->oid.slotid);
7141  error_code = ER_LC_BADFORCE_OPERATION;
7142  break;
7143  } /* end-switch */
7144 
7145  if (LOG_CHECK_LOG_APPLIER (thread_p) || num_ignore_error > 0)
7146  {
7147  bool need_to_abort_oneobj = false;
7148 
7149  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
7150  {
7151  if (LOG_CHECK_LOG_APPLIER (thread_p))
7152  {
7153  need_to_abort_oneobj = true;
7154  }
7155  else
7156  {
7157  error_code = locator_filter_errid (thread_p, num_ignore_error, ignore_error_list);
7158  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
7159  {
7160  /* error is filtered out */
7161  OID_SET_NULL (&obj->oid);
7162  need_to_abort_oneobj = true;
7163  }
7164  }
7165  }
7166 
7167  if (need_to_abort_oneobj)
7168  {
7169  (void) xtran_server_end_topop (thread_p, LOG_RESULT_TOPOP_ABORT, &oneobj_lsa);
7170  }
7171  else
7172  {
7173  (void) xtran_server_end_topop (thread_p, LOG_RESULT_TOPOP_ATTACH_TO_OUTER, &oneobj_lsa);
7174  }
7175  }
7176 
7177  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
7178  {
7179  /*
7180  * Problems... Maybe, the transaction should
7181  * be aborted by the caller...Quit..
7182  */
7183  goto error;
7184  }
7185  } /* end-for */
7186 
7187  if (force_scancache != NULL)
7188  {
7189  locator_end_force_scan_cache (thread_p, force_scancache);
7190  force_scancache = NULL;
7191  }
7192 
7193  /* handle multi-update case */
7194  if (mobjs->start_multi_update)
7195  {
7196  error_code = locator_force_for_multi_update (thread_p, force_area);
7197  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
7198  {
7199  goto error;
7200  }
7201  }
7202 
7203  (void) xtran_server_end_topop (thread_p, LOG_RESULT_TOPOP_ATTACH_TO_OUTER, &lsa);
7204 
7205  return error_code;
7206 
7207 error:
7208 
7209  /* The reevaluation at update phase of update is currently disabled */
7210  assert (error_code != ER_MVCC_NOT_SATISFIED_REEVALUATION);
7211  assert_release (error_code == ER_FAILED || error_code == er_errid ());
7212 
7213  if (force_scancache != NULL)
7214  {
7215  locator_end_force_scan_cache (thread_p, force_scancache);
7216  }
7217 
7218  (void) xtran_server_end_topop (thread_p, LOG_RESULT_TOPOP_ABORT, &lsa);
7219 
7220  return error_code;
7221 }
7222 
7223 /*
7224  * locator_allocate_copy_area_by_attr_info () - Transforms attribute
7225  * information into a disk representation and allocates a
7226  * LC_COPYAREA big enough to fit the representation
7227  *
7228  * return: the allocated LC_COPYAREA if all OK, NULL otherwise
7229  *
7230  * attr_info(in/out): Attribute information
7231  * (Set as a side effect to fill the rest of values)
7232  * old_recdes(in): The old representation of the object or NULL if this is a
7233  * new object (to be inserted).
7234  * new_recdes(in): The resulting new representation of the object.
7235  * copyarea_length_hint(in): An estimated size for the LC_COPYAREA or -1 if
7236  * an estimated size is not known.
7237  * lob_create_flag(in) :
7238  *
7239  * Note: The allocated should be freed by using locator_free_copy_area ()
7240  */
7241 LC_COPYAREA *
7242 locator_allocate_copy_area_by_attr_info (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, HEAP_CACHE_ATTRINFO * attr_info, RECDES * old_recdes,
7243  RECDES * new_recdes, const int copyarea_length_hint, int lob_create_flag)
7244 {
7245  LC_COPYAREA *copyarea = NULL;
7246  int copyarea_length = copyarea_length_hint <= 0 ? DB_PAGESIZE : copyarea_length_hint;
7247  SCAN_CODE scan = S_DOESNT_FIT;
7248 
7249  while (scan == S_DOESNT_FIT)
7250  {
7251  copyarea = locator_allocate_copy_area_by_length (copyarea_length);
7252  if (copyarea == NULL)
7253  {
7254  break;
7255  }
7256 
7257  new_recdes->data = copyarea->mem;
7258  new_recdes->area_size = copyarea->length;
7259 
7260  if (lob_create_flag == LOB_FLAG_EXCLUDE_LOB)
7261  {
7262  scan = heap_attrinfo_transform_to_disk_except_lob (thread_p, attr_info, old_recdes, new_recdes);
7263  }
7264  else
7265  {
7266  scan = heap_attrinfo_transform_to_disk (thread_p, attr_info, old_recdes, new_recdes);
7267  }
7268 
7269  if (scan != S_SUCCESS)
7270  {
7271  /* Get the real length used in the copy area */
7272  copyarea_length = copyarea->length;
7273  locator_free_copy_area (copyarea);
7274  copyarea = NULL;
7275  new_recdes->data = NULL;
7276  new_recdes->area_size = 0;
7277 
7278  /* Is more space needed ? */
7279  if (scan == S_DOESNT_FIT)
7280  {
7281  /*
7282  * The object does not fit into copy area, increase the area
7283  * to estimated size included in length of record descriptor.
7284  */
7285  if (copyarea_length < (-new_recdes->length))
7286  {
7287  copyarea_length = DB_ALIGN (-new_recdes->length, MAX_ALIGNMENT);
7288  }
7289  else
7290  {
7291  /*
7292  * This is done for security purposes only, since the
7293  * transformation may not have given us the correct length,
7294  * somehow.
7295  */
7296  copyarea_length += DB_PAGESIZE;
7297  }
7298  }
7299  }
7300  }
7301  return copyarea;
7302 }
7303 
7304 /*
7305  * locator_attribute_info_force () - Force an object represented by attribute
7306  * information structure
7307  *
7308  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
7309  *
7310  * hfid(in): Where of the object
7311  * oid(in/out): The object identifier
7312  * (Set as a side effect when operation is insert)
7313  * attr_info(in/out): Attribute information
7314  * (Set as a side effect to fill the rest of values)
7315  * att_id(in): Updated attr id array
7316  * n_att_id(in/out): Updated attr id array length
7317  * (Set as a side effect to fill the rest of values)
7318  * operation(in): Type of operation (either LC_FLUSH_INSERT,
7319  * LC_FLUSH_UPDATE, or LC_FLUSH_DELETE)
7320  * op_type(in):
7321  * scan_cache(in):
7322  * force_count(in):
7323  * not_check_fk(in):
7324  * pruning_type(in):
7325  * pcontext(in): partition pruning context
7326  * func_preds(in): cached function index expressions
7327  * mvcc_reev_data(in): MVCC reevaluation data
7328  * force_in_place(in): if UPDATE_INPLACE_NONE then the 'in place' will not be
7329  * forced and the update style will be decided in this
7330  * function. Otherwise the update of the instance will be
7331  * made in place and according to provided style.
7332  * need_locking(in): true, if need locking
7333  *
7334  * Note: Force an object represented by an attribute information structure.
7335  * For insert the oid is set as a side effect.
7336  * For delete, the attr_info does not need to be given.
7337  */
7338 int
7339 locator_attribute_info_force (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const HFID * hfid, OID * oid, HEAP_CACHE_ATTRINFO * attr_info,
7340  ATTR_ID * att_id, int n_att_id, LC_COPYAREA_OPERATION operation, int op_type,
7341  HEAP_SCANCACHE * scan_cache, int *force_count, bool not_check_fk,
7342  REPL_INFO_TYPE repl_info, int pruning_type, PRUNING_CONTEXT * pcontext,
7343  FUNC_PRED_UNPACK_INFO * func_preds, MVCC_REEV_DATA * mvcc_reev_data,
7344  UPDATE_INPLACE_STYLE force_update_inplace, RECDES * rec_descriptor, bool need_locking)
7345 {
7346  LC_COPYAREA *copyarea = NULL;
7347  RECDES new_recdes;
7348  SCAN_CODE scan = S_SUCCESS; /* Scan return value for next operation */
7349  RECDES copy_recdes;
7350  RECDES *old_recdes = NULL;
7351  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
7352  HFID class_hfid;
7353  OID class_oid;
7354  MVCC_SNAPSHOT *saved_mvcc_snapshot = NULL;
7355 
7356  /*
7357  * While scanning objects, the given scancache does not fix the last
7358  * accessed page. So, the object must be copied to the record descriptor.
7359  */
7360  copy_recdes.data = NULL;
7361 
7362  /* Backup the provided class_oid and class_hfid because the locator actions bellow will change them if this is a
7363  * pruning operation. This changes must not be reflected in the calls to this function. */
7364  HFID_COPY (&class_hfid, hfid);
7365  if (attr_info != NULL)
7366  {
7367  COPY_OID (&class_oid, &attr_info->class_oid);
7368  }
7369  switch (operation)
7370  {
7371  case LC_FLUSH_UPDATE:
7372  case LC_FLUSH_UPDATE_PRUNE:
7373  case LC_FLUSH_UPDATE_PRUNE_VERIFY:
7374  /* MVCC snapshot no needed for now scan_cache->mvcc_snapshot = logtb_get_mvcc_snapshot (thread_p); */
7375  if (rec_descriptor != NULL)
7376  {
7377  copy_recdes = *rec_descriptor;
7378  }
7379  else if (HEAP_IS_UPDATE_INPLACE (force_update_inplace) || need_locking == false)
7380  {
7381  HEAP_GET_CONTEXT context;
7382 
7383  /* don't consider visiblity, just get the last version of the object */
7384  heap_init_get_context (thread_p, &context, oid, &class_oid, &copy_recdes, scan_cache, COPY, NULL_CHN);
7385  scan = heap_get_last_version (thread_p, &context);
7386  heap_clean_get_context (thread_p, &context);
7387 
7388  assert ((lock_get_object_lock (oid, &class_oid, LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p)) >= X_LOCK)
7389  || (lock_get_object_lock (&class_oid, oid_Root_class_oid,
7390  LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p) >= X_LOCK)));
7391  }
7392  else
7393  {
7394  /* The oid has been already locked in select phase, however need to get the last object that may differ by
7395  * the current one in case that transaction updates same OID many times during command execution */
7396  /* TODO: investigate if this is still true */
7397  if (scan_cache && scan_cache->mvcc_snapshot != NULL)
7398  {
7399  /* Why is snapshot set to NULL? */
7400  saved_mvcc_snapshot = scan_cache->mvcc_snapshot;
7401  scan_cache->mvcc_snapshot = NULL;
7402  }
7403 
7404  scan = locator_lock_and_get_object (thread_p, oid, &class_oid, &copy_recdes, scan_cache, X_LOCK, COPY,
7405  NULL_CHN, LOG_ERROR_IF_DELETED);
7406  if (saved_mvcc_snapshot != NULL)
7407  {
7408  scan_cache->mvcc_snapshot = saved_mvcc_snapshot;
7409  }
7410  }
7411 
7412  if (scan == S_SUCCESS)
7413  {
7414  /* do nothing for the moment */
7415  }
7416  else if (scan == S_ERROR || scan == S_DOESNT_FIT)
7417  {
7418  /* Whenever an error including an interrupt was broken out, quit the update. */
7419  return ER_FAILED;
7420  }
7421  else if (scan == S_DOESNT_EXIST)
7422  {
7423  int err_id = er_errid ();
7424  if (err_id == ER_HEAP_NODATA_NEWADDRESS)
7425  {
7426  /* it is an immature record. go ahead to update */
7427  er_clear (); /* clear ER_HEAP_NODATA_NEWADDRESS */
7428  }
7429  else
7430  {
7431  return ((err_id == NO_ERROR) ? ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT : err_id); /* other errors should return S_ERROR? */
7432  }
7433  }
7434  else if (scan == S_SNAPSHOT_NOT_SATISFIED)
7435  {
7436  return ER_FAILED;
7437  }
7438  else
7439  {
7440  assert (false);
7441  return ER_FAILED;
7442  }
7443 
7444  old_recdes = &copy_recdes;
7445 
7446  /* Fall through */
7447 
7448  case LC_FLUSH_INSERT:
7449  case LC_FLUSH_INSERT_PRUNE:
7450  case LC_FLUSH_INSERT_PRUNE_VERIFY:
7451  copyarea =
7452  locator_allocate_copy_area_by_attr_info (thread_p, attr_info, old_recdes, &new_recdes, -1,
7453  LOB_FLAG_INCLUDE_LOB);
7454  if (copyarea == NULL)
7455  {
7456  error_code = ER_FAILED;
7457  break;
7458  }
7459 
7460  /* Assume that it has indices */
7461  if (LC_IS_FLUSH_INSERT (operation))
7462  {
7463  error_code =
7464  locator_insert_force (thread_p, &class_hfid, &class_oid, oid, &new_recdes, true, op_type, scan_cache,
7465  force_count, pruning_type, pcontext, func_preds, UPDATE_INPLACE_NONE);
7466  }
7467  else
7468  {
7469  int has_index;
7470 
7471  assert (LC_IS_FLUSH_UPDATE (operation));
7472 
7473  /* MVCC snapshot no needed for now scan_cache->mvcc_snapshot = logtb_get_mvcc_snapshot (thread_p); */
7474  has_index = LC_FLAG_HAS_INDEX;
7475  if (heap_attrinfo_check_unique_index (thread_p, attr_info, att_id, n_att_id))
7476  {
7477  has_index |= LC_FLAG_HAS_UNIQUE_INDEX;
7478  }
7479 
7480  error_code =
7481  locator_update_force (thread_p, &class_hfid, &class_oid, oid, old_recdes, &new_recdes, has_index,
7482  att_id, n_att_id, op_type, scan_cache, force_count, not_check_fk, repl_info,
7483  pruning_type, pcontext, mvcc_reev_data, force_update_inplace, need_locking);
7484  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
7485  {
7486  ASSERT_ERROR ();
7487  }
7488  }
7489 
7490  if (copyarea != NULL)
7491  {
7492  locator_free_copy_area (copyarea);
7493  copyarea = NULL;
7494  new_recdes.data = NULL;
7495  new_recdes.area_size = 0;
7496  }
7497  break;
7498 
7499  case LC_FLUSH_DELETE:
7500  error_code =
7501  locator_delete_force (thread_p, &class_hfid, oid, true, op_type, scan_cache, force_count, mvcc_reev_data,
7502  need_locking);
7503  break;
7504 
7505  default:
7506  /*
7507  * Problems forcing the object. Don't known what flush/force operation
7508  * to execute on the object... This is a system error...
7509  * Maybe, the transaction should be aborted by the caller...Quit..
7510  */
7511  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_LC_BADFORCE_OPERATION, 4, operation, oid->volid, oid->pageid,
7512  oid->slotid);
7513  error_code = ER_LC_BADFORCE_OPERATION;
7514  break;
7515  }
7516 
7517  return error_code;
7518 }
7519 
7520 /*
7521  * locator_was_index_already_applied () - Check B-Tree was already added
7522  * or removed entries
7523  *
7524  * return: true if index was already applied
7525  *
7526  * index_attrinfo(in): information of indices
7527  * btid(in): btid of index
7528  * pos(in): index position on indices
7529  *
7530  * Note: B-Tree can be shared by constraints (PK, or FK). The shared B-Tree can
7531  * be added or removed entries one more times during one INSERT or DELETE
7532  * statement is executing. Therefore, we need to check B-Tree was already added
7533  * or removed entries.
7534  */
7535 static bool
7536 locator_was_index_already_applied (HEAP_CACHE_ATTRINFO * index_attrinfo, BTID * btid, int pos)
7537 {
7538  OR_INDEX *index;
7539  int i;
7540 
7541  for (i = 0; i < pos; i++)
7542  {
7543  index = &(index_attrinfo->last_classrepr->indexes[i]);
7544  if (BTID_IS_EQUAL (btid, &index->btid))
7545  {
7546  return true;
7547  }
7548  }
7549 
7550  return false;
7551 }
7552 
7553 /*
7554  * locator_add_or_remove_index () - Add or remove index entries
7555  *
7556  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
7557  *
7558  * recdes(in): The object
7559  * inst_oid(in): The object identifier
7560  * class_oid(in): The class object identifier
7561  * is_insert(in): whether to add or remove the object from the indexes
7562  * op_type(in):
7563  * scan_cache(in):
7564  * datayn(in): true if the target object is "data",
7565  * false if the target object is "schema"
7566  * need_replication(in): true if replication is needed
7567  * hfid(in):
7568  * func_preds(in): cached function index expressions
7569  *
7570  * Note:Either insert indices (in_insert) or delete indices.
7571  */
7572 int
7573 locator_add_or_remove_index (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, RECDES * recdes, OID * inst_oid, OID * class_oid, int is_insert,
7574  int op_type, HEAP_SCANCACHE * scan_cache, bool datayn, bool need_replication, HFID * hfid,
7575  FUNC_PRED_UNPACK_INFO * func_preds)
7576 {
7577  return locator_add_or_remove_index_internal (thread_p, recdes, inst_oid, class_oid, is_insert, op_type, scan_cache,
7578  datayn, need_replication, hfid, func_preds, FOR_INSERT_OR_DELETE);
7579 }
7580 
7581 /*
7582  * locator_add_or_remove_index_for_moving () - Add or remove index entries
7583  * To move record between partitions.
7584  *
7585  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
7586  *
7587  * recdes(in): The object
7588  * inst_oid(in): The object identifier
7589  * class_oid(in): The class object identifier
7590  * is_insert(in): whether to add or remove the object from the indexes
7591  * op_type(in):
7592  * scan_cache(in):
7593  * datayn(in): true if the target object is "data",
7594  * false if the target object is "schema"
7595  * need_replication(in): true if replication is needed
7596  * hfid(in):
7597  * func_preds(in): cached function index expressions
7598  *
7599  * Note:Either insert indices (in_insert) or delete indices.
7600  */
7601 static int
7602 locator_add_or_remove_index_for_moving (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, RECDES * recdes, OID * inst_oid, OID * class_oid,
7603  int is_insert, int op_type, HEAP_SCANCACHE * scan_cache, bool datayn,
7604  bool need_replication, HFID * hfid, FUNC_PRED_UNPACK_INFO * func_preds)
7605 {
7606  return locator_add_or_remove_index_internal (thread_p, recdes, inst_oid, class_oid, is_insert, op_type, scan_cache,
7607  datayn, need_replication, hfid, func_preds, FOR_MOVE);
7608 }
7609 
7610 /*
7611  * locator_add_or_remove_index_internal () - helper function for
7612  * locator_add_or_remove_index () and
7613  * locator_add_or_remove_index_for_moving ()
7614  *
7615  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
7616  *
7617  * recdes(in): The object
7618  * inst_oid(in): The object identifier
7619  * class_oid(in): The class object identifier
7620  * is_insert(in): whether to add or remove the object from the indexes
7621  * op_type(in):
7622  * scan_cache(in):
7623  * datayn(in): true if the target object is "data",
7624  * false if the target object is "schema"
7625  * need_replication(in): true if replication is needed
7626  * hfid(in):
7627  * func_preds(in): cached function index expressions
7628  * idx_action_flag(in): is moving record between partitioned table?
7629  * If FOR_MOVE, this delete(&insert) is caused by
7630  * 'UPDATE ... SET ...', NOT 'DELETE FROM ...'
7631  *
7632  * Note:Either insert indices (in_insert) or delete indices.
7633  */
7634 static int
7635 locator_add_or_remove_index_internal (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, RECDES * recdes, OID * inst_oid, OID * class_oid,
7636  int is_insert, int op_type, HEAP_SCANCACHE * scan_cache, bool datayn,
7637  bool need_replication, HFID * hfid, FUNC_PRED_UNPACK_INFO * func_preds,
7638  LOCATOR_INDEX_ACTION_FLAG idx_action_flag)
7639 {
7640  int num_found;
7641  int i, num_btids;
7642  HEAP_CACHE_ATTRINFO index_attrinfo;
7643  BTID btid;
7644  DB_VALUE *key_dbvalue, *key_ins_del = NULL;
7645  DB_VALUE dbvalue;
7646  int dummy_unique;
7647  BTREE_UNIQUE_STATS *unique_stat_info;
7648  HEAP_IDX_ELEMENTS_INFO idx_info;
7649  char buf[DBVAL_BUFSIZE + MAX_ALIGNMENT], *aligned_buf;
7650  OR_INDEX *index;
7651  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
7652  OR_PREDICATE *or_pred = NULL;
7653  DB_LOGICAL ev_res;
7654  bool use_mvcc = false;
7655  MVCCID mvccid;
7656  MVCC_REC_HEADER *p_mvcc_rec_header = NULL;
7657 
7658 /* temporary disable standalone optimization (non-mvcc insert/delete style).
7659  * Must be activated when dynamic heap is introduced */
7660 /* #if defined (SERVER_MODE) */
7661  MVCC_REC_HEADER mvcc_rec_header[2];
7662 /* #endif */
7663 
7664 #if defined(ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP)
7665  char *classname = NULL;
7666 #endif /* ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP */
7667 
7668  assert_release (class_oid != NULL);
7669  assert_release (!OID_ISNULL (class_oid));
7670 
7671  key_dbvalue = NULL;
7672  db_make_null (&dbvalue);
7673 
7674  aligned_buf = PTR_ALIGN (buf, MAX_ALIGNMENT);
7675 
7676 #if defined(SERVER_MODE)
7677  if (!mvcc_is_mvcc_disabled_class (class_oid))
7678  {
7679  /* Use MVCC if it's not disabled for current class */
7680  use_mvcc = true;
7681  mvccid = logtb_get_current_mvccid (thread_p);
7682  }
7683 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
7684 
7685  /*
7686  * Populate the index_attrinfo structure.
7687  * Return the number of indexed attributes found.
7688  */
7689  num_found = heap_attrinfo_start_with_index (thread_p, class_oid, NULL, &index_attrinfo, &idx_info);
7690  num_btids = idx_info.num_btids;
7691 
7692  if (num_found == 0)
7693  {
7694  return NO_ERROR;
7695  }
7696  else if (num_found < 0)
7697  {
7698  return ER_FAILED;
7699  }
7700 
7701  /*
7702  * At this point, there are indices and the index attrinfo has
7703  * been initialized
7704  *
7705  * Read the values of the indexed attributes
7706  */
7707  if (idx_info.has_single_col)
7708  {
7709  error_code = heap_attrinfo_read_dbvalues (thread_p, inst_oid, recdes, NULL, &index_attrinfo);
7710  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
7711  {
7712  goto error;
7713  }
7714  }
7715 
7716 #if defined(ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP)
7717  if (heap_get_class_name (thread_p, class_oid, &classname) != NO_ERROR || classname == NULL)
7718  {
7719  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
7720  goto error;
7721  }
7722 #endif /* ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP */
7723 
7724  for (i = 0; i < num_btids; i++)
7725  {
7726  index = &(index_attrinfo.last_classrepr->indexes[i]);
7727  or_pred = index->filter_predicate;
7728  if (or_pred && or_pred->pred_stream)
7729  {
7730  error_code =
7731  locator_eval_filter_predicate (thread_p, &index->btid, or_pred, class_oid, &inst_oid, 1, &recdes, &ev_res);
7732  if (error_code == ER_FAILED)
7733  {
7734  goto error;
7735  }
7736  else if (ev_res != V_TRUE)
7737  {
7738  continue;
7739  }
7740  }
7741  /*
7742  * Generate a B-tree key contained in a DB_VALUE and return a
7743  * pointer to it.
7744  */
7745  key_dbvalue =
7746  heap_attrvalue_get_key (thread_p, i, &index_attrinfo, recdes, &btid, &dbvalue, aligned_buf,
7747  (func_preds ? &func_preds[i] : NULL), NULL);
7748  if (key_dbvalue == NULL)
7749  {
7750  error_code = ER_FAILED;
7751  goto error;
7752  }
7753 
7754  if (i < 1 || !locator_was_index_already_applied (&index_attrinfo, &index->btid, i))
7755  {
7756  if (scan_cache == NULL)
7757  {
7758  unique_stat_info = NULL;
7759  }
7760  else
7761  {
7762  if (op_type == MULTI_ROW_UPDATE || op_type == MULTI_ROW_INSERT || op_type == MULTI_ROW_DELETE)
7763  {
7764  unique_stat_info = &(scan_cache->index_stat_info[i]);
7765  }
7766  else
7767  {
7768  unique_stat_info = NULL;
7769  }
7770  }
7771  if (use_mvcc)
7772  {
7773  btree_set_mvcc_header_ids_for_update (thread_p, !is_insert, is_insert, &mvccid, mvcc_rec_header);
7774  p_mvcc_rec_header = mvcc_rec_header;
7775  }
7776 
7777  if (is_insert)
7778  {
7779 #if defined(ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP)
7780  CUBRID_IDX_INSERT_START (classname, index->btname);
7781 #endif /* ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP */
7782 
7783  if (index->type == BTREE_FOREIGN_KEY)
7784  {
7785  if (lock_object (thread_p, inst_oid, class_oid, X_LOCK, LK_UNCOND_LOCK) != LK_GRANTED)
7786  {
7787  goto error;
7788  }
7789  }
7790 
7791  error_code =
7792  btree_insert (thread_p, &btid, key_dbvalue, class_oid, inst_oid, op_type, unique_stat_info,
7793  &dummy_unique, p_mvcc_rec_header);
7794 
7795 #if defined(ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP)
7796  CUBRID_IDX_INSERT_END (classname, index->btname, (error_code != NO_ERROR));
7797 #endif /* ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP */
7798  }
7799  else
7800  {
7801 #if defined(ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP)
7802  CUBRID_IDX_DELETE_START (classname, index->btname);
7803 #endif /* ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP */
7804 
7805  if (use_mvcc == true)
7806  {
7807  /* in MVCC logical deletion means MVCC DEL_ID insertion */
7808  error_code =
7809  btree_mvcc_delete (thread_p, &btid, key_dbvalue, class_oid, inst_oid, op_type, unique_stat_info,
7810  &dummy_unique, p_mvcc_rec_header);
7811  }
7812  else
7813  {
7814  error_code =
7815  btree_physical_delete (thread_p, &btid, key_dbvalue, inst_oid, class_oid, &dummy_unique, op_type,
7816  unique_stat_info);
7817  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
7818  {
7819  ASSERT_ERROR ();
7820 
7821 #if defined(ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP)
7822  CUBRID_IDX_DELETE_END (classname, index->btname, 1);
7823 #endif /* ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP */
7824 
7825  goto error;
7826  }
7827  }
7828 #if defined(ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP)
7829  CUBRID_IDX_DELETE_END (classname, index->btname, (error_code != NO_ERROR));
7830 #endif /* ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP */
7831 
7832  }
7833  }
7834 
7835  if (!locator_Dont_check_foreign_key && index->type == BTREE_PRIMARY_KEY && index->fk)
7836  {
7837  /* actually key_prefix_length is -1 for BTREE_PRIMARY_KEY; must be changed when key_prefix_length will be
7838  * added to FK and PK */
7839  if (is_insert)
7840  {
7841  ; /* nop */
7842  }
7843  else
7844  {
7845  if (idx_action_flag == FOR_MOVE)
7846  {
7847  /* This delete is caused by 'UPDATE ... SET ...' between partitioned tables. It first delete a
7848  * record in a partitioned table and insert a record in another partitioned table. It should check
7849  * the 'ON UPDATE ...' condition, not check 'ON DELETE ...' condition. */
7850  error_code = locator_check_primary_key_update (thread_p, index, key_dbvalue);
7851  }
7852  else
7853  {
7854  error_code = locator_check_primary_key_delete (thread_p, index, key_dbvalue);
7855  }
7856  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
7857  {
7858  goto error;
7859  }
7860  }
7861  }
7862 
7863  /*
7864  * for replication,
7865  * Following step would be executed only when the target index is a
7866  * primary key.
7867  * The right place to insert a replication log info is here
7868  * to avoid another "fetching key values"
7869  * Generates the replication log info. for data insert/delete
7870  * for the update cases, refer to locator_update_force()
7871  */
7872  if (need_replication && index->type == BTREE_PRIMARY_KEY && error_code == NO_ERROR
7873  && !LOG_CHECK_LOG_APPLIER (thread_p) && log_does_allow_replication () == true)
7874  {
7875  error_code =
7876  repl_log_insert (thread_p, class_oid, inst_oid, datayn ? LOG_REPLICATION_DATA : LOG_REPLICATION_STATEMENT,
7877  is_insert ? RVREPL_DATA_INSERT : RVREPL_DATA_DELETE, key_dbvalue,
7878  REPL_INFO_TYPE_RBR_NORMAL);
7879  }
7880  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
7881  {
7882  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
7883  goto error;
7884  }
7885 
7886 #if 0
7887  if (key_ins_del != NULL && !DB_IS_NULL (key_dbvalue) && !btree_multicol_key_is_null (key_dbvalue))
7888  {
7889  BTREE_CHECKSCAN bt_checkscan;
7890  DISK_ISVALID isvalid = DISK_VALID;
7891 
7892  /* start a check-scan on index */
7893  if (btree_keyoid_checkscan_start (thread_p, &btid, &bt_checkscan) != NO_ERROR)
7894  {
7895  goto error;
7896  }
7897 
7898  isvalid = btree_keyoid_checkscan_check (thread_p, &bt_checkscan, class_oid, key_dbvalue, inst_oid);
7899 
7900  if (er_errid () == ER_INTERRUPTED)
7901  {
7902  /* in case of user interrupt */
7903  ; /* do not check isvalid */
7904  }
7905  else
7906  {
7907  if (is_insert)
7908  {
7909  assert (isvalid == DISK_VALID); /* found */
7910  }
7911  else
7912  {
7913  assert (isvalid == DISK_INVALID); /* not found */
7914  }
7915  }
7916 
7917  /* close the index check-scan */
7918  btree_keyoid_checkscan_end (thread_p, &bt_checkscan);
7919  }
7920 #endif
7921 
7922  if (key_dbvalue == &dbvalue)
7923  {
7924  pr_clear_value (&dbvalue);
7925  key_dbvalue = NULL;
7926  }
7927  }
7928 
7929 error:
7930 
7931  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, &index_attrinfo);
7932 
7933  if (key_dbvalue == &dbvalue)
7934  {
7935  pr_clear_value (&dbvalue);
7936  key_dbvalue = NULL;
7937  }
7938 
7939 #if defined(ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP)
7940  if (classname != NULL)
7941  {
7942  free_and_init (classname);
7943  }
7944 #endif /* ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP */
7945 
7946  return error_code;
7947 }
7948 
7949 #if defined(ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
7950 /*
7951  * locator_make_midxkey_domain () -
7952  *
7953  * return:
7954  *
7955  * index(in):
7956  */
7957 static TP_DOMAIN *
7958 locator_make_midxkey_domain (OR_INDEX * index)
7959 {
7960  TP_DOMAIN *set_domain;
7961  TP_DOMAIN *domain = NULL;
7962 
7963  OR_ATTRIBUTE **atts;
7964  int num_atts, i;
7965 
7966  if (index == NULL || index->n_atts < 2)
7967  {
7968  return NULL;
7969  }
7970 
7971  num_atts = index->n_atts;
7972  atts = index->atts;
7973 
7974  set_domain = NULL;
7975  for (i = 0; i < num_atts; i++)
7976  {
7977  if (i == 0)
7978  {
7979  set_domain = tp_domain_copy (atts[i]->domain, 0);
7980  if (set_domain == NULL)
7981  {
7982  return NULL;
7983  }
7984  domain = set_domain;
7985  }
7986  else
7987  {
7988  domain->next = tp_domain_copy (atts[i]->domain, 0);
7989  if (domain->next == NULL)
7990  {
7991  goto error;
7992  }
7993  domain = domain->next;
7994  }
7995  }
7996 
7997  domain = tp_domain_construct (DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY, (DB_OBJECT *) 0, num_atts, 0, set_domain);
7998 
7999  if (domain)
8000  {
8001  return tp_domain_cache (domain);
8002  }
8003  else
8004  {
8005  goto error;
8006  }
8007 
8008 error:
8009 
8010  if (set_domain)
8011  {
8012  TP_DOMAIN *td, *next;
8013 
8014  /* tp_domain_free(set_domain); */
8015  for (td = set_domain, next = NULL; td != NULL; td = next)
8016  {
8017  next = td->next;
8018  tp_domain_free (td);
8019  }
8020  }
8021 
8022  return NULL;
8023 }
8024 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
8025 
8026 /*
8027  * locator_eval_filter_predicate () - evaluate index filter predicate
8028  *
8029  * return: error code
8030  *
8031  * btid(in): btid of index
8032  * or_pred(in): index filter predicate
8033  * class_oid(in): object identifier of the class
8034  * inst_oids(in): object identifiers of the instances
8035  * num_insts(in): the length of inst_oids, recs, results
8036  * recs(in): record descriptors
8037  * results(out): predicate evaluation results
8038  */
8039 static int
8040 locator_eval_filter_predicate (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, BTID * btid, OR_PREDICATE * or_pred, OID * class_oid,
8041  OID ** inst_oids, int num_insts, RECDES ** recs, DB_LOGICAL * results)
8042 {
8043  int i;
8044  PRED_EXPR_WITH_CONTEXT *pred_filter = NULL;
8045  PR_EVAL_FNC filter_eval_func = NULL;
8046  DB_TYPE single_node_type = DB_TYPE_NULL;
8047  HL_HEAPID old_pri_heap_id = HL_NULL_HEAPID;
8048  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
8049 
8050  if (or_pred == NULL || class_oid == NULL || recs == NULL || inst_oids == NULL || num_insts <= 0 || results == NULL
8051  || or_pred->pred_stream == NULL || btid == NULL)
8052  {
8053  assert (false);
8054  return ER_FAILED;
8055  }
8056 
8057  error_code = fpcache_claim (thread_p, btid, or_pred, &pred_filter);
8058  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
8059  {
8060  ASSERT_ERROR ();
8061  return error_code;
8062  }
8063  assert (pred_filter != NULL);
8064 
8065  error_code =
8066  heap_attrinfo_start (thread_p, class_oid, pred_filter->num_attrs_pred, pred_filter->attrids_pred,
8067  pred_filter->cache_pred);
8068  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
8069  {
8070  ASSERT_ERROR ();
8071  goto end;
8072  }
8073  filter_eval_func = eval_fnc (thread_p, pred_filter->pred, &single_node_type);
8074  assert (filter_eval_func != NULL);
8075 
8076  for (i = 0; i < num_insts; i++)
8077  {
8078  error_code = heap_attrinfo_read_dbvalues (thread_p, inst_oids[i], recs[i], NULL, pred_filter->cache_pred);
8079  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
8080  {
8081  goto end;
8082  }
8083 
8084  /* use global heap for memory allocation */
8085  old_pri_heap_id = db_change_private_heap (thread_p, 0);
8086  results[i] = (*filter_eval_func) (thread_p, pred_filter->pred, NULL, inst_oids[i]);
8087  if (results[i] == V_ERROR)
8088  {
8089  /* restore private heap */
8090  (void) db_change_private_heap (thread_p, old_pri_heap_id);
8091  error_code = ER_FAILED;
8092  goto end;
8093  }
8094  /* restore private heap */
8095  (void) db_change_private_heap (thread_p, old_pri_heap_id);
8096  }
8097 
8098 end:
8099  if (pred_filter)
8100  {
8101  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, pred_filter->cache_pred);
8102  /* Except for db_value regu variable, all regu variables from pred expression are cleared. */
8103  old_pri_heap_id = db_change_private_heap (thread_p, 0);
8104  qexec_clear_pred_context (thread_p, pred_filter, false);
8105  (void) db_change_private_heap (thread_p, old_pri_heap_id);
8106  }
8107 
8108  fpcache_retire (thread_p, class_oid, btid, pred_filter);
8109  return error_code;
8110 }
8111 
8112 /*
8113  * locator_update_index () - Update index entries
8114  *
8115  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
8116  *
8117  * new_recdes(in): The new recdes object
8118  * old_recdes(in): The old recdes object
8119  * att_id(in): Updated attr id array
8120  * n_att_id(in): Updated attr id array length
8121  * oid(in): The identifier of old/new object
8122  * class_oid(in): The class object identifier
8123  * op_type(in):
8124  * scan_cache(in):
8125  * repl_info(in/out): replication info, set need_replication to false when
8126  * no primary is found
8127  *
8128  * Note: Update the index entries of the given object.
8129  */
8130 int
8131 locator_update_index (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, RECDES * new_recdes, RECDES * old_recdes, ATTR_ID * att_id, int n_att_id,
8132  OID * oid, OID * class_oid, int op_type, HEAP_SCANCACHE * scan_cache, REPL_INFO * repl_info)
8133 {
8134  HEAP_CACHE_ATTRINFO space_attrinfo[2];
8135  HEAP_CACHE_ATTRINFO *new_attrinfo = NULL;
8136  HEAP_CACHE_ATTRINFO *old_attrinfo = NULL;
8137  int new_num_found, old_num_found;
8138  BTID new_btid, old_btid;
8139  int pk_btid_index = -1;
8140  DB_VALUE *new_key = NULL, *old_key = NULL;
8141  DB_VALUE *repl_old_key = NULL;
8142  DB_VALUE new_dbvalue, old_dbvalue;
8143  bool new_isnull, old_isnull;
8144  PR_TYPE *pr_type;
8145  OR_INDEX *index = NULL;
8146  int i, j, k, num_btids, old_num_btids, unique;
8147  bool found_btid = true;
8148  BTREE_UNIQUE_STATS *unique_stat_info;
8149  HEAP_IDX_ELEMENTS_INFO new_idx_info;
8150  HEAP_IDX_ELEMENTS_INFO old_idx_info;
8151  char newbuf[DBVAL_BUFSIZE + MAX_ALIGNMENT], *aligned_newbuf;
8152  char oldbuf[DBVAL_BUFSIZE + MAX_ALIGNMENT], *aligned_oldbuf;
8153  DB_TYPE dbval_type;
8154  TP_DOMAIN *key_domain = NULL;
8155  int error_code;
8156  DB_LOGICAL ev_results[2];
8157  bool do_delete_only = false;
8158  bool do_insert_only = false;
8159  OID *inst_oids[2];
8160  RECDES *recs[2];
8161  bool same_key = true;
8162  int c = DB_UNK;
8163  bool use_mvcc = false;
8164  MVCC_REC_HEADER *p_mvcc_rec_header = NULL;
8165  /* TODO: MVCC_BTREE_DELETE_OBJECT is removed due to recovery issue regarding MVCCID. Must find a solution to recover
8166  * MVCC info on rollback (otherwise we will have inconsistencies regarding visibility). */
8167  /* MVCC_BTREE_OP_ARGUMENTS mvcc_args, *mvcc_args_p = NULL; */
8168  MVCCID mvccid;
8169 /* temporary disable standalone optimization (non-mvcc insert/delete style).
8170  * Must be activated when dynamic heap is introduced */
8171 /* #if defined(SERVER_MODE) */
8172  MVCC_REC_HEADER mvcc_rec_header[2];
8173 /* #endif */
8174 #if defined(ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP)
8175  char *classname = NULL;
8176  bool is_started = false;
8177 #endif /* ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP */
8178  LOG_TDES *tdes;
8179  LOG_LSA preserved_repl_lsa;
8180  int tran_index;
8181 
8182  assert_release (class_oid != NULL);
8183  assert_release (!OID_ISNULL (class_oid));
8184 
8185  mvccid = MVCCID_NULL;
8186 
8187 #if defined(SERVER_MODE)
8188  if (!mvcc_is_mvcc_disabled_class (class_oid))
8189  {
8190  use_mvcc = true;
8191 
8192  mvccid = logtb_get_current_mvccid (thread_p);
8193  }
8194 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
8195 
8196  LSA_SET_NULL (&preserved_repl_lsa);
8197 
8198  db_make_null (&new_dbvalue);
8199  db_make_null (&old_dbvalue);
8200 
8201  aligned_newbuf = PTR_ALIGN (newbuf, MAX_ALIGNMENT);
8202  aligned_oldbuf = PTR_ALIGN (oldbuf, MAX_ALIGNMENT);
8203 
8204  new_num_found = heap_attrinfo_start_with_index (thread_p, class_oid, NULL, &space_attrinfo[0], &new_idx_info);
8205  num_btids = new_idx_info.num_btids;
8206  if (new_num_found < 0)
8207  {
8208  return ER_FAILED;
8209  }
8210  new_attrinfo = &space_attrinfo[0];
8211 
8212  old_num_found = heap_attrinfo_start_with_index (thread_p, class_oid, NULL, &space_attrinfo[1], &old_idx_info);
8213  old_num_btids = old_idx_info.num_btids;
8214  if (old_num_found < 0)
8215  {
8216  error_code = ER_FAILED;
8217  goto error;
8218  }
8219  old_attrinfo = &space_attrinfo[1];
8220 
8221  if (new_num_found != old_num_found)
8222  {
8223  if (new_num_found > 0)
8224  {
8225  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, &space_attrinfo[0]);
8226  }
8227  if (old_num_found > 0)
8228  {
8229  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, &space_attrinfo[1]);
8230  }
8231  return ER_FAILED;
8232  }
8233 
8234  if (new_num_found == 0)
8235  {
8236  /* No need to replicate this record since there is no primary key */
8237  if (repl_info != NULL)
8238  {
8239  repl_info->need_replication = false;
8240  }
8241 
8242  return NO_ERROR;
8243  }
8244 
8245  /*
8246  * There are indices and the index attrinfo has been initialized
8247  * Indices must be updated when the indexed attributes have changed in value
8248  * Get the new and old values of key and update the index when
8249  * the keys are different
8250  */
8251 
8252  new_attrinfo = &space_attrinfo[0];
8253  old_attrinfo = &space_attrinfo[1];
8254 
8255  error_code = heap_attrinfo_read_dbvalues (thread_p, oid, new_recdes, NULL, new_attrinfo);
8256  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
8257  {
8258  goto error;
8259  }
8260  error_code = heap_attrinfo_read_dbvalues (thread_p, oid, old_recdes, NULL, old_attrinfo);
8261  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
8262  {
8263  goto error;
8264  }
8265 
8266  /*
8267  * Ensure that we have the same number of indexes and
8268  * get the number of B-tree IDs.
8269  */
8270  if (old_attrinfo->last_classrepr->n_indexes != new_attrinfo->last_classrepr->n_indexes)
8271  {
8272  error_code = ER_FAILED;
8273  goto error;
8274  }
8275 
8276 #if defined(ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP)
8277  if (heap_get_class_name (thread_p, class_oid, &classname) != NO_ERROR || classname == NULL)
8278  {
8279  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
8280  goto error;
8281  }
8282 #endif /* ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP */
8283 
8284  for (i = 0; i < num_btids; i++)
8285  {
8286  index = &(new_attrinfo->last_classrepr->indexes[i]);
8287  if (pk_btid_index == -1 && repl_info != NULL && repl_info->need_replication == true
8288  && !LOG_CHECK_LOG_APPLIER (thread_p) && index->type == BTREE_PRIMARY_KEY
8289  && log_does_allow_replication () == true)
8290  {
8291  pk_btid_index = i;
8292  }
8293 
8294  /* check for specified update attributes */
8295  if ((att_id != NULL) && ((use_mvcc == false) || (index->type == BTREE_PRIMARY_KEY && index->fk != NULL)))
8296  {
8297  found_btid = false; /* guess as not found */
8298 
8299  for (j = 0; j < n_att_id && !found_btid; j++)
8300  {
8301  for (k = 0; k < index->n_atts && !found_btid; k++)
8302  {
8303  if (att_id[j] == (ATTR_ID) (index->atts[k]->id))
8304  { /* the index key_type has updated attr */
8305  found_btid = true;
8306  }
8307  }
8308  }
8309 
8310  /* in MVCC, in case of BTREE_PRIMARY_KEY having FK need to update PK index but skip foreign key restrictions
8311  * checking */
8312  if (!found_btid && !index->filter_predicate && (index->type != BTREE_PRIMARY_KEY || index->fk == NULL))
8313  {
8314  continue; /* skip and go ahead */
8315  }
8316  }
8317 
8318  do_delete_only = false;
8319  do_insert_only = false;
8320  if (index->filter_predicate)
8321  {
8322  inst_oids[0] = inst_oids[1] = oid;
8323  recs[0] = old_recdes;
8324  recs[1] = new_recdes;
8325  error_code =
8326  locator_eval_filter_predicate (thread_p, &index->btid, index->filter_predicate, class_oid, inst_oids, 2,
8327  recs, ev_results);
8328  if (error_code == ER_FAILED)
8329  {
8330  goto error;
8331  }
8332 
8333  if (ev_results[0] != V_TRUE)
8334  {
8335  if (ev_results[1] != V_TRUE)
8336  {
8337  /* the old rec and the new rec does not satisfied the filter predicate */
8338  continue;
8339  }
8340  else
8341  {
8342  /* the old rec does not satisfied the filter predicate */
8343  /* the new rec satisfied the filter predicate */
8344  do_insert_only = true;
8345  }
8346  }
8347  else
8348  {
8349  if (ev_results[1] != V_TRUE)
8350  {
8351  /* the old rec satisfied the filter predicate the new rec does not satisfied the filter predicate */
8352  do_delete_only = true;
8353  }
8354  else
8355  {
8356  if (found_btid == false)
8357  {
8358  /* the old rec satisfied the filter predicate the new rec satisfied the filter predicate the
8359  * index does not contain updated attributes */
8360  continue;
8361  }
8362  /* nothing to do - update operation */
8363  }
8364  }
8365  }
8366 
8367  new_key =
8368  heap_attrvalue_get_key (thread_p, i, new_attrinfo, new_recdes, &new_btid, &new_dbvalue, aligned_newbuf, NULL,
8369  NULL);
8370  old_key =
8371  heap_attrvalue_get_key (thread_p, i, old_attrinfo, old_recdes, &old_btid, &old_dbvalue, aligned_oldbuf, NULL,
8372  &key_domain);
8373 
8374  if ((new_key == NULL) || (old_key == NULL))
8375  {
8376  error_code = ER_FAILED;
8377  goto error;
8378  }
8379 
8380  dbval_type = DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (old_key);
8381  if (DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (new_key) != dbval_type)
8382  {
8383  error_code = ER_FAILED;
8384  goto error;
8385  }
8386 
8387  if (scan_cache == NULL)
8388  {
8389  unique_stat_info = NULL;
8390  }
8391  else
8392  {
8393  if (op_type == MULTI_ROW_UPDATE || op_type == MULTI_ROW_INSERT || op_type == MULTI_ROW_DELETE)
8394  {
8395  unique_stat_info = &(scan_cache->index_stat_info[i]);
8396  }
8397  else
8398  {
8399  unique_stat_info = NULL;
8400  }
8401  }
8402 
8403  new_isnull = db_value_is_null (new_key);
8404  old_isnull = db_value_is_null (old_key);
8405  pr_type = PR_TYPE_FROM_ID (dbval_type);
8406  if (pr_type == NULL)
8407  {
8408  error_code = ER_FAILED;
8409  goto error;
8410  }
8411 
8412  assert (key_domain != NULL);
8413  if (pr_type->id == DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY)
8414  {
8415  assert (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (key_domain) == DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY);
8416  new_key->data.midxkey.domain = old_key->data.midxkey.domain = key_domain;
8417  }
8418  else
8419  {
8420  assert (old_isnull || TP_ARE_COMPARABLE_KEY_TYPES (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (key_domain), pr_type->id));
8421  }
8422 
8423  same_key = true; /* init */
8424  if ((new_isnull && !old_isnull) || (old_isnull && !new_isnull))
8425  {
8426  same_key = false;
8427  }
8428  else
8429  {
8430  if (!(new_isnull && old_isnull))
8431  {
8432  c = btree_compare_key (old_key, new_key, key_domain, 0, 1, NULL);
8433 
8434  if (c == DB_UNK)
8435  {
8436  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
8437  error_code = er_errid ();
8438  goto error;
8439  }
8440 
8441  if (c != DB_EQ)
8442  {
8443  same_key = false;
8444  }
8445  }
8446  }
8447 
8448 #if defined(ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP)
8449  CUBRID_IDX_UPDATE_START (classname, index->btname);
8450  is_started = true;
8451 #endif /* ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP */
8452 
8453  if (!same_key || do_delete_only || do_insert_only)
8454  {
8455  if (i < 1 || !locator_was_index_already_applied (new_attrinfo, &index->btid, i))
8456  {
8457  if (mvccid != MVCCID_NULL)
8458  {
8459  btree_set_mvcc_header_ids_for_update (thread_p, do_delete_only, do_insert_only, &mvccid,
8460  mvcc_rec_header);
8461  p_mvcc_rec_header = mvcc_rec_header;
8462  }
8463  if (do_delete_only)
8464  {
8465  if (use_mvcc)
8466  {
8467  /* in MVCC logical deletion means MVCC DEL_ID insertion */
8468  error_code =
8469  btree_mvcc_delete (thread_p, &old_btid, old_key, class_oid, oid, op_type, unique_stat_info,
8470  &unique, p_mvcc_rec_header);
8471  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
8472  {
8473  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
8474  goto error;
8475  }
8476  }
8477  else
8478  {
8479  error_code =
8480  btree_physical_delete (thread_p, &old_btid, old_key, oid, class_oid, &unique, op_type,
8481  unique_stat_info);
8482  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
8483  {
8484  ASSERT_ERROR ();
8485  goto error;
8486  }
8487  }
8488  }
8489  else
8490  {
8491  /* in MVCC - update index key means insert index key */
8492  if ((do_insert_only == true))
8493  {
8494  if (index->type == BTREE_FOREIGN_KEY)
8495  {
8496  if (lock_object (thread_p, oid, class_oid, X_LOCK, LK_UNCOND_LOCK) != LK_GRANTED)
8497  {
8498  goto error;
8499  }
8500  }
8501 
8502  error_code =
8503  btree_insert (thread_p, &old_btid, new_key, class_oid, oid, op_type, unique_stat_info,
8504  &unique, p_mvcc_rec_header);
8505  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
8506  {
8507  ASSERT_ERROR ();
8508  goto error;
8509  }
8510  }
8511  else
8512  {
8513  error_code =
8514  btree_update (thread_p, &old_btid, old_key, new_key, class_oid, oid, op_type,
8515  unique_stat_info, &unique, p_mvcc_rec_header);
8516 
8517  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
8518  {
8519  goto error;
8520  }
8521  }
8522  }
8523  }
8524 
8525 #if defined(ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP)
8526  CUBRID_IDX_UPDATE_END (classname, index->btname, 0);
8527 #endif /* ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP */
8528 
8529  /* In MVCC need to check for specified update attributes */
8530  if (!locator_Dont_check_foreign_key && !same_key && index->type == BTREE_PRIMARY_KEY && index->fk
8531  && found_btid)
8532  {
8533  assert (do_insert_only == false && do_delete_only == false);
8534 
8535  tran_index = LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p);
8536  tdes = LOG_FIND_TDES (tran_index);
8537 
8538  if (pk_btid_index == i)
8539  {
8540  /*
8541  * save lsa before it is overwritten by FK action. No need
8542  * to consider in-place update (repl_update_lsa) since it updates
8543  * index first and then updates heap
8544  */
8545  LSA_COPY (&preserved_repl_lsa, &tdes->repl_insert_lsa);
8546  LSA_SET_NULL (&tdes->repl_insert_lsa);
8547  }
8548 
8549  error_code = locator_check_primary_key_update (thread_p, index, old_key);
8550  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
8551  {
8552  goto error;
8553  }
8554 
8555  if (pk_btid_index == i)
8556  {
8557  /* restore repl_insert_lsa */
8558  assert (LSA_ISNULL (&tdes->repl_insert_lsa));
8559  LSA_COPY (&tdes->repl_insert_lsa, &preserved_repl_lsa);
8560  }
8561  }
8562 
8563 #if 0
8564  {
8565  BTREE_CHECKSCAN bt_checkscan;
8566  DISK_ISVALID isvalid = DISK_VALID;
8567 
8568  /* start a check-scan on index */
8569  if (btree_keyoid_checkscan_start (thread_p, &old_btid, &bt_checkscan) != NO_ERROR)
8570  {
8571  goto error;
8572  }
8573 
8574  if (!do_insert_only && !DB_IS_NULL (old_key) && !btree_multicol_key_is_null (old_key))
8575  {
8576  isvalid = btree_keyoid_checkscan_check (thread_p, &bt_checkscan, class_oid, old_key, old_oid);
8577 
8578  if (er_errid () == ER_INTERRUPTED)
8579  {
8580  /* in case of user interrupt */
8581  ; /* do not check isvalid */
8582  }
8583  else
8584  {
8585  assert (isvalid == DISK_INVALID); /* not found */
8586  }
8587  }
8588 
8589  if (!do_delete_only && !DB_IS_NULL (new_key) && !btree_multicol_key_is_null (new_key))
8590  {
8591 
8592  isvalid = btree_keyoid_checkscan_check (thread_p, &bt_checkscan, class_oid, new_key, new_oid);
8593  if (er_errid () == ER_INTERRUPTED)
8594  {
8595  /* in case of user interrupt */
8596  ; /* do not check isvalid */
8597  }
8598  else
8599  {
8600  assert (isvalid == DISK_VALID); /* found */
8601  }
8602  }
8603 
8604  /* close the index check-scan */
8605  btree_keyoid_checkscan_end (thread_p, &bt_checkscan);
8606  }
8607 #endif
8608  }
8609 
8610  if (pk_btid_index == i && repl_old_key == NULL)
8611  {
8612  repl_old_key = pr_make_ext_value ();
8613  pr_clone_value (old_key, repl_old_key);
8614  }
8615 
8616  if (new_key == &new_dbvalue)
8617  {
8618  pr_clear_value (&new_dbvalue);
8619  new_key = NULL;
8620  }
8621  if (old_key == &old_dbvalue)
8622  {
8623  pr_clear_value (&old_dbvalue);
8624  old_key = NULL;
8625  }
8626  }
8627 
8628  if (pk_btid_index != -1)
8629  {
8630  assert (repl_info != NULL);
8631 
8632  if (repl_old_key == NULL)
8633  {
8634  key_domain = NULL;
8635  repl_old_key =
8636  heap_attrvalue_get_key (thread_p, pk_btid_index, old_attrinfo, old_recdes, &old_btid, &old_dbvalue,
8637  aligned_oldbuf, NULL, &key_domain);
8638  if (repl_old_key == NULL)
8639  {
8640  error_code = ER_FAILED;
8641  goto error;
8642  }
8643 
8644  old_isnull = db_value_is_null (repl_old_key);
8645  pr_type = pr_type_from_id (DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (repl_old_key));
8646  if (pr_type == NULL)
8647  {
8648  error_code = ER_FAILED;
8649  goto error;
8650  }
8651 
8652  if (pr_type->id == DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY)
8653  {
8654  /*
8655  * The asc/desc properties in midxkey from log_applier may be
8656  * inaccurate. therefore, we should use btree header's domain
8657  * while processing btree search request from log_applier.
8658  */
8659  repl_old_key->data.midxkey.domain = key_domain;
8660  }
8661 
8662  error_code =
8663  repl_log_insert (thread_p, class_oid, oid, LOG_REPLICATION_DATA, RVREPL_DATA_UPDATE, repl_old_key,
8664  (REPL_INFO_TYPE) repl_info->repl_info_type);
8665  if (repl_old_key == &old_dbvalue)
8666  {
8667  pr_clear_value (&old_dbvalue);
8668  }
8669  }
8670  else
8671  {
8672  error_code =
8673  repl_log_insert (thread_p, class_oid, oid, LOG_REPLICATION_DATA, RVREPL_DATA_UPDATE, repl_old_key,
8674  (REPL_INFO_TYPE) repl_info->repl_info_type);
8675  pr_free_ext_value (repl_old_key);
8676  repl_old_key = NULL;
8677  }
8678  }
8679  else
8680  {
8681  /*
8682  * clear repl_insert_lsa to make sure that FK action
8683  * does not overwrite the original update's target lsa.
8684  */
8685  tran_index = LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p);
8686  tdes = LOG_FIND_TDES (tran_index);
8687 
8688  LSA_SET_NULL (&tdes->repl_insert_lsa);
8689 
8690  /* No need to replicate this record since there is no primary key */
8691  if (repl_info != NULL)
8692  {
8693  repl_info->need_replication = false;
8694  }
8695  }
8696 
8697  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, new_attrinfo);
8698  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, old_attrinfo);
8699 
8700 #if defined(ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP)
8701  if (classname != NULL)
8702  {
8703  free_and_init (classname);
8704  }
8705 #endif /* ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP */
8706 
8707  return error_code;
8708 
8709 error:
8710 
8711  if (new_key == &new_dbvalue)
8712  {
8713  pr_clear_value (&new_dbvalue);
8714  new_key = NULL;
8715  }
8716  if (old_key == &old_dbvalue)
8717  {
8718  pr_clear_value (&old_dbvalue);
8719  old_key = NULL;
8720  }
8721 
8722  if (repl_old_key != NULL)
8723  {
8724  pr_free_ext_value (repl_old_key);
8725  }
8726 
8727  /* Deallocate any index_list .. if any */
8728 
8729  if (new_attrinfo != NULL)
8730  {
8731  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, new_attrinfo);
8732  }
8733 
8734  if (old_attrinfo != NULL)
8735  {
8736  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, old_attrinfo);
8737  }
8738 
8739 #if defined(ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP)
8740  if (is_started == true)
8741  {
8742  CUBRID_IDX_UPDATE_END (classname, index->btname, 1);
8743  }
8744  if (classname != NULL)
8745  {
8746  free_and_init (classname);
8747  }
8748 #endif /* ENABLE_SYSTEMTAP */
8749 
8750  return error_code;
8751 }
8752 
8753 /*
8754  * xlocator_remove_class_from_index () - Removes class instances from the B-tree
8755  *
8756  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
8757  *
8758  * class_oid(in): The class object identifier
8759  * btid(in): B-tree ID
8760  * hfid(in): Heap ID
8761  *
8762  * Note: This function searches for instances belonging to the passes
8763  * class OID and removes the ones found. This function is used to
8764  * remove a class from a spanning B-tree such as a UNIQUE.
8765  */
8766 int
8767 xlocator_remove_class_from_index (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OID * class_oid, BTID * btid, HFID * hfid)
8768 {
8769  HEAP_CACHE_ATTRINFO index_attrinfo;
8770  HEAP_SCANCACHE scan_cache;
8771  OID inst_oid, *p_inst_oid = &inst_oid;
8772  int key_index, i, num_btids, num_found, dummy_unique, key_found;
8773  RECDES copy_rec, *p_copy_rec = &copy_rec;
8774  BTID inst_btid;
8775  DB_VALUE dbvalue;
8776  DB_VALUE *dbvalue_ptr = NULL;
8777  SCAN_CODE scan;
8778  char *new_area;
8779  BTREE_UNIQUE_STATS unique_info;
8780  HEAP_IDX_ELEMENTS_INFO idx_info;
8781  char buf[DBVAL_BUFSIZE + MAX_ALIGNMENT], *aligned_buf;
8782  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
8783  OR_INDEX *index = NULL;
8784  DB_LOGICAL ev_res;
8785  MVCC_SNAPSHOT *mvcc_snapshot = NULL;
8786 
8787  if (class_oid != NULL && !OID_IS_ROOTOID (class_oid))
8788  {
8789  mvcc_snapshot = logtb_get_mvcc_snapshot (thread_p);
8790  if (mvcc_snapshot == NULL)
8791  {
8792  error_code = er_errid ();
8793  return (error_code == NO_ERROR ? ER_FAILED : error_code);
8794  }
8795  }
8796 
8797  db_make_null (&dbvalue);
8798 
8799  aligned_buf = PTR_ALIGN (buf, MAX_ALIGNMENT);
8800 
8801  /* allocate memory space for copying an instance image. */
8802  copy_rec.area_size = DB_PAGESIZE;
8803  copy_rec.data = (char *) malloc (copy_rec.area_size);
8804  if (copy_rec.data == NULL)
8805  {
8806  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) (copy_rec.area_size));
8807  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
8808  }
8809 
8810  /* initialize 'unique_info' structure. */
8811  BTID_COPY (&(unique_info.btid), btid);
8812  unique_info.num_nulls = 0;
8813  unique_info.num_keys = 0;
8814  unique_info.num_oids = 0;
8815 
8816  /* Start a scan cursor */
8817  error_code = heap_scancache_start (thread_p, &scan_cache, hfid, class_oid, false, false, mvcc_snapshot);
8818  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
8819  {
8820  free_and_init (copy_rec.data);
8821  return error_code;
8822  }
8823 
8824  /*
8825  * Populate the index_attrinfo structure.
8826  * Return the number of indexed attributes found.
8827  */
8828  num_found = heap_attrinfo_start_with_index (thread_p, class_oid, NULL, &index_attrinfo, &idx_info);
8829  num_btids = idx_info.num_btids;
8830  if (num_found < 1)
8831  {
8832  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache);
8833  free_and_init (copy_rec.data);
8834  return ER_FAILED;
8835  }
8836 
8837  /* Loop over each instance of the class found in the heap */
8838  inst_oid.volid = hfid->vfid.volid;
8839  inst_oid.pageid = NULL_PAGEID;
8840  inst_oid.slotid = NULL_SLOTID;
8841  key_found = false;
8842  key_index = 0;
8843 
8844  while (true)
8845  {
8846  if (dbvalue_ptr == &dbvalue)
8847  {
8848  pr_clear_value (&dbvalue);
8849  dbvalue_ptr = NULL;
8850  }
8851 
8852  scan = heap_next (thread_p, hfid, class_oid, &inst_oid, &copy_rec, &scan_cache, COPY);
8853  if (scan != S_SUCCESS)
8854  {
8855  if (scan != S_DOESNT_FIT)
8856  {
8857  break;
8858  }
8859 
8860  new_area = (char *) realloc (copy_rec.data, -(copy_rec.length));
8861  if (new_area == NULL)
8862  {
8863  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) (-(copy_rec.length)));
8864  error_code = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
8865  goto error;
8866  }
8867  copy_rec.area_size = -copy_rec.length;
8868  copy_rec.data = new_area;
8869  continue;
8870  }
8871 
8872  error_code = heap_attrinfo_read_dbvalues (thread_p, &inst_oid, &copy_rec, NULL, &index_attrinfo);
8873  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
8874  {
8875  goto error;
8876  }
8877 
8878  /* Find the correct key by matching the BTID */
8879  if (key_found == false)
8880  {
8881  for (i = 0; i < num_btids; i++)
8882  {
8883  if (dbvalue_ptr == &dbvalue)
8884  {
8885  pr_clear_value (&dbvalue);
8886  dbvalue_ptr = NULL;
8887  }
8888 
8889  dbvalue_ptr =
8890  heap_attrvalue_get_key (thread_p, i, &index_attrinfo, &copy_rec, &inst_btid, &dbvalue, aligned_buf,
8891  NULL, NULL);
8892  if (dbvalue_ptr == NULL)
8893  {
8894  continue;
8895  }
8896 
8897  if (BTID_IS_EQUAL (btid, &inst_btid))
8898  {
8899  key_found = true;
8900  key_index = i;
8901  index = &(index_attrinfo.last_classrepr->indexes[key_index]);
8902  break;
8903  }
8904  }
8905  }
8906  /*
8907  * We already know the correct BTID index (key_index) so just use it
8908  * to retrieve the key
8909  */
8910  else
8911  {
8912  dbvalue_ptr =
8913  heap_attrvalue_get_key (thread_p, key_index, &index_attrinfo, &copy_rec, &inst_btid, &dbvalue, aligned_buf,
8914  NULL, NULL);
8915  }
8916 
8917  /* Delete the instance from the B-tree */
8918  if (key_found == false || dbvalue_ptr == NULL)
8919  {
8920  error_code = ER_FAILED;
8921  goto error;
8922  }
8923 
8924  assert (index != NULL);
8925  if (index->filter_predicate)
8926  {
8927  error_code =
8928  locator_eval_filter_predicate (thread_p, &index->btid, index->filter_predicate, class_oid, &p_inst_oid, 1,
8929  &p_copy_rec, &ev_res);
8930  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
8931  {
8932  goto error;
8933  }
8934 
8935  if (ev_res != V_TRUE)
8936  {
8937  continue;
8938  }
8939  }
8940 
8941  error_code =
8942  btree_physical_delete (thread_p, btid, dbvalue_ptr, &inst_oid, class_oid, &dummy_unique, MULTI_ROW_DELETE,
8943  &unique_info);
8944  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
8945  {
8946  ASSERT_ERROR ();
8947  goto error;
8948  }
8949  }
8950 
8951  if (unique_info.num_nulls != 0 || unique_info.num_keys != 0 || unique_info.num_oids != 0)
8952  {
8953  error_code =
8954  logtb_tran_update_unique_stats (thread_p, btid, unique_info.num_keys, unique_info.num_oids,
8955  unique_info.num_nulls, true);
8956  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
8957  {
8958  goto error;
8959  }
8960  }
8961 
8962  error_code = heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache);
8963  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
8964  {
8965  goto error;
8966  }
8967  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, &index_attrinfo);
8968 
8969 end:
8970  if (copy_rec.data != NULL)
8971  {
8972  free_and_init (copy_rec.data);
8973  }
8974 
8975  if (dbvalue_ptr == &dbvalue)
8976  {
8977  pr_clear_value (dbvalue_ptr);
8978  dbvalue_ptr = NULL;
8979  }
8980 
8981  return error_code;
8982 
8983 error:
8984 
8985  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache);
8986  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, &index_attrinfo);
8987 
8988  goto end;
8989 }
8990 
8991 /*
8992  * locator_notify_decache () - Notify of a decache
8993  *
8994  * return:
8995  *
8996  * class_oid(in):
8997  * oid(in): Oid to decache
8998  * notify_area(in): Information used for notification purposes
8999  *
9000  * Note: Add an entry in the fetch area with respect to decaching an
9001  * object at the workspace.
9002  */
9003 static bool
9004 locator_notify_decache (const OID * class_oid, const OID * oid, void *notify_area)
9005 {
9006  LC_COPYAREA_DESC *notify;
9007  LC_COPYAREA_ONEOBJ *obj; /* Describe on object in area */
9008  int i;
9009 
9010  /* safe guard. oid must be not null. */
9011  if (OID_ISNULL (oid))
9012  {
9013  assert (false);
9014  return true;
9015  }
9016 
9017  notify = (LC_COPYAREA_DESC *) notify_area;
9018  if (notify->recdes->area_size <= SSIZEOF (**notify->obj))
9019  {
9020  return false;
9021  }
9022 
9023  /*
9024  * Make sure that the object is not already part of the notification area
9025  */
9026  obj = LC_START_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (notify->mobjs);
9027  obj = LC_PRIOR_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (obj);
9028  for (i = 0; i < notify->mobjs->num_objs; i++)
9029  {
9030  obj = LC_NEXT_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (obj);
9031  if (OID_EQ (&obj->oid, oid))
9032  {
9033  /* The object is already in the notification/fetch area */
9034  obj->operation = LC_FETCH_DECACHE_LOCK;
9035  return true;
9036  }
9037  }
9038  /*
9039  * The object was not part of the notification/fetch area
9040  */
9041  notify->mobjs->num_objs++;
9042  COPY_OID (&((*notify->obj)->class_oid), class_oid);
9043  COPY_OID (&((*notify->obj)->oid), oid);
9044  (*notify->obj)->flag = 0;
9045  (*notify->obj)->hfid = NULL_HFID;
9046  (*notify->obj)->length = -1;
9047  (*notify->obj)->operation = LC_FETCH_DECACHE_LOCK;
9048 
9049  (*notify->obj)->offset = -1;
9050  *notify->obj = LC_NEXT_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (*notify->obj);
9051  notify->recdes->area_size -= sizeof (**notify->obj);
9052 
9053  return true;
9054 }
9055 
9056 /*
9057  * xlocator_notify_isolation_incons () - Synchronize possible inconsistencies related
9058  * to non two phase locking
9059  *
9060  * return:
9061  *
9062  * synch_area(in): Pointer to area where the name of the objects are placed.
9063  *
9064  * Note: Notify all inconsistencies related to the transaction
9065  * isolation level.
9066  */
9067 bool
9068 xlocator_notify_isolation_incons (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LC_COPYAREA ** synch_area)
9069 {
9070  LC_COPYAREA_DESC prefetch_des; /* Descriptor for decache of objects related to transaction isolation level */
9071  LC_COPYAREA_MANYOBJS *mobjs; /* Describe multiple objects in area */
9072  LC_COPYAREA_ONEOBJ *obj; /* Describe on object in area */
9073  RECDES recdes; /* Record descriptor for insertion */
9074  int offset; /* Place to store next object in area */
9075  bool more_synch = false;
9076 
9077  *synch_area = locator_allocate_copy_area_by_length (DB_PAGESIZE);
9078  if (*synch_area == NULL)
9079  {
9080  return false;
9081  }
9082 
9083  mobjs = LC_MANYOBJS_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (*synch_area);
9084  LC_RECDES_IN_COPYAREA (*synch_area, &recdes);
9085  obj = LC_START_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (mobjs);
9086  mobjs->num_objs = 0;
9087  offset = 0;
9088 
9089  prefetch_des.mobjs = mobjs;
9090  prefetch_des.obj = &obj;
9091  prefetch_des.offset = &offset;
9092  prefetch_des.recdes = &recdes;
9093  lock_notify_isolation_incons (thread_p, locator_notify_decache, &prefetch_des);
9094  if (mobjs->num_objs == 0)
9095  {
9096  /*
9097  * Don't need to notify of any client workspace lock decaches
9098  * (i.e., possible object inconsistencies).
9099  */
9100  locator_free_copy_area (*synch_area);
9101  *synch_area = NULL;
9102  }
9103  else if (recdes.area_size >= SSIZEOF (*obj))
9104  {
9105  more_synch = true;
9106  }
9107 
9108  return more_synch;
9109 }
9110 
9111 static DISK_ISVALID
9112 locator_repair_btree_by_insert (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OID * class_oid, BTID * btid, DB_VALUE * key, OID * inst_oid)
9113 {
9114  DISK_ISVALID isvalid = DISK_INVALID;
9115 #if defined(SERVER_MODE)
9116  int tran_index;
9117 
9118  tran_index = LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p);
9119 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
9120 
9121  if (lock_object (thread_p, inst_oid, class_oid, X_LOCK, LK_UNCOND_LOCK) != LK_GRANTED)
9122  {
9123  return DISK_INVALID;
9124  }
9125 
9126  log_sysop_start (thread_p);
9127 
9128  if (btree_insert (thread_p, btid, key, class_oid, inst_oid, SINGLE_ROW_INSERT, NULL, NULL, NULL) == NO_ERROR)
