9129  {
9130  isvalid = DISK_VALID;
9131  log_sysop_commit (thread_p);
9132  }
9133  else
9134  {
9135  ASSERT_ERROR ();
9136  log_sysop_abort (thread_p);
9137  }
9138 
9139 #if defined(SERVER_MODE)
9140  lock_remove_all_inst_locks (thread_p, tran_index, class_oid, X_LOCK);
9141 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
9142 
9143  return isvalid;
9144 }
9145 
9146 static DISK_ISVALID
9147 locator_repair_btree_by_delete (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OID * class_oid, BTID * btid, OID * inst_oid)
9148 {
9149  DB_VALUE key;
9150  bool clear_key = false;
9151  int dummy_unique;
9152  DISK_ISVALID isvalid = DISK_INVALID;
9153 #if defined(SERVER_MODE)
9154  int tran_index;
9155 
9156  tran_index = LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p);
9157 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
9158 
9159  if (btree_find_key (thread_p, btid, inst_oid, &key, &clear_key) != DISK_VALID)
9160  {
9161  return DISK_INVALID;
9162  }
9163 
9164  if (lock_object (thread_p, inst_oid, class_oid, X_LOCK, LK_UNCOND_LOCK) == LK_GRANTED)
9165  {
9166  log_sysop_start (thread_p);
9167 
9168  if (btree_physical_delete (thread_p, btid, &key, inst_oid, class_oid, &dummy_unique, SINGLE_ROW_DELETE, NULL) ==
9169  NO_ERROR)
9170  {
9171  isvalid = DISK_VALID;
9172  log_sysop_commit (thread_p);
9173  }
9174  else
9175  {
9176  ASSERT_ERROR ();
9177  log_sysop_abort (thread_p);
9178  }
9179 
9180 #if defined(SERVER_MODE)
9181  lock_remove_all_inst_locks (thread_p, tran_index, class_oid, X_LOCK);
9182 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
9183  }
9184 
9185  if (clear_key)
9186  {
9187  pr_clear_value (&key);
9188  }
9189 
9190  return isvalid;
9191 }
9192 
9193 /*
9194  * locator_check_btree_entries () - Check consistency of btree entries and heap
9195  *
9196  * return: valid
9197  *
9198  * btid(in): Btree identifier
9199  * hfid(in): Heap identfier of the instances of class that are indexed
9200  * class_oid(in): The class identifier
9201  * n_attr_ids(in): Number of attribute ids (size of the array).
9202  * attr_ids(in): Attribute ID array.
9203  * btname(in) :
9204  * repair(in):
9205  *
9206  * Note: Check the consistency of the btree entries against the
9207  * instances stored on heap and vive versa.
9208  */
9209 DISK_ISVALID
9210 locator_check_btree_entries (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, BTID * btid, HFID * hfid, OID * class_oid, int n_attr_ids,
9211  ATTR_ID * attr_ids, int *atts_prefix_length, const char *btname, bool repair)
9212 {
9213  DISK_ISVALID isvalid = DISK_VALID;
9214  DISK_ISVALID isallvalid = DISK_VALID;
9215  OID inst_oid, *p_inst_oid = &inst_oid;
9216  RECDES record = RECDES_INITIALIZER, *recordp = &record; /* Record descriptor for copying object */
9217  SCAN_CODE scan;
9218  HEAP_SCANCACHE scan_cache;
9219  BTREE_CHECKSCAN bt_checkscan;
9220  BTREE_SCAN bt_scan;
9221  HEAP_CACHE_ATTRINFO attr_info;
9222  int num_btree_oids = 0;
9223  int num_heap_oids = 0;
9224  int oid_cnt;
9225  OID *oid_area = NULL;
9226  INDX_SCAN_ID isid;
9227  BTREE_ISCAN_OID_LIST oid_list;
9228  int i;
9229  DB_VALUE dbvalue;
9230  DB_VALUE *key = NULL;
9231  char buf[DBVAL_BUFSIZE + MAX_ALIGNMENT], *aligned_buf;
9232  char *classname = NULL;
9233  KEY_VAL_RANGE key_val_range;
9234  int index_id;
9235  OR_INDEX *index = NULL;
9236  DB_LOGICAL ev_res;
9237  OR_CLASSREP *classrepr = NULL;
9238  MVCC_SNAPSHOT *mvcc_snapshot = NULL;
9239  BTID btid_info;
9240 #if defined(SERVER_MODE)
9241  int tran_index;
9242 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
9243  bool is_scancache_started = false;
9244  bool is_attrinfo_started = false;
9245  bool is_bt_checkscan_started = false;
9246 
9247  mvcc_snapshot = logtb_get_mvcc_snapshot (thread_p);
9248  if (mvcc_snapshot == NULL)
9249  {
9250  return DISK_ERROR;
9251  }
9252  db_make_null (&dbvalue);
9253 
9254  aligned_buf = PTR_ALIGN (buf, MAX_ALIGNMENT);
9255 
9256 #if defined(SERVER_MODE)
9257  tran_index = LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p);
9258 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
9259 
9260  scan_init_index_scan (&isid, NULL, mvcc_snapshot);
9261 
9262  /* Start a scan cursor and a class attribute information */
9263  if (heap_scancache_start (thread_p, &scan_cache, hfid, class_oid, false, false, mvcc_snapshot) != NO_ERROR)
9264  {
9265  return DISK_ERROR;
9266  }
9267  is_scancache_started = true;
9268 
9269  if (heap_attrinfo_start (thread_p, class_oid, n_attr_ids, attr_ids, &attr_info) != NO_ERROR)
9270  {
9271  goto error;
9272  }
9273  is_attrinfo_started = true;
9274 
9275  classrepr = attr_info.last_classrepr;
9276  if (classrepr == NULL)
9277  {
9278  goto error;
9279  }
9280  index_id = -1;
9281  for (i = 0; i < classrepr->n_indexes; i++)
9282  {
9283  if (BTID_IS_EQUAL (&(classrepr->indexes[i].btid), btid))
9284  {
9285  index_id = i;
9286  break;
9287  }
9288  }
9289  assert (index_id != -1);
9290 
9291  index = &(attr_info.last_classrepr->indexes[index_id]);
9292  assert (index != NULL);
9293 
9294  /*
9295  * Step 1) From Heap to B+tree
9296  */
9297 
9298  /* start a check-scan on index */
9299  if (btree_keyoid_checkscan_start (thread_p, btid, &bt_checkscan) != NO_ERROR)
9300  {
9301  goto error;
9302  }
9303  is_bt_checkscan_started = true;
9304 
9305  inst_oid.volid = hfid->vfid.volid;
9306  inst_oid.pageid = NULL_PAGEID;
9307  inst_oid.slotid = NULL_SLOTID;
9308 
9309  while ((scan = heap_next (thread_p, hfid, class_oid, &inst_oid, &record, &scan_cache, COPY)) == S_SUCCESS)
9310  {
9311  num_heap_oids++;
9312 
9313  if (index->filter_predicate)
9314  {
9315  if (locator_eval_filter_predicate (thread_p, &index->btid, index->filter_predicate, class_oid, &p_inst_oid, 1,
9316  &recordp, &ev_res) != NO_ERROR)
9317  {
9318  isallvalid = DISK_ERROR;
9319  }
9320  else if (ev_res != V_TRUE)
9321  {
9322  /*
9323  * To exclude the heap OID of which record cannot satisfy the
9324  * conditions of the index filter predicate.
9325  */
9326  num_heap_oids--;
9327  continue;
9328  }
9329  }
9330 
9331  /* Make sure that the index entry exist */
9332  if ((n_attr_ids == 1 && heap_attrinfo_read_dbvalues (thread_p, &inst_oid, &record, NULL, &attr_info) != NO_ERROR)
9333  || (key = heap_attrvalue_get_key (thread_p, index_id, &attr_info, &record, &btid_info, &dbvalue, aligned_buf,
9334  NULL, NULL)) == NULL)
9335  {
9336  if (isallvalid != DISK_INVALID)
9337  {
9338  isallvalid = DISK_ERROR;
9339  }
9340  }
9341  else
9342  {
9343  assert (key != NULL);
9344 
9345  if (db_value_is_null (key) || btree_multicol_key_is_null (key))
9346  {
9347  /* Do not check the btree since unbound values are not recorded */
9348  num_heap_oids--;
9349  }
9350  else
9351  {
9352  isvalid = btree_keyoid_checkscan_check (thread_p, &bt_checkscan, class_oid, key, &inst_oid);
9353 
9354  if (er_errid () == ER_INTERRUPTED)
9355  {
9356  /* in case of user interrupt */
9357  goto error;
9358  }
9359 
9360  if (isvalid == DISK_INVALID)
9361  {
9362  if (repair)
9363  {
9364  isvalid = locator_repair_btree_by_insert (thread_p, class_oid, btid, key, &inst_oid);
9365  }
9366 
9367  if (isvalid == DISK_INVALID)
9368  {
9369  char *key_dmp;
9370 
9371  key_dmp = pr_valstring (thread_p, key);
9372 
9373  if (!OID_ISNULL (class_oid))
9374  {
9375  if (heap_get_class_name (thread_p, class_oid, &classname) != NO_ERROR)
9376  {
9377  /* ignore */
9378  er_clear ();
9379  }
9380  }
9381 
9382  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_LC_INCONSISTENT_BTREE_ENTRY_TYPE1, 12,
9383  (btname) ? btname : "*UNKNOWN-INDEX*", (classname) ? classname : "*UNKNOWN-CLASS*",
9384  class_oid->volid, class_oid->pageid, class_oid->slotid, (key_dmp) ? key_dmp : "_NULL_KEY",
9385  inst_oid.volid, inst_oid.pageid, inst_oid.slotid, btid->vfid.volid, btid->vfid.fileid,
9386  btid->root_pageid);
9387 
9388  if (key_dmp)
9389  {
9390  db_private_free (thread_p, key_dmp);
9391  }
9392 
9393  if (classname)
9394  {
9395  free_and_init (classname);
9396  }
9397 
9398  if (isallvalid != DISK_INVALID)
9399  {
9400  isallvalid = isvalid;
9401  }
9402  }
9403  }
9404  }
9405  }
9406 
9407  if (key == &dbvalue)
9408  {
9409  pr_clear_value (key);
9410  key = NULL;
9411  }
9412  }
9413 
9414  if (scan != S_END && isallvalid != DISK_INVALID)
9415  {
9416  isallvalid = DISK_ERROR;
9417  }
9418 
9419  /* close the index check-scan */
9420  btree_keyoid_checkscan_end (thread_p, &bt_checkscan);
9421  is_bt_checkscan_started = false;
9422 
9423  /* Finish scan cursor and class attribute cache information */
9424  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, &attr_info);
9425  is_attrinfo_started = false;
9426 
9427  /*
9428  * Step 2) From B+tree to Heap
9429  */
9430 
9431  BTREE_INIT_SCAN (&bt_scan);
9432 
9433  isid.oid_list = &oid_list;
9434  isid.oid_list->oid_cnt = 0;
9435  isid.oid_list->oidp = (OID *) malloc (ISCAN_OID_BUFFER_CAPACITY);
9436  if (isid.oid_list->oidp == NULL)
9437  {
9438  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) ISCAN_OID_BUFFER_SIZE);
9439 
9440  isallvalid = DISK_ERROR;
9441  goto error;
9442  }
9443  isid.oid_list->capacity = ISCAN_OID_BUFFER_CAPACITY / OR_OID_SIZE;
9444  isid.oid_list->max_oid_cnt = isid.oid_list->capacity;
9445  isid.oid_list->next_list = NULL;
9446  isid.indx_info = NULL;
9447 
9448  /* alloc index key copy_buf */
9449  isid.copy_buf = (char *) db_private_alloc (thread_p, DBVAL_BUFSIZE);
9450  if (isid.copy_buf == NULL)
9451  {
9452  isallvalid = DISK_ERROR;
9453  goto error;
9454  }
9455  isid.copy_buf_len = DBVAL_BUFSIZE;
9456  memset ((void *) (&(isid.indx_cov)), 0, sizeof (INDX_COV));
9457  memset ((void *) (&(isid.multi_range_opt)), 0, sizeof (MULTI_RANGE_OPT));
9458 
9459  scan_init_iss (&isid);
9460 
9461  if (heap_scancache_start (thread_p, &isid.scan_cache, hfid, class_oid, true, true, mvcc_snapshot) != NO_ERROR)
9462  {
9463  isallvalid = DISK_ERROR;
9464  goto error;
9465  }
9466 
9467  isid.check_not_vacuumed = true;
9468  db_make_null (&key_val_range.key1);
9469  db_make_null (&key_val_range.key2);
9470  key_val_range.range = INF_INF;
9471  key_val_range.num_index_term = 0;
9472  do
9473  {
9474  /* search index */
9475  if (btree_prepare_bts (thread_p, &bt_scan, btid, &isid, &key_val_range, NULL, class_oid, NULL, NULL, false, NULL)
9476  != NO_ERROR)
9477  {
9478  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
9479  break;
9480  }
9481  if (btree_range_scan (thread_p, &bt_scan, btree_range_scan_select_visible_oids) != NO_ERROR)
9482  {
9483  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
9484  break;
9485  }
9486  oid_cnt = bt_scan.n_oids_read_last_iteration;
9487  if (oid_cnt < 0)
9488  {
9489  assert (false);
9490  break;
9491  }
9492  oid_area = isid.oid_list->oidp;
9493  num_btree_oids += oid_cnt;
9494  for (i = 0; i < oid_cnt; i++)
9495  {
9496  if (!heap_does_exist (thread_p, class_oid, &oid_area[i]))
9497  {
9498  isvalid = DISK_INVALID;
9499 
9500  if (repair)
9501  {
9502  /* don't care about filter predicate here since we are sure that oid_area[i] is contained in tree,
9503  * the keys has been already S_LOCK-ed. */
9504  isvalid = locator_repair_btree_by_delete (thread_p, class_oid, btid, &oid_area[i]);
9505  }
9506 
9507  if (isvalid == DISK_VALID)
9508  {
9509  num_btree_oids--;
9510  }
9511  else
9512  {
9513  if (!OID_ISNULL (class_oid))
9514  {
9515  if (heap_get_class_name (thread_p, class_oid, &classname) != NO_ERROR)
9516  {
9517  /* ignore */
9518  er_clear ();
9519  }
9520  }
9521 
9522  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_LC_INCONSISTENT_BTREE_ENTRY_TYPE2, 11,
9523  (btname) ? btname : "*UNKNOWN-INDEX*", (classname) ? classname : "*UNKNOWN-CLASS*",
9524  class_oid->volid, class_oid->pageid, class_oid->slotid, oid_area[i].volid, oid_area[i].pageid,
9525  oid_area[i].slotid, btid->vfid.volid, btid->vfid.fileid, btid->root_pageid);
9526 
9527  if (classname)
9528  {
9529  free_and_init (classname);
9530  }
9531 
9532  isallvalid = DISK_INVALID;
9533  }
9534  }
9535  }
9536 
9537  }
9538  while (!BTREE_END_OF_SCAN (&bt_scan));
9539 
9540  if (heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &isid.scan_cache) != NO_ERROR)
9541  {
9542  isallvalid = DISK_INVALID;
9543  }
9544 
9545  if (num_heap_oids != num_btree_oids)
9546  {
9547  if (!OID_ISNULL (class_oid))
9548  {
9549  if (heap_get_class_name (thread_p, class_oid, &classname) != NO_ERROR)
9550  {
9551  /* ignore */
9552  er_clear ();
9553  }
9554  }
9555 
9556  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_LC_INCONSISTENT_BTREE_ENTRY_TYPE3, 10,
9557  (btname) ? btname : "*UNKNOWN-INDEX*", (classname) ? classname : "*UNKNOWN-CLASS*", class_oid->volid,
9558  class_oid->pageid, class_oid->slotid, num_heap_oids, num_btree_oids, btid->vfid.volid, btid->vfid.fileid,
9559  btid->root_pageid);
9560 
9561  if (classname)
9562  {
9563  free_and_init (classname);
9564  }
9565 
9566  isallvalid = DISK_INVALID;
9567  }
9568 
9569  if (isid.check_not_vacuumed && isid.not_vacuumed_res != DISK_VALID)
9570  {
9571  er_set (ER_FATAL_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_INDEX_FOUND_NOT_VACUUMED, 5,
9572  (btname) ? btname : "*UNKNOWN-INDEX*", (classname) ? classname : "*UNKNOWN-CLASS*", class_oid->volid,
9573  class_oid->pageid, class_oid->slotid);
9574  isallvalid = isid.not_vacuumed_res;
9575  }
9576 
9577 end:
9578 
9579  if (key == &dbvalue)
9580  {
9581  pr_clear_value (key);
9582  }
9583 
9584  if (isid.oid_list != NULL && isid.oid_list->oidp != NULL)
9585  {
9586  free_and_init (isid.oid_list->oidp);
9587  }
9588 
9589  /* free index key copy_buf */
9590  if (isid.copy_buf)
9591  {
9592  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isid.copy_buf);
9593  }
9594 
9595  if (is_scancache_started && heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache) != NO_ERROR)
9596  {
9597  isallvalid = DISK_INVALID;
9598  }
9599 
9600  if (is_bt_checkscan_started)
9601  {
9602  btree_keyoid_checkscan_end (thread_p, &bt_checkscan);
9603  }
9604 
9605  if (is_attrinfo_started)
9606  {
9607  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, &attr_info);
9608  }
9609 
9610  return isallvalid;
9611 
9612 error:
9613  isallvalid = DISK_ERROR;
9614  goto end;
9615 }
9616 
9617 /*
9618  * locator_check_unique_btree_entries () - Check consistency of unique btree entries
9619  * and heaps
9620  *
9621  * return: valid
9622  *
9623  * btid(in): Btree identifier
9624  * class_oid(in):
9625  * classrec(in):
9626  * attr_ids(in): Array of indexed attributes for the btid
9627  * repair(in):
9628  *
9629  * Note: Check the consistency of the unique btree entries against the
9630  * instances stored on heap and vice versa. Unique btrees are
9631  * special because they span hierarchies and can have multiple
9632  * heaps associated with them.
9633  */
9634 static DISK_ISVALID
9635 locator_check_unique_btree_entries (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, BTID * btid, OID * cls_oid, RECDES * classrec,
9636  ATTR_ID * attr_ids, const char *btname, bool repair)
9637 {
9638  DISK_ISVALID isvalid = DISK_VALID, isallvalid = DISK_VALID;
9639  OID inst_oid, *p_inst_oid = &inst_oid;
9640  RECDES peek = RECDES_INITIALIZER, *p_peek = &peek;
9641  SCAN_CODE scan;
9642  HEAP_SCANCACHE *scan_cache = NULL;
9643  BTREE_CHECKSCAN bt_checkscan;
9644  BTREE_SCAN bt_scan;
9645  HEAP_CACHE_ATTRINFO attr_info;
9646  DB_VALUE *key = NULL;
9647  DB_VALUE dbvalue;
9648  int num_btree_oids = 0, num_heap_oids = 0, num_nulls = 0;
9649  int oid_cnt;
9650  OID *oid_area = NULL;
9651  int num_classes, scancache_inited = 0, attrinfo_inited = 0;
9652  int i, j, index_id;
9653  HFID *hfids = NULL, *hfid = NULL;
9654  OID *class_oids = NULL, *class_oid = NULL;
9655  INDX_SCAN_ID isid;
9656  BTREE_ISCAN_OID_LIST oid_list;
9657  char buf[DBVAL_BUFSIZE + MAX_ALIGNMENT], *aligned_buf;
9658  char *classname = NULL;
9659  KEY_VAL_RANGE key_val_range;
9660  OR_INDEX *index;
9661  DB_LOGICAL ev_res;
9662  int partition_local_index = 0;
9663  MVCC_SNAPSHOT *mvcc_snapshot = NULL;
9664 #if defined(SERVER_MODE)
9665  int tran_index;
9666 #else
9667  int btree_oid_cnt, btree_null_cnt, btree_key_cnt;
9668 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
9669  bool bt_checkscan_inited = false;
9670 
9671  mvcc_snapshot = logtb_get_mvcc_snapshot (thread_p);
9672  if (mvcc_snapshot == NULL)
9673  {
9674  return DISK_ERROR;
9675  }
9676  db_make_null (&dbvalue);
9677 
9678  aligned_buf = PTR_ALIGN (buf, MAX_ALIGNMENT);
9679 
9680 #if defined(SERVER_MODE)
9681  tran_index = LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p);
9682 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
9683 
9684  scan_init_index_scan (&isid, NULL, mvcc_snapshot);
9685 
9686  /* get all the heap files associated with this unique btree */
9687  if (or_get_unique_hierarchy (thread_p, classrec, attr_ids[0], btid, &class_oids, &hfids, &num_classes,
9688  &partition_local_index) != NO_ERROR
9689  || class_oids == NULL || hfids == NULL || num_classes < 1)
9690  {
9691  if (class_oids != NULL)
9692  {
9693  free_and_init (class_oids);
9694  }
9695 
9696  if (hfids != NULL)
9697  {
9698  free_and_init (hfids);
9699  }
9700 
9701  goto error;
9702  }
9703 
9704  /*
9705  * Step 1) Check if all instances of all the heaps are in the unique btree.
9706  */
9707 
9708  scan_cache = (HEAP_SCANCACHE *) malloc (num_classes * sizeof (HEAP_SCANCACHE));
9709  if (scan_cache == NULL)
9710  {
9711  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, num_classes * sizeof (HEAP_SCANCACHE));
9712  goto error;
9713  }
9714 
9715  if (partition_local_index == 1)
9716  {
9717  if (num_classes == 1)
9718  {
9719  /* partition class with local index */
9720  COPY_OID (&class_oids[0], cls_oid);
9721  or_class_hfid (classrec, &hfids[0]);
9722  }
9723  else
9724  {
9725  /* a partitioned class and a local index */
9726  goto end;
9727  }
9728  }
9729 
9730  for (j = 0; j < num_classes; j++)
9731  {
9732  hfid = &hfids[j];
9733  class_oid = &class_oids[j];
9734 
9735  /* Start a scan cursor and a class attribute information */
9736  if (heap_scancache_start (thread_p, &scan_cache[j], hfid, class_oid, true, false, mvcc_snapshot) != NO_ERROR)
9737  {
9738  goto error;
9739  }
9740  scancache_inited++;
9741 
9742  index_id = heap_attrinfo_start_with_btid (thread_p, class_oid, btid, &attr_info);
9743  if (index_id < 0)
9744  {
9745  goto error;
9746  }
9747  index = &(attr_info.last_classrepr->indexes[index_id]);
9748  assert (index != NULL);
9749 
9750  attrinfo_inited = 1;
9751 
9752  /* start a check-scan on index */
9753  if (btree_keyoid_checkscan_start (thread_p, btid, &bt_checkscan) != NO_ERROR)
9754  {
9755  goto error;
9756  }
9757  bt_checkscan_inited = true;
9758 
9759  inst_oid.volid = hfid->vfid.volid;
9760  inst_oid.pageid = NULL_PAGEID;
9761  inst_oid.slotid = NULL_SLOTID;
9762 
9763  while ((scan = heap_next (thread_p, hfid, class_oid, &inst_oid, &peek, &scan_cache[j], PEEK)) == S_SUCCESS)
9764  {
9765  num_heap_oids++;
9766 
9767  if (index->filter_predicate)
9768  {
9769  if (locator_eval_filter_predicate
9770  (thread_p, btid, index->filter_predicate, class_oid, &p_inst_oid, 1, &p_peek, &ev_res) != NO_ERROR)
9771  {
9772  goto error;
9773  }
9774  else if (ev_res != V_TRUE)
9775  {
9776  continue;
9777  }
9778  }
9779 
9780  /* Make sure that the index entry exists */
9781  if ((heap_attrinfo_read_dbvalues (thread_p, &inst_oid, &peek, NULL, &attr_info) != NO_ERROR)
9782  ||
9783  ((key =
9784  heap_attrvalue_get_key (thread_p, index_id, &attr_info, &peek, btid, &dbvalue, aligned_buf, NULL,
9785  NULL)) == NULL))
9786  {
9787  if (isallvalid != DISK_INVALID)
9788  {
9789  isallvalid = DISK_ERROR;
9790  }
9791  }
9792  else
9793  {
9794  assert (key != NULL);
9795 
9796  if (db_value_is_null (key) || btree_multicol_key_is_null (key))
9797  {
9798  num_nulls++;
9799  }
9800  else
9801  {
9802  isvalid = btree_keyoid_checkscan_check (thread_p, &bt_checkscan, class_oid, key, &inst_oid);
9803 
9804  if (er_errid () == ER_INTERRUPTED)
9805  {
9806  /* in case of user interrupt */
9807  goto error;
9808  }
9809 
9810  if (isvalid == DISK_INVALID)
9811  {
9812  if (repair)
9813  {
9814  isvalid = locator_repair_btree_by_insert (thread_p, class_oid, btid, key, &inst_oid);
9815  }
9816 
9817  if (isvalid == DISK_INVALID)
9818  {
9819  char *key_dmp;
9820 
9821  key_dmp = pr_valstring (thread_p, key);
9822  if (!OID_ISNULL (class_oid))
9823  {
9824  if (heap_get_class_name (thread_p, class_oid, &classname) != NO_ERROR)
9825  {
9826  /* ignore */
9827  er_clear ();
9828  }
9829  }
9830 
9831  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_LC_INCONSISTENT_BTREE_ENTRY_TYPE1, 12,
9832  (btname) ? btname : "*UNKNOWN-INDEX*", (classname) ? classname : "*UNKNOWN-CLASS*",
9833  class_oid->volid, class_oid->pageid, class_oid->slotid,
9834  (key_dmp) ? key_dmp : "_NULL_KEY", inst_oid.volid, inst_oid.pageid, inst_oid.slotid,
9835  btid->vfid.volid, btid->vfid.fileid, btid->root_pageid);
9836 
9837  if (key_dmp)
9838  {
9839  db_private_free (thread_p, key_dmp);
9840  }
9841 
9842  if (classname)
9843  {
9844  free_and_init (classname);
9845  }
9846 
9847  if (isallvalid != DISK_INVALID)
9848  {
9849  isallvalid = isvalid;
9850  }
9851  }
9852  }
9853  }
9854  }
9855 
9856  if (key == &dbvalue)
9857  {
9858  pr_clear_value (key);
9859  }
9860  }
9861 
9862  if (scan != S_END && isallvalid != DISK_INVALID)
9863  {
9864  isallvalid = DISK_ERROR;
9865  }
9866 
9867  /* close the index check-scan */
9868  btree_keyoid_checkscan_end (thread_p, &bt_checkscan);
9869  bt_checkscan_inited = false;
9870 
9871  /* Finish scan cursor and class attribute cache information */
9872  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, &attr_info);
9873  attrinfo_inited = 0;
9874  }
9875 
9876  /*
9877  * Step 2) Check that all the btree entries are members of one of the heaps.
9878  */
9879 
9880  BTREE_INIT_SCAN (&bt_scan);
9881 
9882  isid.oid_list = &oid_list;
9883  isid.oid_list->oid_cnt = 0;
9884  isid.oid_list->oidp = (OID *) malloc (ISCAN_OID_BUFFER_CAPACITY);
9885  if (isid.oid_list->oidp == NULL)
9886  {
9887  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) ISCAN_OID_BUFFER_SIZE);
9888  goto error;
9889  }
9890  isid.oid_list->capacity = ISCAN_OID_BUFFER_CAPACITY / OR_OID_SIZE;
9891  isid.oid_list->max_oid_cnt = isid.oid_list->capacity;
9892  isid.oid_list->next_list = NULL;
9893  /* alloc index key copy_buf */
9894  isid.copy_buf = (char *) db_private_alloc (thread_p, DBVAL_BUFSIZE);
9895  if (isid.copy_buf == NULL)
9896  {
9897  goto error;
9898  }
9899  isid.copy_buf_len = DBVAL_BUFSIZE;
9900 
9901  if (heap_scancache_start (thread_p, &isid.scan_cache, hfid, class_oid, true, true, mvcc_snapshot) != NO_ERROR)
9902  {
9903  goto error;
9904  }
9905 
9906  isid.check_not_vacuumed = true;
9907  db_make_null (&key_val_range.key1);
9908  db_make_null (&key_val_range.key2);
9909  key_val_range.range = INF_INF;
9910  key_val_range.num_index_term = 0;
9911 
9912  do
9913  {
9914  /* search index */
9915  if (btree_prepare_bts (thread_p, &bt_scan, btid, &isid, &key_val_range, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, false, NULL) !=
9916  NO_ERROR)
9917  {
9918  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
9919  break;
9920  }
9921  if (btree_range_scan (thread_p, &bt_scan, btree_range_scan_select_visible_oids) != NO_ERROR)
9922  {
9923  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
9924  break;
9925  }
9926  oid_cnt = bt_scan.n_oids_read_last_iteration;
9927 
9928  /* TODO: unique with prefix length */
9929  /* ^ What is this TODO? ^ */
9930 
9931  if (oid_cnt == -1)
9932  {
9933  assert (false);
9934  break;
9935  }
9936 
9937  oid_area = isid.oid_list->oidp;
9938 
9939  num_btree_oids += oid_cnt;
9940  for (i = 0; i < oid_cnt; i++)
9941  {
9942  if (!heap_does_exist (thread_p, NULL, &oid_area[i]))
9943  {
9944  isvalid = DISK_INVALID;
9945  if (repair)
9946  {
9947  /* don't care about filter predicate here since we are sure that oid_area[i] is contained in tree the
9948  * keys has been already S_LOCK-ed. */
9949  isvalid = locator_repair_btree_by_delete (thread_p, class_oid, btid, &oid_area[i]);
9950  }
9951 
9952  if (isvalid == DISK_VALID)
9953  {
9954  num_btree_oids--;
9955  }
9956  else
9957  {
9958  if (!OID_ISNULL (class_oid))
9959  {
9960  if (heap_get_class_name (thread_p, class_oid, &classname) != NO_ERROR)
9961  {
9962  /* ignore */
9963  er_clear ();
9964  }
9965  }
9966 
9967  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_LC_INCONSISTENT_BTREE_ENTRY_TYPE2, 11,
9968  (btname) ? btname : "*UNKNOWN-INDEX*", (classname) ? classname : "*UNKNOWN-CLASS*",
9969  class_oid->volid, class_oid->pageid, class_oid->slotid, oid_area[i].volid, oid_area[i].pageid,
9970  oid_area[i].slotid, btid->vfid.volid, btid->vfid.fileid, btid->root_pageid);
9971 
9972  if (classname)
9973  {
9974  free_and_init (classname);
9975  }
9976 
9977  isallvalid = DISK_INVALID;
9978  }
9979  }
9980  else
9981  {
9982  OID cl_oid;
9983  int found = 0;
9984 
9985  /*
9986  * check to make sure that the OID is one of the OIDs from our
9987  * list of classes.
9988  */
9989  if (heap_get_class_oid (thread_p, &oid_area[i], &cl_oid) != S_SUCCESS)
9990  {
9991  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &isid.scan_cache);
9992  goto error;
9993  }
9994 
9995  for (j = 0, found = 0; found == 0 && class_oids != NULL && j < num_classes; j++)
9996  {
9997  if (OID_EQ (&cl_oid, &(class_oids[j])))
9998  {
9999  found = 1;
10000  }
10001  }
10002 
10003  if (!found)
10004  {
10005  if (!OID_ISNULL (class_oid))
10006  {
10007  if (heap_get_class_name (thread_p, class_oid, &classname) != NO_ERROR)
10008  {
10009  /* ignore */
10010  er_clear ();
10011  }
10012  }
10013 
10014  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_LC_INCONSISTENT_BTREE_ENTRY_TYPE8, 11,
10015  (btname) ? btname : "*UNKNOWN-INDEX*", (classname) ? classname : "*UNKNOWN-CLASS*",
10016  class_oid->volid, class_oid->pageid, class_oid->slotid, oid_area[i].volid, oid_area[i].pageid,
10017  oid_area[i].slotid, btid->vfid.volid, btid->vfid.fileid, btid->root_pageid);
10018 
10019  if (classname)
10020  {
10021  free_and_init (classname);
10022  }
10023  isallvalid = DISK_INVALID;
10024  }
10025  }
10026  }
10027  }
10028  while (!BTREE_END_OF_SCAN (&bt_scan));
10029 
10030  free_and_init (isid.oid_list->oidp);
10031  /* free index key copy_buf */
10032  if (isid.copy_buf)
10033  {
10034  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isid.copy_buf);
10035  }
10036 
10037  if (heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &isid.scan_cache) != NO_ERROR)
10038  {
10039  goto error;
10040  }
10041 
10042  /* check to see that the btree root statistics are correct. */
10043 #if defined(SA_MODE)
10044  if (logtb_get_global_unique_stats (thread_p, btid, &btree_oid_cnt, &btree_null_cnt, &btree_key_cnt) != NO_ERROR)
10045  {
10046  goto error;
10047  }
10048 #endif
10049 
10050  /* Do the numbers add up? */
10051  if (num_heap_oids != num_btree_oids + num_nulls)
10052  {
10053  if (!OID_ISNULL (class_oid))
10054  {
10055  if (heap_get_class_name (thread_p, class_oid, &classname) != NO_ERROR)
10056  {
10057  /* ignore */
10058  er_clear ();
10059  }
10060  }
10061 
10062  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_LC_INCONSISTENT_BTREE_ENTRY_TYPE4, 11,
10063  (btname) ? btname : "*UNKNOWN-INDEX*", (classname) ? classname : "*UNKNOWN-CLASS*", class_oid->volid,
10064  class_oid->pageid, class_oid->slotid, num_heap_oids, num_btree_oids, num_nulls, btid->vfid.volid,
10065  btid->vfid.fileid, btid->root_pageid);
10066 
10067  if (classname)
10068  {
10069  free_and_init (classname);
10070  }
10071 
10072  isallvalid = DISK_INVALID;
10073  }
10074 
10075 #if defined(SA_MODE)
10076  if (num_heap_oids != btree_oid_cnt)
10077  {
10078  if (!OID_ISNULL (class_oid))
10079  {
10080  if (heap_get_class_name (thread_p, class_oid, &classname) != NO_ERROR)
10081  {
10082  /* ignore */
10083  er_clear ();
10084  }
10085  }
10086 
10087  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_LC_INCONSISTENT_BTREE_ENTRY_TYPE5, 10,
10088  (btname) ? btname : "*UNKNOWN-INDEX*", (classname) ? classname : "*UNKNOWN-CLASS*", class_oid->volid,
10089  class_oid->pageid, class_oid->slotid, num_heap_oids, btree_oid_cnt, btid->vfid.volid, btid->vfid.fileid,
10090  btid->root_pageid);
10091 
10092  if (classname)
10093  {
10094  free_and_init (classname);
10095  }
10096 
10097  isallvalid = DISK_INVALID;
10098  }
10099 
10100  if (num_nulls != btree_null_cnt)
10101  {
10102  if (!OID_ISNULL (class_oid))
10103  {
10104  if (heap_get_class_name (thread_p, class_oid, &classname) != NO_ERROR)
10105  {
10106  /* ignore */
10107  er_clear ();
10108  }
10109  }
10110 
10111  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_LC_INCONSISTENT_BTREE_ENTRY_TYPE7, 10,
10112  (btname) ? btname : "*UNKNOWN-INDEX*", (classname) ? classname : "*UNKNOWN-CLASS*", class_oid->volid,
10113  class_oid->pageid, class_oid->slotid, num_nulls, btree_null_cnt, btid->vfid.volid, btid->vfid.fileid,
10114  btid->root_pageid);
10115 
10116  if (classname)
10117  {
10118  free_and_init (classname);
10119  }
10120  isallvalid = DISK_INVALID;
10121  }
10122 
10123  /* finally check if the btree thinks that it is unique */
10124  if (btree_oid_cnt != btree_null_cnt + btree_key_cnt)
10125  {
10126  if (!OID_ISNULL (class_oid))
10127  {
10128  if (heap_get_class_name (thread_p, class_oid, &classname) != NO_ERROR)
10129  {
10130  /* ignore */
10131  er_clear ();
10132  }
10133  }
10134 
10135  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_LC_INCONSISTENT_BTREE_ENTRY_TYPE6, 11,
10136  (btname) ? btname : "*UNKNOWN-INDEX*", (classname) ? classname : "*UNKNOWN-CLASS*", class_oid->volid,
10137  class_oid->pageid, class_oid->slotid, btree_oid_cnt, btree_null_cnt, btree_key_cnt, btid->vfid.volid,
10138  btid->vfid.fileid, btid->root_pageid);
10139 
10140  if (classname)
10141  {
10142  free_and_init (classname);
10143  }
10144 
10145  isallvalid = DISK_INVALID;
10146  }
10147 #endif
10148 
10149  if (isid.check_not_vacuumed && isid.not_vacuumed_res != DISK_VALID)
10150  {
10151  er_set (ER_FATAL_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_INDEX_FOUND_NOT_VACUUMED, 5,
10152  (btname) ? btname : "*UNKNOWN-INDEX*", (classname) ? classname : "*UNKNOWN-CLASS*", class_oid->volid,
10153  class_oid->pageid, class_oid->slotid);
10154  isallvalid = isid.not_vacuumed_res;
10155  }
10156 
10157 end:
10158 
10159  for (j = 0; j < scancache_inited; j++)
10160  {
10161  if (heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache[j]) != NO_ERROR)
10162  {
10163  goto error;
10164  }
10165  }
10166 
10167  if (scan_cache)
10168  {
10169  free_and_init (scan_cache);
10170  }
10171 
10172  free_and_init (class_oids);
10173  free_and_init (hfids);
10174 
10175  return isallvalid;
10176 
10177 error:
10178 
10179  if (isid.oid_list != NULL && isid.oid_list->oidp != NULL)
10180  {
10181  free_and_init (isid.oid_list->oidp);
10182  }
10183 
10184  /* free index key copy_buf */
10185  if (isid.copy_buf)
10186  {
10187  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isid.copy_buf);
10188  }
10189 
10190  if (class_oids)
10191  {
10192  free_and_init (class_oids);
10193  }
10194 
10195  if (hfids)
10196  {
10197  free_and_init (hfids);
10198  }
10199 
10200  if (attrinfo_inited)
10201  {
10202  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, &attr_info);
10203  }
10204 
10205  for (j = 0; j < scancache_inited; j++)
10206  {
10207  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache[j]);
10208  }
10209 
10210  if (scan_cache)
10211  {
10212  free_and_init (scan_cache);
10213  }
10214 
10215  if (bt_checkscan_inited)
10216  {
10217  btree_keyoid_checkscan_end (thread_p, &bt_checkscan);
10218  }
10219 
10220  return DISK_ERROR;
10221 }
10222 
10223 /*
10224  * locator_check_class () - Check consistency of a class
10225  *
10226  * return: valid
10227  *
10228  * repair(in):
10229  */
10230 DISK_ISVALID
10231 locator_check_class (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OID * class_oid, RECDES * peek, HFID * class_hfid, BTID * index_btid,
10232  bool repair)
10233 {
10234  DISK_ISVALID isvalid = DISK_VALID, rv = DISK_VALID;
10235  HEAP_CACHE_ATTRINFO attr_info;
10236  int i;
10237  HEAP_IDX_ELEMENTS_INFO idx_info;
10238  BTID *btid;
10239  ATTR_ID *attrids = NULL;
10240  int n_attrs;
10241  char *btname = NULL;
10242  int *attrs_prefix_length = NULL;
10243 
10244  if (heap_attrinfo_start_with_index (thread_p, class_oid, peek, &attr_info, &idx_info) < 0)
10245  {
10246  return DISK_ERROR;
10247  }
10248 
10249  if (idx_info.num_btids <= 0)
10250  {
10251  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, &attr_info);
10252  return DISK_VALID;
10253  }
10254 
10255  for (i = 0; i < idx_info.num_btids && rv != DISK_ERROR; i++)
10256  {
10257  btid = heap_indexinfo_get_btid (i, &attr_info);
10258  if (btid == NULL)
10259  {
10260  isvalid = DISK_ERROR;
10261  break;
10262  }
10263 
10264  if (index_btid != NULL && !BTID_IS_EQUAL (btid, index_btid))
10265  {
10266  continue;
10267  }
10268 
10269  n_attrs = heap_indexinfo_get_num_attrs (i, &attr_info);
10270  if (n_attrs <= 0)
10271  {
10272  isvalid = DISK_ERROR;
10273  break;
10274  }
10275 
10276  attrids = (ATTR_ID *) malloc (n_attrs * sizeof (ATTR_ID));
10277  if (attrids == NULL)
10278  {
10279  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, n_attrs * sizeof (ATTR_ID));
10280  isvalid = DISK_ERROR;
10281  break;
10282  }
10283 
10284  if (heap_indexinfo_get_attrids (i, &attr_info, attrids) != NO_ERROR)
10285  {
10286  free_and_init (attrids);
10287  isvalid = DISK_ERROR;
10288  break;
10289  }
10290 
10291  attrs_prefix_length = (int *) malloc (n_attrs * sizeof (int));
10292  if (attrs_prefix_length == NULL)
10293  {
10294  free_and_init (attrids);
10295  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, n_attrs * sizeof (int));
10296  isvalid = DISK_ERROR;
10297  break;
10298  }
10299 
10300  if (heap_indexinfo_get_attrs_prefix_length (i, &attr_info, attrs_prefix_length, n_attrs) != NO_ERROR)
10301  {
10302  free_and_init (attrids);
10303  free_and_init (attrs_prefix_length);
10304  isvalid = DISK_ERROR;
10305  break;
10306  }
10307 
10308  if (heap_get_indexinfo_of_btid (thread_p, class_oid, btid, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, &btname, NULL) != NO_ERROR)
10309  {
10310  free_and_init (attrids);
10311  free_and_init (attrs_prefix_length);
10312  isvalid = DISK_ERROR;
10313  break;
10314  }
10315 
10316  if (xbtree_get_unique_pk (thread_p, btid))
10317  {
10318  rv = locator_check_unique_btree_entries (thread_p, btid, class_oid, peek, attrids, btname, repair);
10319  }
10320  else
10321  {
10322  rv =
10323  locator_check_btree_entries (thread_p, btid, class_hfid, class_oid, n_attrs, attrids, attrs_prefix_length,
10324  btname, repair);
10325  }
10326  if (rv != DISK_VALID)
10327  {
10328  isvalid = DISK_ERROR;
10329  }
10330 
10331  free_and_init (attrids);
10332  if (attrs_prefix_length)
10333  {
10334  free_and_init (attrs_prefix_length);
10335  }
10336  if (btname)
10337  {
10338  free_and_init (btname);
10339  }
10340  }
10341 
10342  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, &attr_info);
10343  return isvalid;
10344 }
10345 
10346 /*
10347  * locator_check_by_class_oid () - Check consistency of a class
10348  *
10349  * return: valid
10350  *
10351  * repair(in):
10352  *
10353  */
10354 DISK_ISVALID
10355 locator_check_by_class_oid (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OID * cls_oid, HFID * hfid, BTID * index_btid, bool repair)
10356 {
10357  RECDES copy_rec = RECDES_INITIALIZER;
10358  HEAP_SCANCACHE scan;
10359  HFID root_hfid;
10360  DISK_ISVALID rv = DISK_ERROR;
10361  MVCC_SNAPSHOT *mvcc_snapshot = NULL;
10362 
10363  mvcc_snapshot = logtb_get_mvcc_snapshot (thread_p);
10364  if (mvcc_snapshot == NULL)
10365  {
10366  return DISK_ERROR;
10367  }
10368 
10369  if (boot_find_root_heap (&root_hfid) != NO_ERROR || HFID_IS_NULL (&root_hfid))
10370  {
10371  return DISK_ERROR;
10372  }
10373 
10374  if (heap_scancache_start (thread_p, &scan, &root_hfid, oid_Root_class_oid, true, false, mvcc_snapshot) != NO_ERROR)
10375  {
10376  return DISK_ERROR;
10377  }
10378 
10379  if (heap_get_class_record (thread_p, cls_oid, &copy_rec, &scan, COPY) != S_SUCCESS)
10380  {
10381  heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan);
10382  return DISK_ERROR;
10383  }
10384 
10385  /* lock class and unlatch page */
10386  if (lock_object (thread_p, cls_oid, oid_Root_class_oid, IS_LOCK, LK_COND_LOCK) != LK_GRANTED)
10387  {
10388  if (scan.page_watcher.pgptr != NULL)
10389  {
10390  pgbuf_ordered_unfix (thread_p, &scan.page_watcher);
10391  }
10392 
10393  if (lock_object (thread_p, cls_oid, oid_Root_class_oid, IS_LOCK, LK_UNCOND_LOCK) != LK_GRANTED)
10394  {
10395  heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan);
10396  return DISK_ERROR;
10397  }
10398 
10399  copy_rec.data = NULL;
10400  if (heap_get_class_record (thread_p, cls_oid, &copy_rec, &scan, COPY) != S_SUCCESS)
10401  {
10402  lock_unlock_object (thread_p, cls_oid, oid_Root_class_oid, IS_LOCK, true);
10403  heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan);
10404  return DISK_ERROR;
10405  }
10406  }
10407 
10408  /* we have lock on class_oid, record COPYed, while page is latched */
10409  if (scan.page_watcher.pgptr != NULL)
10410  {
10411  pgbuf_ordered_unfix (thread_p, &scan.page_watcher);
10412  }
10413 
10414  rv = locator_check_class (thread_p, cls_oid, &copy_rec, hfid, index_btid, repair);
10415 
10416  lock_unlock_object (thread_p, cls_oid, oid_Root_class_oid, IS_LOCK, true);
10417 
10418  heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan);
10419 
10420  return rv;
10421 }
10422 
10423 /*
10424  * locator_check_all_entries_of_all_btrees () - Check consistency of all
10425  * entries of all btrees
10426  *
10427  * return: valid
10428  *
10429  * repair(in):
10430  *
10431  * Note: Check the consistency of all entries of all btrees against the
10432  * the corresponding heaps.
10433  */
10434 DISK_ISVALID
10435 locator_check_all_entries_of_all_btrees (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, bool repair)
10436 {
10437  RECDES copy_rec = RECDES_INITIALIZER; /* Record descriptor for copy object */
10438  HFID root_hfid;
10439  HFID hfid;
10440  OID oid;
10441  HEAP_SCANCACHE scan;
10442  SCAN_CODE code = S_SUCCESS;
10443  DISK_ISVALID isallvalid = DISK_VALID;
10444  MVCC_SNAPSHOT *mvcc_snapshot = NULL;
10445 
10446  mvcc_snapshot = logtb_get_mvcc_snapshot (thread_p);
10447  if (mvcc_snapshot == NULL)
10448  {
10449  return DISK_ERROR;
10450  }
10451 
10452  /*
10453  * Find all the classes.
10454  * If the class has an index, check the logical consistency of the index
10455  */
10456 
10457  /* Find the heap for the root classes */
10458 
10459  if (boot_find_root_heap (&root_hfid) != NO_ERROR || HFID_IS_NULL (&root_hfid))
10460  {
10461  return DISK_ERROR;
10462  }
10463 
10464  if (heap_scancache_start (thread_p, &scan, &root_hfid, oid_Root_class_oid, true, false, mvcc_snapshot) != NO_ERROR)
10465  {
10466  return DISK_ERROR;
10467  }
10468 
10469  oid.volid = root_hfid.vfid.volid;
10470  oid.pageid = NULL_PAGEID;
10471  oid.slotid = NULL_SLOTID;
10472 
10473  while (isallvalid != DISK_ERROR)
10474  {
10475  copy_rec.data = NULL;
10476  code = heap_next (thread_p, &root_hfid, oid_Root_class_oid, &oid, &copy_rec, &scan, COPY);
10477  if (code != S_SUCCESS)
10478  {
10479  break;
10480  }
10481 
10482  or_class_hfid (&copy_rec, &hfid);
10483  if (HFID_IS_NULL (&hfid))
10484  {
10485  continue;
10486  }
10487 
10488  /* lock class and unlatch page */
10489  if (lock_object (thread_p, &oid, oid_Root_class_oid, IS_LOCK, LK_COND_LOCK) != LK_GRANTED)
10490  {
10491  if (scan.page_watcher.pgptr != NULL)
10492  {
10493  pgbuf_ordered_unfix (thread_p, &scan.page_watcher);
10494  }
10495 
10496  if (lock_object (thread_p, &oid, oid_Root_class_oid, IS_LOCK, LK_UNCOND_LOCK) != LK_GRANTED)
10497  {
10498  break;
10499  }
10500 
10501  copy_rec.data = NULL;
10502  code = heap_get_class_record (thread_p, &oid, &copy_rec, &scan, COPY);
10503  if (code != S_SUCCESS)
10504  {
10505  break;
10506  }
10507  }
10508 
10509  /* we have lock on class_oid, record COPYed, while page is latched */
10510  if (scan.page_watcher.pgptr != NULL)
10511  {
10512  pgbuf_ordered_unfix (thread_p, &scan.page_watcher);
10513  }
10514 
10515  if (locator_check_class (thread_p, &oid, &copy_rec, &hfid, NULL, repair) != DISK_VALID)
10516  {
10517  isallvalid = DISK_ERROR;
10518  }
10519 
10520  lock_unlock_object (thread_p, &oid, oid_Root_class_oid, IS_LOCK, true);
10521  }
10522 
10523  if (code != S_END)
10524  {
10525  isallvalid = DISK_ERROR;
10526  }
10527 
10528  /* End the scan cursor */
10529  if (heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan) != NO_ERROR)
10530  {
10531  isallvalid = DISK_ERROR;
10532  }
10533 
10534  return isallvalid;
10535 }
10536 
10537 /*
10538  * locator_guess_sub_classes () - Guess the subclasses of the given hinted classes
10539  *
10540  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
10541  *
10542  * lockhint_subclasses(in): lockhint structure which describes classes
10543  * The content is updated and the structure itself may be
10544  * reallocated
10545  *
10546  * Note:This function guess the subclasses identifiers of requested
10547  * subclasses for the classes referenced by the lockhint
10548  * structure. The lockhint structure is updated to contain the
10549  * needed subclasses.
10550  *
10551  * The subclasses are only guessed for lock hint purposes and
10552  * they should not be used for any other purposes (it is OK, to
10553  * send the objects to the client). That is, the found subclasses
10554  * reflects the classes on the server(database volumes) as they
10555  * are when the function is invoked; the function does not wait
10556  * even when the classes/subclasses may be in the process of been
10557  * updated by any transaction.
10558  *
10559  * In general the function is used to approximately find out all
10560  * needed subclasses, so that they can be locked along with a
10561  * requested set of classes all at once...and not in pieces since
10562  * the later can produce deadlocks.
10563  */
10564 static int
10565 locator_guess_sub_classes (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LC_LOCKHINT ** lockhint_subclasses)
10566 {
10567  int ref_num; /* Max and reference number in request area */
10568  int max_stack; /* Total size of stack */
10569  int stack_actual_size; /* Actual size of stack */
10570  int *stack; /* The stack for the search */
10571  int max_oid_list; /* Max number of immediate subclasses */
10572  OID *oid_list = NULL; /* List of ref for one object */
10573  HEAP_SCANCACHE scan_cache; /* Scan cache used for fetching purposes */
10574  SCAN_CODE scan; /* Scan return value for an object */
10575  void *new_ptr;
10576  RECDES peek_recdes;
10577  LC_LOCKHINT *lockhint;
10578  int num_original_classes;
10579  LOCK lock;
10580  int i, j, k;
10581  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
10582 
10583  /*
10584  * Start a scan cursor for fetching the desired classes.
10585  */
10586 
10587  error_code = heap_scancache_start (thread_p, &scan_cache, NULL, NULL, true, false, NULL);
10588  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
10589  {
10590  return error_code;
10591  }
10592 
10593  lockhint = *lockhint_subclasses;
10594 
10595  /*
10596  * Let's assume a number of subclasses for allocation purposes of the stack.
10597  * We will assume at least one subclass per class and a minimum of 10
10598  * subclasses for all requested classes.
10599  */
10600 
10601  max_stack = lockhint->max_classes * 2;
10602  if (max_stack < 10)
10603  {
10604  max_stack = 10;
10605  }
10606  max_oid_list = max_stack;
10607 
10608  stack = (int *) malloc (sizeof (*stack) * max_stack);
10609  if (stack == NULL)
10610  {
10611  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (*stack) * max_stack);
10612  error_code = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
10613  goto error;
10614  }
10615  oid_list = (OID *) malloc (sizeof (*oid_list) * max_oid_list);
10616  if (oid_list == NULL)
10617  {
10618  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (*oid_list) * max_oid_list);
10619  error_code = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
10620  goto error;
10621  }
10622 
10623  /*
10624  * Obtain the subclasses requested.
10625  */
10626 
10627  num_original_classes = lockhint->num_classes;
10628  for (i = 0; i < num_original_classes; i++)
10629  {
10630  if (OID_ISNULL (&lockhint->classes[i].oid) || OID_ISTEMP (&lockhint->classes[i].oid)
10631  || lockhint->classes[i].need_subclasses <= 0)
10632  {
10633  /*
10634  * It has already been visited or we don't care about its subclasses
10635  */
10636  continue;
10637  }
10638 
10639  /*
10640  * Make sure that this is a valid class
10641  */
10642 
10643  if (!heap_does_exist (thread_p, NULL, &lockhint->classes[i].oid))
10644  {
10645  if (er_errid () == ER_INTERRUPTED)
10646  {
10647  error_code = ER_INTERRUPTED;
10648  goto error;
10649  }
10650 
10651  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT, 3, lockhint->classes[i].oid.volid,
10652  lockhint->classes[i].oid.pageid, lockhint->classes[i].oid.slotid);
10653  /*
10654  * The class did not exist, continue even in the event of errors.
10655  * Eliminate this class from the list of requested classes.
10656  */
10657  OID_SET_NULL (&lockhint->classes[i].oid);
10658  continue;
10659  }
10660 
10661  /*
10662  * Add the class to the stack and indicate that it has not been visited.
10663  */
10664 
10665  /* Initialize the stack and push the element */
10666  stack_actual_size = 0;
10667  stack[stack_actual_size++] = i;
10668 
10669  /*
10670  * Star a kind of depth-first search algorithm to find out subclasses
10671  */
10672 
10673  while (stack_actual_size > 0)
10674  {
10675  /* Pop */
10676  ref_num = stack[--stack_actual_size];
10677 
10678  /*
10679  * Get the class to find out its immediate subclasses
10680  */
10681 
10682  scan = heap_get_class_record (thread_p, &lockhint->classes[ref_num].oid, &peek_recdes, &scan_cache, PEEK);
10683  if (scan != S_SUCCESS)
10684  {
10685  if (scan != S_DOESNT_EXIST && (lockhint->quit_on_errors == (int) true || er_errid () == ER_INTERRUPTED))
10686  {
10687  error_code = ER_FAILED;
10688  goto error;
10689  }
10690 
10691  /*
10692  * Continue after an error. Remove the class from the list of
10693  * requested classes
10694  */
10695 
10696  if (ref_num == lockhint->num_classes - 1)
10697  {
10698  /* Last element remove it */
10699  lockhint->num_classes--;
10700  }
10701  else
10702  {
10703  /* Marked it as invalid */
10704  OID_SET_NULL (&lockhint->classes[ref_num].oid);
10705  }
10706  er_clear ();
10707  continue;
10708  }
10709 
10710  /*
10711  * has the class been visited ?
10712  */
10713 
10714  if (lockhint->classes[i].need_subclasses <= 0)
10715  {
10716  /*
10717  * This class has already been visited;
10718  */
10719  continue;
10720  }
10721 
10722 
10723  /*
10724  * Object has never been visited. First time in the stack.
10725  * Mark this class as visited.
10726  */
10727 
10728  lockhint->classes[ref_num].need_subclasses = -lockhint->classes[ref_num].need_subclasses;
10729 
10730  /*
10731  * Find all immediate subclasses for this class
10732  */
10733 
10734  OID_SET_NULL (&oid_list[0]);
10735 
10736  error_code = orc_subclasses_from_record (&peek_recdes, &max_oid_list, &oid_list);
10737  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
10738  {
10739  if (lockhint->quit_on_errors == (int) true)
10740  {
10741  goto error;
10742  }
10743 
10744  /* Continue even in the case of an error */
10745  error_code = NO_ERROR;
10746  continue;
10747  }
10748 
10749  /*
10750  * Add the above references to the stack if these classes have not
10751  * been already been visited or if their current level is smaller
10752  * than their visited level
10753  */
10754 
10755  for (k = 0; k < max_oid_list && !OID_ISNULL (&oid_list[k]); k++)
10756  {
10757  /*
10758  * Has this class already been listed ?
10759  */
10760  for (j = 0; j < lockhint->num_classes; j++)
10761  {
10762  if (OID_EQ (&oid_list[k], &lockhint->classes[j].oid))
10763  {
10764  break; /* It is already listed */
10765  }
10766  }
10767 
10768  if (j == lockhint->num_classes)
10769  {
10770  /*
10771  * This is the first time we have seen this class. Push the
10772  * class onto the stack.
10773  * Make sure that we have area in the stack and the lockhint
10774  * area
10775  */
10776 
10777  if (stack_actual_size >= max_stack)
10778  {
10779  /* Expand the stack by two */
10780  max_stack = max_stack * 2;
10781  new_ptr = realloc (stack, sizeof (*stack) * max_stack);
10782  if (new_ptr == NULL)
10783  {
10784  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
10785  sizeof (*stack) * max_stack);
10786  if (lockhint->quit_on_errors == false)
10787  {
10788  /* Finish but without an error */
10789  break;
10790  }
10791  error_code = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
10792  goto error;
10793  }
10794  stack = (int *) new_ptr;
10795  }
10796  if (lockhint->num_classes >= lockhint->max_classes)
10797  {
10798  /* Expand the lockhint area by two */
10799  new_ptr = locator_reallocate_lockhint (lockhint, (lockhint->max_classes * 2));
10800  if (new_ptr == NULL)
10801  {
10802  if (lockhint->quit_on_errors == false)
10803  {
10804  /* Finish but without an error */
10805  break;
10806  }
10807  error_code = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
10808  goto error;
10809  }
10810  lockhint = *lockhint_subclasses = (LC_LOCKHINT *) new_ptr;
10811  }
10812 
10813  /*
10814  * Push the class on the stack.
10815  */
10816 
10817  /* Push */
10818  stack[stack_actual_size++] = lockhint->num_classes;
10819 
10820  COPY_OID (&lockhint->classes[lockhint->num_classes].oid, &oid_list[k]);
10821  lockhint->classes[lockhint->num_classes].chn = CHN_UNKNOWN_ATCLIENT;
10822  lockhint->classes[lockhint->num_classes].lock = lockhint->classes[ref_num].lock;
10823  lockhint->classes[lockhint->num_classes].need_subclasses = 1;
10824  lockhint->num_classes++;
10825 
10826  }
10827  else
10828  {
10829  /*
10830  * This is a class that has already been listed and it may
10831  * have already been visited.
10832  */
10833  assert (lockhint->classes[j].lock >= NULL_LOCK && lockhint->classes[ref_num].lock >= NULL_LOCK);
10834 
10835  if (lockhint->classes[j].need_subclasses >= 0)
10836  {
10837  /*
10838  * The class is only listed at this point. It will be
10839  * visited later. The lock may need to be changed, as well
10840  * as its subclass flag
10841  */
10842 
10843  /* May be lock change */
10844  lockhint->classes[j].lock = lock_Conv[lockhint->classes[j].lock][lockhint->classes[ref_num].lock];
10845  assert (lockhint->classes[j].lock != NA_LOCK);
10846 
10847  /* Make sure that subclasses are obtained */
10848  lockhint->classes[j].need_subclasses = 1;
10849  }
10850  else
10851  {
10852  /*
10853  * This class has already been visited. We may need to
10854  * revisit if a lock conversion is needed as a result of
10855  * several super classes
10856  */
10857  lock = lock_Conv[lockhint->classes[j].lock][lockhint->classes[ref_num].lock];
10858  assert (lock != NA_LOCK);
10859 
10860  if (lockhint->classes[j].lock != lock)
10861  {
10862  /*
10863  * Re-visit
10864  */
10865  lockhint->classes[j].lock = lock;
10866  lockhint->classes[j].need_subclasses = 1;
10867  /* Push */
10868  stack[stack_actual_size++] = j;
10869  }
10870  }
10871  }
10872  }
10873  }
10874  }
10875 
10876  free_and_init (stack);
10877  free_and_init (oid_list);
10878  error_code = heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache);
10879  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
10880  {
10881  return error_code;
10882  }
10883 
10884  /*
10885  * Scan the lockhint area to make the prune levels positive
10886  */
10887 
10888  for (i = 0; i < lockhint->num_classes; i++)
10889  {
10890  lockhint->classes[i].need_subclasses = -lockhint->classes[i].need_subclasses;
10891  }
10892 
10893  return error_code;
10894 
10895 error:
10896 
10897  if (stack)
10898  {
10899  free_and_init (stack);
10900  }
10901  if (oid_list)
10902  {
10903  free_and_init (oid_list);
10904  }
10905  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache);
10906 
10907  return error_code;
10908 }
10909 
10910 /*
10911  * xlocator_find_lockhint_class_oids () - Find the oids associated with the given
10912  * classes
10913  *
10914  * return: LC_FIND_CLASSNAME
10915  * (either of LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST,
10916  * LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED,
10917  * LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR)
10918  *
10919  * num_classes(in): Number of needed classes
10920  * many_classnames(in): Name of the classes
10921  * many_locks(in): The desired lock for each class
10922  * many_need_subclasses(in): Wheater or not the subclasses are needed.
10923  * many_flags(in): flags associated with class names
10924  * guessed_class_oids(in):
10925  * guessed_class_chns(in):
10926  * quit_on_errors(in): Wheater to continue finding the classes in case of
10927  * an error, such as a class does not exist or a lock
10928  * one a may not be granted.
10929  * hlock(in): hlock structure which is set to describe the
10930  * classes
10931  * fetch_area(in):
10932  *
10933  * Note: This function find the class identifiers of the given class
10934  * names and requested subclasses of the above classes, and lock
10935  * the classes with given locks. The function does not quit when
10936  * an error is found and the value of quit_on_errors is false.
10937  * In this case the class (an may be its subclasses) with the
10938  * error is not locked/fetched.
10939  * The function tries to lock all the classes at once, however if
10940  * this fails and the function is allowed to continue when errors
10941  * are detected, the classes are locked individually.
10942  *
10943  * The subclasses are only guessed for locking purposed and they
10944  * should not be used for any other purposes. For example, the
10945  * subclasses should not given to the upper levels of the system.
10946  *
10947  * In general the function is used to find out all needed classes
10948  * and lock them togheter.
10949  */
10950 LC_FIND_CLASSNAME
10951 xlocator_find_lockhint_class_oids (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, int num_classes, const char **many_classnames,
10952  LOCK * many_locks, int *many_need_subclasses, LC_PREFETCH_FLAGS * many_flags,
10953  OID * guessed_class_oids, int *guessed_class_chns, bool quit_on_errors,
10954  LC_LOCKHINT ** hlock, LC_COPYAREA ** fetch_area)
10955 {
10956  int tran_index;
10957  LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *entry;
10958  const char *classname;
10959  LOCK tmp_lock;
10960  LC_FIND_CLASSNAME find = LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST;
10961  LC_FIND_CLASSNAME allfind = LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST;
10962  bool allneed_subclasses = false;
10963  int retry;
10964  int i, j;
10965  int n;
10966 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
10967  int check_own;
10968 #endif
10969 
10970  *fetch_area = NULL;
10971 
10972  /*
10973  * Let's assume the number of classes that are going to be described in the
10974  * lockhint area.
10975  */
10976 
10977  *hlock = locator_allocate_lockhint (num_classes, quit_on_errors);
10978  if (*hlock == NULL)
10979  {
10980  return LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
10981  }
10982 
10983  /*
10984  * Find the class oids of the given classnames.
10985  */
10986 
10987  tran_index = LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p);
10988 
10989  for (i = 0; i < num_classes && (allfind == LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST || quit_on_errors == false); i++)
10990  {
10991  classname = many_classnames[i];
10992  if (classname == NULL || !(many_flags[i] & LC_PREF_FLAG_LOCK))
10993  {
10994  continue;
10995  }
10996 
10997  if (many_need_subclasses[i])
10998  {
10999  allneed_subclasses = true;
11000  }
11001 
11002  n = (*hlock)->num_classes;
11003  find = LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST;
11004  retry = 1;
11005 
11006  while (retry)
11007  {
11008  retry = 0;
11009 
11010  /*
11011  * Describe the hinted class
11012  */
11013 
11014  (*hlock)->classes[n].chn = CHN_UNKNOWN_ATCLIENT;
11015  (*hlock)->classes[n].lock = many_locks[i];
11016  (*hlock)->classes[n].need_subclasses = many_need_subclasses[i];
11017 
11018  if (csect_enter_as_reader (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE, INF_WAIT) != NO_ERROR)
11019  {
11020  assert (false);
11021  return LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
11022  }
11023 
11024  entry = ((LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY *) mht_get (locator_Mht_classnames, classname));
11025 
11026  if (entry != NULL)
11027  {
11028  COPY_OID (&(*hlock)->classes[n].oid, &entry->e_current.oid);
11029  assert (find == LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST);
11030 
11031  if (locator_is_exist_class_name_entry (thread_p, entry))
11032  {
11033  assert (find == LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST); /* OK, go ahead */
11034  }
11035  else
11036  {
11037  assert (entry->e_current.action != LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST);
11038 
11039  /*
11040  * We can only proceed if the entry belongs to the current
11041  * transaction, otherwise, we must lock the class associated
11042  * with the classname and retry the operation once the lock
11043  * is granted.
11044  */
11045  assert (find == LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST);
11046 
11047  if (entry->e_tran_index == tran_index)
11048  {
11049  if (entry->e_current.action == LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED
11050  || entry->e_current.action == LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED_RENAME)
11051  {
11052  find = LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED;
11053  }
11054  else
11055  {
11056  assert (find == LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST); /* OK, go ahead */
11057  }
11058  }
11059  else
11060  {
11061  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
11062 
11063  /*
11064  * Do not know the fate of this entry until the transaction is
11065  * committed or aborted. Get the lock and retry later on.
11066  */
11067  if ((*hlock)->classes[n].lock != NULL_LOCK)
11068  {
11069  tmp_lock = (*hlock)->classes[n].lock;
11070  }
11071  else
11072  {
11073  tmp_lock = IS_LOCK;
11074  }
11075 
11076  if (lock_object (thread_p, &(*hlock)->classes[n].oid, oid_Root_class_oid, tmp_lock,
11077  LK_UNCOND_LOCK) != LK_GRANTED)
11078  {
11079  /*
11080  * Unable to acquired the lock; exit retry-loop
11081  */
11082  allfind = find = LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
11083  assert (allfind == LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR);
11084  }
11085  else
11086  {
11087  /*
11088  * Try again
11089  * Remove the lock.. since the above was a dirty read
11090  */
11091  lock_unlock_object (thread_p, &(*hlock)->classes[n].oid, oid_Root_class_oid, tmp_lock, true);
11092  retry = 1;
11093  }
11094 
11095  /* already exit cset */
11096  continue;
11097  }
11098  }
11099  }
11100  else
11101  {
11102  assert (entry == NULL);
11103 
11104  find = LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED;
11105  }
11106 
11107 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
11108  check_own = csect_check_own (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
11109  assert (check_own >= 1);
11110 #endif
11111 
11112  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
11113 
11114  } /* while (retry) */
11115 
11116  if (find == LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST)
11117  {
11118  /*
11119  * If the client has guessed the right class_oid, use the cache
11120  * coherency number on the client to avoid sending the class object
11121  */
11122  if (guessed_class_oids != NULL && OID_EQ (&(*hlock)->classes[n].oid, &guessed_class_oids[i]))
11123  {
11124  (*hlock)->classes[n].chn = guessed_class_chns[i];
11125  }
11126 
11127  n++;
11128  (*hlock)->num_classes = n;
11129  }
11130  else
11131  {
11132  if (allfind != LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR)
11133  {
11134  allfind = find;
11135  }
11136  if (find == LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED)
11137  {
11138  er_set (ER_WARNING_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_LC_UNKNOWN_CLASSNAME, 1, classname);
11139  }
11140  }
11141  } /* for (i = 0; ... ) */
11142 
11143  /*
11144  * Eliminate any duplicates. Note that we did not want to do above since
11145  * we did not want to modify the original arrays.
11146  */
11147 
11148  for (i = 0; i < (*hlock)->num_classes; i++)
11149  {
11150  if (OID_ISNULL (&(*hlock)->classes[i].oid))
11151  {
11152  continue;
11153  }
11154  /*
11155  * Is this duplicated ?
11156  */
11157  for (j = i + 1; j < (*hlock)->num_classes; j++)
11158  {
11159  if (OID_EQ (&(*hlock)->classes[i].oid, &(*hlock)->classes[j].oid))
11160  {
11161  /* Duplicate class, merge the lock and the subclass entry */
11162  assert ((*hlock)->classes[i].lock >= NULL_LOCK && (*hlock)->classes[j].lock >= NULL_LOCK);
11163  (*hlock)->classes[i].lock = lock_Conv[(*hlock)->classes[i].lock][(*hlock)->classes[j].lock];
11164  assert ((*hlock)->classes[i].lock != NA_LOCK);
11165 
11166  if ((*hlock)->classes[i].need_subclasses == 0)
11167  {
11168  (*hlock)->classes[i].need_subclasses = (*hlock)->classes[j].need_subclasses;
11169  }
11170 
11171  /* Now eliminate the entry */
11172  OID_SET_NULL (&(*hlock)->classes[j].oid);
11173  }
11174  }
11175  }
11176 
11177  /*
11178  * Do we need to get subclasses ?
11179  */
11180 
11181  if (allneed_subclasses == true && (allfind == LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST || quit_on_errors == false))
11182  {
11183  if (locator_guess_sub_classes (thread_p, &(*hlock)) != NO_ERROR)
11184  {
11185  allfind = LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
11186  }
11187  }
11188 
11189  if (allfind == LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST || quit_on_errors == false)
11190  {
11191  if (xlocator_fetch_lockhint_classes (thread_p, (*hlock), fetch_area) != NO_ERROR)
11192  {
11193  allfind = LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
11194  if (quit_on_errors == true)
11195  {
11196  locator_free_lockhint ((*hlock));
11197  *hlock = NULL;
11198  }
11199  }
11200  }
11201  else
11202  {
11203  locator_free_lockhint ((*hlock));
11204  *hlock = NULL;
11205  }
11206 
11207  if (logtb_tran_prepare_count_optim_classes (thread_p, many_classnames, many_flags, num_classes) != NO_ERROR)
11208  {
11209  allfind = LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR;
11210  }
11211 
11212  return allfind;
11213 }
11214 
11215 /*
11216  * xlocator_fetch_lockhint_classes () - Lock and fetch a set of classes
11217  *
11218  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
11219  *
11220  * lockhint(in): Description of hinted classses
11221  * fetch_area(in/out): Pointer to area where the objects are placed
11222  *
11223  */
11224 int
11225 xlocator_fetch_lockhint_classes (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LC_LOCKHINT * lockhint, LC_COPYAREA ** fetch_area)
11226 {
11227  LOCATOR_RETURN_NXOBJ nxobj; /* Description to return next object */
11228  LC_COPYAREA_DESC prefetch_des; /* Descriptor for decache of objects related to transaction isolation level */
11229  SCAN_CODE scan = S_SUCCESS;
11230  int copyarea_length;
11231  int i;
11232  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
11233 
11234  *fetch_area = NULL;
11235 
11236  if (lockhint->num_classes <= 0)
11237  {
11238  lockhint->num_classes_processed = lockhint->num_classes;
11239  return NO_ERROR;
11240  }
11241 
11242  if (lockhint->num_classes_processed == -1)
11243  {
11244  /*
11245  * FIRST CALL.
11246  * Initialize num of object processed.
11247  */
11248  lockhint->num_classes_processed = 0;
11249 
11250  /* Obtain the locks */
11251  if (lock_classes_lock_hint (thread_p, lockhint) != LK_GRANTED)
11252  {
11253  if (lockhint->quit_on_errors != false)
11254  {
11255  return ER_FAILED;
11256  }
11257  else
11258  {
11259  error_code = ER_FAILED;
11260  /* Lock individual classes */
11261  for (i = 0; i < lockhint->num_classes; i++)
11262  {
11263  if (OID_ISNULL (&lockhint->classes[i].oid))
11264  {
11265  continue;
11266  }
11267  if (lock_object (thread_p, &lockhint->classes[i].oid, oid_Root_class_oid, lockhint->classes[i].lock,
11268  LK_UNCOND_LOCK) != LK_GRANTED)
11269  {
11270  OID_SET_NULL (&lockhint->classes[i].oid);
11271  }
11272  else
11273  {
11274  /* We are unable to continue since we lock at least one */
11275  error_code = NO_ERROR;
11276  }
11277  }
11278  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
11279  {
11280  return error_code;
11281  }
11282  }
11283  }
11284  }
11285 
11286  /*
11287  * Start a scan cursor for getting the classes
11288  */
11289 
11290  error_code = heap_scancache_start (thread_p, &nxobj.area_scancache, NULL, NULL, true, false, NULL);
11291  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
11292  {
11293  lock_unlock_classes_lock_hint (thread_p, lockhint);
11294  return error_code;
11295  }
11296 
11297  nxobj.ptr_scancache = &nxobj.area_scancache;
11298 
11299  /*
11300  * Assume that there are not any classes larger than one page. If there are
11301  * the number of pages is fixed later.
11302  */
11303 
11304  /* Assume that the needed object can fit in one page */
11305  copyarea_length = DB_PAGESIZE;
11306 
11307  nxobj.mobjs = NULL;
11308  nxobj.comm_area = NULL;
11309 
11310  while (scan == S_SUCCESS && (lockhint->num_classes_processed < lockhint->num_classes))
11311  {
11312  nxobj.comm_area = locator_allocate_copy_area_by_length (copyarea_length);
11313  if (nxobj.comm_area == NULL)
11314  {
11315  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &nxobj.area_scancache);
11316  lock_unlock_classes_lock_hint (thread_p, lockhint);
11317  return ER_FAILED;
11318  }
11319 
11320  nxobj.mobjs = LC_MANYOBJS_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (nxobj.comm_area);
11321  nxobj.obj = LC_START_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (nxobj.mobjs);
11322  LC_RECDES_IN_COPYAREA (nxobj.comm_area, &nxobj.recdes);
11323  nxobj.area_offset = 0;
11324  nxobj.mobjs->num_objs = 0;
11325 
11326  /*
11327  * Place the classes on the communication area, don't place those classes
11328  * with correct chns.
11329  */
11330 
11331  for (i = lockhint->num_classes_processed; scan == S_SUCCESS && i < lockhint->num_classes; i++)
11332  {
11333  if (OID_ISNULL (&lockhint->classes[i].oid) || OID_ISTEMP (&lockhint->classes[i].oid))
11334  {
11335  lockhint->num_classes_processed += 1;
11336  continue;
11337  }
11338 
11339  /* Now return the object */
11340  /* Since classes are already locked, call locator_lock_and_return_object with NULL_LOCK as lock_mode argument
11341  * to skip locking. */
11342  scan =
11343  locator_lock_and_return_object (thread_p, &nxobj, oid_Root_class_oid, &lockhint->classes[i].oid,
11344  lockhint->classes[i].chn, NULL_LOCK, S_SELECT);
11345  if (scan == S_SUCCESS)
11346  {
11347  lockhint->num_classes_processed += 1;
11348  }
11349  else if (scan == S_DOESNT_FIT && nxobj.mobjs->num_objs == 0)
11350  {
11351  /*
11352  * The first object on the copy area does not fit.
11353  * Get a larger area
11354  */
11355 
11356  /* Get the real length of the fetch/copy area */
11357 
11358  copyarea_length = nxobj.comm_area->length;
11359 
11360  if ((-nxobj.recdes.length) > copyarea_length)
11361  {
11362  copyarea_length = (DB_ALIGN (-nxobj.recdes.length, MAX_ALIGNMENT) + sizeof (*nxobj.mobjs));
11363  }
11364  else
11365  {
11366  copyarea_length += DB_PAGESIZE;
11367  }
11368 
11369  locator_free_copy_area (nxobj.comm_area);
11370  scan = S_SUCCESS;
11371  break; /* finish the for */
11372  }
11373  else if (scan != S_DOESNT_FIT && (scan == S_DOESNT_EXIST || lockhint->quit_on_errors == false))
11374  {
11375  OID_SET_NULL (&lockhint->classes[i].oid);
11376  lockhint->num_classes_processed += 1;
11377  scan = S_SUCCESS;
11378  }
11379  else
11380  {
11381  break; /* Quit on errors */
11382  }
11383  }
11384  }
11385 
11386  /* End the scan cursor */
11387  error_code = heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &nxobj.area_scancache);
11388  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
11389  {
11390  /* There was an error.. */
11391  if (nxobj.mobjs != NULL)
11392  {
11393  locator_free_copy_area (nxobj.comm_area);
11394  }
11395  lock_unlock_classes_lock_hint (thread_p, lockhint);
11396  return error_code;
11397  }
11398 
11399  if (scan == S_ERROR)
11400  {
11401  /* There was an error.. */
11402  if (nxobj.mobjs != NULL)
11403  {
11404  locator_free_copy_area (nxobj.comm_area);
11405  }
11406  lock_unlock_classes_lock_hint (thread_p, lockhint);
11407  return ER_FAILED;
11408  }
11409  else if (nxobj.mobjs != NULL && nxobj.mobjs->num_objs == 0)
11410  {
11411  locator_free_copy_area (nxobj.comm_area);
11412  }
11413  else
11414  {
11415  *fetch_area = nxobj.comm_area;
11416  }
11417 
11418  if (*fetch_area != NULL)
11419  {
11420  prefetch_des.mobjs = nxobj.mobjs;
11421  prefetch_des.obj = &nxobj.obj;
11422  prefetch_des.offset = &nxobj.area_offset;
11423  prefetch_des.recdes = &nxobj.recdes;
11424  lock_notify_isolation_incons (thread_p, locator_notify_decache, &prefetch_des);
11425  }
11426 
11427  if (lockhint->num_classes_processed >= lockhint->num_classes)
11428  {
11429  lock_unlock_classes_lock_hint (thread_p, lockhint);
11430  }
11431 
11432  return NO_ERROR;
11433 }
11434 
11435 /*
11436  * xlocator_assign_oid_batch () - Assign a group of permanent oids
11437  *
11438  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
11439  *
11440  * oidset(in): LC_OIDSET describing all of the temp oids
11441  *
11442  * Note:Permanent oids are assigned to each of the temporary oids
11443  * listed in the LC_OIDSET.
11444  */
11445 int
11446 xlocator_assign_oid_batch (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LC_OIDSET * oidset)
11447 {
11448  LC_CLASS_OIDSET *class_oidset;
11449  LC_OIDMAP *oid;
11450  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
11451 
11452  /* establish a rollback point in case we get an error part way through */
11453  log_sysop_start (thread_p);
11454 
11455  /* Now assign the OID's stop on the first error */
11456  for (class_oidset = oidset->classes; class_oidset != NULL; class_oidset = class_oidset->next)
11457  {
11458  for (oid = class_oidset->oids; oid != NULL; oid = oid->next)
11459  {
11460  error_code =
11461  xlocator_assign_oid (thread_p, &class_oidset->hfid, &oid->oid, oid->est_size, &class_oidset->class_oid,
11462  NULL);
11463  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
11464  {
11465  goto error;
11466  }
11467  }
11468  }
11469 
11470  /* accept the operation */
11471  log_sysop_attach_to_outer (thread_p);
11472 
11473  return error_code;
11474 
11475 error:
11476  /* rollback the operation */
11477  log_sysop_abort (thread_p);
11478  return error_code;
11479 }
11480 
11481 #if defined(ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
11482 /*
11483  * locator_increase_catalog_count () -
11484  *
11485  * return:
11486  *
11487  * cls_oid(in): Class OID
11488  *
11489  * Note:Increase the 'tot_objects' counter of the CLS_INFO
11490  * and do update the catalog record in-place.
11491  */
11492 static void
11493 locator_increase_catalog_count (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OID * cls_oid)
11494 {
11495  CLS_INFO *cls_infop = NULL;
11496 
11497  /* retrieve the class information */
11498  cls_infop = catalog_get_class_info (thread_p, cls_oid);
11499  if (cls_infop == NULL)
11500  {
11501  return;
11502  }
11503 
11504  if (cls_infop->ci_hfid.vfid.fileid < 0 || cls_infop->ci_hfid.vfid.volid < 0)
11505  {
11506  /* The class does not have a heap file (i.e. it has no instances); so no statistics can be obtained for this
11507  * class; just set 'tot_objects' field to 0. */
11508  /* Is it safe not to initialize the other fields of CLS_INFO? */
11509  cls_infop->ci_tot_objects = 0;
11510  }
11511  else
11512  {
11513  /* increase the 'tot_objects' counter */
11514  cls_infop->ci_tot_objects++;
11515  }
11516 
11517  /* update the class information to the catalog */
11518  /* NOTE that tot_objects may not be correct because changes are NOT logged. */
11519  (void) catalog_update_class_info (thread_p, cls_oid, cls_infop, true);
11520 
11521  catalog_free_class_info_and_init (cls_infop);
11522 }
11523 
11524 /*
11525  * locator_decrease_catalog_count () -
11526  *
11527  * return:
11528  *
11529  * cls_oid(in): Class OID
11530  *
11531  * Note: Descrease the 'tot_objects' counter of the CLS_INFO
11532  * and do update the catalog record in-place.
11533  */
11534 static void
11535 locator_decrease_catalog_count (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OID * cls_oid)
11536 {
11537  CLS_INFO *cls_infop = NULL;
11538 
11539  /* retrieve the class information */
11540  cls_infop = catalog_get_class_info (thread_p, cls_oid);
11541  if (cls_infop == NULL)
11542  {
11543  return;
11544  }
11545 
11546  if (cls_infop->ci_hfid.vfid.fileid < 0 || cls_infop->ci_hfid.vfid.volid < 0)
11547  {
11548  /* The class does not have a heap file (i.e. it has no instances); so no statistics can be obtained for this
11549  * class; just set 'tot_objects' field to 0. */
11550  /* Is it an error to delete an instance with no heap file? */
11551  cls_infop->ci_tot_objects = 0;
11552  }
11553 
11554  /* decrease the 'tot_objects' counter */
11555  if (cls_infop->ci_tot_objects > 0)
11556  {
11557  cls_infop->ci_tot_objects--;
11558  }
11559 
11560  /* update the class information to the catalog */
11561  /* NOTE that tot_objects may not be correct because changes are NOT logged. */
11562  (void) catalog_update_class_info (thread_p, cls_oid, cls_infop, true);
11563 
11564  catalog_free_class_info_and_init (cls_infop);
11565 }
11566 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
11567 
11568 /*
11569  * xrepl_set_info () -
11570  *
11571  * return:
11572  *
11573  * repl_info(in):
11574  */
11575 int
11576 xrepl_set_info (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, REPL_INFO * repl_info)
11577 {
11578  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
11579 
11580  if (!LOG_CHECK_LOG_APPLIER (thread_p) && log_does_allow_replication () == true)
11581  {
11582  switch (repl_info->repl_info_type)
11583  {
11584  case REPL_INFO_TYPE_SBR:
11585  error_code = repl_log_insert_statement (thread_p, (REPL_INFO_SBR *) repl_info->info);
11586  break;
11587  default:
11588  error_code = ER_REPL_ERROR;
11589  er_set (ER_WARNING_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_REPL_ERROR, 1, "can't make repl sbr info");
11590  break;
11591  }
11592  }
11593 
11594  return error_code;
11595 }
11596 
11597 /*
11598  * xrepl_log_get_append_lsa () -
11599  *
11600  * return:
11601  */
11602 LOG_LSA *
11603 xrepl_log_get_append_lsa (void)
11604 {
11605  return log_get_append_lsa ();
11606 }
11607 
11608 /*
11609  * xlocator_check_fk_validity () -
11610  *
11611  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
11612  *
11613  * cls_oid(in):
11614  * hfid(in):
11615  * key_type(in):
11616  * n_attrs(in):
11617  * attr_ids(in):
11618  * pk_cls_oid(in):
11619  * pk_btid(in):
11620  * fk_name(in):
11621  */
11622 int
11623 xlocator_check_fk_validity (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OID * cls_oid, HFID * hfid, TP_DOMAIN * key_type, int n_attrs,
11624  int *attr_ids, OID * pk_cls_oid, BTID * pk_btid, char *fk_name)
11625 {
11626  HEAP_SCANCACHE scan_cache;
11627  HEAP_CACHE_ATTRINFO attr_info;
11628  OID oid;
11629  RECDES copy_recdes;
11630  DB_VALUE *key_val, tmpval;
11631  char midxkey_buf[DBVAL_BUFSIZE + MAX_ALIGNMENT], *aligned_midxkey_buf;
11632  int error_code;
11633  MVCC_SNAPSHOT *mvcc_snapshot = NULL;
11634 
11635  mvcc_snapshot = logtb_get_mvcc_snapshot (thread_p);
11636  if (mvcc_snapshot == NULL)
11637  {
11638  error_code = er_errid ();
11639  return (error_code == NO_ERROR ? ER_FAILED : error_code);
11640  }
11641 
11642  db_make_null (&tmpval);
11643 
11644  aligned_midxkey_buf = PTR_ALIGN (midxkey_buf, MAX_ALIGNMENT);
11645 
11646  error_code = heap_scancache_start (thread_p, &scan_cache, hfid, cls_oid, false, false, mvcc_snapshot);
11647  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
11648  {
11649  return error_code;
11650  }
11651 
11652  error_code = heap_attrinfo_start (thread_p, cls_oid, n_attrs, attr_ids, &attr_info);
11653  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
11654  {
11655  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache);
11656  return error_code;
11657  }
11658 
11659  OID_SET_NULL (&oid);
11660  oid.volid = hfid->vfid.volid;
11661 
11662  copy_recdes.data = NULL;
11663  while (heap_next (thread_p, hfid, NULL, &oid, &copy_recdes, &scan_cache, COPY) == S_SUCCESS)
11664  {
11665  if (n_attrs == 1)
11666  {
11667  error_code = heap_attrinfo_read_dbvalues (thread_p, &oid, &copy_recdes, NULL, &attr_info);
11668  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
11669  {
11670  goto end;
11671  }
11672  }
11673 
11674  key_val =
11675  heap_attrinfo_generate_key (thread_p, n_attrs, attr_ids, NULL, &attr_info, &copy_recdes, &tmpval,
11676  aligned_midxkey_buf, NULL);
11677  if (key_val == NULL)
11678  {
11679  error_code = ER_FAILED;
11680  goto end;
11681  }
11682 
11683  error_code =
11684  btree_check_foreign_key (thread_p, cls_oid, hfid, &oid, key_val, n_attrs, pk_cls_oid, pk_btid, fk_name);
11685 
11686  if (key_val == &tmpval)
11687  {
11688  pr_clear_value (&tmpval);
11689  }
11690 
11691  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
11692  {
11693  goto end;
11694  }
11695  }
11696 
11697 end:
11698 
11699  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache);
11700  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, &attr_info);
11701 
11702  return error_code;
11703 }
11704 
11705 /*
11706  * xlocator_lock_and_fetch_all () - Fetch all class instances that can be locked
11707  * in specified locked time
11708  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
11709  *
11710  * hfid(in): Heap file where the instances of the class are placed
11711  * instance_lock(in): Instance lock to aquire
11712  * instance_lock_timeout(in): Timeout for instance lock
11713  * class_oid(in): Class identifier of the instances to fetch
11714  * class_lock(in): Lock to acquire (Set as a side effect to NULL_LOCKID)
11715  * nobjects(out): Total number of objects to fetch.
11716  * nfetched(out): Current number of object fetched.
11717  * nfailed_instance_locks(out): count failed instance locks
11718  * last_oid(out): Object identifier of last fetched object
11719  * fetch_area(in/out): Pointer to area where the objects are placed
11720  * mvcc_snapshot(in): the snapshot to be applied in scan
11721  *
11722  */
11723 int
11724 xlocator_lock_and_fetch_all (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const HFID * hfid, LOCK * instance_lock,
11725  int *instance_lock_timeout, OID * class_oid, LOCK * class_lock, int *nobjects,
11726  int *nfetched, int *nfailed_instance_locks, OID * last_oid, LC_COPYAREA ** fetch_area,
11727  MVCC_SNAPSHOT * mvcc_snapshot)
11728 {
11729  LC_COPYAREA_DESC prefetch_des; /* Descriptor for decache of objects related to transaction isolation level */
11730  LC_COPYAREA_MANYOBJS *mobjs; /* Describe multiple objects in area */
11731  LC_COPYAREA_ONEOBJ *obj; /* Describe on object in area */
11732  RECDES recdes; /* Record descriptor for insertion */
11733  int offset; /* Place to store next object in area */
11734  int round_length; /* Length of object rounded to integer alignment */
11735  int copyarea_length;
11736  OID oid;
11737  HEAP_SCANCACHE scan_cache;
11738  SCAN_CODE scan;
11739  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
11740 
11741  if (fetch_area == NULL)
11742  {
11743  return ER_FAILED;
11744  }
11745  *fetch_area = NULL;
11746 
11747  if (nfailed_instance_locks == NULL)
11748  {
11749  return ER_FAILED;
11750  }
11751  *nfailed_instance_locks = 0;
11752 
11753  if (OID_ISNULL (last_oid))
11754  {
11755  /* FIRST TIME. */
11756 
11757  /* Obtain the desired lock for the class scan */
11758  if (*class_lock != NULL_LOCK
11759  && lock_object (thread_p, class_oid, oid_Root_class_oid, *class_lock, LK_UNCOND_LOCK) != LK_GRANTED)
11760  {
11761  /*
11762  * Unable to acquired lock
11763  */
11764  *class_lock = NULL_LOCK;
11765  *nobjects = -1;
11766  *nfetched = -1;
11767 
11768  error_code = ER_FAILED;
11769  goto error;
11770  }
11771 
11772  /* Get statistics */
11773  last_oid->volid = hfid->vfid.volid;
11774  last_oid->pageid = NULL_PAGEID;
11775  last_oid->slotid = NULL_SLOTID;
11776  /* Estimate the number of objects to be fetched */
11777  *nobjects = heap_estimate_num_objects (thread_p, hfid);
11778  *nfetched = 0;
11779  if (*nobjects == -1)
11780  {
11781  error_code = ER_FAILED;
11782  goto error;
11783  }
11784  }
11785 
11786  /* Set OID to last fetched object */
11787  COPY_OID (&oid, last_oid);
11788 
11789  /* Start a scan cursor for getting several classes */
11790  error_code = heap_scancache_start (thread_p, &scan_cache, hfid, class_oid, true, false, mvcc_snapshot);
11791  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
11792  {
11793  goto error;
11794  }
11795 
11796  /* Assume that the next object can fit in one page */
11797  copyarea_length = DB_PAGESIZE;
11798 
11799  while (true)
11800  {
11801  *fetch_area = locator_allocate_copy_area_by_length (copyarea_length);
11802  if (*fetch_area == NULL)
11803  {
11804  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache);
11805  error_code = ER_FAILED;
11806  goto error;
11807  }
11808 
11809  mobjs = LC_MANYOBJS_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (*fetch_area);
11810  LC_RECDES_IN_COPYAREA (*fetch_area, &recdes);
11811  obj = LC_START_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (mobjs);
11812  mobjs->num_objs = 0;
11813  offset = 0;
11814 
11815  while (true)
11816  {
11817  if (instance_lock && (*instance_lock != NULL_LOCK))
11818  {
11819  int lock_result = 0;
11820 
11821  scan = heap_next (thread_p, hfid, class_oid, &oid, &recdes, &scan_cache, COPY);
11822  if (scan != S_SUCCESS)
11823  {
11824  break;
11825  }
11826 
11827  if (instance_lock_timeout == NULL)
11828  {
11829  lock_result = lock_object (thread_p, &oid, class_oid, *instance_lock, LK_UNCOND_LOCK);
11830  }
11831  else
11832  {
11833  lock_result =
