11834  lock_object_wait_msecs (thread_p, &oid, class_oid, *instance_lock, LK_UNCOND_LOCK,
11835  *instance_lock_timeout);
11836  }
11837 
11838  if (lock_result != LK_GRANTED)
11839  {
11840  (*nfailed_instance_locks)++;
11841  continue;
11842  }
11843 
11844  scan = heap_get_visible_version (thread_p, &oid, class_oid, &recdes, &scan_cache, COPY, NULL_CHN);
11845  if (scan != S_SUCCESS)
11846  {
11847  (*nfailed_instance_locks)++;
11848  continue;
11849  }
11850 
11851  }
11852  else
11853  {
11854  scan = heap_next (thread_p, hfid, class_oid, &oid, &recdes, &scan_cache, COPY);
11855  if (scan != S_SUCCESS)
11856  {
11857  break;
11858  }
11859  }
11860 
11861  mobjs->num_objs++;
11862  COPY_OID (&obj->class_oid, class_oid);
11863  COPY_OID (&obj->oid, &oid);
11864  obj->flag = 0;
11865  obj->hfid = NULL_HFID;
11866  obj->length = recdes.length;
11867  obj->offset = offset;
11868  obj->operation = LC_FETCH;
11869  obj = LC_NEXT_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (obj);
11870  round_length = DB_ALIGN (recdes.length, MAX_ALIGNMENT);
11871 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
11872  /* suppress valgrind UMW error */
11873  memset (recdes.data + recdes.length, 0, MIN (round_length - recdes.length, recdes.area_size - recdes.length));
11874 #endif
11875  offset += round_length;
11876  recdes.data += round_length;
11877  recdes.area_size -= round_length + sizeof (*obj);
11878  }
11879 
11880  if (scan != S_DOESNT_FIT || mobjs->num_objs > 0)
11881  {
11882  break;
11883  }
11884  /*
11885  * The first object does not fit into given copy area
11886  * Get a larger area
11887  */
11888 
11889  /* Get the real length of current fetch/copy area */
11890  copyarea_length = (*fetch_area)->length;
11891  locator_free_copy_area (*fetch_area);
11892 
11893  /*
11894  * If the object does not fit even when the copy area seems to be
11895  * large enough, increase the copy area by at least one page size.
11896  */
11897 
11898  if ((-recdes.length) > copyarea_length)
11899  {
11900  copyarea_length = DB_ALIGN (-recdes.length, MAX_ALIGNMENT) + sizeof (*mobjs);
11901  }
11902  else
11903  {
11904  copyarea_length += DB_PAGESIZE;
11905  }
11906  }
11907 
11908  if (scan == S_END)
11909  {
11910  /*
11911  * This is the end of the loop. Indicate the caller that no more calls
11912  * are needed by setting nobjects and nfetched to the same value.
11913  */
11914  error_code = heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache);
11915  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
11916  {
11917  *nobjects = *nfetched = -1;
11918  goto error;
11919  }
11920 
11921  *nfetched += mobjs->num_objs;
11922  *nobjects = *nfetched;
11923  OID_SET_NULL (last_oid);
11924  }
11925  else if (scan == S_ERROR)
11926  {
11927  /* There was an error.. */
11928  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache);
11929  *nobjects = *nfetched = -1;
11930  error_code = ER_FAILED;
11931  goto error;
11932  }
11933  else if (mobjs->num_objs != 0)
11934  {
11935  heap_scancache_end_when_scan_will_resume (thread_p, &scan_cache);
11936  /* Set the last_oid.. and the number of fetched objects */
11937  obj = LC_PRIOR_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (obj);
11938  COPY_OID (last_oid, &obj->oid);
11939  *nfetched += mobjs->num_objs;
11940  /*
11941  * If the guess on the number of objects to fetch was low, reset the
11942  * value, so that the caller continue to call us until the end of the
11943  * scan
11944  */
11945  if (*nobjects <= *nfetched)
11946  {
11947  *nobjects = *nfetched + 10;
11948  }
11949  }
11950  else
11951  {
11952  error_code = heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache);
11953  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
11954  {
11955  goto end;
11956  }
11957  }
11958 
11959  if (*fetch_area != NULL)
11960  {
11961  prefetch_des.mobjs = mobjs;
11962  prefetch_des.obj = &obj;
11963  prefetch_des.offset = &offset;
11964  prefetch_des.recdes = &recdes;
11965  lock_notify_isolation_incons (thread_p, locator_notify_decache, &prefetch_des);
11966  }
11967 
11968 end:
11969 
11970  return error_code;
11971 
11972 error:
11973  if (*class_lock != NULL_LOCK)
11974  {
11975  lock_unlock_object (thread_p, class_oid, oid_Root_class_oid, *class_lock, false);
11976  }
11977  if (*fetch_area != NULL)
11978  {
11979  locator_free_copy_area (*fetch_area);
11980  *fetch_area = NULL;
11981  }
11982  return error_code;
11983 }
11984 
11985 /*
11986  * xlocator_upgrade_instances_domain () - scans all instances of a class and
11987  * performs an in-place domain upgrade of the specified attribute
11988  * (identified by its id) from the domain found in its current
11989  * stored representation to the domain found in the last
11990  * representation
11991  *
11992  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER_ status otherwise
11993  *
11994  * thread_p(in): thread context
11995  * class_oid(in): class to upgrade
11996  * att_id(in): attribute id within class to update
11997  *
11998  * Note: This function is used in context of ALTER CHANGE (type change
11999  * syntax). Proper lock (SCH_M_LOCK) is assumed when this function
12000  * is reached.
12001  * The entire tuple is rewritten using the new latest representation.
12002  */
12003 int
12004 xlocator_upgrade_instances_domain (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OID * class_oid, int att_id)
12005 {
12006  LOCK class_lock = SCH_M_LOCK;
12007  LOCK oid_lock = X_LOCK;
12008  LC_COPYAREA *fetch_area = NULL; /* Area where objects are received */
12009  LC_COPYAREA_MANYOBJS *mobjs = NULL; /* Describe multiple objects in area */
12010  LC_COPYAREA_ONEOBJ *obj = NULL; /* Describe one object in area */
12011  RECDES recdes;
12012  HEAP_CACHE_ATTRINFO attr_info;
12013  HEAP_SCANCACHE upd_scancache;
12014  int error = NO_ERROR;
12015  HFID hfid;
12016  int nobjects = 0, nfetched = 0, i = 0;
12017  OID last_oid;
12018  bool scancache_inited = false;
12019  bool attrinfo_inited = false;
12020  int tran_index;
12021  LOG_TDES *tdes = LOG_FIND_CURRENT_TDES (thread_p);
12022  MVCCID threshold_mvccid;
12023 
12024  HFID_SET_NULL (&hfid);
12025  OID_SET_NULL (&last_oid);
12026 
12027  if (class_oid == NULL || OID_ISNULL (class_oid) || att_id < 0)
12028  {
12029  error = ER_UNEXPECTED;
12030  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 1, "Unexpected argument of class OID or attribute id.");
12031  goto error_exit;
12032  }
12033 
12034  tran_index = LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p);
12035  nobjects = 0;
12036  nfetched = -1;
12037 
12038  error = heap_get_hfid_from_class_oid (thread_p, class_oid, &hfid);
12039  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12040  {
12041  goto error_exit;
12042  }
12043 
12044  error = heap_scancache_start_modify (thread_p, &upd_scancache, &hfid, class_oid, SINGLE_ROW_UPDATE, NULL);
12045  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12046  {
12047  goto error_exit;
12048  }
12049  scancache_inited = true;
12050 
12051  if (tdes->block_global_oldest_active_until_commit == false)
12052  {
12053  /* do not allow to advance with vacuum_Global_oldest_active_mvccid */
12054  ATOMIC_INC_32 (&vacuum_Global_oldest_active_blockers_counter, 1);
12055  tdes->block_global_oldest_active_until_commit = true;
12056  }
12057  else
12058  {
12059  assert (vacuum_Global_oldest_active_blockers_counter > 0);
12060  }
12061 
12062  /* Can't use vacuum_Global_oldest_active_mvccid here. That's because we want to avoid scenarios where VACUUM compute
12063  * oldest active mvccid, but didn't set yet vacuum_Global_oldest_active_mvccid, current transaction uses the old
12064  * value of vacuum_Global_oldest_active_mvccid, then VACUUM uses updated value of vacuum_Global_oldest_active_mvccid.
12065  * In such scenario, VACUUM can remove heap records that can't be removed by the current thread. */
12066  threshold_mvccid = logtb_get_oldest_active_mvccid (thread_p);
12067 
12068  /* VACUUM all cleanable heap objects before upgrading the domain */
12069  error = heap_vacuum_all_objects (thread_p, &upd_scancache, threshold_mvccid);
12070  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12071  {
12072  goto error_exit;
12073  }
12074 
12075  error = heap_attrinfo_start (thread_p, class_oid, -1, NULL, &attr_info);
12076  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12077  {
12078  goto error_exit;
12079  }
12080  attrinfo_inited = true;
12081 
12082  while (nobjects != nfetched)
12083  {
12084  int nfailed_instances = 0;
12085 
12086  error =
12087  xlocator_lock_and_fetch_all (thread_p, &hfid, &oid_lock, NULL, class_oid, &class_lock, &nobjects, &nfetched,
12088  &nfailed_instances, &last_oid, &fetch_area, NULL);
12089  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12090  {
12091  goto error_exit;
12092  }
12093 
12094  if (nfailed_instances != 0)
12095  {
12096  error = ER_UNEXPECTED;
12097  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 1, "Some instance is not locked.");
12098  goto error_exit;
12099  }
12100 
12101  if (fetch_area == NULL)
12102  {
12103  error = ER_UNEXPECTED;
12104  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 1, "Fetch area should not be NULL.");
12105  goto error_exit;
12106  }
12107  mobjs = LC_MANYOBJS_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (fetch_area);
12108  obj = LC_START_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (mobjs);
12109 
12110  for (i = 0; i < mobjs->num_objs; i++)
12111  {
12112  if (obj->operation == LC_FETCH_DECACHE_LOCK)
12113  {
12114  /* Skip decache lock objects, they have been added by lock_notify_isolation_incons function. */
12115  obj = LC_NEXT_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (obj);
12116  continue;
12117  }
12118  LC_RECDES_TO_GET_ONEOBJ (fetch_area, obj, &recdes);
12119 
12120  error = heap_attrinfo_clear_dbvalues (&attr_info);
12121  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12122  {
12123  goto error_exit;
12124  }
12125 
12126  error = heap_attrinfo_read_dbvalues (thread_p, &obj->oid, &recdes, NULL, &attr_info);
12127  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12128  {
12129  goto error_exit;
12130  }
12131 
12132  error = heap_object_upgrade_domain (thread_p, &upd_scancache, &attr_info, &obj->oid, att_id);
12133 
12134  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12135  {
12136  goto error_exit;
12137  }
12138 
12139  COPY_OID (&last_oid, &obj->oid);
12140  obj = LC_NEXT_ONEOBJ_PTR_IN_COPYAREA (obj);
12141  }
12142  if (fetch_area)
12143  {
12144  locator_free_copy_area (fetch_area);
12145  fetch_area = NULL;
12146  }
12147  }
12148 
12149 error_exit:
12150 
12151  if (fetch_area)
12152  {
12153  locator_free_copy_area (fetch_area);
12154  fetch_area = NULL;
12155  }
12156  if (attrinfo_inited)
12157  {
12158  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, &attr_info);
12159  }
12160  if (scancache_inited)
12161  {
12162  heap_scancache_end_modify (thread_p, &upd_scancache);
12163  }
12164 
12165  return error;
12166 }
12167 
12168 /*
12169  * locator_filter_errid() -
12170  *
12171  * return:
12172  * num_ignore_error_count(in):
12173  * ignore_error_list(in):
12174  * error_code(in):
12175  */
12176 static int
12177 locator_filter_errid (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, int num_ignore_error_count, int *ignore_error_list)
12178 {
12179  int i;
12180  int error_code;
12181 
12182  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
12183  error_code = er_errid ();
12184 
12185  for (i = 0; i < num_ignore_error_count; i++)
12186  {
12187  if (ignore_error_list[i] == error_code)
12188  {
12189  er_clear ();
12190  return NO_ERROR;
12191  }
12192  }
12193  return error_code;
12194 }
12195 
12196 /*
12197  * locator_get_partition_scancache () - setup a cache for repeated operations
12198  * which require partition pruning
12199  * return : PRUNING_SCAN_CACHE on success, NULL on error
12200  * pcontext (in) : pruning context
12201  * class_oid (in) : OID of the pruned partition
12202  * hfid (in) : HFID of the pruned partition
12203  * op_type (in) : operation type
12204  * has_function_indexes (in) : true if function indexes should be cached
12205  */
12206 PRUNING_SCAN_CACHE *
12207 locator_get_partition_scancache (PRUNING_CONTEXT * pcontext, const OID * class_oid, const HFID * hfid, int op_type,
12208  bool has_function_indexes)
12209 {
12210  PRUNING_SCAN_CACHE *scan_cache = NULL;
12211  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
12212 
12213  scan_cache = partition_get_scancache (pcontext, class_oid);
12214  if (scan_cache != NULL)
12215  {
12216  /* already cached, return it */
12217  return scan_cache;
12218  }
12219 
12220  /* create a new one and cache it */
12221  scan_cache = partition_new_scancache (pcontext);
12222  if (scan_cache == NULL)
12223  {
12224  return NULL;
12225  }
12226  error_code = locator_start_force_scan_cache (pcontext->thread_p, &scan_cache->scan_cache, hfid, class_oid, op_type);
12227  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
12228  {
12229  return NULL;
12230  }
12231 
12232  scan_cache->is_scan_cache_started = true;
12233 
12234  if (has_function_indexes)
12235  {
12236  HEAP_CACHE_ATTRINFO attr_info;
12237 
12238  error_code = heap_attrinfo_start (pcontext->thread_p, class_oid, -1, NULL, &attr_info);
12239  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
12240  {
12241  return NULL;
12242  }
12243  scan_cache->n_indexes = attr_info.last_classrepr->n_indexes;
12244  error_code =
12245  heap_init_func_pred_unpack_info (pcontext->thread_p, &attr_info, class_oid, &scan_cache->func_index_pred);
12246  heap_attrinfo_end (pcontext->thread_p, &attr_info);
12247  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
12248  {
12249  scan_cache->n_indexes = 0;
12250  scan_cache->func_index_pred = NULL;
12251  return NULL;
12252  }
12253  }
12254 
12255  return scan_cache;
12256 }
12257 
12258 /*
12259  * locator_area_op_to_pruning_type () - get pruning_type operation from
12260  * locator area operation
12261  * return: pruning type
12262  * op (in) : locator operation
12263  */
12264 static int
12265 locator_area_op_to_pruning_type (LC_COPYAREA_OPERATION op)
12266 {
12267  switch (op)
12268  {
12269  case LC_FLUSH_INSERT:
12270  case LC_FLUSH_UPDATE:
12271  case LC_FLUSH_DELETE:
12272  return DB_NOT_PARTITIONED_CLASS;
12273 
12274  case LC_FLUSH_INSERT_PRUNE:
12275  case LC_FLUSH_UPDATE_PRUNE:
12276  return DB_PARTITIONED_CLASS;
12277 
12278  case LC_FLUSH_INSERT_PRUNE_VERIFY:
12279  case LC_FLUSH_UPDATE_PRUNE_VERIFY:
12280  return DB_PARTITION_CLASS;
12281 
12282  default:
12283  assert (false);
12284  return 0;
12285  }
12286  return 0;
12287 }
12288 
12289 static int
12290 locator_prefetch_index_page (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OID * class_oid, RECDES * classrec, RECDES * recdes,
12291  int btid_index, HEAP_CACHE_ATTRINFO * attr_info)
12292 {
12293  int error = NO_ERROR;
12294  BTID *btid = NULL;
12295 
12296  btid = heap_indexinfo_get_btid (btid_index, attr_info);
12297  if (btid == NULL)
12298  {
12299  return ER_FAILED;
12300  }
12301 
12302  error = locator_prefetch_index_page_internal (thread_p, btid, class_oid, classrec, recdes);
12303  return error;
12304 }
12305 
12306 static int
12307 locator_prefetch_index_page_internal (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, BTID * btid, OID * class_oid, RECDES * classrec,
12308  RECDES * recdes)
12309 {
12310  int error = NO_ERROR;
12311  BTREE_CHECKSCAN bt_checkscan, *bt_checkscan_p = NULL;
12312  HEAP_CACHE_ATTRINFO attr_info;
12313  HEAP_CACHE_ATTRINFO *attr_info_p = NULL;
12314  HFID hfid;
12315  int index_id = -1;
12316  char buf[DBVAL_BUFSIZE + MAX_ALIGNMENT], *aligned_buf;
12317  DB_VALUE dbvalue;
12318  DB_VALUE *key = NULL;
12319  KEY_VAL_RANGE key_val_range;
12320  INDX_SCAN_ID isid;
12321  BTID tmp_btid = *btid;
12322 
12323  aligned_buf = PTR_ALIGN (buf, MAX_ALIGNMENT);
12324 
12325  or_class_hfid (classrec, &hfid);
12326  if (HFID_IS_NULL (&hfid))
12327  {
12328  return NO_ERROR;
12329  }
12330 
12331  index_id = heap_attrinfo_start_with_btid (thread_p, class_oid, &tmp_btid, &attr_info);
12332  if (index_id < 0)
12333  {
12334  goto free_and_return;
12335  }
12336  attr_info_p = &attr_info;
12337 
12338  if (btree_keyoid_checkscan_start (thread_p, &tmp_btid, &bt_checkscan) != NO_ERROR)
12339  {
12340  error = ER_FAILED;
12341  goto free_and_return;
12342  }
12343  bt_checkscan_p = &bt_checkscan;
12344 
12345  BTREE_INIT_SCAN (&bt_checkscan_p->btree_scan);
12346  scan_init_index_scan (&isid, &bt_checkscan_p->oid_list, NULL);
12347 
12348  if (heap_attrinfo_read_dbvalues_without_oid (thread_p, recdes, attr_info_p) != NO_ERROR)
12349  {
12350  error = ER_FAILED;
12351  goto free_and_return;
12352  }
12353 
12354  key = heap_attrvalue_get_key (thread_p, index_id, attr_info_p, recdes, &tmp_btid, &dbvalue, aligned_buf, NULL, NULL);
12355  if (key == NULL)
12356  {
12357  error = ER_FAILED;
12358  goto free_and_return;
12359  }
12360 
12361  PR_SHARE_VALUE (key, &key_val_range.key1);
12362  PR_SHARE_VALUE (key, &key_val_range.key2);
12363  key_val_range.range = GE_LE;
12364  key_val_range.num_index_term = 0;
12365 
12366  btree_keyval_search (thread_p, &tmp_btid, S_SELECT, &bt_checkscan_p->btree_scan, &key_val_range, class_oid, NULL,
12367  &isid, false);
12368 
12369  btree_scan_clear_key (&bt_checkscan.btree_scan);
12370 
12371 free_and_return:
12372  if (key == &dbvalue)
12373  {
12374  pr_clear_value (key);
12375  }
12376 
12377  if (bt_checkscan_p)
12378  {
12379  btree_keyoid_checkscan_end (thread_p, bt_checkscan_p);
12380  }
12381 
12382  if (attr_info_p)
12383  {
12384  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, attr_info_p);
12385  }
12386 
12387  return error;
12388 }

12390 /*
12391  * locator_incr_num_transient_classnames - increase number
12392  *
12393  * return:
12394  *
12395  * tran_index(in):
12396  *
12397  */
12398 static void
12399 locator_incr_num_transient_classnames (int tran_index)
12400 {

12402 
12403  tdes = LOG_FIND_TDES (tran_index);
12404  /* ignore ER_LOG_UNKNOWN_TRANINDEX : It may be detected somewhere else. */
12405  if (tdes != NULL)
12406  {
12407  assert (tdes->num_transient_classnames >= 0);
12408  tdes->num_transient_classnames += 1;
12409  }
12410 }
12411

12413  * locator_decr_num_transient_classnames - decrease number
12414  *
12415  * return:
12416  *
12417  * tran_index(in):
12418  *
12419  * NOTE:
12420  */
12421 static void
12422 locator_decr_num_transient_classnames (int tran_index)

12425 
12426  tdes = LOG_FIND_TDES (tran_index);
12427  /* ignore ER_LOG_UNKNOWN_TRANINDEX : It may be detected somewhere else. */
12428  if (tdes != NULL)
12429  {
12430  tdes->num_transient_classnames -= 1;
12431  assert (tdes->num_transient_classnames >= 0);
12432  }
12433 }
12434 
12435 /*
12436  * locator_get_num_transient_classnames -
12437  *
12438  * return:
12439  *
12440  * tran_index(in):
12441  *
12442  * NOTE:
12443  */
12444 static int
12445 locator_get_num_transient_classnames (int tran_index)
12446 {
12447  LOG_TDES *tdes;
12448 
12449  tdes = LOG_FIND_TDES (tran_index);
12450  /* ignore ER_LOG_UNKNOWN_TRANINDEX : It may be detected somewhere else. */
12451  if (tdes != NULL)
12452  {
12453  assert (tdes->num_transient_classnames >= 0);
12454  return tdes->num_transient_classnames;
12455  }
12456  else
12457  {
12458  return 1; /* someone exists */
12459  }
12460 }

12462 /*
12463  * locator_is_exist_class_name_entry -
12464  *
12465  * return:
12466  *
12467  * entry(in):
12468  *
12469  * NOTE: debugging function
12470  */
12471 static bool
12472 locator_is_exist_class_name_entry (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOCATOR_CLASSNAME_ENTRY * entry)
12473 {
12474 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
12475  int check_own;
12476 
12477  check_own = csect_check_own (thread_p, CSECT_LOCATOR_SR_CLASSNAME_TABLE);
12478  assert (check_own >= 1);
12479 #endif
12480 
12481  if (entry != NULL && entry->e_current.action == LC_CLASSNAME_EXIST)
12482  {
12483  assert (entry->e_name != NULL);
12484  assert (entry->e_tran_index == NULL_TRAN_INDEX);
12485 
12486  assert (!OID_ISNULL (&entry->e_current.oid));
12487  assert (heap_does_exist (thread_p, oid_Root_class_oid, &entry->e_current.oid));
12488 
12489  assert (LSA_ISNULL (&entry->e_current.savep_lsa));
12490  assert (entry->e_current.prev == NULL);
12491 
12492  return true;
12493  }
12494 
12495  return false;
12496 }

12498 /*
12499  * xchksum_insert_repl_log_and_demote_table_lock -
12500  *
12501  * return: error code
12502  *
12503  * repl_info(in):
12504  *
12505  * NOTE: insert replication log and demote the read lock of the table
12506  */
12507 int
12508 xchksum_insert_repl_log_and_demote_table_lock (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, REPL_INFO * repl_info, const OID * class_oidp)
12509 {
12510  LOG_TDES *tdes;
12511  int error = NO_ERROR;
12512 
12513  tdes = LOG_FIND_CURRENT_TDES (thread_p);
12514  if (tdes == NULL)
12515  {
12516  er_set (ER_FATAL_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_LOG_UNKNOWN_TRANINDEX, 1,
12517  LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p));
12518 
12519  return ER_LOG_UNKNOWN_TRANINDEX;
12520  }
12521 
12522  /* need to start a topop to make sure the repl log is inserted in a correct order */
12523  log_sysop_start (thread_p);
12524 
12525  repl_start_flush_mark (thread_p);
12526 
12527  error = xrepl_set_info (thread_p, repl_info);
12528 
12529  repl_end_flush_mark (thread_p, false);
12530 
12531  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12532  {
12533  ASSERT_ERROR ();
12534  log_sysop_abort (thread_p);
12535  }
12536  else
12537  {
12538  /* manually append repl info */
12539  log_append_repl_info (thread_p, tdes, false);
12540 
12541  log_sysop_commit (thread_p);
12542  }
12543 
12544 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
12545  /* demote S-lock to IS-lock to allow blocking writers to resume. This will not hurt transactional consistencies of
12546  * checksumdb. */
12547  lock_demote_read_class_lock_for_checksumdb (thread_p, tdes->tran_index, class_oidp);
12548 
12549  assert (lock_get_object_lock (class_oidp, oid_Root_class_oid, tdes->tran_index) == IS_LOCK);
12550 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
12551 
12552  return error;
12553 }
12554

12556  * locator_rv_redo_rename () - Dummy logical redo function that does nothing.
12557  *
12558  * return : NO_ERROR
12559  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry.
12560  * rcv (in) : Recovery data.
12561  */
12562 int
12563 locator_rv_redo_rename (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv)
12564 {
12565  /* Does nothing on recovery. */
12566  return NO_ERROR;
12567 }
12568 
12569 /*
12570  * redistribute_partition_data () - redistribute partition data
12571  *
12572  * return : error code
12573  *
12574  * thread_p (in) :
12575  * class_oid (in) : parent class OID
12576  * no_oids (in) : number of OIDs in the list (promoted partitions)
12577  * oid_list (in) : partition OID list (promoted partitions)
12578  */
12579 static int
12580 redistribute_partition_data (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OID * class_oid, int no_oids, OID * oid_list)
12581 {
12582  int error = NO_ERROR;
12583  int i = 0;
12584  RECDES recdes;
12585  HFID hfid, class_hfid;
12586  OID inst_oid;
12587  SCAN_CODE scan = S_SUCCESS;
12588  VPID vpid;
12589  PGBUF_WATCHER old_page_watcher;
12590  PGSLOTID slotid;
12591  HEAP_SCANCACHE parent_scan_cache, scan_cache;
12592  PRUNING_CONTEXT pcontext;
12593  bool is_scan_end = false;
12594  bool is_parent_scancache_started = false;
12595  bool is_part_scancache_started = false;
12596  bool is_pcontext_inited = false;
12597  int force_count = -1;
12598  OID oid;
12599  OID cls_oid;
12600  LOG_TDES *tdes = LOG_FIND_CURRENT_TDES (thread_p);
12601  MVCCID threshold_mvccid = MVCCID_NULL;
12602 
12603  assert (tdes != NULL);
12604 
12605  PGBUF_INIT_WATCHER (&old_page_watcher, PGBUF_ORDERED_RANK_UNDEFINED, PGBUF_ORDERED_NULL_HFID);
12606 
12607  error = heap_get_hfid_from_class_oid (thread_p, class_oid, &class_hfid);
12608  if (error != NO_ERROR || HFID_IS_NULL (&class_hfid))
12609  {
12610  error = ER_FAILED;
12611  goto exit;
12612  }
12613 
12614  /* start scan cache for insert on parent class */
12615  error = heap_scancache_start_modify (thread_p, &parent_scan_cache, &class_hfid, class_oid, SINGLE_ROW_INSERT, NULL);
12616  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12617  {
12618  goto exit;
12619  }
12620  is_parent_scancache_started = true;
12621 
12622  /* initialize pruning context for parent class */
12623  (void) partition_init_pruning_context (&pcontext);
12624  error = partition_load_pruning_context (thread_p, class_oid, DB_PARTITIONED_CLASS, &pcontext);
12625  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12626  {
12627  goto exit;
12628  }
12629  is_pcontext_inited = true;
12630 
12631  recdes.data = NULL;
12632 
12633  for (i = 0; i < no_oids; i++)
12634  {
12635  if (OID_ISNULL (&oid_list[i]))
12636  {
12637  goto exit;
12638  }
12639 
12640  error = heap_get_hfid_from_class_oid (thread_p, &oid_list[i], &hfid);
12641  if (error != NO_ERROR || HFID_IS_NULL (&hfid))
12642  {
12643  error = ER_FAILED;
12644  goto exit;
12645  }
12646 
12647  PGBUF_INIT_WATCHER (&old_page_watcher, PGBUF_ORDERED_HEAP_NORMAL, &hfid);
12648 
12649  error = heap_scancache_start (thread_p, &scan_cache, &hfid, &oid_list[i], false, false, NULL);
12650  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12651  {
12652  goto exit;
12653  }
12654  is_part_scancache_started = true;
12655 
12656  if (tdes->block_global_oldest_active_until_commit == false)
12657  {
12658  /* do not allow to advance with vacuum_Global_oldest_active_mvccid */
12659  ATOMIC_INC_32 (&vacuum_Global_oldest_active_blockers_counter, 1);
12660  tdes->block_global_oldest_active_until_commit = true;
12661  }
12662  else
12663  {
12664  assert (vacuum_Global_oldest_active_blockers_counter > 0);
12665  }
12666 
12667  if (threshold_mvccid == MVCCID_NULL)
12668  {
12669  /* Can't use vacuum_Global_oldest_active_mvccid here. That's because we want to avoid scenarios where VACUUM
12670  * compute oldest active mvccid, but didn't set yet vacuum_Global_oldest_active_mvccid, current transaction
12671  * uses the old value of vacuum_Global_oldest_active_mvccid, then VACUUM uses updated value of
12672  * vacuum_Global_oldest_active_mvccid.
12673  * In such scenario, VACUUM can remove heap records that can't be removed by the current thread. */
12674  threshold_mvccid = logtb_get_oldest_active_mvccid (thread_p);
12675  }
12676 
12677  /* VACUUM all cleanable heap objects before upgrading the domain */
12678  error = heap_vacuum_all_objects (thread_p, &scan_cache, threshold_mvccid);
12679  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12680  {
12681  ASSERT_ERROR ();
12682  goto exit;
12683  }
12684 
12685  /* start with first OID of the first page */
12686  vpid.volid = hfid.vfid.volid;
12687  vpid.pageid = hfid.hpgid;
12688  is_scan_end = false;
12689  while (!is_scan_end)
12690  {
12691  if (scan_cache.page_watcher.pgptr == NULL)
12692  {
12693  error =
12694  pgbuf_ordered_fix (thread_p, &vpid, OLD_PAGE_PREVENT_DEALLOC, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE,
12695  &scan_cache.page_watcher);
12696  if (old_page_watcher.pgptr != NULL)
12697  {
12698  pgbuf_ordered_unfix (thread_p, &old_page_watcher);
12699  }
12700  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12701  {
12702  goto exit;
12703  }
12704  }
12705 
12706  slotid = 0;
12707  while (true)
12708  {
12709  /* get next record */
12710  scan = spage_next_record (scan_cache.page_watcher.pgptr, &slotid, &recdes, PEEK);
12711  if (scan == S_ERROR)
12712  {
12713  error = ER_FAILED;
12714  goto exit;
12715  }
12716  else if (scan == S_END)
12717  {
12718  /* move to next page */
12719  error = heap_vpid_next (thread_p, &hfid, scan_cache.page_watcher.pgptr, &vpid);
12720  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12721  {
12722  goto exit;
12723  }
12724 
12725  /* keep latch on current page until the next page is fixed */
12726  pgbuf_replace_watcher (thread_p, &scan_cache.page_watcher, &old_page_watcher);
12727 
12728  if (VPID_ISNULL (&vpid))
12729  {
12730  /* no more pages in the current heap file */
12731  is_scan_end = true;
12732  }
12733  break;
12734  }
12735 
12736  if (slotid == HEAP_HEADER_AND_CHAIN_SLOTID)
12737  {
12738  /* skip the header */
12739  continue;
12740  }
12741 
12742  if (recdes.type != REC_HOME && recdes.type != REC_BIGONE && recdes.type != REC_RELOCATION)
12743  {
12744  continue;
12745  }
12746 
12747  inst_oid.pageid = vpid.pageid;
12748  inst_oid.volid = vpid.volid;
12749  inst_oid.slotid = slotid;
12750 
12751  recdes.data = NULL;
12752 
12753  if (heap_get_visible_version (thread_p, &inst_oid, class_oid, &recdes, &scan_cache, COPY, NULL_CHN) !=
12754  S_SUCCESS)
12755  {
12756  error = ER_FAILED;
12757  goto exit;
12758  }
12759 
12760  /* make sure that pruning does not change the given class OID */
12761  COPY_OID (&cls_oid, class_oid);
12762  error =
12763  locator_insert_force (thread_p, &class_hfid, &cls_oid, &oid, &recdes, true, SINGLE_ROW_INSERT,
12764  &parent_scan_cache, &force_count, DB_PARTITIONED_CLASS, &pcontext, NULL,
12765  UPDATE_INPLACE_OLD_MVCCID);
12766  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12767  {
12768  goto exit;
12769  }
12770  }
12771  }
12772 
12773  if (old_page_watcher.pgptr != NULL)
12774  {
12775  pgbuf_ordered_unfix (thread_p, &old_page_watcher);
12776  }
12777  if (is_part_scancache_started == true)
12778  {
12779  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache);
12780  is_part_scancache_started = false;
12781  }
12782  }
12783 
12784 exit:
12785  if (old_page_watcher.pgptr != NULL)
12786  {
12787  pgbuf_ordered_unfix (thread_p, &old_page_watcher);
12788  }
12789  if (scan_cache.page_watcher.pgptr != NULL)
12790  {
12791  pgbuf_ordered_unfix (thread_p, &scan_cache.page_watcher);
12792  }
12793  if (is_parent_scancache_started == true)
12794  {
12795  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &parent_scan_cache);
12796  }
12797  if (is_part_scancache_started == true)
12798  {
12799  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &scan_cache);
12800  }
12801  if (is_pcontext_inited == true)
12802  {
12803  partition_clear_pruning_context (&pcontext);
12804  }
12805 
12806  return error;
12807 }
12808 
12809 /*
12810  * xlocator_redistribute_partition_data () - redistribute partition data
12811  *
12812  * return : error code
12813  *
12814  * thread_p (in) :
12815  * class_oid (in) : parent class OID
12816  * no_oids (in) : number of OIDs in the list (promoted partitions)
12817  * oid_list (in) : partition OID list (promoted partitions)
12818  */
12819 int
12820 xlocator_redistribute_partition_data (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OID * class_oid, int no_oids, OID * oid_list)
12821 {
12822  return redistribute_partition_data (thread_p, class_oid, no_oids, oid_list);
12823 }
12824 
12825 /*
12826  * locator_lock_and_get_object_internal () - Internal function: aquire lock and return object
12827  *
12828  * return : scan code
12829  * thread_p (in) :
12830  * context (in/out): Heap get context .
12831  * lock_mode (in) : Type of lock.
12832  *
12833  * NOTE: Caller must handle the cleanup of context
12834  */
12835 static SCAN_CODE
12836 locator_lock_and_get_object_internal (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, HEAP_GET_CONTEXT * context, LOCK lock_mode)
12837 {
12838  SCAN_CODE scan = S_SUCCESS;
12839  bool lock_acquired = false;
12840 
12841  assert (context != NULL);
12842  assert (context->oid_p != NULL && !OID_ISNULL (context->oid_p));
12843  assert (context->class_oid_p != NULL && !OID_ISNULL (context->class_oid_p));
12844  assert (lock_mode > NULL_LOCK); /* this is not the appropriate function for NULL_LOCK */
12845  assert (context->scan_cache != NULL);
12846 
12847  /* try to lock the object conditionally, if it fails unfix page watchers and try unconditionally */
12848 
12849  if (lock_object (thread_p, context->oid_p, context->class_oid_p, lock_mode, LK_COND_LOCK) != LK_GRANTED)
12850  {
12851  if (context->scan_cache && context->scan_cache->cache_last_fix_page && context->home_page_watcher.pgptr != NULL)
12852  {
12853  /* prevent caching home page watcher in scan_cache */
12854  pgbuf_ordered_unfix (thread_p, &context->home_page_watcher);
12855  }
12856  heap_clean_get_context (thread_p, context);
12857  if (lock_object (thread_p, context->oid_p, context->class_oid_p, lock_mode, LK_UNCOND_LOCK) != LK_GRANTED)
12858  {
12859  goto error;
12860  }
12861 
12862  lock_acquired = true;
12863 
12864  /* Prepare for getting record again. Since pages have been unlatched, others may have changed them */
12865  scan = heap_prepare_get_context (thread_p, context, false, LOG_WARNING_IF_DELETED);
12866  if (scan != S_SUCCESS)
12867  {
12868  goto error;
12869  }
12870  }
12871  else
12872  {
12873  lock_acquired = true;
12874  }
12875 
12876  assert (OID_IS_ROOTOID (context->class_oid_p) || lock_mode == S_LOCK || lock_mode == X_LOCK);
12877 
12878  /* Lock should be aquired now -> get recdes */
12879  if (context->recdes_p != NULL)
12880  {
12881  scan = heap_get_last_version (thread_p, context);
12882  /* this scan_code must be preserved until the end of this function to be returned; - unless an error occur */
12883  if (scan != S_SUCCESS && scan != S_SUCCESS_CHN_UPTODATE)
12884  {
12885  goto error;
12886  }
12887  }
12888 
12889  /* Check isolation restrictions and the visibility of the object if it belongs to a mvcc class */
12890  if (!mvcc_is_mvcc_disabled_class (context->class_oid_p))
12891  {
12892  MVCC_REC_HEADER recdes_header;
12893 
12894  /* get header: directly from recdes if it has been obtained, otherwise from heap */
12895  if (context->recdes_p == NULL || scan == S_SUCCESS_CHN_UPTODATE)
12896  {
12897  /* ensure context is prepared to get header of the record */
12898  if (heap_prepare_get_context (thread_p, context, false, LOG_WARNING_IF_DELETED) != S_SUCCESS)
12899  {
12900  scan = S_ERROR;
12901  goto error;
12902  }
12903  if (heap_get_mvcc_header (thread_p, context, &recdes_header) != S_SUCCESS)
12904  {
12905  scan = S_ERROR;
12906  goto error;
12907  }
12908  }
12909  else if (or_mvcc_get_header (context->recdes_p, &recdes_header) != NO_ERROR)
12910  {
12911  goto error;
12912  }
12913 
12914  /* Check REPEATABLE READ/SERIALIZABLE isolation restrictions. */
12915  if (logtb_find_current_isolation (thread_p) > TRAN_READ_COMMITTED
12916  && logtb_check_class_for_rr_isolation_err (context->class_oid_p))
12917  {
12918  /* In these isolation levels, the transaction is not allowed to modify an object that was already
12919  * modified by other transactions. This would be true if last version matched the visible version.
12920  *
12921  * TODO: We already know here that this last row version is not deleted. It would be enough to just
12922  * check whether the insert MVCCID is considered active relatively to transaction's snapshot.
12923  */
12924  MVCC_SNAPSHOT *tran_snapshot = logtb_get_mvcc_snapshot (thread_p);
12925  MVCC_SATISFIES_SNAPSHOT_RESULT snapshot_res;
12926 
12927  assert (tran_snapshot != NULL && tran_snapshot->snapshot_fnc != NULL);
12928  snapshot_res = tran_snapshot->snapshot_fnc (thread_p, &recdes_header, tran_snapshot);
12929  if (snapshot_res == TOO_OLD_FOR_SNAPSHOT)
12930  {
12931  /* Not visible. */
12932  er_set (ER_WARNING_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT, 3, context->oid_p->volid,
12933  context->oid_p->pageid, context->oid_p->slotid);
12934  scan = S_DOESNT_EXIST;
12935  goto error;
12936  }
12937  else if (snapshot_res == TOO_NEW_FOR_SNAPSHOT)
12938  {
12939  /* Trying to modify a version already modified by concurrent transaction, which is an isolation conflict.
12940  */
12941  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_MVCC_SERIALIZABLE_CONFLICT, 0);
12942  goto error;
12943  }
12944  else if (MVCC_IS_HEADER_DELID_VALID (&recdes_header))
12945  {
12946  /* Trying to modify version deleted by concurrent transaction, which is an isolation conflict. */
12947  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_MVCC_SERIALIZABLE_CONFLICT, 0);
12948  goto error;
12949  }
12950  else
12951  {
12952  /* Last version is also visible version and it is not deleted. Fall through. */
12953  }
12954  }
12955 
12956  if (MVCC_IS_HEADER_DELID_VALID (&recdes_header))
12957  {
12958  scan = S_DOESNT_EXIST;
12959  goto error;
12960  }
12961  }
12962 
12963  return scan;
12964 
12965 error:
12966 
12967  if (scan == S_ERROR)
12968  {
12969  /* Caller should handle error setting for other scan codes e.g. S_DOESNT_EXIST, S_DOESNT_FIT. */
12970  ASSERT_ERROR ();
12971  }
12972 
12973  if (lock_acquired)
12974  {
12975  lock_unlock_object_donot_move_to_non2pl (thread_p, context->oid_p, context->class_oid_p, lock_mode);
12976  }
12977 
12978  return (scan != S_SUCCESS && scan != S_SUCCESS_CHN_UPTODATE) ? scan : S_ERROR;
12979 }
12980 
12981 /*
12982  * locator_lock_and_get_object_with_evaluation () - Get MVCC object version for delete/update and check reevaluation.
12983  *
12984  * return : SCAN_CODE.
12985  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry.
12986  * oid (in) : Object OID.
12987  * class_oid (in) : Class OID.
12988  * recdes (out) : Record descriptor.
12989  * scan_cache (in) : Heap scan cache.
12990  * ispeeking (in) : PEEK or COPY.
12991  * old_chn (in) : CHN of known record data.
12992  * mvcc_reev_data (in) : MVCC reevaluation data.
12993  * (obsolete) non_ex_handling_type (in): - LOG_ERROR_IF_DELETED: write the
12994  * ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT error to log
12995  * - LOG_WARNING_IF_DELETED: set only warning
12996  *
12997  * Note: This function will lock the object with X_LOCK. This lock type should correspond to delete/update operations.
12998  */
12999 SCAN_CODE
13000 locator_lock_and_get_object_with_evaluation (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OID * oid, OID * class_oid, RECDES * recdes,
13001  HEAP_SCANCACHE * scan_cache, int ispeeking, int old_chn,
13002  MVCC_REEV_DATA * mvcc_reev_data,
13003  NON_EXISTENT_HANDLING non_ex_handling_type)
13004 {
13005  HEAP_GET_CONTEXT context;
13006  SCAN_CODE scan = S_SUCCESS;
13007  RECDES recdes_local = RECDES_INITIALIZER;
13008  MVCC_REC_HEADER mvcc_header = MVCC_REC_HEADER_INITIALIZER;
13009  DB_LOGICAL ev_res = V_UNKNOWN; /* Re-evaluation result. */
13010  OID class_oid_local = OID_INITIALIZER;
13011  LOCK lock_mode = X_LOCK;
13012  int err = NO_ERROR;
13013 
13014  if (recdes == NULL && mvcc_reev_data != NULL)
13015  {
13016  /* peek if only for reevaluation */
13017  recdes = &recdes_local;
13018  ispeeking = PEEK;
13019  old_chn = NULL_CHN;
13020  }
13021 
13022  if (class_oid == NULL)
13023  {
13024  class_oid = &class_oid_local;
13025  }
13026 
13027  if (scan_cache && ispeeking == COPY && recdes != NULL)
13028  {
13029  /* Allocate an area to hold the object. Assume that the object will fit in two pages for not better estimates. */
13030  if (heap_scan_cache_allocate_area (thread_p, scan_cache, DB_PAGESIZE * 2) != NO_ERROR)
13031  {
13032  return S_ERROR;
13033  }
13034  }
13035  heap_init_get_context (thread_p, &context, oid, class_oid, recdes, scan_cache, ispeeking, old_chn);
13036 
13037  /* get class_oid if it is unknown */
13038  if (OID_ISNULL (class_oid))
13039  {
13040  err = heap_prepare_object_page (thread_p, oid, &context.home_page_watcher, context.latch_mode);
13041  if (err != NO_ERROR)
13042  {
13043  ASSERT_ERROR ();
13044  heap_clean_get_context (thread_p, &context);
13045 
13046  /* for non existent object, return S_DOESNT_EXIST and let the caller handle the case */
13047  return err == ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT ? S_DOESNT_EXIST : S_ERROR;
13048  }
13049  if (heap_get_class_oid_from_page (thread_p, context.home_page_watcher.pgptr, class_oid) != NO_ERROR)
13050  {
13051  heap_clean_get_context (thread_p, &context);
13052  return S_DOESNT_EXIST;
13053  }
13054  }
13055 
13056  scan = locator_lock_and_get_object_internal (thread_p, &context, lock_mode);
13057 
13058  /* perform reevaluation */
13059  if (mvcc_reev_data != NULL && (scan == S_SUCCESS || scan == S_SUCCESS_CHN_UPTODATE))
13060  {
13061  if (scan == S_SUCCESS_CHN_UPTODATE)
13062  {
13063  /* PEEK record */
13064  scan = heap_get_record_data_when_all_ready (thread_p, &context);
13065  assert (scan == S_SUCCESS);
13066  }
13067 
13068  if (or_mvcc_get_header (recdes, &mvcc_header) != NO_ERROR)
13069  {
13070  scan = S_ERROR;
13071  goto exit;
13072  }
13073 
13074  if (scan_cache->mvcc_snapshot)
13075  {
13076  MVCC_SATISFIES_SNAPSHOT_RESULT snapshot_res;
13077 
13078  snapshot_res = scan_cache->mvcc_snapshot->snapshot_fnc (thread_p, &mvcc_header, scan_cache->mvcc_snapshot);
13079  if (snapshot_res == SNAPSHOT_SATISFIED)
13080  {
13081  /* Skip the re-evaluation if last version is visible. It should be the same as the visible version
13082  * which was already evaluated. */
13083  goto exit;
13084  }
13085  }
13086  ev_res = locator_mvcc_reev_cond_and_assignment (thread_p, scan_cache, mvcc_reev_data, &mvcc_header, oid, recdes);
13087  if (ev_res != V_TRUE)
13088  {
13089  /* did not pass the evaluation or error occurred - unlock object */
13090  lock_unlock_object_donot_move_to_non2pl (thread_p, oid, class_oid, lock_mode);
13091  }
13092  switch (ev_res)
13093  {
13094  case V_TRUE:
13095  /* Object was locked and passed re-evaluation. Get record. */
13096  goto exit;
13097  case V_ERROR:
13098  /* Error. */
13099  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
13100  scan = S_ERROR;
13101  goto exit;
13102  case V_FALSE:
13103  case V_UNKNOWN:
13104  /* Record didn't pass re-evaluation. Return S_SUCCESS and let the caller handle the case. */
13105  goto exit;
13106  default:
13107  /* Unhandled. */
13108  assert_release (false);
13109  scan = S_ERROR;
13110  goto exit;
13111  }
13112 
13113  }
13114 
13115 exit:
13116  heap_clean_get_context (thread_p, &context);
13117  return scan;
13118 }
13119 
13120 /*
13121  * locator_get_object () - Retrieve heap objects and decide the type of lock according to the operation type
13122  *
13123  * return : Scan code.
13124  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry.
13125  * oid (in) : Object identifier.
13126  * class_oid (in) : Class oid.
13127  * recdes (out) : Record descriptor.
13128  * scan_cache (in): Scan cache.
13129  * op_type (in) : Requested type of operation.
13130  * lock_mode (in) : Lock type, see note.
13131  * ispeeking (in) : Peek record or copy.
13132  *
13133  * Note: This function should be used when class_oid is unknown, which is required to decide lock_mode;
13134  * When lock_mode is known, a more appropriate function is recommended.
13135  *
13136  * op_type and lock_mode exclude each other according to class type:
13137  * - root class : lock_mode is considered, op_type is ignored
13138  * - instance class: op_type is considered, a new lock_mode is used (according to op_type)
13139  */
13140 SCAN_CODE
13141 locator_get_object (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const OID * oid, OID * class_oid, RECDES * recdes,
13142  HEAP_SCANCACHE * scan_cache, SCAN_OPERATION_TYPE op_type, LOCK lock_mode, int ispeeking, int chn)
13143 {
13144  SCAN_CODE scan_code;
13145  OID class_oid_local = OID_INITIALIZER;
13146  HEAP_GET_CONTEXT context;
13147  int err;
13148 
13149  /* decide the type of lock before anything */
13150 
13151  assert (oid != NULL && !OID_ISNULL (oid));
13152 
13153  if (class_oid == NULL)
13154  {
13155  /* mandatory to decide the lock type */
13156  class_oid = &class_oid_local;
13157  }
13158 
13159  if (scan_cache && ispeeking == COPY && recdes != NULL)
13160  {
13161  /* Allocate an area to hold the object. Assume that the object will fit in two pages for not better estimates. */
13162  if (heap_scan_cache_allocate_area (thread_p, scan_cache, DB_PAGESIZE * 2) != NO_ERROR)
13163  {
13164  return S_ERROR;
13165  }
13166  }
13167 
13168  heap_init_get_context (thread_p, &context, oid, class_oid, recdes, scan_cache, ispeeking, chn);
13169 
13170  /* get class_oid if it is unknown */
13171  if (OID_ISNULL (class_oid))
13172  {
13173  err = heap_prepare_object_page (thread_p, oid, &context.home_page_watcher, context.latch_mode);
13174  if (err != NO_ERROR)
13175  {
13176  ASSERT_ERROR ();
13177  heap_clean_get_context (thread_p, &context);
13178 
13179  /* for non existent object, return S_DOESNT_EXIST and let the caller handle the case */
13180  return err == ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT ? S_DOESNT_EXIST : S_ERROR;
13181  }
13182  if (heap_get_class_oid_from_page (thread_p, context.home_page_watcher.pgptr, class_oid) != NO_ERROR)
13183  {
13184  heap_clean_get_context (thread_p, &context);
13185  return S_DOESNT_EXIST;
13186  }
13187  }
13188 
13189  /* decide lock_mode according to class_oid and op_type */
13190  if (!OID_IS_ROOTOID (class_oid))
13191  {
13192  if (op_type == S_SELECT && !mvcc_is_mvcc_disabled_class (class_oid))
13193  {
13194  /* S_SELECT and mvcc class */
13195  lock_mode = NULL_LOCK;
13196  }
13197  else if (op_type == S_DELETE || op_type == S_UPDATE)
13198  {
13199  assert (lock_mode > S_LOCK);
13200  lock_mode = X_LOCK;
13201  }
13202  else
13203  {
13204  /* S_SELECT and non-mvcc class || S_SELECT_WITH_LOCK */
13205  assert (op_type == S_SELECT || op_type == S_SELECT_WITH_LOCK);
13206  if (lock_mode > S_LOCK)
13207  {
13208  assert (false);
13209  lock_mode = X_LOCK;
13210  }
13211  else
13212  {
13213  lock_mode = S_LOCK;
13214  }
13215  }
13216  }
13217 
13218  if (op_type == S_SELECT && lock_mode == NULL_LOCK)
13219  {
13220  /* No locking */
13221  scan_code = heap_get_visible_version_internal (thread_p, &context, false);
13222  }
13223  else
13224  {
13225  /* Locking */
13226  scan_code = locator_lock_and_get_object_internal (thread_p, &context, lock_mode);
13227  }
13228 
13229  heap_clean_get_context (thread_p, &context);
13230 
13231  return scan_code;
13232 }
13233 
13234 
13235 /*
13236  * locator_lock_and_get_object () - Get MVCC object version for delete/update.
13237  *
13238  * return : SCAN_CODE.
13239  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry.
13240  * oid (in) : Object OID.
13241  * class_oid (in) : Class OID.
13242  * recdes (out) : Record descriptor.
13243  * scan_cache (in) : Heap scan cache.
13244  * ispeeking (in) : PEEK or COPY.
13245  * old_chn (in) : CHN of known record data.
13246  * mvcc_reev_data (in) : MVCC reevaluation data.
13247  * (obsolete) non_ex_handling_type (in): - LOG_ERROR_IF_DELETED: write the
13248  * ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT error to log
13249  * - LOG_WARNING_IF_DELETED: set only warning
13250  */
13251 SCAN_CODE
13252 locator_lock_and_get_object (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const OID * oid, OID * class_oid, RECDES * recdes,
13253  HEAP_SCANCACHE * scan_cache, LOCK lock, int ispeeking, int old_chn,
13254  NON_EXISTENT_HANDLING non_ex_handling_type)
13255 {
13256  HEAP_GET_CONTEXT context;
13257  SCAN_CODE scan_code;
13258 
13259  if (scan_cache && ispeeking == COPY && recdes != NULL)
13260  {
13261  /* Allocate an area to hold the object. Assume that the object will fit in two pages for not better estimates. */
13262  if (heap_scan_cache_allocate_area (thread_p, scan_cache, DB_PAGESIZE * 2) != NO_ERROR)
13263  {
13264  return S_ERROR;
13265  }
13266  }
13267 
13268  heap_init_get_context (thread_p, &context, oid, class_oid, recdes, scan_cache, ispeeking, old_chn);
13269  scan_code = locator_lock_and_get_object_internal (thread_p, &context, lock);
13270  heap_clean_get_context (thread_p, &context);
13271  return scan_code;
13272 }
13273 
13274 /*
13275  * locator_mvcc_reev_cond_and_assignment () -
13276  *
13277  * return: DB_LOGICAL
13278  * thread_p(in): thread entry
13279  * scan_cache(in):
13280  * mvcc_reev_data_p(in/out):
13281  * mvcc_header_p(in):
13282  * curr_row_version_oid_p(in):
13283  * recdes(in):
13284  */
13285 /* TODO: We need to reevaluate relation between primary key * and foreign key. */
13286 static DB_LOGICAL
13287 locator_mvcc_reev_cond_and_assignment (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, HEAP_SCANCACHE * scan_cache,
13288  MVCC_REEV_DATA * mvcc_reev_data_p, MVCC_REC_HEADER * mvcc_header_p,
13289  const OID * curr_row_version_oid_p, RECDES * recdes)
13290 {
13291  DB_LOGICAL ev_res = V_TRUE;
13292 
13293  if (mvcc_reev_data_p == NULL)
13294  {
13295  return ev_res;
13296  }
13297 
13298  assert (mvcc_header_p != NULL && curr_row_version_oid_p != NULL);
13299 
13300  ev_res = V_TRUE;
13301  if (!MVCC_IS_REC_INSERTED_BY_ME (thread_p, mvcc_header_p))
13302  {
13303  switch (mvcc_reev_data_p->type)
13304  {
13305  case REEV_DATA_SCAN:
13306  ev_res = locator_mvcc_reevaluate_filters (thread_p, mvcc_reev_data_p->select_reev_data,
13307  curr_row_version_oid_p, recdes);
13308  mvcc_reev_data_p->filter_result = ev_res;
13309  break;
13310 
13311  case REEV_DATA_UPDDEL:
13312  ev_res =
13313  locator_mvcc_reev_cond_assigns (thread_p, &scan_cache->node.class_oid, curr_row_version_oid_p, scan_cache,
13314  recdes, mvcc_reev_data_p->upddel_reev_data);
13315  mvcc_reev_data_p->filter_result = ev_res;
13316  break;
13317 
13318  default:
13319  break;
13320  }
13321  }
13322  else
13323  {
13324  mvcc_reev_data_p->filter_result = V_TRUE;
13325  }
13326 
13327  return ev_res;
13328 }
13329 
13330 /*
13331  * locator_mvcc_reev_cond_assigns () - reevaluates conditions and assignments
13332  * at update/delete stage of an UPDATE/DELETE
13333  * statement
13334  * return: result of reevaluation
13335  * thread_p(in): thread entry
13336  * class_oid(in): OID of the class that triggered reevaluation
13337  * oid(in) : The OID of the latest version of record that triggered
13338  * reevaluation
13339  * scan_cache(in): scan_cache
13340  * recdes(in): Record descriptor that will contain the updated/deleted record
13341  * mvcc_reev_data(in): The structure that contains data needed for
13342  * reevaluation
13343  *
13344  * Note: the current transaction already acquired X-LOCK on oid parameter
13345  * before calling this function. If the condition returns false then
13346  * the lock must be released by the caller.
13347  * The function reevaluates entire condition: key range, key filter and
13348  * data filter.
13349  * This function allocates memory for recdes and deallocates it if it
13350  * was already allocated for previous reevaluated record. After last
13351  * reevaluation this memory must be deallocated by one of its callers
13352  * (e.g. qexec_execute_update).
13353  */
13354 static DB_LOGICAL
13355 locator_mvcc_reev_cond_assigns (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OID * class_oid, const OID * oid, HEAP_SCANCACHE * scan_cache,
13356  RECDES * recdes, MVCC_UPDDEL_REEV_DATA * mvcc_reev_data)
13357 {
13358  DB_LOGICAL ev_res = V_TRUE;
13359  UPDDEL_MVCC_COND_REEVAL *mvcc_cond_reeval = NULL;
13360  int idx;
13361 
13362  /* reevaluate condition for each class involved into */
13363  for (mvcc_cond_reeval = mvcc_reev_data->mvcc_cond_reev_list; mvcc_cond_reeval != NULL;
13364  mvcc_cond_reeval = mvcc_cond_reeval->next)
13365  {
13366  ev_res =
13367  locator_mvcc_reeval_scan_filters (thread_p, oid, scan_cache, recdes, mvcc_cond_reeval,
13368  mvcc_reev_data->curr_upddel == mvcc_cond_reeval);
13369  if (ev_res != V_TRUE)
13370  {
13371  goto end;
13372  }
13373  }
13374 
13375  if (mvcc_reev_data->new_recdes == NULL)
13376  {
13377  /* Seems that the caller wants to reevaluate only the condition */
13378  goto end;
13379  }
13380 
13381  /* reload data from classes involved only in right side of assignments (not in condition) */
13382  if (mvcc_reev_data->curr_extra_assign_reev != NULL)
13383  {
13384  for (idx = 0; idx < mvcc_reev_data->curr_extra_assign_cnt; idx++)
13385  {
13386  mvcc_cond_reeval = mvcc_reev_data->curr_extra_assign_reev[idx];
13387  ev_res = locator_mvcc_reeval_scan_filters (thread_p, oid, scan_cache, recdes, mvcc_cond_reeval, false);
13388  if (ev_res != V_TRUE)
13389  {
13390  goto end;
13391  }
13392  }
13393  }
13394 
13395  /* after reevaluation perform assignments */
13396  if (mvcc_reev_data->curr_assigns != NULL)
13397  {
13398  UPDATE_MVCC_REEV_ASSIGNMENT *assign = mvcc_reev_data->curr_assigns;
13399  int rc;
13400  DB_VALUE *dbval = NULL;
13401 
13402  if (heap_attrinfo_clear_dbvalues (mvcc_reev_data->curr_attrinfo) != NO_ERROR)
13403  {
13404  ev_res = V_ERROR;
13405  goto end;
13406  }
13407  for (; assign != NULL; assign = assign->next)
13408  {
13409  if (assign->constant != NULL)
13410  {
13411  rc = heap_attrinfo_set (oid, assign->att_id, assign->constant, mvcc_reev_data->curr_attrinfo);
13412  }
13413  else
13414  {
13415  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, assign->regu_right, mvcc_reev_data->vd, (OID *) class_oid, (OID *) oid,
13416  NULL, &dbval) != NO_ERROR)
13417  {
13418  ev_res = V_ERROR;
13419  goto end;
13420  }
13421  rc = heap_attrinfo_set (oid, assign->att_id, dbval, mvcc_reev_data->curr_attrinfo);
13422  if (dbval->need_clear)
13423  {
13424  pr_clear_value (dbval);
13425  }
13426  }
13427  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
13428  {
13429  ev_res = V_ERROR;
13430  goto end;
13431  }
13432  }
13433 
13434  /* TO DO - reuse already allocated area */
13435  if (mvcc_reev_data->copyarea != NULL)
13436  {
13437  locator_free_copy_area (mvcc_reev_data->copyarea);
13438  mvcc_reev_data->new_recdes->data = NULL;
13439  mvcc_reev_data->new_recdes->area_size = 0;
13440  }
13441  mvcc_reev_data->copyarea =
13442  locator_allocate_copy_area_by_attr_info (thread_p, mvcc_reev_data->curr_attrinfo, recdes,
13443  mvcc_reev_data->new_recdes, -1, LOB_FLAG_INCLUDE_LOB);
13444  if (mvcc_reev_data->copyarea == NULL)
13445  {
13446  ev_res = V_ERROR;
13447  goto end;
13448  }
13449  }
13450 
13451 end:
13452 
13453  return ev_res;
13454 }
13455 
13456 /*
13457  * locator_mvcc_reeval_scan_filters () - reevaluates conditions for a scan table
13458  * at update/delete stage of an UPDATE/DELETE
13459  * statement
13460  * return: result of reevaluation
13461  * thread_p(in): thread entry
13462  * oid(in) : The OID of the latest version of record that triggered
13463  * reevaluation
13464  * scan_cache(in): scan_cache
13465  * recdes(in): Record descriptor of the record to be updated/deleted.
13466  * mvcc_cond_reeval(in): The structure that contains data needed for
13467  * reevaluation
13468  * is_upddel(in): true if current scan is updated/deleted when reevaluation
13469  * occured.
13470  *
13471  * Note: The current transaction already acquired X-LOCK on oid parameter
13472  * before calling this function. If the condition returns false then
13473  * the lock must be released by the caller.
13474  * The function reevaluates entire condition: key range, key filter and
13475  * data filter.
13476  */
13477 static DB_LOGICAL
13478 locator_mvcc_reeval_scan_filters (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const OID * oid, HEAP_SCANCACHE * scan_cache,
13479  RECDES * recdes, UPDDEL_MVCC_COND_REEVAL * mvcc_cond_reeval, bool is_upddel)
13480 {
13481  OID *cls_oid = NULL;
13482  const OID *oid_inst = NULL;
13483  MVCC_SCAN_REEV_DATA scan_reev;
13484  RECDES temp_recdes, *recdesp = NULL;
13485  HEAP_SCANCACHE local_scan_cache;
13486  bool scan_cache_inited = false;
13487  SCAN_CODE scan_code;
13488  DB_LOGICAL ev_res = V_TRUE;
13489 
13490  cls_oid = &mvcc_cond_reeval->cls_oid;
13491  if (!is_upddel)
13492  {
13493  /* the class is different than the class to be updated/deleted, so use the latest version of row */
13494  recdesp = &temp_recdes;
13495  oid_inst = oid;
13496  if (heap_scancache_quick_start_with_class_hfid (thread_p, &local_scan_cache, &scan_cache->node.hfid) != NO_ERROR)
13497  {
13498  ev_res = V_ERROR;
13499  goto end;
13500  }
13501  scan_cache_inited = true;
13502  scan_code = heap_get_visible_version (thread_p, oid_inst, NULL, recdesp, &local_scan_cache, PEEK, NULL_CHN);
13503  if (scan_code != S_SUCCESS)
13504  {
13505  ev_res = V_ERROR;
13506  goto end;
13507  }
13508  }
13509  else
13510  {
13511  /* the class to be updated/deleted */
13512  recdesp = recdes;
13513  oid_inst = mvcc_cond_reeval->inst_oid;
13514  }
13515 
13516  if (mvcc_cond_reeval->rest_attrs->num_attrs != 0)
13517  {
13518  if (heap_attrinfo_read_dbvalues (thread_p, oid_inst, recdesp, NULL, mvcc_cond_reeval->rest_attrs->attr_cache) !=
13519  NO_ERROR)
13520  {
13521  ev_res = V_ERROR;
13522  goto end;
13523  }
13524 
13525  if (fetch_val_list (thread_p, mvcc_cond_reeval->rest_regu_list, NULL, cls_oid, (OID *) oid_inst, NULL, PEEK)
13526  != NO_ERROR)
13527  {
13528  ev_res = V_ERROR;
13529  goto end;
13530  }
13531  }
13532 
13533  if (mvcc_cond_reeval->range_filter.scan_pred != NULL || mvcc_cond_reeval->key_filter.scan_pred != NULL
13534  || mvcc_cond_reeval->data_filter.scan_pred != NULL)
13535  {
13536  /* evaluate conditions */
13537  scan_reev.range_filter = &mvcc_cond_reeval->range_filter;
13538  scan_reev.key_filter = &mvcc_cond_reeval->key_filter;
13539  scan_reev.data_filter = &mvcc_cond_reeval->data_filter;
13540  scan_reev.qualification = &mvcc_cond_reeval->qualification;
13541  ev_res = locator_mvcc_reevaluate_filters (thread_p, &scan_reev, oid_inst, recdesp);
13542  }
13543 
13544 end:
13545  if (scan_cache_inited)
13546  {
13547  heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &local_scan_cache);
13548  }
13549 
13550  return ev_res;
13551 }
13552 
13553 /*
13554  * locator_mvcc_reevaluate_filters () - reevaluates key range, key filter and data
13555  * filter predicates
13556  * return: result of reevaluation
13557  * thread_p(in): thread entry
13558  * mvcc_reev_data(in): The structure that contains data needed for
13559  * reevaluation
13560  * oid(in) : The record that was modified by other transactions and is
13561  * involved in filters.
13562  * recdes(in): Record descriptor that will contain the record
13563  */
13564 static DB_LOGICAL
13565 locator_mvcc_reevaluate_filters (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, MVCC_SCAN_REEV_DATA * mvcc_reev_data, const OID * oid,
13566  RECDES * recdes)
13567 {
13568  FILTER_INFO *filter;
13569  DB_LOGICAL ev_res = V_TRUE;
13570 
13571  filter = mvcc_reev_data->range_filter;
13572  if (filter != NULL && filter->scan_pred != NULL && filter->scan_pred->pred_expr != NULL)
13573  {
13574  if (heap_attrinfo_read_dbvalues (thread_p, oid, recdes, NULL, filter->scan_attrs->attr_cache) != NO_ERROR)
13575  {
13576  return V_ERROR;
13577  }
13578  ev_res =
13579  (*filter->scan_pred->pr_eval_fnc) (thread_p, filter->scan_pred->pred_expr, filter->val_descr, (OID *) oid);
13580  ev_res = update_logical_result (thread_p, ev_res, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
13581  if (ev_res != V_TRUE)
13582  {
13583  goto end;
13584  }
13585  }
13586 
13587  filter = mvcc_reev_data->key_filter;
13588  if (filter != NULL && filter->scan_pred != NULL && filter->scan_pred->pred_expr != NULL)
13589  {
13590  if (heap_attrinfo_read_dbvalues (thread_p, oid, recdes, NULL, filter->scan_attrs->attr_cache) != NO_ERROR)
13591  {
13592  return V_ERROR;
13593  }
13594  ev_res =
13595  (*filter->scan_pred->pr_eval_fnc) (thread_p, filter->scan_pred->pred_expr, filter->val_descr, (OID *) oid);
13596  ev_res = update_logical_result (thread_p, ev_res, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
13597  if (ev_res != V_TRUE)
13598  {
13599  goto end;
13600  }
13601  }
13602 
13603  filter = mvcc_reev_data->data_filter;
13604  if (filter != NULL && filter->scan_pred != NULL && filter->scan_pred->pred_expr != NULL)
13605  {
13606  ev_res = eval_data_filter (thread_p, (OID *) oid, recdes, NULL, filter);
13607  ev_res =
13608  update_logical_result (thread_p, ev_res, (int *) mvcc_reev_data->qualification, mvcc_reev_data->key_filter,
13609  recdes, oid);
13610  }
13611 
13612 end:
13613  return ev_res;
13614 }
13615 
13616 /*
13617  * locator_decide_operation_type () - returns the operation type that corresponds to the provided lock mode.
13618  *
13619  * return : operation type
13620  * lock_mode (in) : lock_mode
13621  */
13622 SCAN_OPERATION_TYPE
13623 locator_decide_operation_type (LOCK lock_mode, LC_FETCH_VERSION_TYPE fetch_version_type)
13624 {
13625  SCAN_OPERATION_TYPE op_type;
13626 
13627  if (lock_mode == NULL_LOCK)
13628  {
13629  /* for non-mvcc classes, corresponding lock for S_SELECT is S_LOCK;
13630  * this inconsistency should be acceptable, as the operation type is ignored anyway for non-mvcc classes */
13631  op_type = S_SELECT;
13632  }
13633  else if (lock_mode <= S_LOCK)
13634  {
13635  op_type = S_SELECT_WITH_LOCK;
13636  }
13637  else
13638  {
13639  op_type = S_DELETE;
13640  /* equivalent to S_UPDATE */
13641  }
13642 
13643  if (lock_mode > NULL_LOCK && lock_mode <= S_LOCK
13644  && (fetch_version_type == LC_FETCH_MVCC_VERSION || fetch_version_type == LC_FETCH_CURRENT_VERSION))
13645  {
13646  /* In this situation, the operation type must be changed to S_SELECT.
13647  * The final lock mode will be decided when class type will be known */
13648  assert (op_type == S_SELECT_WITH_LOCK);
13649  op_type = S_SELECT;
13650  }
13651 
13652  return op_type;
13653 }
13654 
13655 /*
13656  * locator_get_lock_mode_from_op_type () - returns the lock mode that corresponds to the provided operation type.
13657  *
13658  * return : lock mode
13659  * lock_mode (in) : operation type
13660  */
13661 LOCK
13662 locator_get_lock_mode_from_op_type (SCAN_OPERATION_TYPE op_type)
13663 {
13664  switch (op_type)
13665  {
13666  case S_SELECT:
13667  case S_SELECT_WITH_LOCK:
13668  /* S_LOCK -> will be converted to NULL_LOCK for mvcc classes */
13669  return S_LOCK;
13670  case S_UPDATE:
13671  case S_DELETE:
13672  return X_LOCK;
13673  default:
13674  assert (false);
13675  return NA_LOCK;
13676  }
13677 }
13678 
13679 int
13680 xlocator_demote_class_lock (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const OID * class_oid, LOCK lock, LOCK * ex_lock)
13681 {
13682  return lock_demote_class_lock (thread_p, class_oid, lock, ex_lock);
13683 }
